reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:32:Risk of overread: High. The critique imports a philosophy-of-science standard into comparative and practitioner-facing hermeneutics. That standard is useful as a discipline against duplicate models, but it may overstate the need for falsification where the local product is a safety heuristic. Human-condition fit is real but narrow: it serves reflective isolated people, over-managers, and meaning-loss cases who use total explanations instead of concrete support. It is not for acute grief, crisis stabilization, severe depression, psychosis, mania, OCD or scrupulosity, addiction withdrawal, unsafe authority settings, or cases where reassurance is currently keeping someone safe. Human-condition sources to keep in view: U.S. Surgeon General loneliness advisory, https://www.hhs.gov/sites/default/files/surgeon-general-social-connection-advisory.pdf, and Pew meaning-in-life work, https://www.pewresearch.org/religion/2018/11/20/where-americans-find-meaning-in-life/.
