reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-grid-stays-backstage-c0163823ff1f73cb.md:51:- Internal Lumenary records: The Road Must Know Its End, Some Paths Refuse the Question of What Remains, When Tools Become Judges, Not Every Check Should Be Yours, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, Stop When Time Is Up, The Question Can Make The Distance, local files in observations and reviews.: overlap: The cluster already contains after-use checks, no-audit gates, path preconditions, holder routing, tool-as-judge warnings, and safety screens for perfectionism, rumination, scrupulosity, burnout, and achievement-contingent self-worth.; difference: This candidate adds administrability as the explicit variable: backstage diagnostic grid versus frontstage maxim plus observable act.; novelty impact: Major downgrade. Treat as an extension of the existing cluster unless blind readers can distinguish delivery location from support holder, custody, and no-audit fields.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-grid-stays-backstage-c0163823ff1f73cb.md:61:- Modern human-condition sources: Curran and Hill on rising perfectionism, https://researchonline.lse.ac.uk/id/eprint/101352/1/Curran_Hill2018.pdf, and WHO burn-out definition, https://www.who.int/standards/classifications/frequently-asked-questions/burn-out-an-occupational-phenomenon: overlap: The target wound is well supported: rising perfectionism, socially prescribed worth pressure, exhaustion, distance, and reduced efficacy.; difference: These sources do not supply the spiritual-practice grid distinction, but they explain why the cohort is vulnerable to turning reflection into performance.; novelty impact: Supports publishability for a narrow cohort, not originality.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-grid-stays-backstage-c0163823ff1f73cb.md:77:- If: Backstage diagnostic structure plus frontstage maxim-and-act is safer than repeated self-administered grids for over-auditors. Then: In screened achievement-driven participants, maxim-plus-act and behavior-only re-entry conditions reduce rumination, shame, tool-performance anxiety, and reassurance seeking more than a repeated After-Use Check, while producing equal or better ordinary action completion within 24 hours. Weakens if: The full self-audit performs as well or better without increased checking or shame, or effects are explained by baseline OCD risk, perfectionism, sleep, workload coercion, social support, therapist alliance, or teacher contact. Test surface: Four-arm pilot: repeated After-Use Check, behavior-only re-entry, maxim-plus-act without rating, and ordinary journaling or usual practice.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-grid-stays-backstage-c0163823ff1f73cb.md:79:- If: The harm mechanism is worth-conversion, not reflection itself. Then: Participants high in contingent self-worth, socially prescribed perfectionism, and reassurance seeking show the largest adverse response to self-rating grids; participants low on these traits or under guided review show less harm or benefit. Weakens if: Adverse response does not interact with contingent self-worth, perfectionism, OCD or scrupulosity risk, guidance, scoring, or frequency. Test surface: Moderation analysis using validated measures of perfectionism, contingent self-worth, rumination, reassurance seeking, burnout, and action completion.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-grid-stays-backstage-c0163823ff1f73cb.md:95:- burnout and perfectionism researchers
