reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stop-when-time-is-up-not-when-it-feels-done-4b185ee8c360296e.json:24:  "exact_claim": "Some reflective work has no natural internal end, especially for people prone to compulsive self-examination, perfectionism, or achievement-contingent self-worth. For those cases, completion should be defined before starting by an external limit, such as a fixed time or one bounded action, and the question should close for the day even if it does not feel resolved. A method has surrendered its hold when the practitioner can stop on schedule, not when reflection finally feels complete.",
