reviews/originality/2026-05-30-do-not-answer-every-question-f89aec6674fa83a6.md:78:- If: Wrong-question import produces distinct failure clusters. Then: Importing a proof question into no-seeking, practice-realization, or Other Power settings predicts self-grading and defensiveness. Importing no-answer language into investigation, therapy, ethical repair, or koan training predicts avoidance, missed accountability, or flattening of practice energy. Weakens if: Failure clusters are generic across paths, or are explained better by trait rumination, perfectionism, isolation, workload coercion, unsafe teachers, trauma, sleep loss, or clinical distress. Test surface: Practitioner and clinician interviews coded for actual failed-student or client cases, source grammar, imported question, wound, repair, and outcome.
