reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:45:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Caregiving, medicine, teamwork, school, transport, and wage labor create shared deadlines that are not merely borrowed comparison clocks.", "confidence_effect": "Keeps the idea at extended. It can only survive by sharply separating coordination obligations from status comparison.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "Some external clocks are obligations of justice, safety, and trust. If path language lets a person dismiss medication times, childcare pickup, workplace dependencies, or promises, the model becomes harmful and false at the practice level."}, "audit_id": "8cd5d80af738d5d8", "claim_units": ["A clock measures repeatable transitions along a worldline.", "There is no single cosmic now that ranks all lives as early, late, ahead, or behind.", "The felt now is where records have reached this body and action remains possible.", "Clocks should coordinate obligations without becoming metaphysical or social verdicts.", "The modern use case is time anxiety, digital comparison, burnout, and feeling late in life."], "confidence": 0.86, "created_at": "2026-05-29T08:10:36+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Distributed systems and team operations", "prediction": "Teams using dependency-aware local timelines, with explicit interface commitments, will show less false lateness blame and better bottleneck diagnosis than teams managed only by global comparison dashboards.", "structural_translation": "A distributed system has local process histories and coordination protocols, not one privileged global now. The practical question is which timestamps mark real dependencies and which merely create misleading rank comparisons.", "would_count_against_it": "A single global deadline dashboard predicts delays, responsibility, morale, and coordination failures as well as or better than dependency-aware local timelines."}, "exact_claim": "A clock measures path-dependent physical change along one worldline, not a universal river of time. The felt now is local enough for conduct and responsibility, and modern suffering worsens when another person's clock becomes a verdict on one's own life rather than a tool for coordination.", "execution_id": "manual-2026-05-29T08:04:03+02:00", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "People trained in the distinction report less behind-in-life and comparative shame language while keeping equal or better punctuality, promise-keeping, and planning behavior.", "if_model_is_right": "The owed-coordination versus borrowed-comparison distinction has practical value.", "test_surface": "Randomized pilot with deadline-stressed students, caregivers, founders, and knowledge workers.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Missed obligations increase, avoidance rises, or outcomes are no better than self-compassion, time management, or ordinary social-clock psychoeducation."}, {"expected_observation": "Students introduced to worldlines and proper time before block-universe diagrams will make fewer claims that relativity proves the present is fake or that there is one hidden cosmic schedule.", "if_model_is_right": "Proper-time-first pedagogy changes metaphysical misconceptions.", "test_surface": "Physics education experiment with pre-post misconception coding.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Misconception rates match standard lessons, or the path framing worsens physics accuracy."}, {"expected_observation": "Digital comparison exposure and perceived social-clock deviation predict behind-in-life distress after controlling for actual deadlines, workload, income, age, and caregiving load.", "if_model_is_right": "Behind-in-life suffering is partly driven by borrowed social clocks rather than workload alone.", "test_surface": "Survey and diary study using social comparison, social-clock deviation, workload, and distress measures.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Distress is fully explained by material overload, insecurity, discrimination, sleep loss, or clinical anxiety, with no added effect from comparison clocks."}], "idea_id": "ec7bc17ccfbd50e0", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Einstein 1905 synchronism time clocks light signals", "Minkowski Space and Time world-line proper time clock", "Stanford Encyclopedia Being and Becoming modern physics local becoming proper time worldline", "Rovelli partial observables time relational clocks", "Page Wootters Evolution Without Evolution time correlations subsystems", "Neugarten social clock early late on time life events", "Elizabeth Freeman chrononormativity productivity time bodies", "Hartmut Rosa social acceleration shrinking present deadline pressure"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path-8cd5d80af738d5d8.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "Einstein does not turn clock locality into a doctrine about comparison, responsibility, or feeling late in life.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the physical claim to known.", "overlap": "Very close for operational clock time, clock synchronization, and moving-clock comparison.", "source": "Einstein, On the Electrodynamics of Moving Bodies, https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/On_the_Electrodynamics_of_Moving_Bodies_(1920_edition)"}, {"difference": "The candidate adds a conduct and social-comparison interpretation.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade for the phrase clock measures a path.", "overlap": "World-points and world-lines already frame physical histories as paths in spacetime.", "source": "Minkowski, Space and Time, https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Translation:Space_and_Time"}, {"difference": "The candidate applies local becoming to spiritual-practical pressure around life schedules.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade. The local-now physics and philosophy are already mapped.", "overlap": "Extremely close. Stein, Arthur, Dieks, and Savitt already connect proper time, worldlines, local becoming, now-points, and causal diamonds.", "source": "SEP, Being and Becoming in Modern Physics, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/spacetime-bebecome/"}, {"difference": "They do not imply that another person's clock should not become a verdict on one's life.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the anti-river and anti-cosmic-clock portion, while leaving room for an applied synthesis.", "overlap": "Both support relational or internal-clock approaches in which time is not an independent universal flow.", "source": "Rovelli, Partial Observables, https://arxiv.org/abs/gr-qc/0110035, and Page and Wootters, Evolution Without Evolution, https://cds.cern.ch/record/143641"}, {"difference": "The candidate speaks of my path or another path, which Dogen may treat as a reifying translation.", "novelty_impact": "Anomaly and partial near-neighbor. It supports local answerability but strains path-self language.", "overlap": "Dogen's being-time already resists external time and treats each being or moment as time, not as a thing located inside time.", "source": "Dogen, Uji source card, notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md"}, {"difference": "The candidate connects social clocks to relativity and proper time.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for the behind-in-life insight.", "overlap": "Very close for the human-condition claim. Social clock theory already explains early, late, and on-time self-evaluation against culturally prescribed life schedules.", "source": "Neugarten social clock theory, via The Time of Our Lives, https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC3894849/"}, {"difference": "The candidate translates these pressures through clock-path language rather than queer theory or critical theory.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades social critique novelty. Remaining contribution is a practical distinction, not a discovery.", "overlap": "Chrononormativity and social acceleration already analyze time as productivity discipline, shrinking present, schedule pressure, and embodied social regulation.", "source": "Elizabeth Freeman, Time Binds, UC Davis summary, https://lettersandsciencemag.ucdavis.edu/bookshelf/time-binds, and Hartmut Rosa, Social Acceleration, Columbia University Press, https://cup.columbia.edu/book/social-acceleration/9780231148351/"}, {"difference": "The candidate adds proper-time path measurement and social comparison language.", "novelty_impact": "Internal originality is reduced. This should be cross-indexed rather than treated as standalone.", "overlap": "Already argued that clocks coordinate action without owning metaphysics and addressed deadline pressure.", "source": "Internal Lumenary prior, observations/codex/2026-05-29-clocks-do-not-own-time.md"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a new physics claim. Name proper time, local becoming, social clock theory, chrononormativity, and social acceleration as prior art.", "Merge or cross-index with Clocks Do Not Own Time unless a separability test shows independent predictive value.", "Build a practice rubric that separates owed coordination, chosen commitment, structural coercion, and borrowed comparison.", "Test for harm by tracking missed obligations, avoidance, and contempt for shared time.", "Interview physicists, social-clock researchers, burnout clinicians, caregivers, and team leads for concrete failure and repair cases.", "Keep the teaching narrow: clocks coordinate paths, but they do not rank the worth of lives."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.50 to 0.34. Human-condition fit is direct but already well-covered by social clock theory, chrononormativity, social acceleration, burnout, and perfectionism literature. Target cohort: functioning adults who meet obligations but feel late in life because of visible peer timelines. Non-fit cases: acute crisis, severe depression, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, people avoiding duties, and people facing structural exploitation where schedule pressure is materially imposed rather than internal comparison.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path-8cd5d80af738d5d8.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Physicists call the physical claim textbook proper time, social scientists call the distress claim social clock or chrononormativity, and practitioners say the distinction does not change repair or instruction.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners can use the distinction to reduce comparative shame while preserving obligations, and can predict which deadlines are owed coordination versus status-contaminated comparison.", "questions": ["Is clock measures a path just standard proper time and local becoming?", "Does borrowed comparison time add anything beyond social clock theory, chrononormativity, or social acceleration?", "Can you name cases where distinguishing coordination from comparison would change guidance?", "What failure would show that path language is excusing avoidance or structural injustice?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Relativity teachers and philosophers of time", "Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen Uji", "Developmental psychologists who study social clock theory", "Clinicians working with burnout, perfectionism, and achievement-contingent self-worth", "Caregivers, team leads, and operations managers responsible for real coordination", "Meditation teachers who work with time anxiety"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Einstein, On the Electrodynamics of Moving Bodies, section 1, https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/On_the_Electrodynamics_of_Moving_Bodies_(1920_edition)", "Minkowski, Space and Time, https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Translation:Space_and_Time"], "risk_of_overread": "Moderate to high. Proper time is a precise physical concept, while a life path is a metaphor. The model may confuse social comparison with real coordination duties, and Dogen may reject the self-path language because it separates a person from being-time.", "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit relied on SEP for Stein, Arthur, Dieks, Savitt, and local becoming. It did not read their full books and papers, full Neugarten originals, Freeman's full Time Binds, or full Hartmut Rosa. No physicist, developmental psychologist, or practitioner interviews were run.", "structural_observation": "Einstein defines time through clocks, local readings, light-signal synchronization, and moving-clock comparison. Minkowski then gives world-points and world-lines as the natural spacetime structure. The candidate's physical core, a clock measures along a path, is therefore close to standard proper-time and worldline thinking rather than a new model."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.92, "novelty": 0.34, "source_reliability": 0.86}, "run_ids": ["manual-2026-05-29T08:04:03+02:00"], "title": "A Clock Measures A Path", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Einstein, Minkowski, local becoming, Rovelli, Page-Wootters, Dogen, social clock theory, chrononormativity, and the prior Lumenary clock record, this idea's possible contribution is a testable practical distinction: separate owed coordination times from borrowed comparison times, then see whether that reduces behind-in-life distress without weakening punctuality or responsibility."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:46:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Coercive or incompetent correction ecologies, including abusive teachers, shame-based communities, misapplied clinical labels, and peer groups that punish dissent.", "confidence_effect": "Keeps the status at extended. Publishability depends on adding unsafe-authority, valid-solitude, and clinical-risk stops before any practice promotion.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If correction is treated as inherently safer than private interpretation, the model can direct vulnerable practitioners toward the very authority structure that distorts or harms them. The rule must distinguish trustworthy correction from coercive control."}, "audit_id": "8144312cebdf1b38", "claim_units": ["Powerful states and a practice's own finality language are insufficient warrants for trust.", "A serious result should be coded by two variables: what claim the practice permits and what remains able to correct the claimant.", "Methods may confirm a recognition, undermine every claim, be released after use, or become embodied as conduct.", "Release of the raft should not mean release of correction.", "The practice candidate targets isolated, self-directed practitioners who may turn experiences into status, shame, or identity."], "confidence": 0.8, "created_at": "2026-05-29T15:20:46+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "AI model governance and incident review", "prediction": "Teams that preserve correction channels after automation will catch high-confidence failures, drift, and misuse earlier than teams that treat the model's output as self-validating.", "structural_translation": "A high-performing model or method should not close the evaluation loop around itself. After a system produces a result, an independent audit, monitoring, escalation, or user-feedback channel must remain able to correct it.", "would_count_against_it": "Closed-loop systems with no independent correction perform as safely and adaptively as audited systems across drift, edge cases, user harm, and escalation metrics."}, "exact_claim": "After a serious practice result, the decisive safety question is not only whether the method is retained, released, confirmed, or undermined. The result remains spiritually immature if it removes every trustworthy correction path: teacher, text, community, ordinary conduct, duty, clinical boundary, or observed effects over time.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260529-150040-20260529-150040", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Split-source coding will find held-out warnings, teacher checks, conduct tests, vows, texts, or community checks even in sources that strongly teach method release or no attainment.", "if_model_is_right": "Traditions that release a method still retain correction paths.", "test_surface": "Primary-text corpus coded separately for method fate, claim permission, correction holder, warnings, repairs, and teaching permission.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Mature sources release method and correction with no replacement, and practitioners show stable ethical integration without identifiable correction holders."}, {"expected_observation": "Stable solo practitioners using the check after unusual practice report less spiritual status-claiming, less shameful doubt, and no rise in dependency, rumination, or isolation compared with plain journaling.", "if_model_is_right": "The Correction Check helps the named modern cohort.", "test_surface": "Two-week randomized pilot with self-directed meditators, app users, retreatants, and cross-tradition readers.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The check increases paranoia, scrupulosity, teacher dependence, shame, or performs no better than rest, ordinary conversation, or established teacher check-ins."}, {"expected_observation": "After controlling for practice intensity, prior beliefs, trait anxiety, social isolation, and clinical history, lack of trusted correction predicts oscillation between attainment claims and collapse into doubt.", "if_model_is_right": "Absence of trustworthy correction predicts unstable interpretation after powerful practice.", "test_surface": "Prospective survey and micro-phenomenological interviews using VCE-style appraisal and support coding.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Instability is better predicted by clinical risk, sleep loss, community abuse, teacher mismatch, or practice intensity, with no independent correction-path effect."}], "idea_id": "0f794e6b87955cdf", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-29-keep-what-can-correct-you.md", "literature_search_queries": ["MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta raft simile right grasp wrong interpretation Arittha", "Ignatius Spiritual Exercises Rule 8 consolation opinions examined before credit", "Varieties of Contemplative Experience interpretations responses teacher guidance social appraisal", "William James Varieties of Religious Experience fruits conduct religious experience", "Talal Asad discursive tradition correct form purpose practice authority", "spiritual bypassing Welwood spiritual practice avoids unresolved emotional issues", "Dogen practice realization correction teacher community Bendowa Genjokoan"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-29-keep-what-can-correct-you-8144312cebdf1b38.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "The candidate generalizes this into a cross-tradition correction-holder rule and a modern solo-practitioner practice.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. The release plus correction structure is already primary-text material.", "overlap": "Very close. The sutta joins wrong-grasp correction, teacher and sangha challenge, right use of Dhamma, and later release of the raft.", "source": "MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html"}, {"difference": "Ignatius works inside Christian discernment of spirits and spiritual direction. The candidate strips the structure into a cross-tradition and clinical-safety heuristic.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade for the practice check. It looks like generalized discernment advice.", "overlap": "Extremely close for post-experience interpretation. Ignatius distinguishes a genuine consolation from later judgments and resolutions that require careful examination.", "source": "Ignatius of Loyola, Spiritual Exercises, Rules for Discernment, https://www.orderofthecommonlife.org/spiritual-exercises-full-text"}, {"difference": "VCE is a research taxonomy, not a short doctrine line about retaining correction after method release.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades novelty, but supports practice-testability if the Correction Check is tested against VCE-style outcomes.", "overlap": "Very close empirically. VCE separates meditation experiences from interpretations, causal attributions, remedies, relationships, teacher responses, distress, impairment, and health behaviors.", "source": "Lindahl et al., The Varieties of Contemplative Experience, PLOS One 2017, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239"}, {"difference": "James does not specify a correction-holder code for method completion.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the conduct-check portion to known pragmatist and psychology-of-religion territory.", "overlap": "Close. James asks that religious states be judged by their fruits rather than by origin or felt intensity alone.", "source": "William James, The Varieties of Religious Experience, Project Gutenberg, https://www.gutenberg.org/files/621/621-h/621-h.html"}, {"difference": "The candidate narrows this to post-practice correction after unusual experience.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades broad originality. The possible contribution is an operational prompt, not a new theory of religious authority.", "overlap": "Close theoretical prior. Practice meaning, correct form, purpose, authority, and doctrine as grammar are already tied to traditions and communities.", "source": "Talal Asad, The Idea of an Anthropology of Islam, https://bpb-ap-se2.wpmucdn.com/thinkspace.csu.edu.au/dist/c/3891/files/2020/10/Asad-Anthropology.pdf, and George Lindbeck, The Nature of Doctrine"}, {"difference": "Sells is about apophatic language, not about correction paths after practice results.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the self-canceling method side, but less so the safety-rule formulation.", "overlap": "Close for self-undermining discourse and the danger of trusting propositions that unsay themselves too quickly.", "source": "Michael Sells, Mystical Languages of Unsaying, https://press.uchicago.edu/ucp/books/book/chicago/M/bo3635525.html"}, {"difference": "This candidate shifts from naming authority to correction after method release.", "novelty_impact": "Internal novelty is reduced. Cross-index rather than publish as a standalone discovery.", "overlap": "Very close internal prior. It already says a practice does not authorize the meaning of its own result and asks who or what can name the event.", "source": "Internal Lumenary prior, A practice cannot name itself, reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.md"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Cross-index with A practice cannot name itself, The Test Is How You Return, Boundary and Custody at the Threshold, and Holding Without Owning.", "Build a correction-holder codebook with values for teacher-held, text-held, community-held, conduct-held, vow-held, clinical-held, ordinary-duty-held, internal-practice-held, unsafe-authority, valid-solitude, and undecidable.", "Use split-source coding: code claim permission from one passage, correction holder from another, and warnings or repairs from held-out manuals or interviews.", "Pilot The Correction Check only with safety stops for rumination, shame, paranoia, dependency, dissociation, mania, trauma activation, and clinical distress.", "Interview practitioners for concrete misinterpretation and repair cases, not agreement with the slogan."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.48 to 0.36. Human-condition fit is real but already strongly supported by loneliness, meaning-loss, perfectionism, burnout, spiritual-direction, and meditation-safety prior art. Target cohort: stable self-directed practitioners, app meditators, cross-tradition seekers, and retreatants without continuing guidance. Non-fit cases: acute crisis, psychosis, mania, dissociation, addiction withdrawal, severe depression, abusive communities, and practitioners already under competent teacher or clinical care.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-29-keep-what-can-correct-you-8144312cebdf1b38.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners identify the rule as ordinary discernment, teacher verification, sangha correction, fruits-of-practice ethics, spiritual direction, or meditation safety guidance, and say it adds no new predictive value.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners say the correction-holder question identifies a real gap in self-directed modern practice, improves triage after unusual experiences, and predicts when solo interpretation becomes risky without forcing people into unsafe authority.", "questions": ["When a student reports a powerful practice result, what is allowed to correct their first interpretation?", "Is 'keep what can correct you' standard guidance in your lineage or a useful new distinction?", "Can you name cases where correction itself caused harm, shame, dependency, or misinterpretation?", "Does the proposed check change guidance, or only rename teacher, sangha, scripture, conduct, and supervision?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Theravada, Zen, Tibetan, Advaita, Sufi, and Ignatian teachers", "Spiritual directors and retreat directors", "Meditation safety clinicians familiar with VCE or Cheetah House work", "Solo practitioners and app meditators outside continuing communities", "Clinicians working with scrupulosity, dissociation, anxiety, and spiritual bypassing"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, Thanissaro translation, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html", "Ignatius of Loyola, Spiritual Exercises, Rule 8 for discernment, https://www.orderofthecommonlife.org/spiritual-exercises-full-text"], "risk_of_overread": "High. The model can turn correction into institutional control, and it can flatten different authority ecologies into a generic safety rule. It may also make valid solitude look deficient, or make abusive communities look like necessary correctives.", "secondary_literature_gap": "This audit did not read full Cassian, Evagrius, Teresa of Avila, John of the Cross, Jonathan Edwards, contemporary spiritual-direction manuals, full Hori, full Katz, full Sharf, or Cheetah House materials. No teachers, clinicians, or solo practitioners were interviewed.", "structural_observation": "MN 22 is already a strong source for this structure. Arittha's private interpretation is challenged by monks and then by the Buddha before the raft simile appears, and the text pairs right grasp with later release. Ignatius gives an even closer practitioner rule: after a consolation, later resolutions and opinions need examination before being trusted. Together they already contain the core pattern, experience or method may be valid, but interpretation still needs correction."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.92, "novelty": 0.36, "source_reliability": 0.82}, "run_ids": ["20260529-150040-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260529-150040-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "Keep What Can Correct You", "unlike_statement": "Unlike MN 22, Ignatian discernment, VCE, James, Asad, Lindbeck, Sells, and the prior Lumenary recognition-gap audit, this idea's possible contribution is a narrow safety heuristic: after method release, verify that some trustworthy correction path remains, and test whether naming that path reduces inflation, shame, and isolated overinterpretation without increasing dependency."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:47:{"agent": "claude", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Stage-mixed traditions and practitioners, where active effort, surrender, grace, teacher recognition, ordinary conduct, and no-attainment are all present at different moments.", "confidence_effect": "Keeps the idea at extended. It can only rise if voice coding predicts warnings, confusion, and repair better than self-power, Other Power, Pargament agency style, teacher style, and clinical-risk baselines.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If most actual paths shift voices by stage, role, and context, then active versus middle voice will not sort traditions or predict guidance. Pure Land practitioners still say the nembutsu, Zen practitioners still sit, Christian grace traditions still discipline attention, and high-striving nondual practitioners may still benefit from release advice despite no-owner doctrine."}, "audit_id": "3f00413ce244b54e", "claim_units": ["The validate-versus-undermine and retain-abandon-embody grid is mostly prior art, not discovery.", "Dogen, Shinran, and the Heart Sutra break the grid by rejecting an active owner who finishes and assigns custody.", "The better variable may be grammatical voice of completion-talk: active, middle, passive, or mixed.", "Release teaching fits people who believed they held or earned the result.", "The modern human problem is achievement-contingent self-worth and burnout, not spiritual completion in general."], "confidence": 0.82, "created_at": "2026-05-29T15:20:46+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Education and workplace performance coaching", "prediction": "Coaches who screen for perceived result ownership before giving detachment advice will reduce perfectionistic rumination and burnout better than coaches who give universal 'let go of the outcome' advice.", "structural_translation": "Advice to let go of outcomes helps people who over-own results as proof of worth. It can misfire for people whose outcomes are mainly constrained by systems, teams, luck, injury, caregiving load, discrimination, or externally assigned roles.", "would_count_against_it": "Screened and universal advice have equal effects, or material constraints, workload, sleep, discrimination, team support, and clinical variables fully explain outcomes with no added effect from ownership-language fit."}, "exact_claim": "Advice to use a method, release it, and not own the result is not a universal account of practice completion. It is medicine for active-voice, self-power practitioners who believe effort earns results and convert those results into worth. Other-power, practice-realization, and no-attainment sources strain the release frame because they deny the practitioner as holder, the method as completed possession, or the linear after in which release would occur.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260529-150040-20260529-150040", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "High-striving practitioners who describe results as earned will show reduced pride, shame, comparison, and burnout after the Earning Check, while other-power or practice-realization practitioners will show little benefit or increased self-monitoring from the same instruction.", "if_model_is_right": "Release teaching is cohort-specific medicine for active earning and result-ownership.", "test_surface": "Randomized pilot stratified by self-power language, perfectionism, tradition background, and achievement-contingent self-worth.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "All cohorts benefit equally, or the instruction mainly licenses avoidance, passivity, or contempt for ordinary responsibility."}, {"expected_observation": "Blind coding of completion-talk as active, middle, passive, mixed, or no-voice predicts held-out warnings, repairs, and supervision needs better than retain, release, embody categories alone.", "if_model_is_right": "Grammatical voice predicts practice guidance better than custody-grid coding.", "test_surface": "Split-source codebook tested on MN 22, Tannisho, Dogen, Heart Sutra, Rinzai koan curriculum, Christian grace texts, and practitioner interviews.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Custody values, tradition identity, teacher style, institution type, or Pargament agency styles predict guidance as well as or better than voice coding."}, {"expected_observation": "Coders will overuse embodied-without-ownership for Dogen, Shinran, Heart Sutra, Dzogchen, apophasis, and other hard cases, with low inter-rater reliability and weak prediction of warnings.", "if_model_is_right": "The embodied-without-ownership cell is too elastic.", "test_surface": "Inter-rater trial comparing the old two-axis grid against active, middle, passive, and mixed voice labels.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The cell has clear boundaries, high inter-rater reliability, and predicts concrete repairs better than voice coding."}], "idea_id": "062e77e78841d7da", "idea_path": "observations/claude/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held.md", "literature_search_queries": ["middle voice Eckhart modern continental philosophy relinquishment human will agency activity passivity", "Shinran jinen honi no calculation Other Power no working is true working", "Tannisho nembutsu not practice not good act self-power Other Power", "Dogen practice and realization are one no means and end zazen", "Pargament religious problem-solving self-directing collaborative deferring styles", "Snakes and Ladders Nagarjuna Wittgenstein therapeutic method no theses", "Heart Sutra no attainment rely on Prajnaparamita"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "Lewin centers Eckhart and Heidegger, not Dogen, Shinran, Heart Sutra, or a modern achievement-cohort practice screen.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. The grammatical-voice relocation is already present in academic theology and philosophy.", "overlap": "Extremely close for the proposed new variable. Lewin explicitly treats mystical relinquishment of will through the middle voice, between activity and passivity.", "source": "David Lewin, The middle voice in Eckhart and modern continental philosophy, https://strathprints.strath.ac.uk/56562/"}, {"difference": "The candidate turns Shinran into a comparative diagnostic against universal release teachings.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the slogan 'you cannot release what you never held' to a Shinran-compatible restatement.", "overlap": "Direct primary near-neighbor. Shinran already denies practicer calculation and says no working is true working in Other Power.", "source": "Shinran, On Jinen-Honi, https://shinranworks.com/letters/lamp-for-the-latter-ages/on-jinen-honi-1258/"}, {"difference": "The candidate uses that structure to set a cohort boundary for modern achievement-driven practitioners.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for the Other Power anomaly and self-power critique.", "overlap": "Very close. Tannisho says nembutsu is not practice or good act for the practicer because it arises wholly from Other Power and is free of self-power.", "source": "Tannisho, A Record in Lament of Divergences, https://shinranworks.com/related-works-by-other-authors/a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/"}, {"difference": "The candidate frames Dogen as evidence for active versus middle voice completion-talk, which may or may not be native to Soto categories.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the no-after and no-owner insight. The possible addition is comparative sorting.", "overlap": "Close anomaly and near-neighbor. Practice-realization already rejects separating means and end, practice and later attainment.", "source": "Soto Zen, Practice and Realization Are One, https://www.sotozen.com/eng/library/stories/vol01.html"}, {"difference": "Pargament studies coping style, not method completion or release of practice results.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades agency novelty. The candidate must show voice coding predicts beyond Pargament-style agency coding.", "overlap": "Very close for agency distribution. Self-directing, collaborative, and deferring styles already distinguish personal agency, exchange with God, and waiting for divine action.", "source": "Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/"}, {"difference": "The candidate uses this as a grid-breaking case rather than as Mahayana teaching in its own right.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the no-attainment and retained-reliance analysis to known primary material.", "overlap": "Close for no attainment plus reliance. The text negates attainment while keeping Prajnaparamita operative.", "source": "Heart Sutra, https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Translation:Shorter_Praj%C3%B1%C4%81p%C4%81ramit%C4%81_H%E1%B9%9Bdaya_S%C5%ABtra"}, {"difference": "They do not offer the same cohort-specific practice screen for achievement-contingent self-worth.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade for the retirement of the two-axis grid. The likely contribution is an applied synthesis.", "overlap": "Close for self-dismantling method, therapeutic no-thesis practice, and apophatic language that turns back on itself.", "source": "Joshua William Smith, Snakes and Ladders, https://philpapers.org/rec/SMISAL-7, and Michael Sells, Mystical Languages of Unsaying, https://press.uchicago.edu/ucp/books/book/chicago/M/bo3635525.html"}, {"difference": "This candidate explicitly falsifies the universal release frame and proposes voice as a better variable.", "novelty_impact": "Internal originality is moderate at best. Run a separability test before publication.", "overlap": "Very close internal neighborhood. These records already contain retain, release, embody, custody, threshold, and return grammars.", "source": "Internal Lumenary priors, Holding Without Owning, The Test Is How You Return, Method's Reckoning, and Boundary and Custody at the Threshold"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a discovery. Publish, if at all, as a bounded practice-fit rule for achievement-contingent self-worth.", "Search and read full Lewin, Pargament, Dogen scholarship, Jodo Shinshu scholarship, grace-effort theology, Gelassenheit, and middle-voice theology before raising novelty.", "Build a separability test against Holding Without Owning, The Test Is How You Return, and Method's Reckoning. Merge if blind readers cannot distinguish the claims.", "Create a voice-coding sheet with values for active, middle, passive, mixed-by-stage, simultaneous-mixed, no-owner, no-threshold, practice-realization, radical Other Power, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.", "Run the Earning Check pilot only after screening for perfectionism, scrupulosity, avoidance, workload coercion, and clinical risk. Track whether it reduces self-worth conversion without weakening responsibility."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.55 to 0.39. The strongest prior-art pressure is Lewin's middle-voice analysis plus Shinran's explicit Other Power and Pargament's agency styles. Human-condition fit is strong but narrow: high-striving people with achievement-contingent self-worth, burnout, comparison, and result-ownership. Non-fit cases include acute crisis, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, scrupulosity, dissociation, psychosis, people in grace-centered or nondual practice who do not experience ownership, and people whose distress is caused mainly by structural exploitation rather than self-rating.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say the claim is simply self-power versus Other Power, grace versus works, practice-realization, or middle-voice theology in new language, and that it does not change sequencing, warning, or repair.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners can use the voice screen to prevent specific mismatches, identify when release advice reinstalls a controller, and predict which students need result-release rather than surrender, teacher guidance, rest, or ordinary responsibility.", "questions": ["Is active, middle, and passive completion-talk a real practitioner distinction, or an imposed analyst metaphor?", "Would 'release the method' confuse or harm a practitioner whose tradition says the work was never self-owned?", "Can you name concrete cases where release advice helped high-striving practitioners but harmed or confused other-power or nondual practitioners?", "Does voice coding change guidance beyond older labels such as self-power, Other Power, grace, surrender, non-attainment, or Pargament coping style?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Jodo Shinshu teachers and scholars", "Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization", "Rinzai Zen teachers familiar with koan curriculum and post-kensho guidance", "Christian spiritual directors familiar with grace and discernment", "Scholars of Eckhart, Heidegger, and middle voice", "Clinicians and coaches working with perfectionism, burnout, and achievement-contingent self-worth"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html", "Shinran, On Jinen-Honi and Tannisho, https://shinranworks.com/letters/lamp-for-the-latter-ages/on-jinen-honi-1258/ and https://shinranworks.com/related-works-by-other-authors/a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/"], "risk_of_overread": "High. 'Middle voice' is an analyst metaphor that may not map cleanly onto Japanese, Sanskrit, Pali, or Chinese practice grammar. The active versus middle distinction may become a renamed self-power versus Other Power distinction, or it may hide stage shifts where effort and surrender coexist.", "secondary_literature_gap": "This audit did not read Japanese, Pali, Sanskrit, Chinese, or commentarial originals. It did not read full Lewin on middle voice, full Heidegger and Eckhart scholarship, full Pargament, full Hori, full Dogen scholarship, or Jodo Shinshu scholarship beyond accessible translations and summaries. No Shin, Soto, Rinzai, or Christian grace practitioners were interviewed.", "structural_observation": "MN 22 assumes a practitioner can grasp the Dhamma rightly, use it for crossing, and then not hold it as a possession. Shinran's jinen-honi and Tannisho relocate efficacy to Other Power and repeatedly reject practicer calculation, making even discussion of no working liable to become another working. This is a strong primary-text basis for narrowing release advice by agency grammar. But it also shows the candidate's central insight is not new inside Shinran: one cannot release as self-power what was never self-power to begin with."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.91, "novelty": 0.39, "source_reliability": 0.8}, "run_ids": ["20260529-150040-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260529-150040-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "You cannot release what you never held", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Lewin on middle voice, Shinran on Other Power, Dogen on practice-realization, Pargament on religious coping styles, Heart Sutra no-attainment reliance, Smith, Sells, and prior Lumenary completion models, this idea's possible contribution is a testable fit rule: give release-the-method advice only to practitioners whose own language shows active earning and result-ownership, then test whether the advice helps them more than it helps other-power, nondual, or practice-realization practitioners."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:48:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Dogen's practice-realization identity and Shinran's Other Power.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence in originality. The model should first code ownership and temporal completion as scope conditions.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "Dogen strains the premise that a road first leads to an end and then receives an after-use instruction. Shinran strains the premise that the practitioner owns the road, trust, or result enough to retain, release, or embody it. These cases may sit outside the grid's conditions of askability."}, "audit_id": "ddc62528ba3f429d", "claim_units": ["Completion is not sufficient; a practice needs guidance for its own after-use.", "The proposed structure has two variables: proof relation, validating versus undermining possession, and carrying relation, retained, released, or embodied.", "Hybrid cases such as MN 22, the Heart Sutra, Rinzai koan curriculum, and Dogen's practice-realization expose the weakness of a simple confirm-or-cancel typology.", "The practical target is achievement-contingent self-worth, burnout, compulsive self-improvement, and spiritual identity built from once-helpful tools.", "The After-Use Check asks what to keep, what to set down, and what to live."], "confidence": 0.84, "created_at": "2026-05-29T15:41:51+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Therapy, coaching, productivity systems, and professional training.", "prediction": "Manuals for effective training should differ by after-use relation: retained methods require routine and supervision, released scaffolds require stopping rules, and embodied methods require observable conduct markers. High achievers should benefit from explicit after-use boundaries more than from open-ended self-improvement tracking.", "structural_translation": "A method that produces benefit needs an after-use instruction: continue as a protocol, retire as scaffolding, or translate into ordinary conduct.", "would_count_against_it": "Training outcomes are explained by dosage, accountability, teacher quality, and baseline mental health, with no added predictive value from after-use categories."}, "exact_claim": "A practice is not trustworthy merely because it produces a strong insight. It must also give after-use guidance: whether its result is validated or possession of the result is undermined, and whether the practice should then be retained, set down, or embodied in ordinary conduct. The modern use case is preventing achievement-driven practitioners from turning methods, insights, therapy, meditation, or productivity systems into proof of worth.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260529-153241-20260529-153241", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Split-source coding will find distinct markers for retain, release, embody, no-threshold, practice-realization, and no-owner cases, and those markers will predict held-out warnings, verification rules, and repair practices.", "if_model_is_right": "Mature practice traditions vary systematically in after-use guidance.", "test_surface": "Inter-rater coding of MN 22, Heart Sutra, Dogen Bendowa or Genjokoan, Tannisho, Rinzai koan curriculum sources, apophatic Christian texts, and Sufi fana or baqa sources.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders cannot agree on the categories, or tradition identity, teacher style, institution type, and general agency models predict warnings just as well."}, {"expected_observation": "Achievement-driven participants with high self-worth contingency report less rumination, comparison, and method-identity after using the check, without reduced responsibility.", "if_model_is_right": "The After-Use Check helps the intended modern cohort.", "test_surface": "Two-week randomized pilot stratified by perfectionism, burnout, self-worth contingency, and clinical-risk screen.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The check increases self-monitoring, shame, avoidance, or tool-performance pressure, or performs no better than generic journaling or rest-and-plan prompts."}], "idea_id": "c4bedb491c09ac97", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end.md", "literature_search_queries": ["raft simile Buddhist teaching let go after crossing method release", "upaya skillful means method abandoned after enlightenment ladder thorn removes thorn", "Nagarjuna Wittgenstein therapeutic method no thesis Snakes and Ladders", "Michael Sells Mystical Languages of Unsaying apophatic self negating discourse", "Victor Hori Rinzai koan curriculum after kensho practice continues", "Dogen practice realization one shusho itto no verification outside practice", "Pargament religious problem solving styles deferring collaborative self directing", "Hadot spiritual exercises practice transformation way of life"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This candidate turns that prior audit instruction into a teaching and practice check for achievement pressure.", "novelty_impact": "Major internal downgrade. Treat as a renamed and applied consolidation unless separability testing shows predictive gain.", "overlap": "Extremely close. The prior audit already recommended rebuilding the model as two axes: validates versus undermines, and retained versus abandoned or embodied.", "source": "Internal Lumenary audit, The Method's Reckoning, https://local/reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.json"}, {"difference": "MN 22 is not a cross-tradition codebook and does not target modern burnout or achievement-contingent self-worth.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. The after-use release structure is known primary material.", "overlap": "Very close for right use followed by non-possession of the method after crossing.", "source": "MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html"}, {"difference": "The candidate adds a practice-facing distinction between proof relation and after-use instruction.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades novelty to renamed or extended unless the two-variable rubric predicts warnings or repairs better than older provisional-method models.", "overlap": "Close for provisional methods that are useful but not finally possessed.", "source": "Upaya, raft, ladder, and thorn-removes-thorn traditions"}, {"difference": "The candidate expands beyond thesis-free therapy into retained, released, and embodied after-use categories.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the anti-possession and self-canceling-method claim. The possible novelty is applied comparative sorting.", "overlap": "Close for therapeutic methods that work by undoing the need for the thesis or method that seemed to support them.", "source": "Joshua William Smith, Snakes and Ladders, https://ueaeprints.uea.ac.uk/id/eprint/80007/"}, {"difference": "Sells is focused on apophatic discourse, not a cross-tradition after-use grid or burnout-oriented practice check.", "novelty_impact": "Strong prior-art pressure against calling self-undermining method original.", "overlap": "Close for discourse and method that turn back on their own claims and prevent possession of the result.", "source": "Michael Sells, Mystical Languages of Unsaying, https://press.uchicago.edu/ucp/books/book/chicago/M/bo3635525.html"}, {"difference": "The candidate tries to absorb this as embodied after-use, but Dogen may reject the tool-result framing altogether.", "novelty_impact": "Major anomaly pressure. If Dogen cannot be coded reliably, the model is only a limited checklist.", "overlap": "Close anomaly to any road-then-end sequence, since practice itself is presented as realization rather than a means to later attainment.", "source": "Soto Zen, Practice and Realization Are One, https://www.sotozen.com/eng/library/stories/vol01.html"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a discovery. Treat as a bounded after-use rubric and practice-fit rule.", "Build a split-source codebook with fields for proof relation, carrying relation, ownership assumption, temporal completion assumption, warning, repair, evidence passage, and analyst-frame refusal.", "Merge or cross-index with The Method's Reckoning, Holding Without Owning, The Test Is How You Return, Keep What Can Correct You, Boundary and Custody at the Threshold, and You cannot release what you never held unless separability testing shows independent predictive gain.", "Run practitioner interviews for concrete post-insight failures and repairs, not agreement with the slogan.", "Pilot The After-Use Check only with screening for perfectionism, scrupulosity, avoidance, workload coercion, dissociation, mania, trauma activation, severe depression, and clinical distress."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.61 to 0.31. The two-axis structure is already an internal audit instruction, and the individual components are strongly represented in MN 22, upaya, apophasis, Dogen, and therapeutic-method literature. Human-condition fit is real but narrow: achievement-driven people who convert methods and insights into worth. Non-fit cases include acute crisis, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, dissociation, psychosis, under-motivation, responsibility avoidance, and structural burnout where the primary remedy is workload or institutional change rather than reflection.", "originality_status": "renamed", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say this is simply upaya, raft teaching, practice-realization, surrender, integration, or ordinary supervision in new language, and that it does not change sequencing, warnings, or repairs.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners can use the two-variable rubric to identify mismatched guidance, prevent method-identity, and predict different repairs for clinging, premature release, hollow insight, and depleted over-management.", "questions": ["Is keep, release, or embody an actual distinction you use in guidance, or an analyst vocabulary imposed from outside?", "Can you name concrete cases where carrying a method after insight caused harm, and what repair was given?", "Does this rubric predict warnings or student repairs better than existing language such as upaya, non-attachment, grace, surrender, practice-realization, or ordinary integration?", "For burned-out high achievers, does the After-Use Check reduce worth-pressure, or does it create another task to perform correctly?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Rinzai Zen teachers familiar with koan curriculum", "Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization", "Jodo Shinshu teachers", "Theravada teachers familiar with MN 22 and upaya", "Christian apophatic spiritual directors", "Sufi teachers familiar with fana and baqa", "Clinicians or coaches working with burnout and perfectionism"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html", "Heart Sutra, no attainment with reliance on Prajnaparamita, https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Translation:Shorter_Praj%C3%B1%C4%81p%C4%81ramit%C4%81_H%E1%B9%9Bdaya_S%C5%ABtra"], "risk_of_overread": "High. Retained, released, and embodied may be analyst categories that flatten native distinctions. Dogen-style practice-realization, Shinran's Other Power, and no-attainment Prajnaparamita may not be hard cases inside the grid; they may reject the temporal and ownership assumptions that make the grid possible.", "secondary_literature_gap": "This audit did not newly inspect Pali, Sanskrit, Chinese, or Japanese originals. Before publication, read fuller work on upaya, raft and ladder metaphors, Hori on koan curricula, Sells on unsaying, Smith on Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein, Dogen scholarship on practice-realization, Shinran scholarship on Other Power, Pargament on agency styles, and Hadot on spiritual exercises.", "structural_observation": "MN 22 is a direct near-neighbor: the teaching is grasped rightly, used for crossing, and not carried as a burden. The Heart Sutra strains a simple release model because it negates attainment while still retaining reliance, mantra, and bodhisattva practice. Together they support a two-variable after-use question, but they also show that the candidate is mostly a comparative rubric for already visible structures."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.92, "novelty": 0.31, "source_reliability": 0.8}, "run_ids": ["20260529-153241-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260529-153241-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "The Road Must Know Its End", "unlike_statement": "Unlike MN 22, upaya, Sells, Smith, Dogen scholarship, and prior Lumenary custody models, this idea's possible contribution is a bounded two-variable after-use rubric that predicts when a practitioner should keep a method, set it down, or let it appear as conduct, especially for achievement-driven people who turn tools into proof of worth."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:49:{"agent": "claude", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Shin and Soto practices still contain concrete actions, warnings, correction, forms, teachers, communities, and conduct expectations.", "confidence_effect": "Keeps the status at renamed rather than candidate discovery. The idea should become a scope-condition addendum unless coding shows clear refusal rather than relocation.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If nembutsu, zazen, teacher correction, vows, forms, and ordinary conduct function as retained or embodied methods, then the custody model is not abolished. It is relocated from self-ownership to vow, practice, teacher, community, or form. The boundary claim would then be overstated."}, "audit_id": "c429f79033672ed2", "claim_units": ["Keep, release, embody assumes practitioner ownership of the method or result.", "Keep, release, embody assumes a temporal after in which custody can be decided.", "Shinran's Other Power refuses practitioner ownership, calculation, and self-generated entrusting.", "Dogen's practice-realization refuses the separation between method, verification, and later custody.", "The bounded model has a modern contraindication: depleted people may be harmed by another stewardship prompt.", "The No-Audit Check is a low-risk alternative for over-managers, unless it licenses avoidance or drift."], "confidence": 0.86, "created_at": "2026-05-29T15:41:51+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Education, therapy, management, and recovery programs.", "prediction": "For exhausted over-managers, interventions that suspend self-evaluation and distribute custody to routines, relationships, or environment will outperform reflective review prompts on rumination and burnout, provided safeguards preserve responsibility.", "structural_translation": "Some interventions assume the learner or client should monitor, evaluate, and own the change process. Others work by reducing self-management, distributing support, or embedding action in practice without a later audit.", "would_count_against_it": "Reflective review prompts help depleted participants as much as no-audit prompts, or no-audit reliably increases avoidance, missed obligations, and helplessness."}, "exact_claim": "The keep, release, embody model silently assumes that the practitioner provisionally owns the method and that there is an after in which custody of the result can be decided. Radical Other Power and practice-realization break those assumptions: in Shinran's jinen honi the practitioner never owns the method, trust, or result, while in Dogen's shusho-itto there is no discrete after outside practice. Therefore the custody model is bounded, and for depleted over-managing people the prompt to decide what to keep, release, or embody can become one more burden.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260529-153241-20260529-153241", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Blind coders can identify texts that grant practitioner ownership and discrete completion separately from texts that relocate or refuse those assumptions, and those codes predict held-out warning and repair patterns.", "if_model_is_right": "Ownership and after are true scope conditions for after-use models.", "test_surface": "Split-source corpus coding with entry passages, doctrinal passages, and held-out manuals or practitioner interviews.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders cannot separate refusal from relocation, or retain, release, embody categories work equally well across Shinran, Dogen, Advaita, Theravada, Rinzai, apophatic Christian, and Sufi sources."}, {"expected_observation": "Participants high in burnout, rumination, and compulsive self-monitoring experience more relief and less self-surveillance from a no-audit prompt than from keep, release, embody review.", "if_model_is_right": "The No-Audit Check is better for depleted over-managers than an After-Use Check.", "test_surface": "Randomized micro-pilot with burnout, depression, perfectionism, responsibility-avoidance, and clinical-risk screening.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "No-audit increases avoidance, helplessness, drift, or missed responsibilities, or the After-Use Check performs equally or better for the depleted cohort."}, {"expected_observation": "The same practitioner is more likely to reject keep, release, embody language when speaking from Jodo Shinshu or Soto practice-realization than when speaking from Advaita inquiry, vipassana, therapy, or productivity training.", "if_model_is_right": "Dual-trained practitioners will switch frames by tradition.", "test_surface": "Semi-structured interviews with dual-trained practitioners, asking for concrete student cases rather than abstract agreement.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Practitioners comfortably translate all traditions into keep, release, embody without loss, or the differences are fully explained by teacher personality and institutional culture."}], "idea_id": "961f70e0ab57ecb8", "idea_path": "observations/claude/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Shinran jinen honi no calculation Other Power natural working of the primal vow", "Tannisho nembutsu not practice not good act practicer Other Power self power", "Dogen Bendowa practice realization one shusho itto verification outside practice", "Dogen practice and realization are one scholarship", "Jodo Shinshu entrusting shinjin given not produced calculation", "Pargament deferring religious coping style agency God control", "burnout overcontrol rumination self monitoring perfectionism intervention", "metacognitive therapy rumination self monitoring worry overmanagement"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "The current idea emphasizes non-ownership and no-after as scope conditions and adds the No-Audit Check for depleted over-managers.", "novelty_impact": "Major internal downgrade. This is best treated as a sibling consolidation, not a separate discovery.", "overlap": "Extremely close. Both argue that release teaching applies to active-voice result-ownership, while Other Power, practice-realization, and no-attainment sources strain or refuse the release frame.", "source": "Internal Lumenary audit, You cannot release what you never held, https://local/reviews/originality/2026-05-29-you-cannot-release-what-you-never-held-3f00413ce244b54e.json"}, {"difference": "The candidate uses Shinran as a scope condition for a comparative after-use model and as a modern caution for over-management.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade for the theological structure. The contribution is a boundary application, not a discovery of non-ownership.", "overlap": "Very close for the non-ownership claim: natural working and Other Power oppose practicer calculation and self-generated control.", "source": "Shinran, On Jinen-Honi, https://shinranworks.com/letters/lamp-for-the-latter-ages/on-jinen-honi-1258/"}, {"difference": "The candidate frames that denial as a failure of keep, release, embody categories.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades to renamed or extended. The primary text already contains the core refusal of ownership.", "overlap": "Very close for denying nembutsu as the practitioner's self-powered good act or possessed practice.", "source": "Tannisho, A Record in Lament of Divergences, https://shinranworks.com/related-works-by-other-authors/a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/"}, {"difference": "The candidate turns this into an explicit scope condition for Lumenary custody models.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the no-after insight to known Soto doctrine, while preserving modest value in the comparative boundary rule.", "overlap": "Very close for refusing a temporal gap between practice and later verification.", "source": "Soto Zen, Shusho Itto, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"}, {"difference": "Pargament studies coping style and control attribution, not method-completion temporality or practitioner ownership as scope conditions.", "novelty_impact": "Reduces novelty of the agency claim. The candidate must show predictive gain beyond deferring, collaborative, and self-directing agency models.", "overlap": "Close for agency relocation away from the individual self and toward divine action, especially deferring and collaborative modes.", "source": "Pargament et al., religious problem-solving styles"}, {"difference": "The candidate connects that clinical risk to theological non-ownership and practice-realization boundary cases.", "novelty_impact": "Supports human-condition relevance but downgrades the practical caution to a known risk unless tested as a specific fit rule.", "overlap": "Close for the caution that reflective review can become rumination, self-surveillance, or another performance demand.", "source": "Clinical and coaching literature on rumination, perfectionism, self-monitoring, and burnout, plus local source cards modern-human-condition-who-burn-out-occupational-phenomenon and modern-human-condition-curran-hill-perfectionism-increasing"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a discovery. Publish, if at all, as a scope-condition addendum to the after-use and custody models.", "Merge or cross-index with You cannot release what you never held, The Road Must Know Its End, The Method's Reckoning, Holding Without Owning, and The Test Is How You Return unless a separability test distinguishes them.", "Build a codebook with fields for practitioner ownership, completion temporality, custody relocation, no-custody frame, support holder, warning, repair, evidence passage, and analyst-frame refusal.", "Close-read Shinran's Japanese terms around jinen honi and hakarai, Dogen on shusho-itto and non-gaining, and practitioner manuals where concrete guidance appears.", "Pilot The No-Audit Check only with explicit stop conditions for avoidance, drift, missed duties, helplessness, depression, dissociation, mania, trauma activation, and clinical distress."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.55 to 0.28. The non-ownership and no-after structures are well established in Shinran and Dogen, and the core Lumenary comparison is already present in the recent audit of You cannot release what you never held. The modern caution overlaps with known rumination, perfectionism, and burnout risks. Human-condition fit is strong for depleted over-managers, caregivers, founders, professionals, students, and serious practitioners who turn even rest into performance. It is not for people who need planning, accountability, medication, therapy, social support, or material workload reduction, nor for acute crisis, addiction withdrawal, severe depression, dissociation, psychosis, mania, or responsibility avoidance.", "originality_status": "renamed", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say the distinction is already standard as Other Power, practice-realization, grace, surrender, non-calculation, or non-gaining mind, and that the no-audit prompt is simply rest from rumination or basic clinical caution.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners can use the two scope questions to prevent a real teaching mismatch, and clinicians or coaches observe that no-audit works better than review prompts for a clearly screened over-management cohort without increasing avoidance.", "questions": ["When guiding students, do you ever ask them what to keep, release, or embody, or would that distort your tradition's grammar?", "In Shin or Soto contexts, is custody abolished, or is it held by vow, practice, teacher, sangha, text, form, or conduct?", "Can you name cases where reflective review became harmful over-management, and what repair helped?", "Would a no-audit prompt relieve depleted people, or would it license avoidance and weaken ordinary responsibility?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Jodo Shinshu ministers and scholars", "Soto Zen teachers and Dogen scholars", "Rinzai Zen teachers", "Theravada teachers familiar with raft and non-clinging instructions", "Christian spiritual directors familiar with grace", "Clinicians working with burnout, perfectionism, rumination, depression, and avoidance", "Coaches or supervisors working with over-managing professionals and caregivers"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Shinran, On Jinen-Honi and Tannisho, https://shinranworks.com/letters/lamp-for-the-latter-ages/on-jinen-honi-1258/ and https://shinranworks.com/related-works-by-other-authors/a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/", "Dogen, Bendowa and shusho-itto practice-realization sources, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"], "risk_of_overread": "Moderate to high. The claim may exaggerate refusal into absence. Other Power and practice-realization may not abolish all custody questions; they may relocate custody to vow, teacher, text, sangha, conduct, or practice itself. The human-condition claim may also overgeneralize depletion, since some burned-out people need structure and accountability rather than non-audit.", "secondary_literature_gap": "This audit did not read Japanese sources, Dogen commentarial scholarship, Jodo Shinshu scholarship, grace-effort theology, Pargament's full agency-style work, or ethnographic practitioner accounts. It also did not verify whether other traditions with inherited practice, ritual-first formation, or apophatic unsaying similarly refuse the ownership-and-after assumptions.", "structural_observation": "Shinran relocates efficacy to Other Power and warns against calculation, so the practitioner is not the owner who later decides how to carry the method. Dogen's practice-realization collapses the gap between practice and verification, so a later custody decision is not the native shape of the path. These are strong boundary cases against a universal after-use grid, but they do not eliminate all guidance: Shin still has nembutsu, warnings, and entrusting language, and Soto still has zazen, discipline, teacher correction, and conduct."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.9, "novelty": 0.28, "source_reliability": 0.78}, "run_ids": ["20260529-153241-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260529-153241-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "When There Is Nothing To Keep Or Release", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Shinran's Other Power, Dogen's practice-realization, Pargament's agency styles, burnout rumination literature, and prior Lumenary release and custody models, this idea's possible contribution is an explicit scope test: before applying keep, release, or embody guidance, first ask whether the tradition grants provisional practitioner ownership and a discrete after, and whether the person has enough agency to benefit from a custody prompt."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:50:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Dogen practice-realization, Shinran Other Power, and the Heart Sutra's no-attainment-with-reliance pattern.", "confidence_effect": "Substantially lowers confidence in universal scope. The model can survive as a heuristic only if it first codes whether a tradition permits a separable result and practitioner custody.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "These cases do not merely choose keep, release, or embody. They challenge the assumed sequence: method first, result next, custody afterward. They may relocate custody to practice, vow, text, teacher, sangha, or conduct rather than grant a practitioner a post-use choice."}, "audit_id": "fc7b25df89b750ea", "claim_units": ["Methods train the practitioner's post-use relation to the method.", "The prior confirming, canceling, dissolving model misses possessability and aftermath.", "A two-axis model, validates versus undermines, and retained versus abandoned versus embodied, explains post-insight risks and training patterns.", "Achievement pressure can turn a released method into a trophy or an embodied method into an endless checklist.", "A mature practice includes aftermath instructions."], "confidence": 0.88, "created_at": "2026-05-29T16:11:58+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Education, therapy, coaching, and organizational training.", "prediction": "Programs that explicitly teach after-use relations for their methods will show better transfer and less dependency, performance identity, or ritualized self-monitoring than programs that only teach the method.", "structural_translation": "Learning methods also have aftermaths: some drills must be retained, some scaffolds should be removed, and some lessons should become ordinary conduct rather than identity.", "would_count_against_it": "After-use instructions add no predictive value over ordinary practice frequency, teacher quality, or workload conditions, or they increase rumination and dependency."}, "exact_claim": "A mature practice is not finished when it produces insight. It also teaches its post-use relation: whether the method validates or undermines its own way of seeing, and whether the practice should be retained, released, or embodied as ordinary conduct.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260529-160250-20260529-160250", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Blind coders can code validates versus undermines and retained versus abandoned versus embodied from instruction passages, then predict held-out warnings, repairs, and verification rules better than tradition label alone.", "if_model_is_right": "Method shape predicts aftermath instruction.", "test_surface": "Split-source corpus coding across MN 22, Heart Sutra, Mandukya, Dogen, Shinran, apophatic Christian, Sufi, Advaita, and koan-training sources.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders cannot agree on the axes, or the axes do not predict held-out warnings better than generic variables such as teacher style, institution, practice intensity, or tradition identity."}, {"expected_observation": "Dual-trained practitioners report trophy insight after confirming methods, nihilistic dismissal or premature release after undermining methods, and endless self-performance after embodied methods.", "if_model_is_right": "Different method shapes create different post-practice temptations.", "test_surface": "Semi-structured practitioner interviews asking for concrete failure and repair cases, not agreement with the model.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Practitioners report the same temptation profile across method types, or differences are better explained by personality, trauma history, teacher style, or institutional culture."}, {"expected_observation": "Screened perfectionistic practitioners show lower self-scoring and rumination after a brief keep, release, ask, or embody check than after generic journaling, without increased avoidance of duties.", "if_model_is_right": "The After-Use Check helps a narrow high-achievement cohort.", "test_surface": "Small randomized micro-pilot with measures for perfectionism, burnout, rumination, responsibility avoidance, and ordinary conduct.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The check increases rumination, scrupulosity, superiority, avoidance, or workload denial, or generic rest performs equally well."}], "idea_id": "eb9eb4682194e725", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape.md", "literature_search_queries": ["MN 22 raft simile Dhamma raft crossing not holding on primary text", "Heart Sutra no attainment relies on Prajnaparamita primary text", "Dogen Bendowa shusho itto practice realization one primary source", "Wittgenstein Tractatus 6.54 throw away ladder Nagarjuna therapeutic method", "Joshua William Smith Snakes and Ladders Nagarjuna Wittgenstein therapy Sophia 2021", "Michael Sells Mystical Languages of Unsaying apophatic discourse", "Pierre Hadot spiritual exercises philosophy as way of life", "Pargament religious problem solving styles self directing collaborative deferring", "WHO burnout occupational phenomenon Curran Hill perfectionism increasing"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This candidate states the two axes more explicitly and frames the issue as method shape rather than road completion.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. This is mostly a renamed or slightly sharpened version of the existing Lumenary after-use model.", "overlap": "Extremely close. The prior audit already names keep, release, and embody as an after-use rubric and lowers novelty for the same MN 22, Heart Sutra, Dogen, Sells, Smith, and achievement-pressure basis.", "source": "Internal Lumenary audit, The Road Must Know Its End, reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.json"}, {"difference": "The current candidate adds modern achievement-contingent self-worth and a low-risk After-Use Check.", "novelty_impact": "Major internal novelty loss. The new value is practical packaging, not discovery.", "overlap": "Very close. It already asks what a method does with its authority at completion and was later instructed to rebuild as two axes: validates versus undermines, retained versus abandoned or embodied.", "source": "Internal Lumenary observation, The Method's Reckoning: What a Practice Does With Its Own Authority at Completion, observations/claude/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion.md"}, {"difference": "The candidate generalizes this into a comparative typology and adds retained and embodied cases.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the release quadrant to known primary-text structure.", "overlap": "The raft simile already gives the core post-use structure: use the teaching for crossing, then do not carry it as a burden.", "source": "MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, https://obo.genaud.net/dhamma-vinaya/ati/mn/mn.022.than.ati.htm"}, {"difference": "The candidate tries to make self-canceling method one quadrant among several practice aftermaths.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the self-canceling portion. Remaining novelty depends on whether the wider typology predicts actual warnings and repairs.", "overlap": "Very close for self-canceling method: propositions or therapeutic arguments are used, then surmounted or dissolved.", "source": "Wittgenstein, Tractatus 6.54, https://tractatus.baneland.de/en/6.54/ and Joshua William Smith, Snakes and Ladders, https://philpapers.org/rec/SMISAL-7"}, {"difference": "Sells focuses on apophatic discourse, while the candidate focuses on whole-practice custody and post-use conduct.", "novelty_impact": "Reduces novelty for the dissolving or unsaying side, but leaves some room for practitioner-facing after-use coding.", "overlap": "Close for language that turns back on its own propositions and names.", "source": "Michael A. Sells, Mystical Languages of Unsaying, https://books.google.com/books/about/Mystical_Languages_of_Unsaying.html?id=84dZQFLEp_0C"}, {"difference": "The candidate treats this as an embodied or third post-use category, while Dogen may reject the post-use grid itself.", "novelty_impact": "Forces downgrade and bounded use. If Dogen is not on the axis, the model must become a scope-limited heuristic.", "overlap": "Close as anomaly and near-neighbor: practice-realization refuses a simple means-result-after sequence.", "source": "Dogen shusho itto, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Cross-index or merge with The Road Must Know Its End, The Method's Reckoning, Holding Without Owning, The Test Is How You Return, Keep What Can Correct You, and You cannot release what you never held.", "Convert the idea into a bounded after-use coding protocol, not doctrine.", "Add a scope gate before coding: does the tradition permit a separable result and practitioner custody?", "Use split-source blind coding. Do not let one passage establish method shape and confirm the predicted warning or repair.", "Pilot The After-Use Check only with screening for perfectionism, scrupulosity, avoidance, workload coercion, dissociation, mania, trauma activation, severe depression, and clinical distress."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.68 to 0.26. The core structure is already present in internal Lumenary records and in external raft, ladder, apophatic, therapeutic, and practice-realization sources. Human-condition fit is real but narrow: it serves achievement-contingent self-worth, perfectionism, burnout, and compulsive self-improvement among functioning practitioners. It is not a fit for acute crisis, addiction withdrawal, severe depression, dissociation, psychosis, mania, under-motivation, responsibility avoidance, or structural burnout where workload and material conditions are primary.", "originality_status": "renamed", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say this is standard raft teaching, upaya, integration, surrender, practice-realization, or supervision in new language, and that the rubric does not change sequencing or repair.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners can use the rubric to distinguish actual failure modes, choose different repairs, and prevent achievement-driven method ownership in cases where older vocabulary was too broad.", "questions": ["Do you actually distinguish practices that should be kept, released, or embodied, or is this outsider vocabulary?", "Can you name concrete cases where carrying a method after it helped became harmful, and what repair was given?", "Does this rubric predict student warnings or repairs better than your existing terms such as upaya, non-attachment, surrender, practice-realization, integration, or ordinary supervision?", "For high-achievement practitioners, does an After-Use Check reduce worth-pressure or create another performance ritual?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Theravada teachers familiar with MN 22 and upaya", "Rinzai Zen teachers familiar with koan curricula", "Soto Zen teachers and Dogen scholars", "Jodo Shinshu ministers", "Advaita teachers", "Christian apophatic spiritual directors", "Sufi teachers familiar with fana and baqa", "Clinicians or coaches working with perfectionism, burnout, and compulsive self-improvement"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, https://obo.genaud.net/dhamma-vinaya/ati/mn/mn.022.than.ati.htm", "Heart Sutra and Dogen shusho itto sources, https://www.mnzencenter.org/uploads/2/9/5/8/29581455/heart.pdf and https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"], "risk_of_overread": "High. Retained, released, and embodied may be analyst categories imposed on traditions whose native grammar is vow, grace, ritual, teacher correction, lineage, or practice-realization. The model may also mistake a single tradition's stage-specific instructions for a stable method type.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Before any public claim, read fuller work on upaya, raft and ladder metaphors, Wittgenstein's ladder, Nagarjuna's no-thesis claim, Hori on koan pedagogy, Sells on apophasis, Hadot on spiritual exercises, Dogen scholarship, Shinran scholarship, and Pargament on religious agency styles. Japanese, Pali, Sanskrit, and Chinese terms were not checked here.", "structural_observation": "MN 22 is a direct release template: the Dhamma is used for crossing and then not carried. The Heart Sutra complicates release because it denies path and attainment while still relying on Prajnaparamita, mantra, recitation, and teacher-mediated practice. Dogen complicates both retention and abandonment because practice and realization are described as one, so there is no clean after-stage where custody is decided."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.92, "novelty": 0.26, "source_reliability": 0.82}, "run_ids": ["20260529-160250-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260529-160250-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "Method release has a shape", "unlike_statement": "Unlike MN 22, Wittgenstein's ladder, Smith's Nagarjuna-Wittgenstein therapy, Sells's apophatic unsaying, Dogen's practice-realization, and prior Lumenary after-use models, this idea's possible contribution is a bounded coding rubric that tests whether method type predicts held-out warnings, repairs, and post-insight temptations in achievement-pressured practitioners."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:51:{"agent": "claude", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Non-instrumental traditions still prescribe forms, warnings, corrections, ethics, teachers, community standards, and ordinary conduct.", "confidence_effect": "Keeps the status at extended rather than candidate discovery. The model must distinguish no separable self-owned result from no discipline, no effect, or no accountability.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If Eihei Shingi, Soto training, Shinran's cautions against licensed evil, nembutsu practice, and community transmission all function as retained disciplines with real effects, then non-instrumentality is not outside the custody apparatus. It is a different custody location: form-held, vow-held, teacher-held, conduct-held, or community-held."}, "audit_id": "6243c8e923d5f36f", "claim_units": ["The recent custody apparatus assumes instrumentality: do this, get that, steward the result.", "Some practices reject a separable result and therefore fall outside the custody grid.", "Dogen's practice-realization makes sitting not a bridge to later enlightenment but the expression of realization itself.", "Shinran's Other Power denies practicer calculation and owned efficacy.", "The first audit question should be whether the practice claims to make something separable.", "The teaching targets achievement-driven people who convert every activity into a scored outcome."], "confidence": 0.86, "created_at": "2026-05-29T16:11:58+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Education, arts, sports, therapy, and management.", "prediction": "For high performers with achievement-contingent self-worth, bounded autotelic activities with no product to display will reduce self-scoring more than another reflective optimization tool, provided duties and clinical risks are protected.", "structural_translation": "Some activities are instrumental drills with separable outputs, while others are autotelic practices whose goods are internal to participation and whose correction is carried by form, community, and conduct.", "would_count_against_it": "No-result activities perform no better than ordinary rest, or they reliably increase avoidance, low mood, passivity, or contempt for necessary outcomes."}, "exact_claim": "Before asking what a practice does with authority over its result, ask whether it claims to produce a separable result at all. Custody, release, and correction vocabulary applies only to instrumental practices. Dogen's practice-realization and Shinran's Other Power dissolve the tool frame because sitting or entrusting is not owned as a means to a later product.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260529-160250-20260529-160250", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Texts and manuals coded as non-instrumental from doctrinal passages will show less result-custody language and more conduct, form, vow, teacher, or community correction language in held-out sources.", "if_model_is_right": "The separable-result question is a real scope gate.", "test_surface": "Split-source coding of Dogen, Shinran, MN 22, koan curricula, Advaita inquiry, apophatic Christian sources, Sufi fana and baqa, and ritual manuals.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Self-described non-instrumental traditions contain result-custody language as centrally as instrumental traditions, or coders cannot distinguish result refusal from result relocation."}, {"expected_observation": "Screened high-achievement participants doing a no-result activity show reduced self-scoring and rumination in the next hour or day compared with metric-free rest or generic mindfulness, without missed duties.", "if_model_is_right": "Achievement-driven people benefit from temporary non-result practice.", "test_surface": "Randomized micro-pilot with perfectionism, burnout, depression, avoidance, and responsibility checks.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The practice increases avoidance, pointlessness, shame, low mood, missed obligations, or performs no better than ordinary leisure."}, {"expected_observation": "Soto and Jodo Shinshu practitioners reject get-result-then-steward language more consistently than Theravada, Advaita, therapy, productivity, or skills-training practitioners, while still naming concrete correction holders.", "if_model_is_right": "Practitioners treat the tool frame as a category mistake in some traditions.", "test_surface": "Dual-trained practitioner interviews asking for failed-student cases and repair instructions.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Practitioners across traditions translate their practices comfortably into tool, result, and stewardship language without loss, or differences are fully explained by teacher personality."}], "idea_id": "0f43230b488f18e5", "idea_path": "observations/claude/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Dogen shusho itto practice realization one cause effect practice realization", "Shinran jinen honi no calculation Other Power practicer", "Tannisho nembutsu not practice not good act Other Power self power", "MN 22 raft simile instrumental practice crossing let go", "instrumental and non-instrumental interpretations of ritual action auto-telicity", "Csikszentmihalyi autotelic activity flow self contained goal", "MacIntyre practice internal goods After Virtue", "Hadot spiritual exercises philosophy way of life transformation", "Pargament religious problem solving styles agency God control"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This candidate uses the broader word instrumentality and asks whether the practice claims to produce a separable result.", "novelty_impact": "Major internal downgrade. The scope-gate framing is useful but not a new discovery.", "overlap": "Extremely close. The prior audit already says keep, release, embody assumes practitioner ownership and a discrete after, and that Shinran and Dogen break those assumptions.", "source": "Internal Lumenary audit, When There Is Nothing To Keep Or Release, reviews/originality/2026-05-29-when-there-is-nothing-to-keep-or-release-c429f79033672ed2.json"}, {"difference": "The candidate applies the same instrumentality critique to contemplative practice authority and achievement-contingent self-worth.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade. The central distinction is known; the contribution is a domain-specific application.", "overlap": "Very close structural near-neighbor. The article explicitly critiques instrumental approaches to ritual action and develops non-instrumental alternatives through auto-telicity and protagonism.", "source": "Instrumental and Non-Instrumental Interpretations of Ritual Action, Global Studies Quarterly, https://academic.oup.com/isagsq/article/6/1/ksag013/8508723"}, {"difference": "The candidate turns this into a scope rule for Lumenary's custody apparatus.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the Dogen example to known Soto doctrine.", "overlap": "Very close. The source states that shusho itto demolishes the generally accepted cause-effect relation between practice and realization.", "source": "Dogen shusho itto, Soto Zen key term, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate uses Shinran as a non-tool boundary case rather than as Pure Land doctrine alone.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the non-ownership claim to known primary-text structure.", "overlap": "Very close. Shinran explicitly rejects practicer calculation and describes Other Power as no working, which undermines self-owned method efficacy.", "source": "Shinran, On Jinen Honi, https://shinranworks.com/hymns-in-japanese/hymns-of-the-dharma-ages/on-jinen-honi/"}, {"difference": "The candidate applies autotelicity to religious and contemplative practice comparison, not general optimal experience.", "novelty_impact": "Reduces novelty of the tool versus non-tool distinction.", "overlap": "Close for the claim that some activity is an end in itself rather than a means to future benefit.", "source": "Csikszentmihalyi and autotelic flow summaries, for example https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/psychology/autotelic-experience"}, {"difference": "MacIntyre is not focused on post-insight custody or spiritual release grammar.", "novelty_impact": "Reduces novelty for practice-as-more-than-instrument, but leaves a possible comparative-religion extension.", "overlap": "Close for practices whose goods are internal to participation and cannot be reduced to external products.", "source": "MacIntyre, After Virtue practice and internal goods, summary at https://philopedia.org/works/after-virtue-a-study-in-moral-theory/"}, {"difference": "Pargament studies coping and control attribution, not whether a practice produces a separable result.", "novelty_impact": "For Shinran-style agency relocation, novelty is low unless the separable-result gate predicts warnings beyond agency-style variables.", "overlap": "Close for agency distribution between individual and divine action, especially deferring and collaborative styles.", "source": "Pargament et al., religious problem-solving styles, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a discovery. Publish, if at all, as a scope-gate addendum to the custody and release models.", "Cross-index with When There Is Nothing To Keep Or Release, You cannot release what you never held, The Road Must Know Its End, The Method's Reckoning, and Holding Without Owning.", "Build a codebook with fields for separable result, instrumentality claim, result custody, correction holder, form holder, conduct holder, support locus, warning, repair, evidence passage, and analyst-frame refusal.", "Read non-instrumental ritual theory, autotelic flow literature, MacIntyre on practices, Dogen's Eihei Shingi, Bendowa and Genjokoan, Shinran and Tannisho in stronger translations before public use.", "Pilot Do One Thing With No Result only with explicit stops for avoidance, pointlessness, low mood, missed duties, dissociation, mania, addiction withdrawal, trauma activation, severe depression, and clinical distress."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.55 to 0.34. The instrumental versus non-instrumental distinction is old and appears directly in Dogen, Shinran, ritual theory, autotelic activity theory, and prior Lumenary non-ownership audits. The useful extension is narrower: using separable-result as a pre-coding scope gate for Lumenary's custody and release apparatus. Human-condition fit is strong for functioning perfectionists, founders, students, creators, and professionals who convert every activity into proof of worth. It is not for under-motivation, responsibility avoidance, severe depression, dissociation, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, acute crisis, coercive workloads, or people who need concrete completed outcomes restored before resultless practice is safe.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-practice-is-a-tool-6243c8e923d5f36f.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners and scholars say this is already standard as practice-realization, Other Power, autotelic ritual, internal goods, non-attachment, grace, or non-gaining mind, and that the scope gate adds no predictive guidance.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners can use the separable-result question to prevent misguidance, identify where accountability is relocated, and predict when outcome language will harm high-achievement students.", "questions": ["In your tradition, is the practice a means to a separable result, an expression of realization or trust, or something else?", "When students treat the practice as a tool for getting something, what goes wrong and how do you repair it?", "If the practice is not a tool, where do correction and accountability reside: teacher, text, vow, form, conduct, community, or clinical care?", "For achievement-driven people, does no-result practice reduce self-scoring, or does it become avoidance and passivity?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Soto Zen teachers and Dogen scholars", "Jodo Shinshu ministers and scholars", "Theravada teachers familiar with MN 22", "Ritual studies scholars", "Christian spiritual directors familiar with grace and contemplation", "Sufi teachers familiar with fana and baqa", "Flow researchers or performance psychologists", "Clinicians working with perfectionism, burnout, depression, and avoidance"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, https://obo.genaud.net/dhamma-vinaya/ati/mn/mn.022.than.ati.htm", "Dogen shusho itto and Shinran jinen honi, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf and https://shinranworks.com/hymns-in-japanese/hymns-of-the-dharma-ages/on-jinen-honi/"], "risk_of_overread": "High. Non-instrumental self-description does not mean absence of discipline, correction, warnings, institutional form, or effects. Dogen still requires continuous practice, and Shinran still has nembutsu, entrusting, and cautions. The model may confuse no owned result with no practical structure.", "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit did not read Eihei Shingi, full Bendowa or Genjokoan in Japanese, Shinran's Japanese around jinen and hakarai, Tannisho anti-license passages in Japanese, ritual theory in depth, Aristotle praxis and poiesis sources, or empirical studies of autotelic practice and perfectionism. These are necessary before raising novelty.", "structural_observation": "MN 22 is explicitly instrumental: effort with the raft gets one across, then the raft should not be carried. Dogen's shusho itto demolishes the cause-effect separation between practice and realization, while Shinran's jinen honi removes calculation by the practicer and locates efficacy in Other Power. The contrast supports a scope distinction, but not a discovery: the instrumental versus non-instrumental contrast is already structurally visible in the primary texts."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.9, "novelty": 0.34, "source_reliability": 0.8}, "run_ids": ["20260529-160250-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260529-160250-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "Not Every Practice Is a Tool", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Dogen's practice-realization, Shinran's Other Power, autotelic activity theory, non-instrumental ritual theory, MacIntyre's internal goods, and prior Lumenary non-ownership audits, this idea's possible contribution is a practical scope gate for comparative coding: ask first whether a practice claims to produce a separable result before applying custody, release, or correction vocabulary."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:52:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Scrupulosity, moral OCD, and reassurance-seeking practitioners who ask teachers, confessors, peers, or AI systems to hold the gate.", "confidence_effect": "Substantially lowers confidence in external gate recommendations. The model needs a mandatory OCD, scrupulosity, dependency, abuse, and clinical-risk screen before any externally held gate is called safer.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "For these users, moving the gate outside the self may not reduce self-scoring. It can create a reassurance loop, approval dependence, compulsive confession, or family and clergy accommodation. ERP often requires reducing reassurance and learning to tolerate uncertainty, so the apparently safer external gate can be the harmful intervention."}, "audit_id": "976d96eaa0a316f4", "claim_units": ["A return test should not be recommended until the practice is checked for whether result language is native, permitted, or imported.", "The model distinguishes a bypassing state from a compulsive self-scoring state.", "The decisive safety variable is who holds the diagnostic gate: self, teacher, peer, clinician, fixed rule, or no diagnostic practice.", "Self-administered return attention may help people who use insight or spiritual language to avoid conduct.", "For compulsive scorers, self-administered return attention may worsen rumination, self-punishment, and achievement-contingent self-worth.", "Oscillators should be classified by current state, not by a stable identity label.", "The human-condition target is achievement-contingent self-worth, perfectionism, burnout, and spiritual or reflective avoidance."], "confidence": 0.78, "created_at": "2026-05-29T16:23:56+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Education, performance coaching, and software engineering review systems.", "prediction": "For high-performing students, athletes, artists, or engineers with achievement-contingent self-worth, fixed-rule or peer-held review gates will reduce rumination and improve follow-through more than repeated private self-evaluation. For avoidant performers, a self-held return check will improve accountability more than resultless rest.", "structural_translation": "A diagnostic check can be self-held, peer-held, coach-held, rule-held, automated, or suspended. The same check helps avoidant performers face reality and harms compulsive optimizers who convert feedback into proof of worth.", "would_count_against_it": "No interaction appears between user state and gate holder, self-evaluation works equally well for compulsive scorers, or external and automated gates simply move self-worth dependence onto approval, metrics, or tool outputs."}, "exact_claim": "A practice-routing model must decide three things before recommending a return test: whether the practice permits result language, whether the practitioner is presently bypassing or self-scoring, and who should hold the diagnostic gate. Self-administered return attention may help the bypasser who uses insight to avoid conduct. For the compulsive scorer, the gate should be externally held by a teacher, peer, clinician, fixed rule, or replaced by resultless practice. For oscillators, the assignment must be state-level and revisable, not a stable identity label.", "execution_id": "dialogue-c34956fd7d2821ce", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Split-source coding will show that texts coded as instrumental from doctrinal or instruction passages contain more held-out return, fruit, stewardship, or conduct-test warnings, while Dogen and Shinran-style non-instrumental cases contain more form, vow, no-calculation, or practice-realization correction language.", "if_model_is_right": "Result-language permission is a real first gate rather than an analyst's imposed vocabulary.", "test_surface": "Blind coding of Ignatius, MN 22, Dogen Bendowa or Genjokoan, Shinran and Tannisho, Rinzai koan training, apophatic Christian texts, Sufi fana and baqa sources, and modern practice manuals.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders cannot reliably distinguish instrumental from non-instrumental cases, or held-out warning and correction language does not differ after controlling for tradition, teacher style, and institution."}, {"expected_observation": "In a screened pilot, bypass-state participants show improved ordinary conduct and reduced avoidance after a return check, while compulsive-scorer participants show more rumination and self-criticism after self-held checks than after fixed-rule, clinician-held, teacher-held, or resultless-practice alternatives.", "if_model_is_right": "Gate custody interacts with practitioner state.", "test_surface": "Randomized micro-pilot with measures for rumination, self-critical rumination, achievement-contingent self-worth, perfectionism, conduct follow-through, avoidance, burnout, and mood.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Self-held return checks help scorers as much as bypassers, or externally held and fixed-rule gates do not reduce rumination relative to self-held checks."}, {"expected_observation": "Within-person diary or EMA data will show the same practitioner moving between bypassing and scoring states across contexts, and state-level routing will predict next-day outcomes better than a one-time trait classification.", "if_model_is_right": "Oscillation is state-level and revisable, not a trait label.", "test_surface": "Two-week ecological momentary assessment with brief prompts after practice, work review, conflict, and rest periods.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Trait labels predict outcomes as well as state-level data, or people classified as oscillators do not show meaningful within-person switching."}, {"expected_observation": "Participants with elevated scrupulosity, OCD reassurance seeking, dependency, or authority-trauma scores will worsen under teacher or peer gate-holding unless the holder follows anti-reassurance and abuse-aware constraints.", "if_model_is_right": "External gate holding is not universally safer.", "test_surface": "Screened clinical-adjacent study and practitioner case review with ERP clinicians, spiritual directors, and meditation teachers.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "External gate holding improves these groups without increased reassurance seeking, dependency, fear, or loss of agency."}], "idea_id": "f1f42b2a44b9a9f6", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Ignatius Spiritual Exercises Annotation 17 director movements thoughts Rule 13 confessor spiritual person", "Dogen shusho itto practice realization result cause effect Bendowa", "Shinran jinen honi no calculation Other Power practicer working", "Pargament religion problem solving process self-directing deferring collaborative coping", "Mor Winquist self-focused attention negative affect meta-analysis private self-focus depression anxiety", "Nolen-Hoeksema rumination response styles theory self-focused attention depression", "spiritual bypassing Picciotto Fox Neto phenomenology psychological avoidance spiritualizing", "Varieties of Contemplative Experience meditation-related challenges teacher clinician support factors", "measurement-based care psychotherapy routine outcome monitoring not-on-track feedback Lambert", "guided versus unguided self-help CBT depression anxiety meta-analysis", "scrupulosity OCD reassurance seeking exposure response prevention spiritual direction", "contingencies of self-worth Crocker Park achievement contingent self-worth perfectionism burnout"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "The candidate adds one clearer operational question: who holds the diagnostic gate when the same test can help bypassers and harm scorers.", "novelty_impact": "Major internal downgrade. Treat as an extension of existing Lumenary safety-routing work, not a standalone discovery.", "overlap": "Very close. The parent records already contain return testing, non-instrumental scope gating, correction holders, and safety worries around achievement-contingent self-worth.", "source": "Internal Lumenary records: The Test Is How You Return, Not Every Practice Is a Tool, Keep What Can Correct You, and related custody and after-use audits supplied in the prompt."}, {"difference": "Ignatius does not frame the issue through achievement-contingent self-worth, result-language scope gates, or clinical rumination risk.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for the core phrase who holds the gate. The new work must show predictive value beyond standard spiritual direction.", "overlap": "Very close for gate custody. Ignatian practice already routes interior movements through disclosure, director guidance, adaptation to the exercitant, and restraint on director overreach.", "source": "Ignatius of Loyola, Spiritual Exercises, Annotations 15 and 17 and Rule 13, https://www.orderofthecommonlife.org/spiritual-exercises-full-text and https://sacred-texts.com/chr/seil/seil78.htm"}, {"difference": "They focus on meditation-related challenges and appraisal, not on return tests, non-instrumental practice scope gates, or self-scoring high achievers.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the triage and support-holder parts to known contemplative-safety territory.", "overlap": "Close structural near-neighbor. These sources ask how experiences are appraised, which social agents shape interpretation, and what type of support a particular experience requires.", "source": "Lindahl, Fisher, Cooper, Rosen, and Britton, The varieties of contemplative experience, PLOS ONE 2017, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239, plus Lindahl, Britton, Cooper, and Kirmayer, Toward a Person-Centered Approach, https://bpb-us-w2.wpmucdn.com/sites.brown.edu/dist/f/330/files/2023/10/Lindahl-2019-Oxford-Handbook-of-Meditation-chapter.pdf"}, {"difference": "Pargament concerns coping with God and individual agency, not diagnostic gate custody across teacher, peer, clinician, fixed rule, or no practice.", "novelty_impact": "Reduces novelty for support-locus language but leaves room for a practice-safety routing extension.", "overlap": "Close for agency and responsibility distribution. Self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles already model who is experienced as holding problem-solving responsibility.", "source": "Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, Journal for the Scientific Study of Religion 1988, summary at https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/"}, {"difference": "The source does not address spiritual return tests, result-language scope, or bypassing versus self-scoring states.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the claim that support-holder assignment is new. The candidate should compare itself against guided, unguided, and stepped-care baselines.", "overlap": "Close clinical analog. Guided self-help and unguided self-help differ by human support, and treatment format affects effectiveness and acceptability.", "source": "Cuijpers et al., Effectiveness and Acceptability of Cognitive Behavior Therapy Delivery Formats in Adults With Depression, JAMA Psychiatry 2019, https://jamanetwork.com/journals/jamapsychiatry/fullarticle/2730724"}, {"difference": "MBC generally measures symptoms and progress, not spiritual result custody or the risk of turning the metric itself into self-worth evidence.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the gate-as-monitoring mechanism. The candidate's test must show it adds safety value beyond ordinary outcome monitoring and clinical feedback.", "overlap": "Close for repeated diagnostic checks whose output informs clinician decisions, especially for not-on-track clients.", "source": "Routine outcome monitoring and measurement-based care literature, for example Collecting Client Feedback, https://www.ovid.com/journals/psythy/pdf/10.1037/a0022238~collecting-client-feedback, and MBC review summaries at https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7246636/"}, {"difference": "The meta-analysis does not prescribe gate holders or distinguish spiritual bypassers from achievement scorers.", "novelty_impact": "Supports the safety rationale but does not make the model original.", "overlap": "Strong support and partial near-neighbor for the risk side. Private self-focus is linked with depression and generalized anxiety, making repeated self-checks risky for ruminative users.", "source": "Mor and Winquist, Self-Focused Attention and Negative Affect: A Meta-Analysis, Psychological Bulletin 2002, DOI http://dx.doi.org/10.1037/0033-2909.128.4.638, indexed at https://cris.huji.ac.il/en/publications/self-focused-attention-and-negative-affect-a-meta-analysis/"}, {"difference": "The literature does not combine bypass detection with non-instrumental scope gating and gate-custody assignment.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the bypasser half of the model to known clinical-spiritual territory.", "overlap": "Close for the bypasser category: spiritual ideas or practices can defend against difficult emotion, psychological work, responsibility, and ordinary conduct.", "source": "Spiritual bypassing literature, for example Picciotto, Fox, and Neto, A phenomenology of spiritual bypass, Journal of Spirituality in Mental Health 2018, indexed at https://openurl.ebsco.com/fulltext/gcd%3A132497915, and Fox and Picciotto, https://brill.com/view/journals/cvj/64/2/article-p227_7.xml"}, {"difference": "The candidate allows external holders as a safety option but does not yet specify when external holding becomes accommodation or reassurance compulsion.", "novelty_impact": "Forces a downgrade unless the model adds an OCD and scrupulosity exclusion pathway and distinguishes correction from reassurance.", "overlap": "Very important anomaly and near-neighbor. External reassurance, confession, and repeated checking can become compulsions that maintain OCD.", "source": "Scrupulosity and OCD reassurance-seeking literature, for example https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2211364914000116 and Yale family accommodation summary https://ysph.yale.edu/ysph/familyaccommodationocd/about/"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a discovery. Publish, if at all, as a provisional safety-routing heuristic for after-use and return-test practices.", "Cross-index with The Test Is How You Return, Not Every Practice Is a Tool, Keep What Can Correct You, Holding Without Owning, and correction-holder audits.", "Build a pre-registered codebook with fields for result-language permission, current state, gate holder, unsafe holder, fixed-rule option, no-practice option, evidence passage, warning, repair, clinical exclusion, and confidence.", "Use split-source blind coding. Do not let one passage both establish the gate and confirm the predicted warning or repair.", "Add mandatory anomaly values for scrupulosity, OCD reassurance seeking, dependency, abusive authority, valid solitude, non-instrumental practice, no-result practice, resultless rest, clinician-held care, and undecidable.", "Read full sources before public use: Ignatian directorial literature, contemporary spiritual direction ethics, VCE and Cheetah House materials, Pargament, measurement-based care, guided self-help, rumination and self-focused attention, achievement-contingent self-worth, perfectionism, spiritual bypassing, and scrupulosity ERP.", "Run practitioner interviews for concrete failure and repair cases, not agreement with the model.", "Pilot only with safety screens for rumination, perfectionism, OCD and scrupulosity, trauma, depression, mania, dissociation, addiction withdrawal, authority harm, avoidance, and workload coercion.", "Test against baselines: ordinary spiritual direction, clinician triage, guided self-help, routine outcome monitoring, ERP anti-reassurance rules, and prior Lumenary correction-holder models."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.62 to 0.42. The gate-holder idea is already close to Ignatian discernment, spiritual direction, contemplative adverse-effects support, routine outcome monitoring, guided self-help, Pargament agency styles, and OCD reassurance literature. The surviving contribution is narrower: a Lumenary safety-routing heuristic that combines result-language permission, current bypassing or scoring state, and diagnostic custody. Human-condition fit is real but bounded. It is for functioning high achievers, founders, students, creators, professionals, and spiritual practitioners who either use insight to avoid conduct or convert practice into proof of worth. It is not for acute crisis, mania, psychosis, severe depression, dissociation, trauma activation, addiction withdrawal, coercive workloads, active OCD or scrupulosity reassurance loops, abusive communities, or people without trustworthy support.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate-976d96eaa0a316f4.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say they already use this structure as ordinary spiritual direction, teacher supervision, pastoral discernment, ERP triage, guided self-help, routine outcome monitoring, or adverse-meditation support, and that the Lumenary framing adds no new prediction or repair rule.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners can use the three-gate sequence to prevent a specific failure they previously missed: result-language mismatch, self-held rumination, or unsafe external authority. Support rises if they can predict concrete student failures and choose different repairs from the codebook before seeing outcomes.", "questions": ["When a practitioner misuses insight, reflection, or spiritual language, how do you decide whether they should self-check, report to a guide, follow a fixed rule, stop the practice, or do something resultless?", "In concrete failure cases, did external guidance help, or did it become reassurance seeking, approval dependence, spiritual abuse, or more self-monitoring?", "Is the question 'does this practice permit result language?' native to your tradition or an analyst's imposition?", "Does this three-gate model change how you would route a student, or does it merely rename standard discernment, clinical triage, supervision, and spiritual direction?", "For high-achievement practitioners, does the gate reduce self-scoring, or does it become another score? What observable sign tells you the difference?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Ignatian spiritual directors", "Soto Zen teachers and Dogen scholars", "Jodo Shinshu ministers and scholars", "Buddhist meditation teachers familiar with adverse meditation experiences", "Clinicians working with contemplative distress", "ERP clinicians treating OCD and scrupulosity", "Therapists working with perfectionism, burnout, and achievement-contingent self-worth", "Peer-support facilitators and chaplains"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Ignatius of Loyola, Spiritual Exercises, Annotations 15 and 17 plus Rule 13 for discernment of spirits, https://www.orderofthecommonlife.org/spiritual-exercises-full-text and https://sacred-texts.com/chr/seil/seil78.htm", "Shinran, On Jinen Honi, and Dogen shusho itto summary, https://shinranworks.com/hymns-in-japanese/hymns-of-the-dharma-ages/on-jinen-honi/ and https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"], "risk_of_overread": "High. External gate holding can mean wise support, coercive authority, reassurance seeking, approval dependence, or institutional abuse. Non-instrumental practice does not mean no correction. Bypasser, scorer, and oscillator are crude state labels unless operationalized with validated measures and concrete behavior markers.", "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit did not read full Ignatian directorial manuals, contemporary spiritual direction ethics, full Dogen Bendowa or Eihei Shingi, Shinran and Tannisho in Japanese, OCD scrupulosity treatment literature beyond abstracts, or the full measurement-based care and guided self-help literatures. It also needs direct work in perfectionism, achievement-contingent self-worth, and contemplative adverse effects before public practice guidance.", "structural_observation": "Ignatius already makes gate custody explicit. The exercitant reports movements and thoughts, the director adapts exercises, and disclosure to a confessor or spiritual person breaks the secrecy of deceptive movements. Yet Annotation 15 also limits the director, the guide is not supposed to seize the final choice. Shinran strains the model from the opposite side: jinen honi rejects practicer calculation and warns that even talking about no-working can become another form of working. Dogen also strains the return-test frame because practice and realization are not separated as cause and later product. The candidate's structure is therefore not a discovery at the primary-text level. Its possible contribution is a routing rule for deciding when Ignatian-style disclosure, clinical support, fixed-rule gating, or no-result practice is appropriate."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.91, "novelty": 0.42, "source_reliability": 0.79}, "run_ids": [], "title": "Who Holds The Gate", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Ignatian spiritual direction, VCE person-centered support, Pargament agency styles, routine outcome monitoring, guided self-help, spiritual bypassing literature, and prior Lumenary return and scope-gate models, this claim says a public practice instruction should pass through three ordered gates: result-language permission, current bypassing versus self-scoring risk, and custody of the diagnostic itself. Its novelty depends on whether that three-gate routing predicts harm, repair, or non-fit better than existing spiritual direction, clinical triage, and contemplative-safety frameworks."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:53:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "OCD, scrupulosity, reassurance seeking, abusive authority, and valid solitude.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence in any public practice unless the codebook includes clinical exclusions, unsafe-authority detection, anti-reassurance rules, and a valid-solitude option.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "The model says a compulsive self-scorer may need a teacher, peer, clinician, or rule to hold the check. In OCD or scrupulosity, the same transfer can become reassurance compulsion. In abusive communities, external holding becomes control. In valid solitude, outside holding can weaken needed self-trust."}, "audit_id": "b9a584e898d8b829", "claim_units": ["A humility, release, or return check can become harmful self-scoring.", "Failure mode should determine check holder.", "Bypassers need conduct accountability more than relief from checking.", "Compulsive self-scorers may need the diagnostic held outside the self or suspended.", "Oscillators require present-state routing, not fixed type assignment.", "The practice is only publishable for a clear cohort: stable high-achievement practitioners harmed by self-scoring."], "confidence": 0.88, "created_at": "2026-05-29T16:49:43+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Software review and knowledge work", "prediction": "High-performing workers whose worth is tied to quality scores will complete more and ruminate less when acceptance criteria or reviewers hold the check, while avoidant workers will need a self-held concrete completion check.", "structural_translation": "The post-practice check becomes the post-output quality diagnostic. Depending on failure mode, quality can be held by the worker, a reviewer, acceptance criteria, a release rule, or temporarily not checked.", "would_count_against_it": "Generic code review, WIP limits, or ordinary management explain all outcome differences, or holder assignment by failure mode adds no predictive value."}, "exact_claim": "Post-practice checks are not automatically safe. The decisive safety variable is who holds the check today: the practitioner, another person, a rule, ordinary conduct, or no check. Bypassers may need a self-held conduct check, compulsive self-scorers may need external, rule-held, or suspended checking, and oscillators need state-based assignment rather than identity labels.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260529-163436-20260529-163436", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Compared with external or rule-held conditions, self-held checks increase rumination, shame, comparison, and repeated interpretation, while not improving next-day conduct.", "if_model_is_right": "Stable high-achievement practitioners high in achievement-contingent self-worth will fare worse with self-held after-use checks than with externally held, rule-held, or suspended checks.", "test_surface": "Two-week randomized pilot using contingencies of self-worth, rumination scales, mood ratings, and concrete duty completion.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Self-held checks reduce rumination and improve conduct as well as or better than external, rule-held, or suspended checks."}, {"expected_observation": "In high-bypass, low-self-scoring participants, a single conduct check increases repair behavior and reduces avoidance without increasing shame.", "if_model_is_right": "Practitioners using insight to avoid responsibility need a self-held return-to-conduct check more than they need rest from checking.", "test_surface": "Screened practice pilot with spiritual bypassing, avoidance, self-worth contingency, and next-day conduct measures.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The conduct check does not improve behavior, or it increases self-scoring at the same rate as in the compulsive scorer group."}, {"expected_observation": "Split-source coding of manuals predicts held-out warnings and repairs involving self, teacher, community, rule, conduct, or no-check options.", "if_model_is_right": "Practice manuals and teachers should assign diagnostic custody differently by stage, risk, and support ecology.", "test_surface": "Blind manual coding plus practitioner interviews using concrete misinterpretation and repair cases.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "All holder assignments are explained by institution type, teacher personality, or generic spiritual direction without added predictive gain from failure-mode coding."}], "idea_id": "774542105bd80eea", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours.md", "literature_search_queries": ["exact structural near neighbor same reflective diagnostic different holder by failure mode spiritual direction", "Ignatius Spiritual Exercises Annotation 15 17 Rule 13 scruples spiritual director", "Pargament religion problem solving self directing deferring collaborative coping", "Varieties of Contemplative Experience support structures appraisal social context meditation challenges", "OCD scrupulosity reassurance seeking compulsion ERP external reassurance", "self focused attention negative affect meta-analysis rumination depression anxiety", "spiritual bypassing Welwood Trungpa practice ego avoidance accountability"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This candidate changes the public line and practice wording, but does not add a new structural variable beyond the gate-holder model.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. Treat as a renamed sibling unless separability testing proves a different prediction.", "overlap": "Extremely close. It already states the three-gate structure: result-language permission, current bypassing versus self-scoring risk, and diagnostic custody.", "source": "Internal Lumenary record: Who Holds The Gate, supplied in recent originality audits."}, {"difference": "Ignatius does not frame the issue through achievement-contingent self-worth, self-scoring, no-check practice, or clinical rumination risk.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the core mechanism to known spiritual direction territory. The possible contribution is a modern safety-routing codebook, not a discovery.", "overlap": "Very close for holder assignment. The exercitant reports movements, the director adapts exercises, secrecy is broken by disclosure, and the director is limited from over-directing the final choice.", "source": "Ignatius of Loyola, Spiritual Exercises, Annotations 7, 15, 17, Rule 13, and scruple notes, https://www.orderofthecommonlife.org/spiritual-exercises-full-text"}, {"difference": "It concerns coping with God and agency, not post-practice diagnostics, result-language checks, or self-worth scoring.", "novelty_impact": "Reduces novelty for custody language, leaves room only for a narrower practice-safety extension.", "overlap": "Close for support locus and agency distribution: self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles already sort who is experienced as carrying problem-solving responsibility.", "source": "Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, 1988, https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/"}, {"difference": "VCE does not offer the exact holder-routing rule for after-use checks in high-achievement self-scorers.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the safety and support parts to established contemplative-adverse-effects territory.", "overlap": "Close for meditation-related challenges, appraisal, differential support structures, and the role of social context in interpreting practice effects.", "source": "Lindahl et al., The Varieties of Contemplative Experience, PLOS ONE 2017, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239"}, {"difference": "It is not about spiritual practice completion or assigning diagnostic custody.", "novelty_impact": "Supports the caution but does not make the model original.", "overlap": "Supports the risk claim that private self-focus can correlate with depression, generalized anxiety, and negative affect.", "source": "Mor and Winquist, Self-Focused Attention and Negative Affect, Psychological Bulletin 2002, DOI 10.1037/0033-2909.128.4.638, indexed at https://www.scirp.org/reference/referencespapers?referenceid=1457149"}, {"difference": "The clinical literature is not about contemplative after-use checks, but it directly constrains any external-holder instruction.", "novelty_impact": "Forces a clinical exclusion pathway and lowers practice-testability for scrupulosity and OCD-like cases.", "overlap": "Important anomaly and near-neighbor. External reassurance and repeated checking can maintain OCD, while ERP requires resisting rituals rather than transferring them to another holder.", "source": "Reassurance seeking in OCD and anxiety disorders, for example https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/behavioural-and-cognitive-psychotherapy/article/abs/patterns-of-reassurance-seeking-and-reassurancerelated-behaviours-in-ocd-and-anxiety-disorders/34C1F20E285643D8D7FAD482052F3EA7 and Stanford ERP summary https://med.stanford.edu/ocd/treatment/psychotherapy.html"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Cross-index or merge with Who Holds The Gate, Keep What Can Correct You, The Test Is How You Return, and correction-holder records.", "Build a pre-registered holder-routing codebook with fields for failure mode, current state, check holder, unsafe holder, no-check option, clinical exclusion, warning, repair, and evidence passage.", "Use split-source coding. Do not let one passage establish holder assignment and confirm the predicted repair.", "Add mandatory anomaly values for OCD reassurance seeking, scrupulosity, dependency, abusive authority, valid solitude, no-product practice, no-result rest, clinician-held care, and undecidable.", "Pilot only with screening for rumination, perfectionism, OCD and scrupulosity, trauma, depression, mania, dissociation, addiction withdrawal, authority harm, avoidance, and workload coercion.", "Interview practitioners for concrete mischeck and repair cases, not agreement with the slogan."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.57 to 0.28. The core is already present in the supplied Who Holds The Gate audit and has close external neighbors in Ignatian direction, spiritual direction, Pargament agency styles, contemplative adverse-effects support, ERP anti-reassurance rules, and self-focused-attention research. Human-condition fit is real but bounded: it serves stable high-achievement practitioners, founders, students, creators, caregivers, and self-directed meditators who convert insight into worth evidence. It is not for acute crisis, mania, psychosis, severe depression, dissociation, addiction withdrawal, active OCD or scrupulosity reassurance loops, abusive authority settings, or people whose main need is restored self-trust.", "originality_status": "renamed", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours-b9a584e898d8b829.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say this is ordinary spiritual direction, sponsorship, supervision, ERP triage, or contemplative-adverse-effects support, and that the Lumenary framing adds no new prediction or repair rule.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners can use the holder-routing question to predict failures they previously missed, especially self-held humility checks worsening self-worth scoring, or external checks becoming reassurance loops.", "questions": ["When a practitioner misuses a reflection or insight, how do you decide whether the next check should be self-held, guide-held, rule-held, conduct-held, or suspended?", "In actual failure cases, did outside guidance reduce harm, or did it become reassurance seeking, dependency, approval hunger, or spiritual abuse?", "Is the bypasser versus self-scorer distinction already native to your practice, or does it change routing decisions?", "For high-achievement practitioners, what observable sign tells you a humility check has become another score?", "Which cases should receive no practice, no check, or clinical referral?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Ignatian spiritual directors", "Buddhist meditation teachers familiar with adverse practice effects", "Jodo Shinshu ministers", "Soto Zen teachers", "ERP clinicians treating OCD and scrupulosity", "Therapists working with perfectionism and burnout", "AA or twelve-step sponsors", "Chaplains and peer-support facilitators"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Ignatius of Loyola, Spiritual Exercises, Annotations 7, 15, 17, Rule 13, and scruple notes 348-350, https://www.orderofthecommonlife.org/spiritual-exercises-full-text", "MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, Heart Sutra, Shinran On Jinen-Honi, and Dogen Bendowa or practice-realization sources, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html, https://www.lotsawahouse.org/words-of-the-buddha/heart-sutra, https://shinranworks.com/letters/lamp-for-the-latter-ages/on-jinen-honi-1258/, https://buddhismnow.com/2023/10/08/practice-within-realisation-dogen/"], "risk_of_overread": "High. External holding can be wise guidance, ordinary sponsorship, clinical triage, coercive authority, approval dependence, or OCD reassurance. No-check can mean healthy rest, avoidance, depression drift, or Dogen-style non-instrumentality. The bypasser, scorer, and oscillator labels are too crude without validated measures and concrete behavior markers.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Still needs full reading of Ignatian directorial manuals, contemporary spiritual direction ethics, AA sponsorship sources, ERP and scrupulosity treatment literature, VCE person-centered support, spiritual bypassing literature, and achievement-contingent self-worth studies before practice publication.", "structural_observation": "Ignatius is the closest primary-text neighbor. The director adapts exercises to the exercitant, receives reports of movements and thoughts, reveals dangerous secrecy to a confessor or spiritual person, and is also restrained from seizing the exercitant's final choice. The scruple notes already distinguish useful sensitivity from harmful over-fineness and counsel a mean. MN 22 adds that the raft must be grasped correctly before release, so release is not a generic self-check. The Heart Sutra denies attainment while retaining reliance on Prajnaparamita. Shinran and Dogen strain the whole model because no-calculation and practice-realization refuse a clean separable product that the practitioner can audit."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.92, "novelty": 0.28, "source_reliability": 0.8}, "run_ids": ["20260529-163436-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260529-163436-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "Not Every Check Should Be Yours", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Ignatian direction, Pargament agency styles, VCE support mapping, ERP anti-reassurance rules, and the prior Lumenary Who Holds The Gate record, this candidate says that a post-practice check must first ask who should hold the diagnostic today, because the same check can repair bypassing and worsen achievement-contingent self-scoring. That distinction is useful, but it is mostly a renamed and narrower safety-routing heuristic."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:57:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Dogen practice-realization, Tannisho Other Power, inherited religion with no discrete threshold, and valid daily repetition without a separable product.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers originality from the proposed 0.62 to about 0.30 and blocks publication as a discovery. It can remain as a safety-oriented coding heuristic.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "These cases refuse the assumed sequence of tool, result, and post-result authority. In Dogen, practice is not merely a ladder to be evaluated afterward. In Tannisho, efficacy is not owned by the practitioner or method. In inherited religion, the authority may be communal and continuous before any explicit insight. In faithful daily repetition, keeping the same form may be obedience or formation rather than self-surveillance."}, "audit_id": "95d52440abfccb6a", "claim_units": ["Stage completion is defined by a change in permitted guidance, not merely by a successful experience.", "Boundary operation and post-threshold custody should be coded together.", "Post-method authority may be retained, released, embodied, externally held, grace-held, vow-held, conduct-held, or refused.", "A method can become a private judge for achievement-driven practitioners.", "The practice fit is bounded: it targets achievement-contingent self-worth, burnout, and perfectionistic self-monitoring, not acute crisis, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, dissociation, or beginners needing simple consistency."], "confidence": 0.72, "created_at": "2026-05-30T07:57:54+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Psychotherapy, coaching, and product workflow", "prediction": "Programs that explicitly route post-success authority to conduct, reviewer, values, rest, or revised rules should show less self-surveillance, dependency, and ritualized checking than programs that only ask whether the method worked.", "structural_translation": "A technique that helps a person or team cross a threshold can become a new authority holder after it succeeds. The same structure appears when a therapy tool, productivity method, OKR system, code review rule, or metrics dashboard changes from aid to private judge.", "would_count_against_it": "Outcomes are fully explained by alliance, task clarity, dose, manager quality, or generic WIP limits, with no added effect from explicit post-method authority routing."}, "exact_claim": "A practice completes a stage not only by working, but by changing what may guide the next action. The audit variable is a two-axis pair: whether the method validates or undermines its own use, and where post-threshold authority is retained, laid down, embodied, handed to teacher or community, held by grace or vow, or refused as possession. The modern risk is that a once-helpful method becomes a private judge of worth, shame, and self-surveillance.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-073531-20260530-073531", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Blind coders can code boundary operation from entry or instruction texts and custody from separate passages, then predict held-out warning, verification, reentry, and repair patterns above tradition-label, teacher-style, and clinical-risk baselines.", "if_model_is_right": "Boundary operation and custody are separable variables with predictive value.", "test_surface": "Split-source codebook, inter-rater reliability, and held-out manual or interview prediction.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders cannot distinguish boundary operation from custody without using the same passages or tradition labels, or predictions vanish when institution, teacher, dose, and risk factors are controlled."}, {"expected_observation": "In a screened two-week pilot, high achievement-contingent self-worth participants using the Authority Check report less method-as-judgment language and more concrete next actions than generic journaling controls.", "if_model_is_right": "Achievement-contingent practitioners are more likely to convert methods into private judges.", "test_surface": "Randomized practice pilot using contingent self-worth, rumination, shame, burnout, and next-day conduct measures.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The check increases rumination, shame, checking, avoidance, or performs no better than a rest-and-plan prompt."}, {"expected_observation": "Teacher-held, vow-held, conduct-held, grace-held, and no-claimant cases generate different repairs after misinterpretation or premature completion.", "if_model_is_right": "Different custody holders predict different repair instructions.", "test_surface": "Concrete failure-case interviews with Zen, Pure Land, Advaita, Christian apophatic, and therapeutic practitioners.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Practitioner interviews show the same repairs across custody types, or repairs track institution and personality better than custody."}], "idea_id": "14451c6726c8ef58", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md", "literature_search_queries": ["\"Snakes and Ladders\" \"Therapy as Liberation\" Nagarjuna Wittgenstein Tractatus Sophia 2021", "\"Mystical Languages of Unsaying\" apophatic discourse turns back on itself", "\"Koan and Kensho\" \"Rinzai Zen Curriculum\" Hori post kensho", "\"Alagaddupama Sutta\" raft simile Dhamma for crossing not for retaining", "Tannisho Other Power self power nembutsu non-practice translation", "Pargament religious problem solving styles self-directing deferring collaborative", "spiritual materialism practice ego self-improvement Trungpa", "Cheetah House adverse meditation effects dissociation hyperarousal"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges-95d52440abfccb6a.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "The current idea recasts the older typology as boundary operation plus custody, and gives it a burnout-facing practice warning.", "novelty_impact": "Major reduction. This is mostly a revision of prior Lumenary work, not a new finding.", "overlap": "Already states that contemplative methods face a self-authority question at completion and proposes method-type as a predictor of verification and transmission.", "source": "Internal Lumenary audit, The Method's Reckoning: What a Practice Does With Its Own Authority at Completion, reviews/originality/audits.jsonl, 2026-05-26"}, {"difference": "The current idea adds sharper language about tools becoming judges and expands custody values, but the test structure is the same family.", "novelty_impact": "Major reduction. Treat as renamed or merged unless separability testing proves added predictive value.", "overlap": "Already codes whether a result stands or is undermined and whether a method is kept, set down, or carried as conduct, with achievement-contingent self-worth as the human problem.", "source": "Internal Lumenary audit, The Test Is How You Return, reviews/originality/audits.jsonl, 2026-05-28"}, {"difference": "Smith is a bilateral comparative philosophy argument, not a cross-tradition custody codebook or burnout practice protocol.", "novelty_impact": "Strong reduction for the self-undermining method unit.", "overlap": "Very close for therapeutic methods that dissolve philosophical attachment and for the ladder or snake pattern of using a method that undercuts possessive thesis-making.", "source": "Joshua William Smith, Snakes and Ladders: Therapy as Liberation in Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein's Tractatus, Sophia 2021, https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11841-020-00804-6"}, {"difference": "Sells analyzes apophatic language, not post-practice custody or authority routing across methods.", "novelty_impact": "Strong reduction for the apophatic and self-canceling language side.", "overlap": "Close for discourse that works by unsaying and turning back on its own names and propositions.", "source": "Michael A. Sells, Mystical Languages of Unsaying, University of Chicago Press, https://press.uchicago.edu/ucp/books/book/chicago/M/bo3635525.html"}, {"difference": "It is about coping and agency with God, not post-threshold method authority or contemplative verification.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction for custody and support-locus language.", "overlap": "Already sorts religious agency by who carries problem-solving responsibility: self, God, or collaboration.", "source": "Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, 1988, indexed in Religious Coping, https://link.springer.com/rwe/10.1007/978-3-030-24348-7_578"}, {"difference": "It does not provide the two-axis authority model.", "novelty_impact": "Improves safety grounding but does not increase originality.", "overlap": "Supports the safety concern that practice can worsen anxiety, intrusive thoughts, dissociation, motivation, meaning, agency, and identity.", "source": "Cheetah House FAQ on meditation-related difficulties, https://www.cheetahhouse.org/faq"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Merge into the method-authority and after-use cluster unless a separability test proves independent predictive gain.", "Build one bounded codebook with fields for boundary operation, custody holder, result stance, method fate, warning, repair, verification, evidence passage, analyst-frame refusal, and clinical exclusion.", "Use split-source blind coding and do not let one passage establish the predictor and confirm the predicted warning or repair.", "Run practitioner interviews for concrete failed-student and repair cases, not agreement with the slogan.", "Pilot The Authority Check only with safety screens for rumination, perfectionism, OCD or scrupulosity, trauma activation, depression, mania, dissociation, addiction withdrawal, authority harm, avoidance, and workload coercion."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.62 to 0.30. The live contribution is a tighter public phrase and a safety-oriented practice prompt for achievement-contingent self-worth. It should be merged or cross-indexed with The Method's Reckoning, The Test Is How You Return, Boundary And Custody At The Threshold, Authority Must Be Returned, Not Every Check Should Be Yours, and prior correction-holder records. Publishability is bounded: potentially useful for stable overproducers and perfectionistic practitioners, not for acute distress, addiction withdrawal, dissociation, severe depression, scrupulosity, abusive authority, underproduction, or cases needing ordinary care.", "originality_status": "renamed", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges-95d52440abfccb6a.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say this is standard raft, upaya, practice-realization, Other Power, spiritual direction, spiritual materialism warning, or ordinary supervision, with no new prediction about repair.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners can use the boundary-custody interaction to predict misuses and repairs they would not have predicted from tradition identity, institution, teacher style, or generic safety screening.", "questions": ["Is boundary operation plus post-threshold custody a real distinction in your training, or does it rename ordinary lineage pedagogy?", "Can you give a concrete case where a student imported the wrong post-method authority and needed a specific repair?", "Does asking what still deserves obedience reduce achievement-contingent self-worth, or does it add another layer of self-monitoring?", "Which cases should not receive this practice at all: crisis, depression, dissociation, addiction withdrawal, scrupulosity, abusive authority, or beginners needing simple repetition?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Rinzai Zen teachers familiar with post-kensho curriculum", "Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization", "Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with Tannisho and Other Power", "Madhyamaka scholars and practitioners", "Advaita inquiry teachers", "Christian apophatic spiritual directors", "Meditation safety clinicians familiar with VCE and Cheetah House cases", "Burnout clinicians working with perfectionism and contingent self-worth"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta raft simile, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html; Heart Sutra no attainment with reliance on prajnaparamita, https://www.fgsitc.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Heart-Sutra-2016.pdf", "Dogen Genjokoan practice-realization, https://brightwayzen.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/For-BWZ-Chant-Book-Genjokoan.pdf; Tannisho sections 6 and 8, Taitetsu Unno translation, https://nembutsu.cc/buddhism/the-tannisho/tannisho-sections-i-to-x/"], "risk_of_overread": "High. Tool, stage, custody, and judge are modern analytic terms. They can distort traditions where practice is expression rather than instrument, where authority never belonged to the practitioner, or where communal, ritual, vow, or grace structures are primary.", "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit found strong near-neighbors in Smith on Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein, Sells on apophatic unsaying, Pargament agency and coping styles, spiritual materialism, spiritual bypassing, VCE and Cheetah House adverse meditation support, and multiple prior Lumenary audits. Full source reliability still requires reading upaya scholarship, Zen post-kensho training, Shinran scholarship, spiritual direction ethics, and practitioner manuals in original languages where possible.", "structural_observation": "MN 22 is a direct near-neighbor for proper use followed by release, but it also requires right grasp before release. The Heart Sutra denies attainment while retaining reliance and mantra, so undermining a result does not imply abandoning the method. Dogen strains the whole stage-completion frame because practice and realization are not cleanly separable. Tannisho strains practitioner-owned authority because nembutsu is presented as free of self-power and not a good act or practice from the practitioner's side. Together, the primary texts support a scoped coding heuristic, not a discovery-level doctrine."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.92, "novelty": 0.3, "source_reliability": 0.82}, "run_ids": ["20260530-073531-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-073531-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "When Tools Become Judges", "unlike_statement": "Unlike MN 22, Smith, Sells, Pargament, spiritual-materialism warnings, VCE safety work, and prior Lumenary return or custody audits, this idea says that the specific interaction between boundary operation and post-threshold custody should predict when a helpful method becomes guidance, conduct, external accountability, rest, or a private judge of worth. That is a useful synthesis, but the structure is mostly inherited from recent internal records."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:60:{"agent": "claude", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "A reflective person in grief, moral repair, trauma integration, or non-instrumental practice who is harmed by stopping on schedule because the timer becomes avoidance, emotional bypassing, or a new compulsive ritual.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence in broad teaching status but preserves the model as a narrow practice-fit rule for screened over-reflectors.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "The model depends on the problem being over-reflection in search of certainty. In grief, confession, repair, trauma integration, or practice-realization, the needed process may be spacious, relational, recurring, or embodied rather than closed for the day by a timer. A timer may also become the reassurance ritual that ERP would target."}, "audit_id": "4b185ee8c360296e", "claim_units": ["Some reflective practices lack a reliable natural terminus.", "For compulsive over-reflectors, felt resolution can be an unreliable and self-perpetuating completion criterion.", "A precommitted external limit, time or one concrete act, should close reflection for the day.", "Continuing past the chosen limit is often avoidance, reassurance seeking, or perfectionism disguised as diligence.", "The rule is contraindicated for under-reflection, acute grief, trauma processing, moral repair, clinical obsessive doubt without support, and non-instrumental practice-realization traditions."], "confidence": 0.86, "created_at": "2026-05-30T08:23:51+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Software engineering and design review", "prediction": "On low-risk tasks, timeboxed review with a written stop rule will reduce churn, duplicate comments, and reopened decisions without reducing defect detection compared with review-until-satisfied.", "structural_translation": "A review or refactor can lack a natural internal feeling of done. For perfectionistic teams or individuals, completion should be defined by a precommitted timebox, acceptance criterion, or one bounded action, not by the feeling that the design is finally clean.", "would_count_against_it": "Defects increase, useful design concerns are suppressed, or ordinary issue scoping and Definition of Done explain all observed benefits."}, "exact_claim": "Some reflective work has no natural internal end, especially for people prone to compulsive self-examination, perfectionism, or achievement-contingent self-worth. For those cases, completion should be defined before starting by an external limit, such as a fixed time or one bounded action, and the question should close for the day even if it does not feel resolved. A method has surrendered its hold when the practitioner can stop on schedule, not when reflection finally feels complete.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-080325-20260530-080325", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "A fixed-time or one-act close reduces same-day reopening, rumination, self-worth distress, and redundant journaling compared with reflect-until-resolved instructions.", "if_model_is_right": "For compulsive over-reflectors, external limits outperform felt-resolution stopping.", "test_surface": "Randomized two-week pilot with screened over-reflectors, daily logs, rumination scales, distress ratings, and action-completion measures.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The external limit performs no better, increases anxiety, becomes a ritual, or reduces responsible action."}, {"expected_observation": "High-rumination and high-perfectionism participants benefit more than under-reflectors, grievers, and avoidant participants.", "if_model_is_right": "The benefit is moderated by failure mode.", "test_surface": "Moderator analysis comparing over-reflection, avoidance, grief, and perfectionism profiles.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The timer helps equally across groups, or mainly helps by ordinary scheduling rather than by reducing compulsive resolution seeking."}, {"expected_observation": "People who endlessly edit adequate documents, plans, or designs complete more work with bounded stopping rules, without lower blind quality ratings.", "if_model_is_right": "The same structure travels to non-introspective over-refinement.", "test_surface": "Writing, planning, or design experiment with blind quality ratings and revision-count metrics.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Quality drops sharply, avoidance rises, or ordinary deadlines explain all benefits."}, {"expected_observation": "Teachers in non-instrumental traditions report that a timed close may be useful for session discipline but does not mark existential completion or method surrender.", "if_model_is_right": "Practice-realization and other non-instrumental contexts are true scope exceptions.", "test_surface": "Practitioner interviews with Soto Zen, Dzogchen, liturgical, and devotional teachers.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Such practitioners endorse the timer as a valid completion criterion for the practice's core aim."}], "idea_id": "e3acb58fb0863e87", "idea_path": "observations/claude/2026-05-30-stop-when-time-is-up-not-when-it-feels-done.md", "literature_search_queries": ["mood-as-input stop rules perseverative checking feel like continuing as many as can", "MacDonald Davey stop rules checking mood as input compulsive checking", "I wash until it feels right stopping criteria obsessive compulsive washing", "exposure response prevention reassurance seeking compulsive checking uncertainty", "rumination-focused cognitive behavioral therapy Watkins rumination intervention", "metacognitive therapy rumination worry detached mindfulness", "implementation intentions Gollwitzer if then planning stop rule goal pursuit", "timeboxing productivity fixed time limit stop rule perfectionism"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stop-when-time-is-up-not-when-it-feels-done-4b185ee8c360296e.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "The candidate applies the stop-rule insight to spiritual self-review and method-release instructions, and recommends a clock or bounded act for non-clinical over-reflectors.", "novelty_impact": "Major reduction. The core mechanism is known, so the idea is mostly a renamed application with a spiritual frame.", "overlap": "Extremely close. This literature already treats perseveration as governed by stop rules and mood, and contrasts continuing until one feels satisfied with rule-based stopping conditions.", "source": "Mood-as-input and stop-rule literature on worry, rumination, and checking, including MacDonald and Davey on stop rules and perseverative checking, and Watkins and Mason on mood-as-input and rumination."}, {"difference": "The source studies compulsive washing, while the candidate addresses ordinary reflective practice and spiritual self-audit.", "novelty_impact": "Major reduction for the felt-completion claim.", "overlap": "Very close on the exact danger of using a felt rightness signal as the criterion for stopping.", "source": "Wahl et al., I wash until it feels right: the phenomenology of stopping criteria in obsessive-compulsive washing, Journal of Anxiety Disorders 2008, https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18221894/."}, {"difference": "The candidate generalizes the logic to ordinary reflection and spiritual self-review, with a time or bounded-action close rather than formal exposure protocol.", "novelty_impact": "Major reduction and a strong safety constraint.", "overlap": "Very close on refusing the internal demand for certainty, stopping reassurance or checking behaviors, and tolerating unresolved doubt.", "source": "ERP and CBT literature on OCD, compulsive checking, reassurance seeking, and intolerance of uncertainty, including International OCD Foundation materials on ERP, https://iocdf.org/about-ocd/treatment/erp/."}, {"difference": "The candidate uses contemplative self-canceling method as the frame and proposes a simple external close for non-clinical use.", "novelty_impact": "Strong reduction for the psychological mechanism and practice design.", "overlap": "Close on the idea that perseverative self-focused analysis maintains distress, and that changing the process of thinking matters more than finding the perfect answer.", "source": "Rumination-focused CBT and metacognitive therapy for rumination and worry, for example Watkins' rumination-focused CBT work and Wells' metacognitive therapy literature."}, {"difference": "The candidate applies precommitment to spiritual or reflective completion rather than general goal pursuit.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate to strong reduction for the behavioral mechanism.", "overlap": "Close on precommitted action rules that replace deliberation in moments where ongoing evaluation would derail behavior.", "source": "Gollwitzer implementation intentions and precommitment research, for example implementation-intention reviews in goal pursuit literature."}, {"difference": "Most productivity methods do not address contemplative method-release, compulsive certainty, or self-worth distress.", "novelty_impact": "Strong reduction for the practical stopping rule.", "overlap": "Close on defining completion externally by time, scope, or agreed done criteria rather than by an unstable sense of perfect completion.", "source": "Productivity methods: timeboxing, Pomodoro, WIP limits, and Definition of Done, with timeboxing commonly defined as assigning a fixed period to an activity."}, {"difference": "This candidate is cleaner at the individual practice level: stop by clock or bounded act, not by felt completion.", "novelty_impact": "Major internal reduction. Treat as a focused practice variant, not a discovery.", "overlap": "Close internal prior art. These already argue for stopping, gating, and blocking repeated refinement when it adds no new source, anomaly, prediction, or test.", "source": "Prior Lumenary records: More Is Not The Same As Progress, Restating Is Not Realizing, The Silence Has A Stopping Rule, Not Every Check Should Be Yours, and The Answer You Keep Finding Is Already Settled."}, {"difference": "The candidate identifies a missing terminus and imports external stopping rules for over-reflectors.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction. The old source names release, not the behavioral anti-compulsion protocol.", "overlap": "Close on the self-canceling or disposable method structure.", "source": "Wittgenstein Tractatus 6.54 and Buddhist raft-simile traditions."}, {"difference": "The candidate explicitly scopes out practice-realization but still risks importing instrumental timeboxing into non-instrumental practice.", "novelty_impact": "Limits generality and lowers publishability as doctrine.", "overlap": "Not a support source, but a structural anomaly: practice may not be an instrument that closes when a clock expires or an action is completed.", "source": "Dogen practice-realization, non-gaining zazen, and other non-instrumental practice traditions."}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Cross-index with More Is Not The Same As Progress, Restating Is Not Realizing, The Silence Has A Stopping Rule, Not Every Check Should Be Yours, and The Answer You Keep Finding Is Already Settled.", "Rewrite as a bounded practice-fit protocol for over-reflection, not as a general teaching about method surrender.", "Add a triage gate before the practice: over-reflection versus avoidance, grief, moral repair, trauma, OCD or scrupulosity, and non-instrumental practice.", "Compare directly against mood-as-input stop-rule training, ERP response prevention, rumination-focused CBT, metacognitive therapy, timeboxing, WIP limits, implementation intentions, and ordinary journaling limits.", "Pilot only with screened non-clinical over-reflectors. Track reopening frequency, anxiety, ritualization, avoidance, shame, action completion, and whether the closing act becomes compulsive."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.55 to 0.24. The narrow contribution is a spiritual framing of established stop-rule, ERP, rumination, and timeboxing principles. The strongest close neighbor is mood-as-input stop-rule research, which already attacks felt completion as a dangerous stopping criterion. Human-condition fit is strong for perfectionists, chronic self-improvers, over-journalers, and achievement-contingent over-reflectors. It is not for acute grief, trauma processing, moral repair, clinical OCD or scrupulosity without trained care, under-reflection, coercive workload, or non-instrumental practice where timed stopping would distort the aim.", "originality_status": "renamed", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stop-when-time-is-up-not-when-it-feels-done-4b185ee8c360296e.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Clinicians and teachers say this is standard stop-rule work, response prevention, postponement, timeboxing, or journaling hygiene, and that the spiritual-method framing adds no new screening or prediction.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners find that the model reliably identifies a neglected failure mode: people understand release intellectually but keep applying release-instructions compulsively, and a bounded external close helps where insight-based advice fails.", "questions": ["Is this more than mood-as-input stop-rule training, ERP response prevention, uncertainty tolerance, rumination-focused CBT, or ordinary timeboxing?", "How would you distinguish an over-reflector helped by a timer from an avoidant person using the timer to evade honesty?", "When does stopping on time become a new compulsion or reassurance ritual?", "In your practice context, does a timed close mark completion, or only a practical boundary around a session?", "What concrete failure cases would make you forbid this practice or require clinician involvement?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["ERP clinicians working with OCD, scrupulosity, reassurance seeking, and checking", "CBT or metacognitive therapists treating rumination and worry", "Spiritual directors familiar with scrupulosity and discernment", "Meditation teachers familiar with non-striving and adverse practice loops", "Soto Zen or other practice-realization teachers", "Writing teachers and editors working with perfectionistic over-revision", "Productivity coaches using timeboxing or WIP limits", "Grief counselors and moral-injury practitioners"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Wittgenstein, Tractatus Logico-Philosophicus 6.54, ladder image, https://www.gutenberg.org/files/5740/5740-h/5740-h.htm; MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta raft simile, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html", "Heart Sutra, https://www.fgsitc.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Heart-Sutra-2016.pdf; Dogen practice-realization sources such as Bendowa or Genjokoan."], "risk_of_overread": "High in clinical, grief, trauma, and moral-repair contexts. A timer can become reassurance, ritual, avoidance, or self-punishment. The model can mistake legitimate repeated practice, mourning, confession, discernment, and non-instrumental sitting for compulsive reopening. It should be framed as a triage rule for a specific failure mode, not as a general spiritual law.", "secondary_literature_gap": "The strongest near-neighbors are not only spiritual texts but clinical and cognitive stop-rule literatures. The audit needs full reading in mood-as-input studies, ERP manuals, intolerance-of-uncertainty protocols, rumination-focused CBT, metacognitive therapy, implementation intentions, and timeboxing research. It also needs practitioner checks from Zen and other non-instrumental practice contexts.", "structural_observation": "Tractatus 6.54 and MN 22 both picture a method that should not be retained as an object after it has served its function. Neither source gives a modern behavioral stopping rule for a person whose compulsion is to keep checking whether they have really let go. The Heart Sutra complicates discard language because it negates attainment while preserving reliance. Dogen complicates it more sharply because practice may not be an instrument whose completion is externally marked. The candidate's distinct structural claim is not self-canceling method, which is old, but the external terminus for people whose inner completion signal is unreliable."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.94, "novelty": 0.24, "source_reliability": 0.84}, "run_ids": ["20260530-080325-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-080325-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "Stop When Time Is Up, Not When It Feels Done", "unlike_statement": "Unlike mood-as-input stop-rule research, obsessive-compulsive stopping-criteria studies, ERP, rumination therapies, timeboxing, implementation intentions, WIP limits, and prior Lumenary stopping-rule records, this idea says that self-canceling spiritual instructions fail for over-reflectors unless completion is moved outside felt resolution into a precommitted clock or bounded act. That combination is usable, but the mechanism is mostly already known."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:64:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Direct recognition, clear-light sleep, or stable solitary realization cases where mature practitioners report immediate knowing with ethical integration and no explicit return-discipline gate, plus the opposite anomaly of abusive or compulsive correction.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers novelty and practice confidence. The model survives as a narrow safety-routing heuristic for isolated overinterpreters and achievement-contingent practitioners, not as a general doctrine.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If some mature sources and practitioners treat silence or recognition as self-evident in a bounded way, the claim that no silence proves itself is too broad. If correction commonly produces shame, dependence, or coercion, return discipline cannot be presented as a universal first layer."}, "audit_id": "b164e521a35f3e68", "claim_units": ["Silence, blankness, or quiet is not self-authenticating evidence of Self, no-self, attainment, worth, or failure.", "Brihadaranyaka and early Buddhist texts disagree about what remains after negation, but both require more than private blankness alone.", "Return discipline, instruction, correction, conduct, and ordinary duty, should be the first audit layer.", "The target cohort is stable self-directed practitioners and high-striving people who convert inner states into worth verdicts.", "The proposed practice delays self, no-self, attainment, failure, and worth claims for twenty-four hours."], "confidence": 0.88, "created_at": "2026-05-30T09:27:02+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Scientific, clinical, and organizational decision making after private insight", "prediction": "Teams or clinicians that require a named return check before acting on a private insight will show fewer overclaimed conclusions, fewer avoidant delays, and fewer identity-protective interpretations than groups relying on intuitive certainty alone.", "structural_translation": "A compelling private perception, hunch, model, or diagnosis is not enough until it returns through review, consequence, replication, patient or user outcome, or ordinary duty.", "would_count_against_it": "Ordinary peer review, supervision, leadership quality, or case complexity explains all improvement, and pre-naming the return check adds no independent value."}, "exact_claim": "A silence or blank state cannot authorize its own meaning; the trustworthy evidence is in the disciplined return: prior instruction, correction after the event, visible conduct, and care for remaining duties and relationships.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-091655-20260530-091655", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Blind coders can identify instruction-before, correction-after, conduct-test, relationship-duty, or no-return-discipline from one source layer and predict held-out warnings or repairs better than tradition label alone.", "if_model_is_right": "Return discipline is an independently codable variable, not just a restatement of tradition identity.", "test_surface": "Split-source coding across Upanishadic, Theravada, Zen, Tibetan, Christian, Sufi, and modern meditation-safety sources.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders need outcome passages to identify return discipline, or tradition label and teacher style predict warnings equally well."}, {"expected_observation": "Stable participants using Return Without Verdict show fewer worth verdicts, shame swings, certainty inflation, and post-state rumination than ordinary journaling or rest-and-plan controls.", "if_model_is_right": "The practice helps achievement-contingent overinterpreters.", "test_surface": "Two-week pilot with screened self-directed practitioners, students, caregivers, and professionals high in perfectionism or achievement-contingent self-worth.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The practice increases rumination, derealization, shame, dependency, avoidance, or performs no better than controls."}, {"expected_observation": "Advaita, Dzogchen, Zen, and apophatic sources that speak strongly about immediate recognition still retain some constraint through teacher, text, lineage, vow, conduct, compassion, or ordinary functioning.", "if_model_is_right": "Even direct-recognition traditions preserve return constraints.", "test_surface": "Close reading plus practitioner interviews asking for concrete misrecognition, warning, and repair cases.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Mature sources explicitly authorize private silence as sufficient warrant with no correction, conduct, lineage, or aftercare, and practitioners show stable integration without those constraints."}, {"expected_observation": "Meditation-related challenge cases improve when interpretation is paired with fitting teacher, community, clinical, or conduct support, rather than relying on spiritual or clinical labeling alone.", "if_model_is_right": "Support routing matters more than the first label applied to a difficult blank state.", "test_surface": "Retrospective VCE-style case coding and a prospective support-routing pilot.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Clinical-risk variables explain outcomes completely, or return-discipline naming adds no value beyond standard triage."}], "idea_id": "876531ae2572b431", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself.md", "literature_search_queries": ["William James Varieties religious experience fruits not roots conduct evidence", "Ignatius Spiritual Exercises Rule 8 consolation opinions examined before credit", "William Alston Perceiving God mystical doxastic practice overriders defeaters", "Proudfoot religious experience concepts beliefs linguistic practices attribution", "Robert Sharf experience Buddhist modernism critique private experience", "Talal Asad discursive tradition correct practice authority orthodoxy", "Lindahl Britton Varieties Contemplative Experience appraisal support meditation challenges", "achievement contingent self worth perfectionism burnout rumination spiritual practice"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "The current idea shifts from correction-holder language to return-discipline language and adds achievement-contingent self-worth as a clearer cohort.", "novelty_impact": "Decisive reduction. Treat as renamed internal work.", "overlap": "Near exact internal prior art. It already says silence after self-questioning becomes usable only when the later report can be corrected by teacher, text, vow, community, clinician, or conduct.", "source": "Prior Lumenary audit, Silence Needs Correction, reviews/originality/2026-05-30-silence-needs-correction-06ae06e9a81492e8.json"}, {"difference": "No Silence Proves Itself compresses the cluster into a post-gap slogan and practice prompt.", "novelty_impact": "Major internal reduction.", "overlap": "Very close. These records already argue that insights and practices must be tested by return, correction, conduct, and non-ownership.", "source": "Prior Lumenary records: Keep What Can Correct You, The Test Is How You Return, A Practice Cannot Name Itself, and Every Insight Has An Appeal Court"}, {"difference": "The candidate generalizes the rule beyond Christian consolation to blankness and achievement-contingent self-worth.", "novelty_impact": "Major reduction.", "overlap": "Very close. Ignatius already separates the intense interior event from later judgments, resolutions, and actions that need examination.", "source": "Ignatius of Loyola, Spiritual Exercises, Rules for Discernment, especially Rule 8, https://sacred-texts.com/chr/seil/seil79.htm"}, {"difference": "James does not formulate a post-gap return-without-verdict practice for modern high-striving practitioners.", "novelty_impact": "Strong reduction.", "overlap": "Close. James and Edwards make practical fruits and conduct the test of religious experience, not origin, intensity, or private certainty.", "source": "William James, The Varieties of Religious Experience, https://www.gutenberg.org/files/621/621-h/621-h.html"}, {"difference": "The candidate is safety-oriented and cross-traditional rather than an epistemic defense of Christian mystical perception.", "novelty_impact": "Strong reduction.", "overlap": "Close on religious experience as belief-forming only within a practice and subject to overriders or defeaters.", "source": "William Alston, mystical doxastic practice discussions, for example Richard Gale summary at https://stafforini.com/works/gale-1994-why-alston-mystical/"}, {"difference": "The candidate turns safety and appraisal concerns into a simple post-blank identity-verdict delay.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate to strong reduction, with useful safety support.", "overlap": "Close on appraisal, interpretation, social context, teacher and clinician support, and differential response to meditation-related challenges.", "source": "Lindahl et al., Varieties of Contemplative Experience, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239, and Progress or Pathology, https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/psychology/articles/10.3389/fpsyg.2020.01905/full"}, {"difference": "The candidate converts deconstructive inspection into a broad return-discipline and self-worth practice.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction for the Buddhist source unit.", "overlap": "Close primary near-neighbor for inspecting consciousness rather than treating it as substance or proof.", "source": "SN 22.95, Foam, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_95.html"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Merge or cross-index with Silence Needs Correction, Keep What Can Correct You, The Test Is How You Return, and A Practice Cannot Name Itself.", "Run a blind distinct-content test against the recent correction-holder and return-test records before generating another post-gap gate.", "Build one return-discipline codebook with fields for instruction-before, correction-after, conduct-test, duty-return, support holder, unsafe holder, no-check option, evidence passage, warning, repair, and clinical exclusion.", "Use split-source coding. Do not let the same passage establish return discipline and confirm the predicted warning or repair.", "Pilot Return Without Verdict only with screened stable overinterpreters and stop for rumination, shame, derealization, dependency, avoidance, dissociation, mania, depression, addiction withdrawal, trauma activation, or medical concern."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.42 to 0.18. The teaching is clear and potentially useful, but it is a renamed synthesis of prior Lumenary correction and return records plus close external near-neighbors in Ignatian discernment, James, Alston, Buddhist not-self inspection, and VCE safety literature. Human-condition fit is strong but narrow: stable self-directed practitioners with achievement-contingent self-worth, burnout, loneliness, or isolated overinterpretation after quiet states. It is not for trauma amnesia, dissociation, panic disorder, psychosis, mania, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, unexplained loss of consciousness, medical or legal reconstruction, abusive authority contexts, or people already under competent guidance.", "originality_status": "renamed", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself-b164e521a35f3e68.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say the rule is standard spiritual direction, fruits testing, lineage verification, Buddhist non-appropriation, or VCE-style support routing, and that the new wording adds no prediction.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners can use return-discipline language to identify overinterpretation earlier, route high-striving practitioners away from worth verdicts, and specify when teacher, text, clinician, conduct, rest, or no-practice is the right holder.", "questions": ["Is this more than standard discernment, fruits testing, teacher verification, not-self strategy, or meditation-safety triage?", "After a powerful blank or quiet, what do you tell a student to trust, delay, check, or stop doing?", "Can you name a case where a blank became pride, shame, despair, avoidance, or self-worth proof?", "Can you name a case where correction itself caused dependency, coercion, rumination, or harm?", "Would Return Without Verdict change practice instructions, or does it only rephrase what competent teachers already do?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Ignatian spiritual directors and directors familiar with scrupulosity", "Buddhist meditation teachers in Theravada, Zen, and Tibetan settings", "Advaita and Dzogchen teachers who teach direct recognition", "Clinicians familiar with meditation-related challenges and dissociation", "Burnout clinicians or coaches working with perfectionism", "Pastoral counselors, chaplains, and spiritual-abuse advocates"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 2.4, 2.5, 3.7.23, and 4.3.23, https://vivekavani.com/bru/ and https://vivekavani.com/bru4c3v23/", "SN 22.59, SN 22.95, MN 44, and Ignatius, Spiritual Exercises Rule 8, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_95.html, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN44.html, https://sacred-texts.com/chr/seil/seil79.htm"], "risk_of_overread": "High. The claim can flatten direct-recognition traditions, overvalue external correction, or convert solitude into suspicion. Correction can be abusive, shaming, dependency-producing, clinically mismatched, or compulsive. The achievement-contingent self-worth practice may help overinterpreters, but can harm people with OCD, scrupulosity, dissociation, mania, severe depression, trauma activation, addiction withdrawal, or genuine medical blackout.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Read William James and Edwards on fruits and practice, Ignatian discernment and spiritual direction ethics, Alston on mystical doxastic practice and overriders, Proudfoot, Sharf, Katz, Taves, Asad, Lindbeck, VCE meditation-challenge work, Cheetah House materials, rumination and scrupulosity literature, and burnout and perfectionism literature before any public practice.", "structural_observation": "Brihadaranyaka does not let the blank speak by itself. It frames the witness through teaching, hearing, reflection, meditation, and metaphysical instruction. SN 22.59 and SN 22.95 refuse ownership of consciousness and train inspection of aggregates rather than trust in blankness. MN 44 treats cessation through prior development, ordered emergence, and post-emergence orientation. Ignatius Rule 8 is an exact Christian near-neighbor: even high consolation requires later opinions and resolutions to be examined before full credit or action. The candidate's return-discipline rule is structurally old."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.92, "novelty": 0.18, "source_reliability": 0.86}, "run_ids": ["20260530-091655-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "No Silence Proves Itself", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Silence Needs Correction, Ignatian discernment, Jamesian fruits, Alstonian overriders, VCE support routing, and prior Lumenary return-test records, this idea says a blank should be judged first by the ecology of return, especially for people who turn inner quiet into a worth verdict. The cohort narrowing is useful, but the core claim is mostly renamed prior art."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:65:{"agent": "claude", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Active scrupulosity or OCD where the trusted helper becomes a reassurance object, plus spiritual-abuse contexts where external custody becomes control.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence substantially. The model needs hard exclusions and a distinction between bounded support, reassurance accommodation, clinical care, ordinary friendship, and unsafe authority.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "The model assumes relational custody relieves the wounded self. In OCD, another person can become part of the compulsion. In abusive or high-control settings, another person can become an unsafe authority. In valid solitude, self-trust may be safer than handing interpretation away."}, "audit_id": "f39d5f3ff774b3f9", "claim_units": ["Unusual quiet, blank, or absorbed states can become harmful when appropriated as worth verdicts.", "A solo correction-audit can reproduce the wound of solo adjudication.", "The proposed safe default is a twenty-four-hour identity-verdict moratorium plus one ordinary act of care.", "Classification of the state, practice type, evidence, or scope should be relationally held by a trusted other.", "The model keeps return discipline and scope gating, but moves adjudication custody outside the wounded self."], "confidence": 0.86, "created_at": "2026-05-30T09:43:31+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Clinical decision support, education, software review, and organizational postmortems after ambiguous signals", "prediction": "High-perfectionism students, clinicians, researchers, or engineers given a no-identity-verdict rule plus one concrete prosocial or repair action and bounded review will show less rumination, fewer defensive interpretations, and faster useful action than those asked to self-audit the meaning of the ambiguous event.", "structural_translation": "When a person is vulnerable to self-worth verdicts, making them classify the meaning of an ambiguous signal can amplify the wound. A bounded second-person or rule-held review plus one concrete repair action should outperform solo meta-analysis.", "would_count_against_it": "Ordinary supervision, rest, generic reflection, or standard review explains all improvement, or the second-person route increases dependency, reassurance seeking, delay, or approval hunger."}, "exact_claim": "After an unusual quiet, blank, or absorbed state, the dangerous act for achievement-contingent, scrupulous, lonely, or over-adjudicating practitioners is not only claiming the state as a verdict, but also self-administering the audit that is supposed to prevent the verdict. For this cohort, the default should be no self or worth claim for twenty-four hours plus one ordinary act of care. Any classification of the state, practice type, evidence, or scope gate should be held by a trusted second person, teacher, peer, or clinician, not by the wounded self alone.", "execution_id": "dialogue-71803861adb45a32", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Participants assigned to solo correction-checks report more worry about whether they did the check correctly than those assigned to no-verdict plus one ordinary act of care.", "if_model_is_right": "For high achievement-contingent but non-clinical overinterpreters, solo audit increases meta-checking compared with a non-adjudicating default.", "test_surface": "Four-arm pilot after quiet-state practice: solo return check, no-verdict plus ordinary care, ordinary rest or conversation, and helper-held routing.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Solo audit produces equal or lower rumination, shame, and meta-checking than the no-verdict or helper-held arms."}, {"expected_observation": "A helper protocol that refuses repeated certainty-seeking and returns the person to ordinary conduct reduces rumination more than unstructured reassurance.", "if_model_is_right": "Relational custody helps only when it is bounded and non-reassuring.", "test_surface": "Stratified pilot measuring reassurance seeking, intolerance of uncertainty, dependency, shame, and completed ordinary action.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Repeated helper reassurance performs as well as bounded custody, or bounded custody increases dependency and anxiety."}, {"expected_observation": "Participants asked to classify whether a practice was instrumental, autotelic, devotional, or non-result show more state-classification loops than those given a universal no-verdict default.", "if_model_is_right": "The scope-gate decision itself becomes compulsive in the target cohort.", "test_surface": "Experimental comparison of classification-first instructions against universal no-verdict instructions.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Classification improves clarity without increasing rumination, or performs better than the no-verdict default."}, {"expected_observation": "The protocol helps lonely or achievement-contingent over-reflectors most, has little effect for ordinary practitioners, and requires exclusion or clinical routing for OCD, scrupulosity, mania, dissociation, severe depression, trauma activation, addiction withdrawal, or unsafe authority contexts.", "if_model_is_right": "Human-condition benefit is narrow and state-dependent.", "test_surface": "Two-week screened pilot using measures of contingencies of self-worth, loneliness, intolerance of uncertainty, rumination, scrupulosity, dependency, and adverse meditation effects.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Effects are not moderated by self-worth contingency, loneliness, or scrupulosity risk, or adverse effects cluster in the intended cohort."}], "idea_id": "0d41fb6f36977938", "idea_path": "observations/claude/2026-05-30-the-audit-you-cannot-hold-alone.md", "literature_search_queries": ["scrupulosity OCD reassurance seeking spiritual direction Ciarrocchi The Doubting Disease", "OCD intolerance of uncertainty checking reassurance seeking exposure response prevention self checking", "Ignatius Spiritual Exercises Rule 8 consolation desolation spiritual director Annotations", "Lindahl Britton Varieties of Contemplative Experience appraisal social support meditation challenges", "achievement contingent self-worth perfectionism rumination Curran Hill perfectionism increasing"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-audit-you-cannot-hold-alone-f39d5f3ff774b3f9.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "The candidate compresses the cluster into one relational default and names the self-issued meta-decision itself as the compulsion.", "novelty_impact": "Decisive downgrade. Treat as renamed consolidation unless a pilot shows the universal no-verdict default predicts better outcomes than the prior holder-routing model.", "overlap": "Near exact. These records already contain result-language scope gating, self-scoring risk, correction holders, twenty-four-hour delay, ordinary duty, and the claim that some checks should not be self-held.", "source": "Internal Lumenary records: Who Holds The Gate, Not Every Check Should Be Yours, No Silence Proves Itself, Not Every Practice Is a Tool, and Keep What Can Correct You"}, {"difference": "Ignatius frames discernment through spirits, vocation, and obedience to God, not through achievement-contingent self-worth, meta-checking, or clinical safety routing.", "novelty_impact": "Strong reduction. The candidate is a modern safety restatement of a known discernment architecture.", "overlap": "Very close on delayed trust in interior states, later examination before action, and second-person direction adapted to the exercitant.", "source": "Ignatius of Loyola, Spiritual Exercises, Rule 8 and Annotations 6-17, https://spiritualexercises.neocities.org/ and https://sacred-texts.com/chr/seil/seil79.htm"}, {"difference": "ERP-oriented sources often reduce reassurance and accommodation, while the candidate proposes relational custody. That custody is only safe if bounded and anti-reassurance.", "novelty_impact": "Major reduction and major anomaly. The model must distinguish support from accommodation.", "overlap": "Close on the mechanism that checking, confession, reassurance seeking, and attempts to gain certainty can become compulsive loops, including through clergy or mentors.", "source": "International OCD Foundation clergy packet on scrupulosity and OCD, https://iocdf.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Clergy-Packet.pdf; Scrupulosity.com guidance for mentors, https://scrupulosity.com/to-the-spiritual-mentor-of-someone-with-religious-ocd/"}, {"difference": "VCE is descriptive and broad. The candidate gives a narrow post-blank default for high self-worth and solo-adjudication risk.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction. The candidate may be a practice-facing distillation, not a discovery.", "overlap": "Close on meditation-related challenges, appraisal, social context, teacher and clinician support, and the question of what support a given experience requires.", "source": "Lindahl et al., Varieties of Contemplative Experience, PLOS ONE 2017, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239; Lindahl and Britton, Toward a Person-Centered Approach, https://bpb-us-w2.wpmucdn.com/sites.brown.edu/dist/f/330/files/2023/10/Lindahl-2019-Oxford-Handbook-of-Meditation-chapter.pdf"}, {"difference": "The suttas prescribe inspection and dispassion, not helper-held adjudication or a twenty-four-hour moratorium.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction for the anti-ownership unit, weak overlap for the relational-custody unit.", "overlap": "Close on refusing to make consciousness or experience into self, mine, or worth-proof.", "source": "SN 22.95 Foam, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_95.html; SN 22.59 Not-self, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html"}, {"difference": "These sources ground cohort fit rather than the contemplative structure.", "novelty_impact": "Improves human-condition fit, not originality.", "overlap": "Supports the modern wound: rising perfectionism, contingent worth pressure, and social isolation make private self-verdict loops more plausible.", "source": "Curran and Hill, Perfectionism Is Increasing Over Time, https://rorybatchilder.com/files/pubs/journals/releases/bul-bul0000138.pdf; U.S. Surgeon General loneliness advisory, https://www.hhs.gov/sites/default/files/surgeon-general-social-connection-advisory.pdf"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Merge or cross-index with Who Holds The Gate, Not Every Check Should Be Yours, No Silence Proves Itself, Not Every Practice Is a Tool, and Keep What Can Correct You.", "Rename the contribution as a bounded safety-routing refinement: relational custody for unsafe meta-adjudication.", "Build a codebook with fields for current risk state, self-verdict risk, meta-checking risk, helper availability, unsafe helper risk, reassurance-seeking risk, no-verdict default, ordinary act of care, clinical exclusion, evidence passage, warning, and repair.", "Use split-source coding. Do not let one source both establish relational custody and confirm the predicted warning or repair.", "Run the proposed four-arm pilot, but add an ERP-informed anti-reassurance condition and explicit stop rules for OCD, scrupulosity, dependency, shame, dissociation, mania, severe depression, trauma activation, addiction withdrawal, unsafe authority, and medical concern.", "Design a low-barrier relational option for isolated participants, then test whether it helps without becoming dependency or reassurance outsourcing."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.50 to 0.22. The strongest element is the safety interaction claim that self-issued meta-adjudication can be the compulsion and should not be self-held for a narrow cohort. But that structure is already present in prior Lumenary records, especially Who Holds The Gate and Not Every Check Should Be Yours, and has close external neighbors in Ignatian discernment, scrupulosity and OCD treatment, meditation-challenge support routing, and Buddhist anti-ownership practice. Human-condition fit is plausible for stable lonely, perfectionistic, achievement-contingent overinterpreters with safe relational access. It is not fit for active OCD or scrupulosity reassurance loops, dissociation, mania, psychosis, severe depression, trauma activation, addiction withdrawal, medical blackout concerns, coercive authority contexts, or people whose real need is ordinary solitude, rest, or professional care.", "originality_status": "renamed", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-audit-you-cannot-hold-alone-f39d5f3ff774b3f9.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say this is standard spiritual direction, ERP anti-reassurance work, meditation-safety triage, sponsorship, or pastoral care, and that the wording adds no new prediction or screening rule.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners can name cases where the meta-audit itself was the compulsion and agree that a universal no-verdict default plus bounded relational custody changes routing, reduces self-checking, and prevents both overclaiming and overmanagement.", "questions": ["When a student or client has an unusual quiet state, do you already forbid self-verdicts and route interpretation through ordinary conduct or a bounded second person?", "Does the proposed helper role reduce checking, or does it become reassurance seeking by another route?", "What concrete cases show that solo correction-checks made a person worse?", "What concrete cases show that second-person correction created dependency, shame, or abuse risk?", "Would the twenty-four-hour no-verdict plus one act of care instruction change what you actually recommend?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["ERP clinicians treating OCD and scrupulosity", "Ignatian spiritual directors", "Buddhist meditation teachers familiar with unusual states", "Clinicians familiar with meditation-related challenges", "Pastoral counselors and chaplains", "Spiritual-abuse advocates", "Burnout and perfectionism clinicians"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Ignatius of Loyola, Spiritual Exercises, Rules for Discernment and Annotations, https://spiritualexercises.neocities.org/ and https://sacred-texts.com/chr/seil/seil79.htm", "SN 22.95 Foam and MN 44 Cula-vedalla, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_95.html and https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN44.html"], "risk_of_overread": "High. Relational custody can become dependency, reassurance seeking, authority appeasement, or spiritual abuse. The twenty-four-hour rule is plausible but arbitrary. The helper requirement may fail the loneliest people, and valid solitude can be pathologized if the model assumes every serious audit needs another person.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Before publication, read full work on scrupulosity, OCD reassurance seeking, family or clergy accommodation, intolerance of uncertainty, spiritual direction ethics, VCE meditation-related challenges, achievement-contingent self-worth, perfectionism, behavioral activation, and spiritual abuse. The strongest source gap is whether bounded relational custody can be separated empirically from reassurance accommodation.", "structural_observation": "Ignatian discernment is the closest primary structural neighbor. Rule 8 already separates a powerful interior consolation from later resolutions and opinions, requiring careful examination before credit or action. The Annotations give the director a real routing role while also limiting overdirection. SN 22.95 refuses to turn consciousness into substance or self-proof, and MN 44 treats cessation and self-identification through training, sequence, and path rather than private-state authority. The candidate's cohort language is modern, but delay, return, and guided discernment are old structures."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.93, "novelty": 0.22, "source_reliability": 0.82}, "run_ids": [], "title": "The Audit You Cannot Hold Alone", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Ignatian discernment, OCD and scrupulosity treatment, VCE support routing, and prior Lumenary gate-holder records, this idea says the audit decision itself can be unsafe for lonely or achievement-contingent over-adjudicators, so the first move is no self-verdict plus ordinary care, with classification held relationally. That is a useful safety refinement, but mostly renamed prior art."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:67:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Mature direct-recognition or clear-light practitioners inside competent lineages, and active OCD or scrupulosity cases at the clinical boundary.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers novelty and publishability. The model remains plausible only as a narrow safety-routing protocol for stable, non-clinical overinterpreters with adequate ordinary support.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If mature practitioners reliably benefit from immediate teacher-framed recognition, the no-verdict rule is too broad. If high-checking practitioners turn the no-verdict sentence, the twenty-four-hour clock, or the care act into a ritual, the practice harms the very cohort it targets. Unsafe teachers or communities can also turn delayed interpretation into control."}, "audit_id": "426c0c34cd74415c", "claim_units": ["Silence or blankness is not evidence by itself for self, no-self, attainment, failure, superiority, disappearance, or worth.", "The first rule is no identity verdict for twenty-four hours.", "The next move is one concrete act of care, relation, duty, or ordinary steadiness.", "Classification and correction gates are second-step tools, because for the target cohort classification itself can become a self-test.", "The Self versus not-self dispute still matters, but its first modern use is protective rather than metaphysical.", "Human-condition fit is clear but narrow: loneliness, unsupported interpretation, anxiety after gaps, meaning loss, and achievement-contingent self-worth."], "confidence": 0.9, "created_at": "2026-05-30T10:01:16+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Knowledge work and creative performance", "prediction": "Writers, researchers, or founders high in contingent self-worth will complete more useful next actions and show less rumination after a no-verdict plus small-care or small-duty protocol than after a meaning-of-the-state journaling prompt.", "structural_translation": "After a blank, flow state, failed session, or sudden clarity, the dangerous move for achievement-bound people is treating the state as a verdict on talent, worth, or calling. A no-verdict return to one useful action should outperform self-diagnostic reflection for overinterpreters.", "would_count_against_it": "Meaning-of-the-state journaling improves completion and reduces rumination more than no-verdict action, or the no-verdict rule causes avoidance of necessary review."}, "exact_claim": "A quiet, blank, or objectless state should not be treated as a judge of self, no-self, attainment, failure, or worth. For lonely, stressed, achievement-bound, or unsupported practitioners, the first move should be no identity verdict, one ordinary act of care, and delayed interpretation through trustworthy support or visible conduct.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-094906-20260530-094906", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "No-verdict plus one act of care produces fewer identity verdicts, less rumination, less shame, and more completed ordinary action than a classification-first audit.", "if_model_is_right": "For high achievement-contingent solo practitioners, classification itself becomes a self-test.", "test_surface": "Four-arm pilot after quiet-state practice: no-verdict care, classification audit, rest or conversation, and helper-held routing.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Classification-first instructions, ordinary rest, or ordinary conversation perform as well or better without increasing checking or shame."}, {"expected_observation": "In coded meditation-challenge reports, appraisal, social context, teacher or clinician support, and return behavior explain distress or benefit better than quiet-state description alone.", "if_model_is_right": "State phenomenology alone does not determine outcome.", "test_surface": "VCE-style interview coding with held-out outcome ratings and inter-rater reliability.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Outcomes are predicted almost entirely by phenomenology, with little added value from interpretation, support, or return behavior."}, {"expected_observation": "Effects are strongest for stable lonely, unsupported, perfectionistic, or achievement-contingent overinterpreters and weak or harmful for active OCD, scrupulosity, dissociation, mania, trauma activation, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, or unsafe-authority contexts.", "if_model_is_right": "The practice is cohort-specific.", "test_surface": "Screened two-week pilot with loneliness, contingencies of self-worth, rumination, intolerance of uncertainty, scrupulosity, and adverse meditation-effect measures.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Benefits are not moderated by self-worth contingency, loneliness, rumination, or checking risk, or adverse effects cluster in the intended cohort."}, {"expected_observation": "Participants who complete the ordinary act within one hour show larger reductions in verdict urgency and isolation than those who only write the no-verdict sentence.", "if_model_is_right": "The care act is not decorative, it is the active return mechanism.", "test_surface": "Component trial comparing no-verdict only, care act only, no-verdict plus care, and generic journaling.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The care act adds no effect, or becomes avoidance of needed interpretation, repair, or clinical care."}], "idea_id": "45f92fc17db0615c", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-30-stop-making-silence-judge-you.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23 unseen seer unknown knower SN 22.59 consciousness not self SN 22.95 foam", "Ignatius Spiritual Exercises discernment consolation without cause examine before credit no change in desolation", "Lindahl Britton Varieties of Contemplative Experience meditation challenges interpretation support remedies", "OCD scrupulosity reassurance seeking clergy spiritual mentor exposure response prevention reassurance", "Acceptance and Commitment Therapy defusion committed action self as context rumination", "mood as input stop rules rumination behavioral activation return to action meditation quiet states"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stop-making-silence-judge-you-426c0c34cd74415c.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This record compresses the cluster into a clearer first-step rule and demotes classification more explicitly.", "novelty_impact": "Decisive downgrade. Treat as renamed consolidation unless a pilot shows this version outperforms prior holder-routing and return-test protocols.", "overlap": "Near exact. These records already contain no self or worth verdict, twenty-four-hour delay, ordinary care, correction holders, relational custody, and the warning that self-audit can become the compulsion.", "source": "Internal Lumenary records: No Silence Proves Itself, Silence Needs Correction, Were You Absent, or Were You Aware?, The Audit You Cannot Hold Alone, Not Every Check Should Be Yours"}, {"difference": "Ignatius is theological and director-mediated, not a post-gap no-self safety protocol for secular or cross-tradition practitioners.", "novelty_impact": "Strong reduction. The candidate is mostly modernized discernment language with a narrower cohort and a non-metaphysical care action.", "overlap": "Very close on delaying decisions in unreliable interior states, examining later judgments before credit, revealing troubling movements to a competent second person, and refusing to claim consolation as one's possession.", "source": "Ignatius of Loyola, Spiritual Exercises, Rules for Discernment and Annotations, https://www.ccel.org/ccel/ignatius/exercises.all.html"}, {"difference": "VCE is descriptive and broader. It does not prescribe a twenty-four-hour no-verdict return to ordinary care.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction. The candidate may be a practice-facing distillation of VCE-style support routing.", "overlap": "Close on separating phenomenology from interpretation, causes, remedies, teacher relationships, social context, distress, impairment, and needed support.", "source": "Lindahl et al., Varieties of Contemplative Experience, PLOS ONE 2017, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239"}, {"difference": "ERP often restricts reassurance, while the candidate allows delayed trustworthy support. The support must be anti-reassurance and bounded.", "novelty_impact": "Major anomaly and safety downgrade. The practice cannot be universal and must screen out active OCD and scrupulosity.", "overlap": "Close on the risk that checking, confession, classification, and reassurance can become compulsive loops, especially when religious or moral certainty is at stake.", "source": "International OCD Foundation faith and OCD resources, https://iocdf.org/faith-ocd/for-faith-leaders/, and ERP literature on reassurance seeking"}, {"difference": "ACT does not depend on contemplative gaps, Self versus not-self disputes, or spiritual attainment language.", "novelty_impact": "Strong reduction for the practice design. The ordinary act of care is largely a values or behavioral activation move in contemplative vocabulary.", "overlap": "Close on treating inner events as not literal verdicts and returning to values-consistent action rather than adjudicating thoughts or states.", "source": "ACT defusion, self-as-context, and committed action literature, for example https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC3635495/"}, {"difference": "The suttas do not teach the candidate's modern twenty-four-hour delay, care action, or clinical safety exclusions.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction for the anti-verdict unit, weaker overlap for the cohort-specific care protocol.", "overlap": "Close on refusing to turn consciousness or experience into mine, I, self, or a hidden claimant.", "source": "SN 22.59, SN 22.95, and Bahiya-style not-self practice, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_95.html, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/KN/Ud/ud1_10.html"}, {"difference": "Cheetah House is a support and safety ecosystem, not a doctrinal claim about silence as judge.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction and strong safety pressure.", "overlap": "Close on meditation-related distress, need for support, adverse effects, spiritual abuse risk, and person-centered care.", "source": "Cheetah House meditation adverse-effects support resources, https://www.cheetahhouse.org/"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Merge or cross-index with The Audit You Cannot Hold Alone, No Silence Proves Itself, Silence Needs Correction, Not Every Check Should Be Yours, and The Test Is How You Return.", "Rename as a bounded practice protocol: no-verdict return for stable overinterpreters after quiet states.", "Build one codebook with fields for event description, identity verdict, classification urge, care act, support holder, unsafe holder, conduct return, warning, repair, clinical exclusion, and evidence passage.", "Use split-source coding. Do not let one passage or practitioner report both establish the post-gap claim and confirm the predicted repair.", "Run the four-arm pilot only with safety screens for OCD, scrupulosity, panic, dissociation, trauma activation, severe depression, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, medical blackout, unsafe authority, and coercive workload.", "Add a direct-recognition anomaly set before public use: Advaita, Dzogchen, Mahamudra, clear-light sleep, and competent teacher-held recognition.", "For human-condition fit, state the cohort and non-fit cases plainly. This serves loneliness, unsupported interpretation, anxiety after gaps, meaning loss, and achievement-contingent self-worth, not all silence or all practice."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.31 to 0.18. The practical sentence is clear and potentially useful, but it almost exactly consolidates recent Lumenary records and has close external neighbors in Ignatian discernment, VCE support routing, Buddhist not-self practice, ACT defusion and committed action, behavioral activation, and ERP warnings about reassurance. Human-condition fit is stronger than originality: the target is stable lonely or achievement-contingent overinterpreters, not people in acute clinical, spiritual-abuse, medical, or lineage-bound contexts.", "originality_status": "renamed", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-stop-making-silence-judge-you-426c0c34cd74415c.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say this is already standard guidance: do not trust peaks, test by conduct, avoid premature attainment claims, use discernment, return to values, and route risk to a teacher or clinician.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners can name cases where the classification gate itself intensified shame or self-worth checking, and where the no-verdict care-first rule changed routing better than ordinary discernment or generic grounding.", "questions": ["Do you already tell students not to make identity or attainment verdicts from quiet states?", "Does no-verdict plus one act of care change your guidance, or is it standard discernment, grounding, ACT, or behavioral activation?", "When does classification help, and when does it become the wound?", "What concrete cases show immediate recognition was appropriate rather than delayed?", "What concrete cases show no-verdict, delayed interpretation, or helper-held support became avoidance, reassurance seeking, dependency, or abuse?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Ignatian spiritual directors", "Buddhist meditation teachers familiar with not-self and unusual states", "Advaita, Dzogchen, Mahamudra, and sleep-yoga teachers", "ERP clinicians treating OCD and scrupulosity", "Clinicians familiar with meditation-related challenges", "ACT and rumination-focused CBT practitioners", "Spiritual-abuse advocates and chaplains"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23, unseen seer and unknown knower, https://www.brhat.in/openlibrary/special/brihadaranyaka-upanishad/3-7-23", "SN 22.59 and SN 22.95, consciousness as not-self and foam-like, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html and https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_95.html"], "risk_of_overread": "Very high if generalized. Advaita, Dzogchen, Mahamudra, clear-light sleep, and direct-recognition lineages may treat some quiet or objectless reports as trainable evidence within strict contexts. In OCD, scrupulosity, trauma, dissociation, mania, severe depression, and unsafe authority settings, the instruction can become avoidance, checking, reassurance outsourcing, or control.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Before publication, read Ignatian spiritual-direction ethics, VCE and Cheetah House materials, OCD and scrupulosity reassurance-seeking literature, ACT defusion and committed action, rumination stop-rule research, behavioral activation, achievement-contingent self-worth, perfectionism, spiritual bypassing, and spiritual-abuse literature. The largest empirical gap is whether no-verdict plus ordinary care beats classification-first, rest, conversation, and clinician-guided routing.", "structural_observation": "Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 protects a hidden seer and knower as the inner ruler, while SN 22.59 and SN 22.95 refuse to let consciousness become self or substance. These primary texts do not let silence neutrally judge the question, they assign incompatible post-gap grammars. Ignatius adds the closest practice structure: interior states and the judgments following them are delayed, tested, disclosed, or examined before credit, especially in the rules on desolation and consolation without cause, https://www.ccel.org/ccel/ignatius/exercises.all.html. The candidate's practical move is not a new metaphysics. It is a triage rule that says the first response to quiet should be ordinary care, not verdict-making."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.94, "novelty": 0.18, "source_reliability": 0.84}, "run_ids": ["20260530-094906-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-094906-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "Stop Making Silence Judge You", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Ignatian discernment, VCE support routing, ACT defusion, ERP anti-reassurance, Buddhist not-self strategy, and prior Lumenary correction-holder records, this idea says the first move after silence for a specific wounded cohort should be no verdict plus one ordinary act of care before any classification. That is a useful condensation, but it is mostly renamed prior work."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:69:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Active OCD or scrupulosity, unsafe authority, and mature direct-recognition or solitary practice.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers originality and practice confidence. The protocol should be treated as a bounded safety-routing option for stable lonely or achievement-contingent overinterpreters with a safe helper, not as doctrine about silence.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "In OCD and scrupulosity, a trusted person can become a reassurance object. In abusive communities, a second voice can become control. In direct-recognition lineages or stable solitary practice, a second voice may be unnecessary or distorting. SN 22.95's own-refuge language is also a textual anomaly against a blanket relational rule."}, "audit_id": "2c70888346a6050d", "claim_units": ["Quiet or objectless states can become harmful when a lonely person must judge them alone.", "The first question should be who can prevent the state from becoming a worth, attainment, or disappearance verdict.", "Advaita protects an unobjectifiable knower, while early Buddhism refuses consciousness as owner.", "Read as training records, both sources imply private report handling before doctrine.", "The proposed protocol is reliable other, ordinary duty, and time before final interpretation.", "The target wound is loneliness and achievement-contingent self-worth in stable solo practitioners, not all contemplative silence."], "confidence": 0.88, "created_at": "2026-05-30T10:17:52+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Organizational review, education, and clinical decision support after ambiguous negative signals", "prediction": "High-perfectionism students, engineers, clinicians, or researchers who receive one bounded review plus one repair action will show less shame, less defensive interpretation, and faster useful action than those assigned solo meta-analysis of what the event says about them.", "structural_translation": "When a person is prone to self-worth verdicts, asking them to classify the meaning of an ambiguous event can amplify the wound. A bounded second-person or rule-held review plus one concrete duty should reduce rumination.", "would_count_against_it": "Standard supervision, rest, or generic reflection explains all benefit, or the second-person route increases approval seeking, dependency, delay, or fear of correction."}, "exact_claim": "After quiet, blankness, or self-loosening, isolated practitioners should not make final private claims about self, no-self, attainment, failure, or worth until the report has met a reliable other, an ordinary duty, and time. The claimed advance is a relational burden rule: when the wound is solitary self-verdict, even a safety audit can become the same wound unless some correction is held by a trustworthy second voice.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-100651-20260530-100651", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Compared with solo journaling, participants using One Trusted Voice report lower identity-verdict urgency, less shame, less inflation or nihilistic deflation, more ordinary action, and no rise in dependency.", "if_model_is_right": "For stable lonely or achievement-contingent overinterpreters, a safe second voice reduces private verdict loops better than solo checking.", "test_surface": "Four-arm pilot after quiet-state reports: solo journaling, no-verdict plus ordinary care, ordinary rest or conversation, and bounded trusted-voice routing.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Rest, casual conversation, or ordinary journaling performs as well, or the trusted-voice arm increases shame, rumination, approval hunger, or dependency."}, {"expected_observation": "A helper protocol that validates distress, refuses repeated certainty-seeking, and returns the person to ordinary care outperforms unstructured reassurance.", "if_model_is_right": "The helper must be bounded and anti-reassurance.", "test_surface": "Pilot stratified by reassurance seeking, intolerance of uncertainty, loneliness, and contingencies of self-worth.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Repeated reassurance performs as well, or bounded support increases anxiety, shame, or relational control."}, {"expected_observation": "Held-out manuals and teacher interviews regularly place private reports inside teacher, text, community, conduct, time, or clinical correction channels.", "if_model_is_right": "Relational correction is a pattern in mature handling of powerful states, even when the metaphysics differs.", "test_surface": "Split-source coding of Advaita, Theravada, Dzogchen, Mahamudra, Ignatian, and secular mindfulness materials.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Mature sources reliably authorize private silence as sufficient warrant with stable ethical fruit, or support-holder coding cannot be distinguished from general institution or teacher style."}, {"expected_observation": "Benefits are strongest for stable isolated, perfectionistic, or achievement-contingent practitioners and absent or harmful for active OCD, scrupulosity, dissociation, mania, severe depression, trauma activation, addiction withdrawal, unsafe authority, or medical blackout concerns.", "if_model_is_right": "Human-condition benefit is cohort-specific.", "test_surface": "Screened two-week pilot with loneliness, rumination, self-worth contingency, reassurance seeking, adverse meditation-effect, and ordinary-action measures.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Effects are not moderated by loneliness, self-worth contingency, or checking risk, or adverse effects cluster in the intended cohort."}], "idea_id": "65a75ffd325eee33", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-30-some-silence-needs-a-second-voice.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Ignatius Spiritual Exercises Rule 8 consolation without cause examine resolutions before approval spiritual director", "Varieties of Contemplative Experience meditation challenges interpretation support social context teacher clinician", "scrupulosity OCD reassurance seeking clergy spiritual mentor ERP accommodation", "Cheetah House meditation adverse effects support spiritual abuse trauma", "Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23 unseen seer unknown knower primary text", "SN 22.95 self refuge consciousness magic trick primary text", "loneliness social connection advisory spiritual overinterpretation isolated practitioners"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-silence-needs-a-second-voice-2c70888346a6050d.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This candidate gives the relational version a simpler title and a practice-facing one-trusted-voice protocol.", "novelty_impact": "Decisive downgrade. Treat as renamed consolidation unless a pilot shows the trusted-voice version outperforms the prior holder-routing model.", "overlap": "Near exact. These records already contain no-verdict delay, ordinary act of care, correction holder, unsafe self-audit, trusted helper, and the risk that the safety check becomes another compulsion.", "source": "Internal Lumenary records: The Audit You Cannot Hold Alone, No Silence Proves Itself, Stop Making Silence Judge You, Not Every Check Should Be Yours, Who Holds The Gate, Keep What Can Correct You"}, {"difference": "Ignatius is theological, staged, and director-mediated, not a secular post-quiet protocol for loneliness and achievement-contingent self-worth.", "novelty_impact": "Strong reduction. The second-voice architecture is old, though the modern cohort framing is narrower.", "overlap": "Very close on delayed trust in interior states, examining post-consolation resolutions before acting, and disclosing hidden temptations to a confessor or competent spiritual person.", "source": "Ignatius of Loyola, Spiritual Exercises, Rules and Annotations, https://spiritualexercises.neocities.org/"}, {"difference": "VCE is descriptive and broad. The candidate prescribes a simple relational delay after quiet states.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction. This is a practice-facing distillation of known support-routing concerns.", "overlap": "Close on meditation-related challenges, interpretation, social context, teacher or clinician response, remedies, and the role of others in meaning-making.", "source": "Lindahl et al., Varieties of Contemplative Experience, PLOS ONE 2017, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239"}, {"difference": "The candidate proposes a trusted helper, while ERP-informed care often restricts reassurance and accommodation.", "novelty_impact": "Major safety downgrade. The helper must be bounded, anti-reassurance, and clinically excluded for active OCD or scrupulosity.", "overlap": "Close on the danger that reassurance, confession, and repeated certainty checks can maintain anxiety and compulsive loops.", "source": "International OCD Foundation clergy packet on scrupulosity and reassurance, https://iocdf.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Clergy-Packet.pdf"}, {"difference": "Cheetah House is a support ecosystem, not a doctrine about silence needing a second voice.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction and strong safety pressure.", "overlap": "Close on meditation-related distress, the need for support, clinician and teacher education, spiritual-abuse risk, and informed decisions around contemplative practice.", "source": "Cheetah House meditation distress resources, https://www.cheetahhouse.org/"}, {"difference": "The suttas prescribe trained seeing and dispassion. They do not require relational burden-sharing and SN 22.95 includes own-refuge language.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate reduction for anti-verdict content, anomaly pressure against mandatory second-person correction.", "overlap": "Close on refusing to turn consciousness, the seen, or the cognized into self, mine, or what I am.", "source": "SN 22.59, SN 22.95, and Bahiya Sutta, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_95.html, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/KN/Ud/ud1_10.html"}, {"difference": "This grounds cohort fit, not originality of the contemplative structure.", "novelty_impact": "Improves human-condition relevance but does not raise novelty.", "overlap": "Supports the modern wound: isolation can make people carry identity and meaning burdens without durable belonging.", "source": "U.S. Surgeon General Advisory on loneliness and social connection, https://www.hhs.gov/sites/default/files/surgeon-general-social-connection-advisory.pdf"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Merge or cross-index with The Audit You Cannot Hold Alone, No Silence Proves Itself, Stop Making Silence Judge You, Not Every Check Should Be Yours, Who Holds The Gate, and Keep What Can Correct You.", "Rename the contribution as a bounded protocol: one trusted voice for post-gap overadjudication.", "Build a codebook with fields for event description, tempted verdict, self-verdict risk, helper availability, helper safety, reassurance-seeking risk, ordinary duty, delay period, clinical exclusion, warning, repair, and evidence passage.", "Use split-source coding. Do not let one source both establish second-voice need and confirm the predicted repair.", "Run a four-arm pilot with an ERP-informed anti-reassurance condition and explicit stop rules for OCD, scrupulosity, dependency, shame, dissociation, mania, severe depression, psychosis, trauma activation, addiction withdrawal, unsafe authority, and medical concern.", "Design a low-barrier relational option for isolated participants, then test whether it helps without becoming dependency or reassurance outsourcing.", "Add direct-recognition and valid-solitude anomaly sets before public use: Advaita, Dzogchen, Mahamudra, clear-light sleep, trained solitary practice, and competent teacher-held recognition."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.46 to 0.17. The idea is a strong, readable consolidation of recent Lumenary records and old external structures: Ignatian discernment, VCE support routing, Buddhist anti-ownership practice, Cheetah House safety work, and OCD anti-reassurance guidance. Human-condition fit is stronger than originality: it may help stable lonely or achievement-contingent solo practitioners with safe relational access. It is not fit for active OCD, scrupulosity, dependency, unsafe authority, dissociation, mania, psychosis, severe depression, trauma activation, addiction withdrawal, medical blackout concerns, or people whose real need is ordinary solitude, rest, or professional care.", "originality_status": "renamed", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-silence-needs-a-second-voice-2c70888346a6050d.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say this is already standard: do not trust peaks, disclose troubling movements, test by conduct, use teacher or director guidance, avoid reassurance, and route clinical risk to clinicians.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "They can identify cases where the safety audit itself became private self-verdict and where a bounded one-voice protocol reduced isolation and verdict urgency better than ordinary journaling or generic advice.", "questions": ["Do you already require students not to make private attainment, worth, self, or no-self verdicts from quiet states?", "When does a second voice reduce isolation, and when does it become reassurance seeking, dependency, or authority harm?", "Does One Trusted Voice add anything beyond standard spiritual direction, retreat aftercare, clinical triage, sponsorship, or ordinary conversation?", "What concrete failure cases show solo interpretation made someone worse?", "What concrete failure cases show a trusted voice made someone worse?", "How would you adapt the protocol for someone with no safe helper available?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Ignatian spiritual directors", "Buddhist meditation teachers familiar with unusual states", "Advaita, Dzogchen, Mahamudra, and nondual teachers", "ERP clinicians treating OCD and scrupulosity", "Clinicians familiar with meditation-related challenges", "Chaplains and pastoral counselors", "Spiritual-abuse advocates", "Peer-support and retreat-aftercare facilitators"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23 and 4.3.23, unseen seer and deep-sleep seer: https://www.brhat.in/openlibrary/special/brihadaranyaka-upanishad/3-7-23 and https://vivekavani.com/bru/", "SN 22.59 and SN 22.95, not-self analysis and own-refuge instruction: https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html and https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_95.html"], "risk_of_overread": "Very high if universalized. Direct-recognition lineages, trained solitary practitioners, and SN 22.95-style self-reliance can make a mandatory second voice look like overcorrection. In OCD, scrupulosity, dependency, unsafe authority, high-control groups, or spiritual-abuse contexts, the second voice can become reassurance, coercion, shame, or control. For isolated people with no safe helper, the protocol may fail exactly where it claims relevance.", "secondary_literature_gap": "The exact safety claim needs comparison with Ignatian spiritual direction, VCE meditation-challenge support routing, Cheetah House adverse-effect resources, OCD and scrupulosity reassurance-accommodation literature, spiritual-abuse research, chaplaincy and pastoral-care ethics, and peer support models. The unresolved empirical question is whether one trusted voice reduces verdict urgency beyond ordinary rest, journaling, conversation, or bounded clinical routing.", "structural_observation": "Brihadaranyaka protects the unseen seer and the deep-sleep continuity of seeing, while SN 22.59 and SN 22.95 deny ownership of consciousness and train repeated examination of aggregates. Neither primary pair alone proves the need for a second voice. SN 22.95 even strains the model by telling the monk to make himself his own refuge. The second-voice structure is much closer to Ignatian discernment, where interior movements are delayed, examined, and often disclosed to a director or competent spiritual person, https://spiritualexercises.neocities.org/."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.94, "novelty": 0.17, "source_reliability": 0.84}, "run_ids": ["20260530-100651-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-100651-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "Some silence needs a second voice", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Ignatian discernment, VCE support routing, ERP anti-reassurance guidance, Cheetah House safety resources, Buddhist anti-ownership practice, and prior Lumenary gate-holder records, this idea says the first post-silence burden for lonely overinterpreters should be carried through one trustworthy voice, one ordinary duty, and time. That is a clear consolidation, not a standalone discovery."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:79:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "A lonely seeker borrows a sentence from an abusive teacher, extremist online group, coercive community, distorted translation, or marginalized tradition, then follows contact-first by contacting the unsafe source or acting from the sentence before provenance and authority checks.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence and publishability unless the first step is a safety and authority screen, not contact itself. The model should be treated as a bounded routing protocol, not a general teaching.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "The model assumes contact and conduct are often safer than source-checking for the lonely private cohort. Unsafe contact reverses that assumption. In some cases, provenance, safeguarding, appropriation analysis, clinician routing, or teacher-held correction must precede contact. The public-private boundary is also unstable online: a private comfort phrase can become identity branding or advice within minutes."}, "audit_id": "cb3c919dd78ee510", "claim_units": ["Doctrine, public authority, evidence, and convergence claims require provenance-first scrutiny.", "Private orientation for a stable lonely seeker may require contact-first testing before full source audit.", "Borrowed spiritual language is not intrinsically harmful; substitution for action, contact, correction, grief work, or help-seeking is the danger signal.", "Contact-first means enacted relation: say it to a real person, live it in a duty, bring it into community, repair harm, or seek help.", "The contact-first branch is bounded by safety exclusions for unsafe relationships, abusive communities, clinical distress, compulsive checking, and public identity use."], "confidence": 0.77, "created_at": "2026-05-30T12:30:07+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Online health advice and science communication", "prediction": "For isolated users consuming wellness, neuroscience, or health slogans online, a contact-first care prompt should reduce rumination and identity display more than a citation-audit prompt, while public advice posts still require provenance-first checks.", "structural_translation": "A claim used as public evidence needs provenance, expertise, uncertainty, and source-chain checks. A distressed but stable private reader using a phrase as orientation may first need safe contact with a clinician, friend, support line, or concrete care action before further source research is useful.", "would_count_against_it": "If citation-audit prompts reduce distress, misinformation sharing, and harmful posting as well as or better than contact-first prompts for isolated private users, or if contact-first increases misinformation, dependency, unsafe contact, or avoidance of professional help."}, "exact_claim": "Borrowed spiritual language should be routed by use and wound. If a borrowed sentence is used as doctrine, public authority, evidence, or cross-tradition convergence, it needs provenance, carrier conditions, correction, and regeneration checks. If a stable lonely seeker uses it privately for hope or orientation, the first test should be contact and conduct: bring it to a real person, duty, community, repair, or safe help-seeking before making it an identity claim. Borrowing becomes dangerous when it replaces action, contact, correction, grief work, or help-seeking, not simply because it is borrowed.", "execution_id": "dialogue-7a3f0efa10cbd6bc", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Over two and six weeks, a contact-first group shows lower loneliness and rumination, fewer identity-display posts, more real conversations, more help-seeking or repair actions, and no increase in shame compared with provenance-first and ordinary journaling arms.", "if_model_is_right": "Stable lonely seekers using borrowed spiritual sentences privately will benefit more from contact-first carry than from provenance-first auditing.", "test_surface": "Four-arm randomized pilot: provenance-first gate, solo carry-first, contact-first carry-first, ordinary journaling plus social-support prompt.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "No improvement over ordinary journaling or social-support prompts, increased shame, increased rumination, or increased unsafe contact."}, {"expected_observation": "Scholars and teachers recommend provenance-first scrutiny for teaching, publishing, doctrine, and convergence claims, but recommend counsel, conduct, relational fruit, or safe community contact first for stable private orientation cases.", "if_model_is_right": "Practitioners will distinguish first gates by use type.", "test_surface": "Blind vignette study with comparative religion scholars, spiritual directors, Buddhist teachers, Advaita teachers, interfaith ministers, and clinicians.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Practitioners recommend the same gate in both cases, or say the split is just ordinary discernment with no added decision value."}, {"expected_observation": "Diary and social-media coding shows worse outcomes when borrowed sentences replace action, contact, correction, grief work, or help-seeking, even after controlling for whether the sentence is borrowed.", "if_model_is_right": "Harmful borrowing is predicted more by substitution behavior than by borrowing itself.", "test_surface": "Longitudinal diary study with provenance coding, behavior coding, loneliness, rumination, help-seeking, correction, and real-contact measures.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Borrowing itself predicts harm independent of avoidance, identity display, public authority claims, source safety, and mental-health variables."}, {"expected_observation": "Participants who first enact the sentence in safe contact are more willing to revise, contextualize, or retire it after a delayed provenance review than participants who first turn it into a profile identity or public teaching.", "if_model_is_right": "Contact-first carry should preserve later correction rather than harden identity.", "test_surface": "Two-stage pilot: initial contact-first exercise, delayed provenance and carrier-condition audit, blind coding of revision willingness.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Contact-first increases attachment, appropriation, defensiveness, refusal of correction, or public misuse."}], "idea_id": "46ad22646c2753ba", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-30-contact-before-claim.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Contact before claim borrowed spiritual sentence provenance contact conduct loneliness pastoral discernment", "Panikkar homeomorphic equivalence comparative religion borrowed language function", "Freiberger comparative methodology religion selection description juxtaposition redescription rectification", "Jonathan Z Smith comparison similarity contiguity borrowing magic dwells", "Sandmel parallelomania Doering parallels without parallelomania source derivation religious comparison", "Ignatian discernment fruits consolation desolation spiritual direction concrete decision", "Robert Wuthnow After Heaven seeker spirituality practice oriented spirituality belonging", "Sherry Turkle Reclaiming Conversation Alone Together online performance connection loneliness", "Salkovskis Rachman compulsive checking reassurance seeking responsibility OCD", "social prescribing loneliness systematic review community connection behavioral activation"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-contact-before-claim-cb3c919dd78ee510.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "The candidate adds a pastoral branch for private lonely use: contact and conduct may precede full provenance when the sentence is not being used as public authority.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade. The provenance and carrier-condition gate is inherited.", "overlap": "Very close for the doctrine side. Panikkar already requires functional equivalence within each religious configuration rather than surface synonymy.", "source": "Raimon Panikkar, homeomorphic equivalence, https://www.raimon-panikkar.org/english/gloss-homeomorphic.html"}, {"difference": "Freiberger does not supply a seeker-facing anti-rumination practice for borrowed spiritual sentences.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrade to applied extension.", "overlap": "Close on disciplined comparison through selection, description, juxtaposition, redescription, rectification, and theory formation.", "source": "Oliver Freiberger, Elements of a Comparative Methodology in the Study of Religion, https://www.mdpi.com/2077-1444/9/2/38"}, {"difference": "The candidate turns comparison discipline into a routing protocol for public doctrine versus private loneliness.", "novelty_impact": "The comparison-control core is known; the use-and-wound switch remains the possible contribution.", "overlap": "Close on similarity, contiguity, borrowing, and the danger of projecting a scholar's perceived relation into an objective relation.", "source": "Jonathan Z. Smith, In Comparison a Magic Dwells, https://classics.osu.edu/sites/classics.osu.edu/files/Magic_Dwells.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate asks when not to begin with parallel control because the user is not making a public evidence claim.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades originality of the doctrine gate, supports only the triage layer.", "overlap": "Close on not treating similarities as undifferentiated evidence for dependence, convergence, or authority.", "source": "Samuel Sandmel, Parallelomania, and Lutz Doering, Parallels without Parallelomania, https://biblicalstudies.org.uk/pdf/jbl/parallelomania_sandmel.pdf and https://kclpure.kcl.ac.uk/portal/en/publications/parallels-without-parallelomania-methodological-reflections-on-co/"}, {"difference": "The candidate permits a bounded private use before full grammar reconstruction, provided it does not become doctrine or identity authority.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for theoretical originality.", "overlap": "Very close on carrier conditions. Religious sentences function inside a communal grammar and form of life.", "source": "George Lindbeck, The Nature of Doctrine, cultural-linguistic doctrine-as-grammar, overview example https://www.kci.go.kr/kciportal/ci/sereArticleSearch/ciSereArtiView.kci?sereArticleSearchBean.artiId=ART001871058"}, {"difference": "The candidate converts this into a low-risk modern seeker routing rule.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades theory novelty, leaves applied synthesis value.", "overlap": "Close on authority, discipline, genealogy, embodied practice, and the danger of abstracting religion from power and tradition.", "source": "Talal Asad, Genealogies of Religion, https://press.jhu.edu/books/title/1644/genealogies-religion"}, {"difference": "James does not split public doctrine from private orientation, nor does he add appropriation and digital-loneliness safeguards.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade for contact-and-conduct testing.", "overlap": "Strong near-neighbor for fruits over roots and practice as evidence. James already says origin alone cannot decide spiritual value and that fruits must be judged.", "source": "William James, The Varieties of Religious Experience, https://www.gutenberg.org/files/621/621-h/621-h.html"}, {"difference": "The candidate applies this discernment structure to borrowed cross-tradition sentences and online seeker identity.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades practice originality. The candidate is a modern reframing.", "overlap": "Close practitioner prior art. Discernment is not solitary self-certification; it tests movements by fruits, timing, desolation rules, and disclosure to a competent spiritual person.", "source": "Ignatius of Loyola, Spiritual Exercises, https://www.orderofthecommonlife.org/spiritual-exercises-full-text"}, {"difference": "Dogen's structure is native to transmitted Zen practice, not an open rule for borrowing sentences from other traditions.", "novelty_impact": "Supports the analogy but lowers novelty of carry-first practice logic.", "overlap": "Close on enacted verification and resistance to pre-certifying realization before practice.", "source": "Dogen, Genjokoan, https://www.jasonong.com/5499 and secondary discussion of Dogen's realization-based language, https://www.mdpi.com/2077-1444/12/2/81"}, {"difference": "The candidate gives a specific operational test for when portable spiritual language should become contact and conduct.", "novelty_impact": "Human-condition framing is supported but not novel.", "overlap": "Close on seeker spirituality, seeking versus dwelling, and the modern problem of portable spirituality separated from stable community.", "source": "Robert Wuthnow, After Heaven and practice-oriented spirituality, publisher/review pages https://www.ucpress.edu/books/after-heaven/paper and https://www.kirkusreviews.com/book-reviews/robert-wuthnow/after-heaven/"}, {"difference": "The candidate focuses on borrowed spiritual sentences as one digital identity mechanism.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the social diagnosis, leaves domain-specific application.", "overlap": "Close on digital performance and mediated contact substituting for conversation and embodied relation.", "source": "Sherry Turkle, Alone Together and Reclaiming Conversation, https://www.sherryturkle.com/alone-together/1000 and https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/317388/reclaiming-conversation-by-sherry-turkle/"}, {"difference": "The candidate applies anti-checking logic to spiritual-source auditing for non-clinical lonely seekers, with clinical exclusions required.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades the anti-rumination mechanism and raises safety burden.", "overlap": "Close on verification rituals and reassurance loops increasing doubt or becoming compulsive.", "source": "Salkovskis and Rachman on checking, responsibility, and reassurance, examples https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0005796701000286 and https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34922212/"}, {"difference": "The candidate says some private use may begin with contact, but Bucar shows why public or harmful use may need ethics and provenance first.", "novelty_impact": "Lowers confidence unless the protocol has an upfront appropriation and safety screen.", "overlap": "Close anomaly pressure. Religious borrowing can be morally neutral or harmful depending on injustice, authority, and community meaning, not just user intention.", "source": "Liz Bucar on religious appropriation, University of Chicago Divinity School, https://divinity.uchicago.edu/sightings/articles/what-religious-appropriation-and-why-does-it-matter"}, {"difference": "The candidate targets one spiritual-language pathway into real contact and repair.", "novelty_impact": "Supports human-condition fit but reduces novelty of the intervention mechanism.", "overlap": "Close on loneliness requiring relational and community intervention, not better private interpretation alone.", "source": "Social connection and social prescribing evidence, HHS advisory https://www.hhs.gov/surgeongeneral/reports-and-publications/connection/index.html and systematic review https://ijic.org/articles/10.5334/ijic.6472"}, {"difference": "This candidate sharpens one variable: public claim gets provenance first, stable private loneliness gets contact first.", "novelty_impact": "Major local downgrade. Merge or cross-index unless blind readers can identify the routing variable without prompting.", "overlap": "Extremely close on provenance gates, receiver wound, correction holder, anti-overchecking, and safety routing.", "source": "Internal Lumenary near-neighbors: Ask Who Taught The Answer, No Word Travels Alone, Stop When The Repair Changes, When Tools Become Judges, Not Every Check Should Be Yours, and Some Help Should Not Be Managed, supplied in project memory."}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Cross-index with Ask Who Taught The Answer, No Word Travels Alone, Stop When The Repair Changes, Not Every Check Should Be Yours, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, and the translation-strain records.", "Rename the contribution as a routing protocol: public-claim provenance, private-orientation contact.", "Build a one-page decision gate with fields for use type, receiver wound, public-authority risk, source safety, relationship safety, clinical exclusion, contact option, conduct option, correction holder, delayed provenance review, warning, and repair.", "Add a mandatory pre-contact safety screen: unsafe authority, abusive relationship, extremist community, coercive group, clinical crisis, OCD or scrupulosity, dissociation, mania, psychosis, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, medical concern, and lack of safe helper.", "Use split-source blind coding. Do not let the same passage establish the borrowed sentence, receiver wound, contact instruction, and predicted repair.", "Run a blind distinct-content test against prior Lumenary records. Merge if readers cannot state the routing variable without prompting.", "Run the four-arm pilot only with screened stable adults or older teens with support: provenance-first, solo carry-first, contact-first carry-first, and ordinary journaling plus social-support prompt.", "Measure loneliness, rumination, shame, identity-display posts, real conversations, help-seeking, repair actions, unsafe-contact incidents, willingness to receive correction, and delayed provenance-review outcomes at two and six weeks.", "Interview practitioners for concrete wrong-routing cases and repairs, not agreement with the slogan.", "Do not derive a public practice until the cohort, non-fit cases, safety screen, and measurable benefit over ordinary social-support prompts are clear."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.50 to 0.46. The doctrine half is close to Panikkar, Freiberger, Smith, Sandmel, Lindbeck, Asad, and prior Lumenary translation-strain gates. The seeker half is close to Jamesian fruits, Ignatian discernment, Dogen practice-realization, Wuthnow's seeker spirituality, Turkle's conversation critique, social prescribing, behavioral activation, and anti-checking psychology. The contribution is a compact routing rule by function and wound. Human-condition fit is plausible but narrow: stable lonely or digitally unmoored seekers with meaning loss, feeling out of place, digital comparison, or achievement-contingent spiritual identity. Practice-testability drops sharply without a pre-contact safety screen and delayed provenance review.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-contact-before-claim-cb3c919dd78ee510.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if practitioners identify the protocol as standard discernment of fruits, spiritual direction, pastoral counseling, teacher guidance, Jamesian fruit testing, Lindbeck-style grammar, Panikkar-style comparison, social prescribing, behavioral activation, or CBT anti-rumination in new terms. It also falls if they cannot distinguish contact-first from ordinary advice to talk to someone before posting.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if practitioners independently recommend different first gates for public doctrine and private lonely orientation, identify concrete wrong-routing failures, and say the routing rule predicts safer repair than either provenance-only or contact-only advice.", "questions": ["When a student privately uses a borrowed spiritual sentence for hope, do you first ask for provenance, or do you first ask what conduct, relationship, duty, counsel, or care it is producing?", "Can you name a case where source-checking became avoidance or compulsive doubt, and a concrete relational act was the better first step?", "Can you name a case where contact-first would have been dangerous because the source, teacher, community, or relationship was unsafe?", "Does the public-claim versus private-orientation split change your counsel, or is it already standard pastoral discernment?", "What observable outcomes would convince you that the protocol helps loneliness rather than merely reducing posting, increasing compliance, or deepening dependence?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["comparative religion scholars", "comparative theologians", "interfaith ministers", "spiritual directors", "Buddhist teachers", "Advaita Vedanta teachers", "Christian pastoral counselors", "clinicians familiar with OCD, scrupulosity, rumination, grief, loneliness, and depression", "social-prescribing or community health practitioners", "stable cross-tradition practitioners"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["William James, The Varieties of Religious Experience, Project Gutenberg, https://www.gutenberg.org/files/621/621-h/621-h.html, read against Ignatius of Loyola, Spiritual Exercises, https://www.orderofthecommonlife.org/spiritual-exercises-full-text", "Dogen, Genjokoan, Aitken and Tanahashi translation, https://www.jasonong.com/5499, read against James and Ignatius as a practice-realization pressure case"], "risk_of_overread": "High if published as a discovery. Conduct-testing, fruits-testing, counsel, disclosure, practice-realization, social connection, and anti-checking are all established. The idea can overread loneliness as a source-confusion problem, or underread appropriation, power, and unsafe community risk. Human-condition fit is clearer than many recent records but narrow: stable lonely or digitally unmoored seekers, people facing meaning loss, feeling out of place, digital comparison, and achievement-contingent spiritual identity. It is not for unsafe relationships, abusive groups, acute grief crisis, OCD or scrupulosity, dissociation, mania, psychosis, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, medical concern, coercive workload, or cases where a teacher, clinician, or safeguarding pathway should hold the next step.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Read pastoral discernment and spiritual-direction literature directly, especially Ignatian discernment manuals, contemporary spiritual direction ethics, Buddhist teacher-student guidance, interfaith pastoral counseling, and religious appropriation ethics. Also read Wuthnow on seeking and practice-oriented spirituality, Roof and Bender on spiritual bricolage and lived spirituality, Pargament on religious coping, Turkle on digital conversation, Salkovskis and Rachman on checking and reassurance, social prescribing evidence, behavioral activation for social connectedness, and prior Lumenary records on translation strain, correction holders, and anti-overchecking.", "structural_observation": "James already separates origin from value and gives a fruits-over-roots test for religious life. Ignatius operationalizes a practitioner version: movements are discerned by where they lead, by timing, by desolation safeguards, and by disclosure to a competent spiritual person. Dogen adds a different enacted-test structure: realization is not certified before practice, it occurs in doing and returning to the place of practice. These sources strongly anticipate the contact-and-conduct side. The candidate's distinct move is not conduct-testing itself, but routing: source-first for public claim, contact-first for stable private orientation, then delayed provenance before teaching or identity authority."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.9, "novelty": 0.46, "source_reliability": 0.79}, "run_ids": [], "title": "Contact Before Claim", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Panikkar, Freiberger, Smith, Sandmel, Lindbeck, Asad, James, Ignatius, Dogen, Wuthnow, Turkle, social prescribing, anti-checking psychology, and recent Lumenary translation-strain records, this candidate's specific contribution is a two-track routing rule: borrowed language used as public doctrine or evidence must pass provenance and regeneration first, while borrowed language used privately by a stable lonely seeker should first be carried into safe contact and conduct so it does not become a substitute for belonging, repair, grief work, or help-seeking."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:84:{"agent": "claude", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "A person with strong external supports collapses more severely because those supports are coercive, shaming, unreliable, or tied to performance, while a strongly self-directed person recovers faster through restored agency, sleep, treatment, and practical problem solving.", "confidence_effect": "Keeps the status at extended and lowers practice confidence until support quality, agency history, clinical risk, and event magnitude are coded separately from continuity location.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "The model assumes externalized holding is protective for the target cohort. If support safety and agency restoration matter more than support location, the core variable is not where continuity sits but whether the holder is trustworthy, noncoercive, and actually available. This also catches the non-fit case: people harmed by denied agency may be injured by surrender language."}, "audit_id": "e30798c2dedf5eaa", "claim_units": ["Continuity can be located in self-command, body, routines, relationships, duty, faith, vows, or community.", "Performance-owned continuity should predict more total destabilization when performance fails.", "The useful intervention is preventative relocation of some steadiness outside self-command, not post-collapse control rebuilding.", "The broad comparative continuity rubric is already duplicated inside Lumenary and in external literature.", "No-gap teachings strain the continuity-across-a-threshold frame because there is no gap to carry continuity across.", "The human-condition fit is narrow: achievement-contingent self-worth and burnout collapse, not denied agency, abuse, acute crisis, or severe clinical distress."], "confidence": 0.78, "created_at": "2026-05-30T14:03:30+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "Organizational resilience and knowledge work", "prediction": "Teams, families, or care systems with distributed continuity before a disruption will recover faster and with less identity crisis than systems held mainly by one heroic performer, after controlling for disruption size and resources.", "structural_translation": "A system whose continuity is held by one performative node collapses harder when that node fails than a system whose continuity is distributed across routines, documentation, relationships, backups, and role redundancy.", "would_count_against_it": "Event magnitude, funding, staffing, and prior load explain recovery completely, and pre-break continuity distribution adds no measurable predictive value."}, "exact_claim": "For people whose steadiness and worth were held mostly by performance and self-command, collapse should be more total than for people whose continuity already lived partly in body, relationship, routine, duty, faith, or recovery support. The broad comparative claim about continuity after self-negation is old and overbuilt. The defensible contribution is a narrow person-level prediction plus a boundary condition: no-gap paths such as Dogen-style practice-realization should not be forced into a carry-across-a-threshold model.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-135009-20260530-135009", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Among people recovering from burnout, grief, caregiving overload, or early addiction recovery, those whose steadiness was mostly performance-owned should report more total destabilization than matched peers whose steadiness was distributed across relationships, routines, body, faith, duty, or recovery groups.", "if_model_is_right": "Pre-collapse continuity location is a real vulnerability variable.", "test_surface": "Prospective or retrospective coded interviews with burnout clinicians, recovery sponsors, chaplains, caregivers, founders, and high-achieving professionals.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Collapse severity is fully explained by sleep loss, trauma history, event magnitude, financial precarity, clinical diagnosis, and support quality, with no independent effect for continuity location."}, {"expected_observation": "Screened high-achievement participants using the practice for two weeks show reduced self-worth conversion, less grip, more concrete help-seeking or routine use, and no increase in helplessness or guilt compared with ordinary rest-and-ask-for-help and planning prompts.", "if_model_is_right": "The practice Name What Carries You addresses the named wound better than generic reflection.", "test_surface": "Small randomized pilot with achievement-contingent self-worth, burnout, rumination, help-seeking, shame, action completion, and adverse-effect measures.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The practice increases dependency, guilt, helplessness, self-monitoring, avoidance, or performs no better than ordinary social support and rest."}, {"expected_observation": "Dogen, Huangbo, and Dzogchen direct-recognition sources should not describe continuity as something carried across a before-after threshold; they should emphasize present practice, direct recognition, or search refusal instead.", "if_model_is_right": "The no-gap boundary is real.", "test_surface": "Split-source close reading of Bendowa, Genjokoan or Uji, Huangbo transmission texts, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out manual, and practitioner interviews.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Close reading finds robust threshold-carry language in no-gap sources, or practitioners report that continuity migration is a native teaching in those settings."}, {"expected_observation": "Blind readers can state the added variables: pre-collapse continuity location, collapse severity, and no-gap exclusion.", "if_model_is_right": "The new claim is distinguishable from the prior continuity cluster.", "test_surface": "Blind distinct-content coding of recent Lumenary continuity and support-holder records with titles removed.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Blind readers cannot distinguish this record from Continuity Ecology Under Negation, Operational Remainder Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, or Some Help Should Not Be Managed."}], "idea_id": "84b6d1547156a7e8", "idea_path": "observations/claude/2026-05-30-what-holds-you-that-you-did-not-build.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Pargament religious coping deferring collaborative self-directing coping styles", "Jack Engler you have to be somebody before you can be nobody spirituality psychology", "Clark Chalmers extended mind religious cognition Krueger religious cognition extended mind", "SN 45.8 Magga vibhanga right effort desire persistence intent translation", "Shinran Tannisho Other Power self power divergence teacher correction", "Dogen Bendowa practice realization shusho itto no gap practice realization one", "attachment theory secure base stress regulation social support review Bowlby secure base", "Linville self-complexity buffer stress depression mixed support", "Crocker Wolfe contingencies of self-worth achievement failure self-esteem", "Alcoholics Anonymous Twelve Steps power greater than ourselves social support recovery"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-what-holds-you-that-you-did-not-build-e30798c2dedf5eaa.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This candidate narrows the ambition to one person-level prediction about pre-collapse continuity location and adds a no-gap exclusion test.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. Treat as an extension and consolidation unless the collapse-severity prediction shows independent value.", "overlap": "Very close. The same variables recur: dissolution target, residue policy, support holder, receiving surface, failure mode, and a warning that the model is too elastic without split-source coding.", "source": "Internal Lumenary continuity cluster: Continuity Ecology Under Negation, Distributed Continuity Architecture, Continuity Location Under Transformative Practice, Operational Remainder Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, plus the candidate file observations/claude/2026-05-30-what-holds-you-that-you-did-not-build.md"}, {"difference": "The candidate widens the holder set beyond God to body, routine, relationship, duty, and prior promises, and predicts collapse severity in performance-owned lives.", "novelty_impact": "Strong reduction for support-locus originality, partial preservation for the burnout-specific prediction.", "overlap": "Very close on responsibility location. Self-directing, deferring, and collaborative coping already code whether the person, God, or a shared relation carries problem-solving.", "source": "Pargament et al., Religion and the Problem-Solving Process: Three Styles of Coping, 1988, indexed at https://icmglt.org/icmlibrary/religion-and-the-problem-solving-process-three-styles-of-coping/ and https://www.kennethpargament.com/rs-coping-measures-dev-gen-rel"}, {"difference": "The candidate translates extension into collapse vulnerability and practice design for achievement-contingent self-worth.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate to strong downgrade. The external-holder ontology is known; the practice-fit and collapse prediction are the local extension.", "overlap": "Close. External artifacts, language, culture, ritual, sacred spaces, songs, relics, and other persons can be part of cognition or religious cognition rather than merely background aids.", "source": "Clark and Chalmers, The Extended Mind, https://consc.net/papers/extended.html, and Joel Krueger, Extended Mind and Religious Cognition, https://philarchive.org/rec/KRUTEM-2"}, {"difference": "The candidate is not merely about attachment figures. It includes bodily rhythms, routines, vows, duties, faith, and recovery supports, and it asks about performance collapse.", "novelty_impact": "Strong reduction for the human kernel that steadiness is partly externally supported.", "overlap": "Close. A person's exploration and stress regulation are supported by reliable others who provide a safe haven and secure base.", "source": "Attachment secure-base literature, for example Feeney and Thrush on secure base support in adulthood, https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC2805473/, and Bowlby secure-base tradition indexed in attachment literature"}, {"difference": "The candidate targets non-addiction performance collapse and asks where continuity sat before the break, not only how recovery is held after admission of powerlessness.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade for surrender and externalized holding; partial novelty remains only if the pre-collapse-location measure predicts severity.", "overlap": "Close practitioner near-neighbor. AA explicitly externalizes recovery through a higher power, another human being, inventory, amends, service, meetings, and sponsorship-like community structures.", "source": "Alcoholics Anonymous official Twelve Steps, https://www.aa.org/the-twelve-steps, and AA social-network support literature such as https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC2289871/"}, {"difference": "The candidate adds a continuity-location and collapse-severity hypothesis rather than only self-esteem contingency or perfectionism trend.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. The wound is known; the proposed holder-map may be a useful practice-specific operationalization.", "overlap": "Close on the target wound. Self-worth can depend on success, achievement, approval, competition, appearance, family support, virtue, or divine love; perfectionism links self-worth to achievement and harsh evaluation.", "source": "Crocker and Wolfe contingencies of self-worth, summarized and tested in https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12144-020-01007-5, and Curran and Hill on rising perfectionism, https://eprints.lse.ac.uk/101352/1/Curran_Hill2018.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate uses Dogen not as support but as a boundary condition against overgeneralized continuity-across-threshold models.", "novelty_impact": "Useful boundary, but not a discovery. It prevents overreach more than it creates a new doctrine.", "overlap": "The no-gap anomaly is not new. Practice-realization unity is a known Soto Zen frame, and the literature already resists treating practice as a means to a later result.", "source": "Dogen shusho itto and Bendowa materials, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf and https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Cross-index with Continuity Ecology Under Negation, Operational Remainder Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, and Keep What Can Correct You.", "Build a bounded codebook with fields for pre-collapse continuity locus, support quality, agency history, collapse severity, clinical risk, event magnitude, sleep, trauma history, and repair path.", "Run the blind distinct-content test on the continuity cluster before generating another support-holder rubric.", "Close-read Dogen, Huangbo, Dzogchen, Shinran, and SN 45.8 for threshold-carry language versus present-act, vow-held, or effort-held language.", "Pilot Name What Carries You only with screened stable high performers and caregivers. Compare against ordinary rest, social support, and planning prompts.", "Add explicit stop rules for denied agency, coercion, spiritual abuse, severe depression, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, acute crisis, and cases where no real support is available."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.42 to 0.36. The broad structure is known through internal Lumenary rubrics, Pargament, extended mind, secure-base theory, AA, and self-worth research. Keep as an extended, testable person-level hypothesis only if pre-collapse continuity location and the no-gap exclusion add predictive power.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-what-holds-you-that-you-did-not-build-e30798c2dedf5eaa.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if clinicians and practitioners say the useful part is standard social support, secure-base work, recovery surrender, religious coping, self-complexity, or self-worth contingency work, and if the continuity-location code adds no prediction beyond support quality and clinical risk.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if practitioners can code pre-collapse continuity location reliably, if that code predicts severity or repair beyond ordinary supports, and if no-gap teachers confirm that the carry-across-threshold model is a category error in their setting.", "questions": ["In concrete collapse cases, do people whose identity was mainly performance-held collapse more totally than people whose continuity was already distributed?", "Is this just secure-base theory, religious coping, recovery surrender, and contingencies of self-worth in new language?", "Would the practice change what you recommend, or would ordinary rest, social support, therapy, and asking for help do the same work?", "Can you name cases where leaning on what the person did not build increased dependency, shame, helplessness, or exposure to unsafe authority?", "Do no-gap traditions you know reject the carry-across-threshold frame, or do they have native language for continuity being held across a shift?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["burnout clinicians", "occupational health researchers", "addiction recovery sponsors", "chaplains and pastoral caregivers", "Jodo Shinshu teachers or scholars", "Soto Zen teachers or scholars", "Theravada teachers", "attachment researchers", "perfectionism and self-worth researchers", "caregiver support practitioners"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Shinran, Tannisho, especially chapters 1, 3, 6, 8, and 11, https://jodoshinshu.faith/tannisho-a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/, read against SN 45.8 Magga-vibhanga Sutta, https://www.accesstoinsight.org/tipitaka/sn/sn45/sn45.008.than.html", "Dogen practice-realization as anomaly, using Bendowa excerpt https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and Soto Zen shusho itto note https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"], "risk_of_overread": "Moderate to high. Shinran's Vow is not merely psychological support, and SN 45.8 right effort is not simple self-command. The no-gap boundary could become too elastic if analysts say practice itself holds continuity in every case. Human-condition fit is real but narrow: it may help stable high performers, founders, caregivers, and perfectionists, but it can harm people whose wound is denied agency, coercive dependence, abusive religion, acute crisis, severe depression, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, or lack of actual support.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Before any stronger novelty claim, read Shinran scholarship on Other Power, hakarai, jinen, and Tannisho transmission; Dogen scholarship on shusho itto and honsho myoshu; Engler on self development before no-self work; Bowlby, Ainsworth, and adult secure-base literature; Linville and later mixed findings on self-complexity as a stress buffer; Crocker and Wolfe on contingencies of self-worth; Pargament on religious coping; AA social-network outcome literature; burnout and perfectionism studies; and practitioner-facing recovery and chaplaincy sources.", "structural_observation": "Tannisho relocates decisive efficacy away from self-powered practice and into Amida's Vow, while still preserving teacher, transmission, and warnings against divergent interpretation. SN 45.8 defines right effort through desire, persistence, intent, and maintenance of skillful qualities, so the practitioner remains an active support locus. The Soto shusho itto material says practice and realization are inseparable and that practice is necessary because realization is already present. This supports the candidate's boundary pressure: some sources contrast support loci, but Dogen does not describe a result carried over a before-after gap."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.9, "novelty": 0.36, "source_reliability": 0.82}, "run_ids": ["20260530-135009-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-135009-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "What Holds You That You Did Not Build", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Pargament's coping styles, extended mind, secure-base theory, AA surrender, contingencies of self-worth, and prior Lumenary continuity rubrics, this idea's specific contribution is to predict that pre-collapse continuity location will add explanatory value for burnout collapse severity, and to exclude no-gap practice-realization cases from a carry-across-threshold model."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:86:{"agent": "claude", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Rinzai koan and huatou practice deliberately uses an impossible or destabilizing question to create great doubt, while Dzogchen can deny path and result yet still require direct introduction, teacher relation, and integration.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence in a binary search-sequence versus search-refusal model. Raises confidence only for a more cautious codebook that includes search-refusal, question-as-medicine, no-distance-with-support, and undecidable.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If a path uses an apparently malformed question as medicine, then question-refusal is not enough to decide that remainder pressure is analyst-made. If no-path language still depends on transmission and repair holders, then the residue question may be relocated to practice ecology rather than abolished."}, "audit_id": "d756c9bf775096c6", "claim_units": ["Some contemplative paths stage a search sequence, so they generate a legitimate downstream remainder question.", "Some paths refuse the search sequence itself, so remainder pressure is malformed there.", "A precondition test should precede continuity, custody, or residue coding.", "The modern harm clarified is achievement-contingent self-worth turned into compulsive auditing for emptiness, detachment, or egolessness."], "confidence": 0.84, "created_at": "2026-05-30T14:21:04+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "psychotherapy and performance coaching", "prediction": "For stable clients using acceptance or values-based practices, asking how to prove acceptance will increase rumination and self-monitoring, while a permitted-question check followed by ordinary valued action will reduce over-control.", "structural_translation": "Some methods stage change as a sequence with a before and after, while acceptance-based or non-striving methods treat the attempt to prove change as part of the control agenda.", "would_count_against_it": "If outcomes are explained fully by trait rumination, therapist alliance, workload, sleep, or clinical risk, and permitted-question coding adds no predictive value."}, "exact_claim": "Before any continuity or residue analysis after self-negation, test whether the path stages self-negation as an event with an after. If a path refuses seeking, before-and-after, or self-owned attainment, the question of what remains may be an analyst artifact rather than a practitioner problem.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-140914-20260530-140914", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Blind coders using only doctrinal or instruction passages can sort cases into search-sequence, search-refusal, question-as-medicine, no-distance-with-support, and undecidable above chance before seeing warnings or repairs.", "if_model_is_right": "The precondition gate has independent coding value.", "test_surface": "Inter-rater coding on SN 22.59, SN 22.95, Huangbo, Bendowa, Tannisho, one Dzogchen direct-introduction source, and one Rinzai koan source.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders cannot agree, or their labels are just tradition labels, teacher style, or genre labels in disguise."}, {"expected_observation": "In search-sequence cases, warnings and repairs cluster around misidentification, clinging, effort, and post-release integration. In search-refusal cases, warnings cluster around seeking, monitoring, conceptualization, and self-grading.", "if_model_is_right": "Remainder pressure is not universal.", "test_surface": "Split-source coding, code path grammar from one corpus and predict held-out warnings, repairs, and practitioner failure cases.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Warnings and failures in search-refusal cases are predicted just as well by support-holder loss, teacher absence, trauma, sleep loss, or institutional harm without using the precondition gate."}, {"expected_observation": "Stable over-auditors using Stop the Emptiness Audit report less self-grading and faster return to ordinary care than journaling-only or rest-only controls, without increased avoidance or reassurance seeking.", "if_model_is_right": "The proposed practice serves only the named modern wound.", "test_surface": "Two-week pilot with screened perfectionistic meditators and self-improvers, excluding OCD, scrupulosity, dissociation, severe depression, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, trauma activation, and acute crisis.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The practice becomes a new checking ritual, increases avoidance of needed repair, worsens rumination, or performs no better than ordinary rest or social contact."}], "idea_id": "85484e1aff3c6503", "idea_path": "observations/claude/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Collingwood logic of question and answer every statement answer to a question hermeneutics", "Gadamer priority of the question hermeneutics Collingwood Truth and Method", "Huangbo Transmission of Mind no seeking using mind to seek Mind", "Dogen Bendowa practice realization one shusho itto practice verification", "Dzogchen no path no practice direct introduction teacher support", "spiritual bypassing self-monitoring meditation detachment empirical research"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This candidate makes a sharper precondition gate: does the path stage a negation event with an after at all?", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. Treat as a scope-condition extension of the no-custody and no-management cluster, not a standalone discovery.", "overlap": "These records already say some teachings reject separable result, ownership, management, and after-use framing, and that support holders must be coded before prescribing private review.", "source": "Internal Lumenary prior: When There Is Nothing To Keep Or Release, Not Every Practice Is a Tool, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, Even No Path Needs Care, and Operational Remainder Ecology, supplied in the prompt history"}, {"difference": "The candidate turns Huangbo's instruction into a comparative coding gate for residue analysis and a modern practice-safety rule.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for the core insight that the search itself can be the problem.", "overlap": "Huangbo already says seeking, conceptual road-making, and using mind to seek Mind are errors.", "source": "Huangbo, On the Transmission of Mind, https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a1-chun-chou-record.htm and https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a2-chun-chou-record-cont.htm"}, {"difference": "The candidate groups Dogen with search-refusal paths, but Dogen still insists on active, continuous practice.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade and anomaly pressure. Dogen supports the gate but resists any no-practice simplification.", "overlap": "Practice and realization are treated as inseparable, which already blocks a simple before-and-after result model.", "source": "Dogen Bendowa and Soto shusho itto, https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate applies that structure to contemplative self-negation and predicts practice failure from a malformed question.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. The formal logic is known; the remainder-gate application is the extension.", "overlap": "Collingwood already makes questions and presuppositions determine what counts as an answer.", "source": "Collingwood, Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/collingwood/"}, {"difference": "The candidate narrows this to a before-remainder audit for no-distance teachings.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade for the hermeneutic claim.", "overlap": "Gadamer already gives priority to the question in understanding and treats interpretation as situated application.", "source": "Gadamer, Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/gadamer/"}, {"difference": "The candidate isolates self-auditing for spiritual residue as a specific mismatch caused by importing a search grammar.", "novelty_impact": "Downgrades safety originality while preserving a narrower hypothesis for coding.", "overlap": "They already show that meditation effects, interpretations, management strategies, teacher relations, community, trauma history, and support influence outcomes.", "source": "VCE and Cheetah House, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239 and https://www.cheetahhouse.org/faq"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Cross-index with When There Is Nothing To Keep Or Release, Not Every Practice Is a Tool, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, Even No Path Needs Care, and The Question Can Make The Distance.", "Build a precondition codebook with values for search-sequence, search-refusal, no-distance-with-support, question-as-medicine, received-without-calculation, practice-realization, valid-solitude, unsafe-avoidance, clinical-routing, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.", "Use split-source coding. Do not let one passage both establish path grammar and confirm the predicted warning or repair.", "Add Rinzai koan practice and Dzogchen direct introduction as anomaly classes, not supporting examples.", "Run practitioner interviews for concrete over-auditing, avoidance, and repair cases. Do not ask only for agreement.", "For human-condition fit, keep the practice limited to stable over-managers and achievement-contingent self-worth. Exclude OCD, scrupulosity, dissociation, severe depression, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, trauma activation, medical blackout concerns, unsafe authority, and acute crisis."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.46 to 0.36. The core no-seeking and no-result logic is old in Huangbo, Dogen, Dzogchen, Shinran-adjacent no-calculation sources, and prior Lumenary no-management records. Retain as an extended precondition-gate hypothesis only if split-source coding shows predictive gain.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if practitioners say this is standard pedagogy under no-seeking, shusho itto, Other Power, direct introduction, koan great doubt, or ordinary spiritual-bypassing triage, and if the gate adds no decisions beyond existing teacher judgment.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if practitioners can use the gate to predict distinct failure modes and repairs before knowing outcomes, especially when it prevents over-managers from turning no-distance teachings into private self-audits.", "questions": ["Does your path stage a real search or negation event with an after, or does it refuse that staging?", "When students ask what remains after letting go, is that a valid practice question, a beginner misunderstanding, an advanced koan-like medicine, or a safety concern?", "Can you name concrete cases where auditing emptiness, detachment, or egolessness helped, and cases where it became spiritual performance or avoidance?", "Would the precondition gate change screening, sequencing, warnings, or repairs in your teaching setting?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Theravada teachers familiar with anatta investigation", "Soto Zen teachers and Dogen scholars", "Chan or Zen teachers familiar with Huangbo and Bankei", "Rinzai koan teachers", "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers", "Jodo Shinshu teachers for Other Power contrast", "meditation-safety clinicians and VCE researchers", "spiritual directors", "clinicians familiar with perfectionism, rumination, OCD, and scrupulosity"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["SN 22.59 and SN 22.95, dhammatalks.org, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html and https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_95.html", "Huangbo, On the Transmission of Mind, Blofeld translation hosted at https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a1-chun-chou-record.htm and https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a2-chun-chou-record-cont.htm, read with Dogen Bendowa excerpts at https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and Soto shusho itto note at https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"], "risk_of_overread": "High. The model can make search-refusal too clean. Huangbo taught through dialogue, Dogen built a practice institution, and Dzogchen no-path language often requires teacher transmission. The modern cohort is clear but narrow: stable over-managers and perfectionistic practitioners who audit their inner state. It is not for beginners needing inquiry, people using non-inquiry to avoid repair, OCD or scrupulosity, dissociation, severe depression, mania, psychosis, acute trauma, addiction withdrawal, or medical blackout concerns.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Search further in Collingwood on the logic of question and answer, Gadamer on the priority of the question, Asad on discursive tradition, Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar, Austin on felicity conditions, Sharf and Katz on contextualism, Dogen scholarship on shusho itto, Chan studies on Huangbo and Bankei, Dzogchen direct-introduction literature, VCE and Cheetah House safety literature, and spiritual bypassing research.", "structural_observation": "SN 22.59 and SN 22.95 explicitly authorize seeing, observing, examining, disenchantment, release, and the knowledge that the task is done. That is a staged investigative grammar. Huangbo repeatedly treats seeking Mind with mind, forming concepts of the Way, or making the Way into a road as the very distortion. Dogen's practice-realization unity blocks a simple cause-then-result reading, while Soto material also says Dogen emphasized active practice because realization is already present. The candidate's gate is textually plausible, but only if it codes the native practice grammar rather than broad tradition names."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.91, "novelty": 0.36, "source_reliability": 0.77}, "run_ids": ["20260530-140914-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-140914-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "Some Paths Refuse the Question of What Remains", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Huangbo, Dogen, Collingwood, Gadamer, VCE, and prior Lumenary no-management records, this idea's specific contribution is a precondition test before remainder coding: only ask what remains if the path first authorizes a self-negation event with an after."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:87:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Koan and huatou practice, plus Shinran's own reply to Senshin, show that a question may be deliberately used, answered, or transformed rather than simply permitted or refused.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence in the broad teaching line. Supports a narrower model with values for permitted question, refused question, transformed question, question-as-medicine, teacher-held question, and undecidable.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "A question that looks wrong from outside can be the authorized method inside a lineage. Also, Shinran refuses self-calculation while still answering doctrinal questions about cause, assurance, and entrusting. This strains any simple permitted versus refused coding."}, "audit_id": "30eeb13d9da3a2bc", "claim_units": ["A teaching permits some practitioner questions and refuses others.", "An imported question can create a false distance, such as attainment to prove, result to manage, or state to defend.", "Wrong-question imports should be coded before remainder, support, or completion models.", "The modern human-condition fit is burnout, loneliness, meaning loss, and achievement-contingent self-worth when practice becomes a private scoreboard."], "confidence": 0.86, "created_at": "2026-05-30T14:21:04+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "software incident response and organizational learning", "prediction": "Teams that first code the question being asked will produce more concrete system repairs and less defensive reporting than teams that move directly to what remains to fix or who owns the failure.", "structural_translation": "A blameless postmortem permits system and repair questions, while an imported ownership or blame question creates defensiveness and false distance from the event.", "would_count_against_it": "If postmortem quality is explained by psychological safety, manager behavior, severity, or process maturity, and question coding adds no measurable prediction."}, "exact_claim": "Before asking what remains after self-negation, identify the question the teaching permits. Carrying a crossing, ownership, or proof question into a no-distance, received, or non-self-owned teaching can create the distance, private performance, and failure pattern the teaching was meant to undo.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-140914-20260530-140914", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Blind coders can identify a source's permitted, refused, or transformed question before reading outcome passages, and those labels predict held-out warnings or repairs better than sentence-role, support-holder, tradition label, or VCE-factor baselines alone.", "if_model_is_right": "The imported-question variable is real and separable from prior models.", "test_surface": "A/B inter-rater coding on SN 22.59, SN 22.95, Shinran letters, Tannisho, Bendowa, Huangbo, Dzogchen direct introduction, and Rinzai koan materials.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders need outcome passages to infer the question, cannot agree, or the variable adds no predictive power beyond existing source-role and correction-holder rubrics."}, {"expected_observation": "Dual-trained practitioners report that carrying a crossing or proof question into no-distance or Other Power settings increases self-grading, private certainty, defensiveness, or withdrawal, while carrying a repair question into ethical-return contexts increases responsibility and reachability.", "if_model_is_right": "Wrong-question imports create distinctive practitioner failures.", "test_surface": "Structured practitioner interviews asking for concrete failed-student and repair cases, not agreement with the wording.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Failures track trauma, isolation, sleep, teacher harm, intensity, or institutional culture better than imported question type."}, {"expected_observation": "Question Before Distance reduces proof-seeking and self-surveillance after quiet states more than ordinary journaling, while increasing ordinary action and willingness to receive correction.", "if_model_is_right": "The practice candidate has a bounded benefit.", "test_surface": "Four-arm pilot with screened stable practitioners: question check, journaling, rest-and-plan, and ordinary support prompt.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "It increases rumination, shame, avoidance, isolation, reassurance seeking, or performs no better than rest, honest conversation, or a simple social-support prompt."}], "idea_id": "80ffd9a12a5c96e3", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Collingwood logic of question and answer presuppositions spiritual practice", "Gadamer priority of the question understanding application hermeneutics", "Austin felicity conditions performative utterance religious language practice", "Lindbeck doctrine grammar religion practice training rules", "Asad discursive tradition correct form purpose practice authority", "wrong question spiritual bypassing meditation self improvement burnout"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This candidate isolates the imported practitioner question as the first failure variable before post-negation remainder coding.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. Merge unless a blind distinct-content test shows the question variable changes decisions.", "overlap": "These records already require coding sentence role, source role, authority, repair, and whether a question or method has become judge.", "source": "Internal Lumenary prior: First Ask What the Words Do, When Tools Become Judges, No Word Travels Alone, Stop When The Repair Changes, and Some Paths Refuse The Question Of What Remains from this batch"}, {"difference": "The candidate moves from philosophical interpretation to practitioner failure prediction after contemplative insight.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for the structural claim; extension remains in the practice-safety application.", "overlap": "Collingwood already holds that propositions function as answers to questions and that presuppositions give rise to questions.", "source": "R. G. Collingwood, logic of question and answer, Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/collingwood/"}, {"difference": "The candidate operationalizes the imported question as a codeable mismatch in no-distance and received paths.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade.", "overlap": "Gadamer already emphasizes the priority of the question, historically effected understanding, application, and the way prejudgments open and distort interpretation.", "source": "Hans-Georg Gadamer, philosophical hermeneutics, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/gadamer/"}, {"difference": "The candidate applies felicity-like conditions to spiritual questions, not only utterances, and predicts self-surveillance failures.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. The analogy is useful but not original as language-action theory.", "overlap": "Austin already shows that utterances do things only under fitting procedures, participants, and circumstances, and can misfire when conditions are wrong.", "source": "J. L. Austin, How to Do Things with Words, https://web.english.upenn.edu/~cavitch/pdf-library/Austin_How_To_Do_Things_with_Words.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate narrows correct form and purpose to the practitioner's initiating question after self-negation.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for the tradition-held permission claim.", "overlap": "Asad already treats tradition as discourse instructing practitioners about correct form and purpose, with authority and correction internal to practice.", "source": "Talal Asad, The Idea of an Anthropology of Islam, https://voidnetwork.gr/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/The-Idea-of-an-Anthropology-of-Islam-by-Talal-Asad.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate predicts a specific modern failure when a self-owned completion question violates that grammar.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade; retain only as empirical-practice extension.", "overlap": "Lindbeck already makes doctrine a rule or grammar regulating religious speech and practice.", "source": "George Lindbeck cultural-linguistic doctrine-as-grammar summaries, https://people.bu.edu/wwildman/bce/mwt_themes_862_lindbeck.htm and https://scielo.org.za/scielo.php?pid=S2074-77052018000100007&script=sci_arttext"}, {"difference": "The candidate distinguishes wrong-question imports from general avoidance or adverse-event factors.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade and important baseline for tests.", "overlap": "These already identify spiritual language and practice as ways to avoid unfinished psychological or relational work, and show that interpretation and management influence meditation difficulties.", "source": "Spiritual bypassing and VCE safety sources, https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/19349637.2017.1417756 and https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Cross-index or merge with Some Paths Refuse The Question Of What Remains, First Ask What The Words Do, When Tools Become Judges, No Word Travels Alone, Stop When The Repair Changes, and Some Help Should Not Be Managed.", "Build a question-permission codebook with values for crossing, receiving, enacting, repairing, waiting, refusing ownership, question-as-medicine, teacher-held question, no-question frame, unsafe-question, clinical-routing, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.", "Run a blind distinct-content test against Some Paths Refuse The Question Of What Remains. Merge if readers cannot state the difference between precondition gate and imported-question failure variable.", "Use split-source coding and do not let the same passage establish permitted question and confirm the predicted warning or repair.", "Add koan practice, Shinran doctrinal Q&A, and valid solitude as anomaly cases before public use.", "For human-condition fit, keep the practice narrow: stable over-managers, burned-out self-improvers, and perfectionistic practitioners. Exclude acute loneliness without support, OCD, scrupulosity, dissociation, psychosis, mania, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, unsafe authority, medical concern, and cases requiring direct accountability or clinical care."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.57 to 0.39. The structural logic is heavily anticipated by Collingwood, Gadamer, Austin, Asad, Lindbeck, spiritual-bypassing research, VCE, and local Lumenary sentence-role and no-management records. Preserve as an extended test protocol only if the imported-question field predicts failures and repairs beyond those baselines.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if practitioners say every tradition already teaches this as right question, right view, proper intention, doctrine as grammar, spiritual direction, or koan pedagogy, and if the question field fails to change real screening or repair decisions.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if practitioners can identify wrong-question imports as a recurring failure pattern, use the distinction before seeing outcomes, and show repairs that differ from generic rest, social contact, or teacher correction.", "questions": ["What question does this teaching allow the practitioner to ask at this stage?", "What question commonly causes harm, spiritual performance, or withdrawal in your setting?", "Can you name cases where changing the question changed the repair, rather than merely changing language?", "Is this just hermeneutics, doctrine-as-grammar, spiritual direction, or ordinary teacher judgment in new terms?", "Would this codebook predict warnings or repairs before knowing the outcome?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Soto Zen teachers", "Rinzai koan teachers", "Jodo Shinshu teachers and scholars", "Theravada insight teachers", "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers", "spiritual directors", "comparative theologians", "religion scholars familiar with Asad and Lindbeck", "VCE researchers and meditation-safety clinicians", "clinicians familiar with burnout, perfectionism, rumination, OCD, and scrupulosity"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["SN 22.59, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html, read against Shinran's reply to Senshin, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/", "Dogen Bendowa excerpts and Soto shusho itto, https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf, read against Huangbo, https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a2-chun-chou-record-cont.htm"], "risk_of_overread": "Moderate to high. The model can collapse hermeneutics, speech-act theory, doctrine-as-grammar, and spiritual-bypassing triage into Lumenary language. It can also make permitted-question coding too subtle for reliable use. Human-condition fit is plausible for stable over-managers, burned-out self-improvers, isolated app meditators, caregivers, founders, and students. It is not for acute loneliness without support, clinical rumination, OCD or scrupulosity, dissociation, psychosis, mania, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, unsafe teacher settings, or cases needing direct accountability.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Read Collingwood, Gadamer, Austin, Searle, Asad, Lindbeck, Sharf, Katz, Pargament, spiritual bypassing research, VCE, Cheetah House, Pure Land studies on hakarai and Other Power, Dogen scholarship on practice-realization, and koan curriculum scholarship by Hori or Rinzai specialists before raising novelty.", "structural_observation": "SN 22.59 permits a disciplined question sequence: is this aggregate controllable, permanent, easeful, fit to regard as mine, self, or what I am? Shinran answers a doctrinal question by refusing calculation on the practicer and relocating assurance to Other Power. Dogen blocks separation of cultivation and realization, while still warning against clever slogans and requiring practice. Huangbo explicitly challenges the question What is the Way and how must it be followed? The candidate's strongest form is not that questions are bad, but that each source licenses a different question grammar with different failure modes."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.92, "novelty": 0.39, "source_reliability": 0.79}, "run_ids": ["20260530-140914-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-140914-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "The Question Can Make the Distance", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Collingwood, Gadamer, Austin, Asad, Lindbeck, spiritual-bypassing research, and prior Lumenary sentence-role records, this idea predicts that the practitioner's imported question itself is a codeable failure variable that can create post-insight distance before any remainder question is asked."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:88:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Structured self-review can be valid and beneficial: Ignatian Examen, Stoic evening review, monastic confession preparation, mood tracking in measurement-based care, early meditation logs, and CBT homework can increase accountability, learning, and repair.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence in any general no-audit teaching. Supports a narrower delivery-location protocol: withhold repeated self-scoring grids from over-auditors unless bounded, externally held, and empirically shown not to increase checking, shame, avoidance, or reassurance seeking.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If repeated self-review helps high achievers when it is time-limited, compassionate, action-linked, and sometimes guided, then the backstage rule is too broad. The real variable may be not grid versus no grid, but scoring, frequency, clinical risk, guidance, interpretation, and whether the act becomes a compulsion. A second anomaly is avoidance: doing one ordinary act can become a way to dodge grief, confession, moral repair, relational accountability, or needed clinical care."}, "audit_id": "c0163823ff1f73cb", "claim_units": ["Recurring practice self-audit can harm achievement-driven people when it becomes proof of worth.", "A diagnostic grid can be useful backstage for a teacher, clinician, designer, or community while being harmful as a repeated frontstage worksheet.", "The safer user-facing form is a non-scoring transition into observable conduct.", "After-use reflection needs path, disposition, and effect gates.", "The human-condition target is narrow: achievement-contingent self-worth, burnout, perfectionism, rumination, and compulsive self-monitoring."], "confidence": 0.85, "created_at": "2026-05-30T14:47:15+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "software incident response and workplace performance review", "prediction": "Teams that keep detailed incident diagnostics backstage with leads while giving contributors one concrete repair or learning action will show less defensive reporting, less burnout-linked self-blame, fewer duplicate meta-meetings, and equal or better repair completion than teams requiring repeated individual reflection grids after every incident or performance miss.", "structural_translation": "Complex diagnostic taxonomies may help incident leads, managers, coaches, or system designers, while repeated individual self-scoring can create defensive performance identity. The frontstage form should often be one concrete repair, handoff, or re-entry behavior rather than another private worth audit.", "would_count_against_it": "If outcomes are explained by manager trust, workload, severity, compensation incentives, team maturity, psychological safety, or process quality, and delivery location adds no measurable prediction."}, "exact_claim": "For achievement-driven people, recurring self-audits about practice are often unsafe. The diagnostic grid should usually remain with teachers, designers, clinicians, communities, or one-time setup. The user-facing form should be brief and behavioral: name the tool lightly, stop making it proof of worth, and perform one ordinary re-entry act. After-use reflection is appropriate only when the path is staged, the person is not caught in compulsive checking, and the check does not increase rumination, shame, avoidance, reassurance seeking, or tool-performance anxiety.", "execution_id": "dialogue-538ea14788624f07", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "In screened achievement-driven participants, maxim-plus-act and behavior-only re-entry conditions reduce rumination, shame, tool-performance anxiety, and reassurance seeking more than a repeated After-Use Check, while producing equal or better ordinary action completion within 24 hours.", "if_model_is_right": "Backstage diagnostic structure plus frontstage maxim-and-act is safer than repeated self-administered grids for over-auditors.", "test_surface": "Four-arm pilot: repeated After-Use Check, behavior-only re-entry, maxim-plus-act without rating, and ordinary journaling or usual practice.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The full self-audit performs as well or better without increased checking or shame, or effects are explained by baseline OCD risk, perfectionism, sleep, workload coercion, social support, therapist alliance, or teacher contact."}, {"expected_observation": "Blind coders can identify delivery location, backstage holder, frontstage burden, scoring, frequency, and re-entry act from intervention descriptions, and these fields predict safety outcomes beyond path type, support holder, clinical risk, and tradition label.", "if_model_is_right": "Delivery location is separable from prior Lumenary custody, support-holder, and no-audit models.", "test_surface": "Inter-rater codebook trial on Lumenary practices plus CBT formulation, ACT exercises, ERP anti-checking rules, Examen, Soto instruction, Pure Land guidance, and MBCT homework.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders cannot distinguish delivery location from support holder or custody, or the field adds no predictive power over prior codebooks."}, {"expected_observation": "Participants high in contingent self-worth, socially prescribed perfectionism, and reassurance seeking show the largest adverse response to self-rating grids; participants low on these traits or under guided review show less harm or benefit.", "if_model_is_right": "The harm mechanism is worth-conversion, not reflection itself.", "test_surface": "Moderation analysis using validated measures of perfectionism, contingent self-worth, rumination, reassurance seeking, burnout, and action completion.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Adverse response does not interact with contingent self-worth, perfectionism, OCD or scrupulosity risk, guidance, scoring, or frequency."}, {"expected_observation": "Teachers, clinicians, and spiritual directors report holding complex distinctions privately while giving vulnerable students simpler conduct, rest, relational, or support instructions, and they can name cases where giving the full grid caused self-surveillance or shame.", "if_model_is_right": "Practitioners already distinguish private diagnostic formulation from public instruction in concrete cases.", "test_surface": "Structured interviews asking for concrete failed-student cases and repairs, not agreement with the slogan.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Practitioners routinely give full grids without harm, or decisions are fully explained by teacher style, tradition, clinical severity, or institutional norms."}], "idea_id": "8fcf92afeb5b6615", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-30-the-grid-stays-backstage.md", "literature_search_queries": ["therapist formulation versus client homework self monitoring rumination checking OCD scrupulosity", "CBT case formulation guides clinical decisions client action plan homework", "behavioral activation rumination cues action activity scheduling depression", "ACT values committed action defusion psychological flexibility health behavior change", "mood as input stop rules worry checking rumination perfectionism", "scrupulosity OCD reassurance seeking exposure response prevention religious rituals avoidance", "measurement based care mood monitoring self monitoring adverse events anxiety burden", "Ignatian Examen scrupulosity spiritual direction excessive self examination", "Dogen practice realization no gaining Bendowa shusho itto", "Shinran hakarai calculation Other Power Tannisho self power", "VCE meditation-related challenges interpretation management strategies teacher support", "instructional scaffolding teacher support fading student metacognition"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-grid-stays-backstage-c0163823ff1f73cb.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This candidate adds administrability as the explicit variable: backstage diagnostic grid versus frontstage maxim plus observable act.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade. Treat as an extension of the existing cluster unless blind readers can distinguish delivery location from support holder, custody, and no-audit fields.", "overlap": "The cluster already contains after-use checks, no-audit gates, path preconditions, holder routing, tool-as-judge warnings, and safety screens for perfectionism, rumination, scrupulosity, burnout, and achievement-contingent self-worth.", "source": "Internal Lumenary records: The Road Must Know Its End, Some Paths Refuse the Question of What Remains, When Tools Become Judges, Not Every Check Should Be Yours, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, Stop When Time Is Up, The Question Can Make The Distance, local files in observations and reviews."}, {"difference": "The candidate applies a similar formulation-to-homework distinction to spiritual practice and says repeated self-use of the grid may be harmful for achievement-driven users.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for the backstage diagnostic idea. Possible extension remains in cross-tradition practice routing.", "overlap": "Case formulation already functions as a clinician-held model that guides decisions not directly specified by generic treatment manuals.", "source": "Persons and Tompkins, case formulation-driven CBT, Beck Institute summary, https://beckinstitute.org/blog/developing-and-using-a-case-formulation-to-guide-cognitive-behavior-therapy/"}, {"difference": "The candidate adds a warning that even spiritual or therapeutic tools can become worth-proof, and proposes a non-scoring re-entry act for a specific cohort.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. The practical frontstage move is close to ACT, but the delivery-location test is more specific.", "overlap": "ACT already emphasizes defusion, acceptance, values, and committed action instead of trying to replace or prove internal states.", "source": "Acceptance and Commitment Therapy for health behavior change, https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/psychology/articles/10.3389/fpsyg.2017.02350/full"}, {"difference": "The candidate spiritualizes the same move around after-use of insight and practice tools.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for behavior-only re-entry. Retain only as an applied spiritual-practice safety rule.", "overlap": "Behavioral activation already moves clients from rumination loops toward scheduled, observable action and uses monitoring only to identify avoidance patterns.", "source": "Behavioral activation and rumination-focused CBT, including rumination cues action formulations, https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Behavioral_activation"}, {"difference": "The candidate applies anti-checking logic to nonclinical spiritual over-auditors while requiring clinical exclusions.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for the safety mechanism. Contribution depends on careful cohort screening and avoiding clinical overreach.", "overlap": "ERP and scrupulosity work already identify checking, self-reassurance, confession, religious ritualizing, avoidance, and reassurance seeking as patterns that can be maintained by attempts to secure certainty.", "source": "Exposure and response prevention for OCD and scrupulosity, including common ERP pitfalls, https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC3423997/, and scrupulosity review, https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S2211364914000116"}, {"difference": "The candidate proposes an external delivery rule: do not give over-auditors a repeating self-completion grid; give a limited re-entry act.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate to strong downgrade. The stop-rule structure is known; the spiritual delivery application is the extension.", "overlap": "This literature already shows that stop rules shape perseverative thought, including rumination and worry, and that subjective completion criteria can prolong cognition.", "source": "Mood-as-input and stop-rule research on worry and rumination, including Fisak et al., https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0005791617301295"}, {"difference": "The candidate names a spiritual analogue: a practice grid can become continuous self-management and worth surveillance.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. This is a known digital and clinical design problem in religious-practice language.", "overlap": "Repeated monitoring can be useful for care and research, but qualitative and review literature reports burden, fixation, distress, subjective mood worsening, and anxiety in some users.", "source": "Mood monitoring, ambulatory assessment, and self-monitoring adverse-event literature, https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12548826/, https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12533931/"}, {"difference": "The candidate does not reject review universally. It says review is safe only under conditions and may need a holder or non-scoring translation for over-auditors.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade and important anomaly. A blanket backstage rule would be false because structured self-review can be central and beneficial.", "overlap": "The Examen is an established structured review practice with presence, gratitude, review, reflection, and looking ahead.", "source": "Ignatian Examen, Saint Joseph's University, https://www.sju.edu/offices/mission/ignatian-resources/examen"}, {"difference": "The candidate connects this to the danger that a diagnostic grid becomes a spiritual self-worth instrument for high achievers.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. The teaching-design principle is old; the modern harm channel is the extension.", "overlap": "Pedagogy already distinguishes expert-held diagnosis, adapted instruction, scaffolding, fading, and capacity-sensitive teaching.", "source": "Buddhist upaya and instructional scaffolding, including teacher-student adaptive support, https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10648-010-9127-6, and upaya pedagogy sources such as https://taojiangscholar.com/papers/Dilemma_of_Skillful_Means_in_Buddhist_Pedagogy.pdf"}, {"difference": "The candidate isolates one design factor, whether the interpretive grid is self-administered or held by care structures.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. It should be tested as one variable within the larger VCE-style context model.", "overlap": "These sources already show that meditation effects depend on interpretation, management strategy, practitioner factors, practice factors, relationships, health behaviors, and support.", "source": "VCE and Cheetah House meditation safety sources, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239, https://www.cheetahhouse.org/faq"}, {"difference": "These sources do not supply the spiritual-practice grid distinction, but they explain why the cohort is vulnerable to turning reflection into performance.", "novelty_impact": "Supports publishability for a narrow cohort, not originality.", "overlap": "The target wound is well supported: rising perfectionism, socially prescribed worth pressure, exhaustion, distance, and reduced efficacy.", "source": "Modern human-condition sources: Curran and Hill on rising perfectionism, https://researchonline.lse.ac.uk/id/eprint/101352/1/Curran_Hill2018.pdf, and WHO burn-out definition, https://www.who.int/standards/classifications/frequently-asked-questions/burn-out-an-occupational-phenomenon"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery or doctrine. Cross-index with The Road Must Know Its End, Some Paths Refuse The Question Of What Remains, When Tools Become Judges, Not Every Check Should Be Yours, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, Stop When Time Is Up, and The Question Can Make The Distance.", "Rename the contribution as a delivery-location protocol for over-auditors: backstage grid, frontstage re-entry act.", "Build a small codebook with fields for target cohort, backstage holder, frontstage burden, scoring or no-scoring, check frequency, path gate, disposition gate, re-entry act, contraindication, warning, repair, evidence passage, and confidence.", "Run a blind distinct-content test against prior Lumenary after-use, no-audit, support-holder, and question-permission records. Merge if readers cannot state the added administrability variable without prompting.", "Use split-source or split-data testing. Do not let the same practitioner case establish the backstage rule and confirm the predicted repair.", "Pilot only with screened stable high performers, caregivers, students, founders, app meditators, and burned-out self-improvers. Exclude OCD or scrupulosity without ERP-informed care, severe depression, mania, psychosis, dissociation, trauma activation, addiction withdrawal, unsafe authority, coercive workload, under-reflection, and cases requiring moral repair or clinical care.", "Compare against baselines: ACT values prompt, behavioral activation activity scheduling, ordinary journaling, timeboxing, ERP-informed no-check instruction, spiritual-direction check-in, measurement-based care, and rest-and-plan prompt.", "Track rumination, shame, reassurance seeking, tool-performance anxiety, avoidance, missed duties, ordinary action within one hour and 24 hours, willingness to receive correction, and whether conduct prompts bypass needed inquiry."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.57 to 0.34. The mechanisms are strongly anticipated by internal Lumenary records, CBT formulation, ACT committed action, behavioral activation, ERP anti-checking logic, mood-as-input stop rules, mood-monitoring safety research, Ignatian Examen, upaya, scaffolding, VCE, and meditation-safety work. Preserve as an extended delivery-location synthesis only if backstage/frontstage coding predicts harms and benefits beyond support holder, custody, path grammar, clinical risk, and generic simplification.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-grid-stays-backstage-c0163823ff1f73cb.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if practitioners say this is routine formulation, ordinary spiritual direction, response prevention, scaffolding, upaya, or product simplification, and if delivery location does not change screening, instruction, repair, or outcome decisions beyond those frameworks.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if practitioners can identify cases where the same grid was useful for the holder but harmful for the practitioner, can predict failure before outcome passages, and can show repairs that differ from generic simplify the worksheet advice.", "questions": ["Do you keep a diagnostic grid or formulation privately while giving the practitioner a simpler action?", "When have worksheets, practice logs, spiritual self-examination, or reflection prompts increased checking, shame, reassurance seeking, spiritual pride, or avoidance?", "What concrete signs tell you to stop self-audit and route the person to conduct, rest, relationship, teacher guidance, fixed rule, or clinical care?", "Is this just case formulation, response prevention, values-based action, behavioral activation, spiritual direction, upaya, or scaffolding in new terms?", "Would the backstage/frontstage distinction change a real instruction for a high-achieving over-manager?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["CBT clinicians using case formulation", "ACT therapists", "behavioral activation clinicians", "ERP clinicians familiar with OCD and scrupulosity", "MBCT and metacognitive therapy teachers", "spiritual directors familiar with Ignatian Examen and scrupulosity", "Soto Zen teachers", "Jodo Shinshu ministers", "Theravada or insight meditation teachers", "VCE or Cheetah House meditation-safety clinicians", "burnout and perfectionism researchers", "mental-health product designers and UX researchers"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["Dogen, Bendowa excerpts, https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf, read against Shinran's reply to Senshin, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/", "MN 22 raft simile, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html, read against the Ignatian Examen, https://www.sju.edu/offices/mission/ignatian-resources/examen"], "risk_of_overread": "High. The idea can rename common clinical and pastoral practice: therapist formulation versus client homework, response prevention for checking, values-based committed action, behavioral activation, scaffolding, upaya, and spiritual direction. Human-condition fit is direct but narrow. It is for stable high performers, students, founders, caregivers, app meditators, and burned-out self-improvers whose practice becomes a verdict on worth. It is not for severe depression, mania, psychosis, dissociation, OCD or scrupulosity without ERP-informed care, trauma activation, addiction withdrawal, unsafe authority settings, coercive workloads, under-reflection, or cases needing moral repair, medical care, or ordinary accountability.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Before publication, read full sources in CBT case formulation, ACT, behavioral activation, rumination-focused CBT, MBCT, metacognitive therapy, mood-as-input stop-rule research, ERP and scrupulosity, spiritual direction ethics, Ignatian discernment, upaya pedagogy, Dogen practice-realization scholarship, Pure Land hakarai and Other Power scholarship, VCE, Cheetah House, measurement-based care, and self-monitoring reactivity.", "structural_observation": "MN 22 supports after-use discipline: a method can be held for crossing and not carried afterward as a burden. Ignatian Examen supports structured review as a legitimate practice, but it frames review as prayer, discernment, gratitude, and concrete amendment rather than private worth-scoring. Dogen strains the tool-result assumption by making cultivation and realization inseparable and warning against clever slogans, while Shinran strains practitioner-owned audit by rejecting calculation in Other Power. The candidate's strongest contribution is not the idea that practices need guidance, or that checking can harm. Those are old. The possible addition is delivery location: the same diagnostic grid may belong backstage as a care-holder's lens, while the practitioner receives only a minimal re-entry act."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.92, "novelty": 0.34, "source_reliability": 0.78}, "run_ids": [], "title": "The Grid Stays Backstage", "unlike_statement": "Unlike CBT formulation, ACT, behavioral activation, ERP, mood-as-input stop rules, mood-monitoring safety research, Ignatian Examen, upaya, scaffolding, VCE, and prior Lumenary after-use records, this idea claims that diagnostic-grid location is itself a testable variable: backstage for care holders and designers, frontstage only as a brief non-scoring re-entry act for achievement-driven over-auditors."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:90:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Rinzai koan and huatou practice, where a destabilizing or impossible question can be the authorized medicine, plus cases where ordinary loneliness needs contact rather than a better question.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence in any simple three-gate checklist. Supports a more complex codebook with question-as-medicine, teacher-held question, no-question frame, clinical routing, ordinary-contact routing, and undecidable.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "A question that looks malformed or harmful outside the lineage may be precisely the path's method inside a teacher-held container. Conversely, a question that passes textual permission can still be useless when the real wound is isolation, sleep debt, coercive work, trauma, or clinical rumination."}, "audit_id": "6c82ef9b2db9c563", "claim_units": ["Deep questions are not automatically beneficial.", "A source or path licenses some questions and refuses or transforms others.", "Correction support is part of whether a question can be safely used.", "The person's wound or cohort fit determines whether the question helps or harms.", "The modern target is burnout, loneliness, meaning loss, anxious overinterpretation, and achievement-contingent self-worth among stable reflective practitioners."], "confidence": 0.87, "created_at": "2026-05-30T15:08:01+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "clinical intake and education", "prediction": "Students or clients given a fit-gated reflection prompt will show more concrete next actions and less rumination than those given an abstractly deep prompt, especially among perfectionistic high performers.", "structural_translation": "A powerful question or assessment task is helpful only when the method permits it, a competent holder can correct misreadings, and it fits the learner or patient's actual problem.", "would_count_against_it": "If outcomes are fully explained by facilitator skill, relationship quality, workload, sleep, or baseline anxiety, and question-source-wound coding adds no measurable prediction."}, "exact_claim": "A self-negating question is teachable only when it passes three gates: the source permits the question, healthy correction can hold the answer, and the question serves the person's actual wound rather than turning practice into private performance or self-audit.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-145302-20260530-145302", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Blind coders can identify source-permitted question, correction holder, and non-fit wound from source and context data before seeing warnings, and those labels predict held-out repair instructions better than tradition label, support-holder-only, or VCE-factor baselines.", "if_model_is_right": "The three gates add predictive value beyond generic good judgment.", "test_surface": "Split-source inter-rater coding across SN 22.59, MN 2, MN 22, Huangbo, Bendowa, Tannisho or Shinran letters, Dzogchen direct introduction, and Rinzai koan sources.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders cannot agree, need outcome passages to infer the gates, or the model adds no prediction beyond teacher style, social ecology, clinical risk, sleep loss, or ordinary support."}, {"expected_observation": "The Question Fit Check reduces proof-seeking, self-surveillance, shame, and withdrawal, and increases ordinary action and willingness to receive correction more than attainment journaling.", "if_model_is_right": "Question-fit screening helps stable over-auditors more than another attainment review.", "test_surface": "Four-arm pilot with screened stable practitioners: question-fit check, ordinary journaling, rest-and-plan, and social-support prompt.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Ordinary rest, conversation, behavioral activation, or social-support prompts work as well or better, or the check becomes another ritualized audit."}, {"expected_observation": "Importing a proof question into no-distance or Other Power settings predicts self-grading and defensiveness, while importing a no-question stance into investigation or repair settings predicts avoidance and missed accountability.", "if_model_is_right": "Different path grammars and wounds produce different failure clusters.", "test_surface": "Practitioner interviews coded for concrete failed-student cases, wrong-question import, wound, repair, and outcome.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Failure clusters are similar across path types, or are better explained by trauma history, isolation, coercion, unsafe teachers, sleep loss, or clinical risk."}], "idea_id": "378f83632320c050", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-30-the-question-must-fit-the-wound.md", "literature_search_queries": ["MN 2 appropriate attention inappropriate self questions spiritual practice", "MN 22 water snake raft simile wrong grasp dhamma", "Collingwood logic of question and answer presuppositions fit for purpose", "Gadamer priority of the question application practical context", "upaya skillful means teaching according to capacity needs", "VCE Progress or Pathology meditation challenges intervention criteria teacher resources", "spiritual bypassing psychological wounds avoidance spiritual practice"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-must-fit-the-wound-6c82ef9b2db9c563.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This candidate compresses the cluster into three gates: source permission, correction support, and wound fit.", "novelty_impact": "Major internal downgrade. Treat as consolidation unless blind readers can state a separable predictive variable.", "overlap": "Very close. These records already code permitted questions, no-distance paths, support holders, over-auditing risk, target cohort, and clinical exclusions.", "source": "Internal Lumenary priors: The Question Can Make The Distance, Some Paths Refuse The Question Of What Remains, Even No Path Needs Care, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, and The Grid Stays Backstage"}, {"difference": "The candidate generalizes the structure across traditions and adds modern wound and correction-holder gates.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for source-permission and right-grasp logic.", "overlap": "Very close. MN 2 already says some questions are unfit attention, while MN 22 warns that a teaching wrongly grasped can harm and rightly grasped can carry one across.", "source": "MN 2 Sabbasava Sutta and MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN2.html and https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html"}, {"difference": "The candidate turns capacity-sensitive teaching into a pre-use audit for self-negating questions and modern self-audit wounds.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade. The wound-fit principle is largely old as skillful means.", "overlap": "Close. Upaya already says teaching and behavior are adapted to the unique needs and capacities of beings, with the Buddha compared to a physician prescribing treatment.", "source": "Upaya-kaushalya, Encyclopedia of Buddhism, https://encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Upaya-kaushalya"}, {"difference": "The candidate applies that hermeneutic logic to practice safety and predicts harm from malformed contemplative questions.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. Formal question-fit is known; the contemplative safety application is the extension.", "overlap": "Close formal near-neighbor. Collingwood's logic of question and answer treats presuppositions as what give rise to questions, and explanations conflict only when answering the same question.", "source": "Collingwood, Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/collingwood/"}, {"difference": "The candidate operationalizes application as a three-gate practice test for self-negating questions.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade for hermeneutic novelty.", "overlap": "Close. Gadamer emphasizes the priority of the question, practical context, and application as part of understanding from the beginning.", "source": "Gadamer, Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/gadamer/"}, {"difference": "The candidate narrows those variables to the initiating question after self-negation.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for safety and support originality. Retain only if question-fit adds prediction beyond VCE-style factors.", "overlap": "Very close on support and wound fit. These studies separate phenomenology, interpretation, management, practitioner factors, practice factors, relationships, health behaviors, teacher skills or resources, functional impairment, and need for intervention.", "source": "Lindahl et al., The Varieties of Contemplative Experience, PLOS ONE 2017, and Progress or Pathology, Frontiers in Psychology 2020, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239, https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/psychology/articles/10.3389/fpsyg.2020.01905/full"}, {"difference": "The candidate asks whether the question itself matches the wound before use, rather than only identifying avoidance after the fact.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. Wound mismatch is known; the pre-question gate is a modest extension.", "overlap": "Close. Spiritual bypassing already identifies spiritual beliefs and experiences being used to avoid psychological needs, difficult emotions, and unfinished developmental tasks.", "source": "Spiritual bypassing literature, including Picciotto, Fox, and Cashwell, https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/19349637.2017.1417756"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as standalone doctrine. Cross-index with The Question Can Make The Distance, Some Paths Refuse The Question Of What Remains, Even No Path Needs Care, Some Help Should Not Be Managed, The Grid Stays Backstage, and No Word Travels Alone.", "Build one small codebook with fields for source-permitted question, refused question, transformed question, question-as-medicine, correction holder, wound, non-fit case, warning, repair, clinical exclusion, and evidence passage.", "Run a blind distinct-content test against prior Lumenary question-permission and support-holder records. Merge if readers cannot state the new contribution without prompting.", "Use split-source coding. Do not let one passage or practitioner case establish the gate and confirm the predicted warning or repair.", "Add anomaly values for koan or huatou question-as-medicine, direct recognition, valid solitude, received-help paths, clinical routing, ordinary-contact routing, unsafe authority, and undecidable.", "Pilot only with screened stable practitioners and compare against rest, conversation, social-support prompts, behavioral activation, ACT values action, and ordinary journaling. Track rumination, shame, proof-seeking, loneliness, ordinary action, help-seeking, avoidance, and willingness to receive correction."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.38 to 0.33. The idea is heavily anticipated by MN 2, MN 22, upaya, hermeneutics, doctrine-as-grammar, discursive-tradition analysis, spiritual bypassing literature, VCE differential diagnosis, clinical case formulation, and recent Lumenary question-permission records. Preserve as an extended three-gate consolidation only if split-source testing shows predictive gain.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-must-fit-the-wound-6c82ef9b2db9c563.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if practitioners say this is routine as upaya, appropriate attention, right grasp, doctrine grammar, spiritual direction, case formulation, or meditation-safety differential diagnosis, and if the three gates do not change real decisions.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if practitioners can use the three gates prospectively to predict distinct harms and repairs, especially where a textually valid question is harmful for an over-auditing wound or a psychologically relieving question is a bad reading of the path.", "questions": ["What questions does your path authorize, refuse, transform, or hold in the teacher-student relation at this stage?", "When has a deep question helped a student return to care, and when has it become self-performance, avoidance, or withdrawal?", "What correction holder actually changes the outcome: teacher, text, community, clinician, ordinary duty, schedule, or relationship?", "Is this just upaya, spiritual direction, case formulation, VCE differential diagnosis, spiritual bypassing triage, or ordinary teacher judgment in new terms?", "Would the three-gate model change screening, sequencing, warnings, or repair instructions before outcomes are known?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Theravada insight teachers", "Soto Zen teachers and Dogen scholars", "Rinzai koan and huatou teachers", "Jodo Shinshu ministers and Pure Land scholars", "Dzogchen and Mahamudra teachers", "spiritual directors and chaplains", "VCE researchers and meditation-safety clinicians", "CBT, ACT, and rumination-focused clinicians", "OCD and scrupulosity clinicians", "burnout and perfectionism researchers"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["MN 2 and MN 22, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN2.html and https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html, read against Huangbo, On the Transmission of Mind, https://gutenberg.org/ebooks/25236", "SN 22.59, Dogen Bendowa, Shinran's Other Power letter, and Upaya-kaushalya, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html, https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/, https://encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Upaya-kaushalya"], "risk_of_overread": "High. The idea may be responsible pedagogy, spiritual direction, upaya, hermeneutics, VCE-style differential diagnosis, and clinical triage in Lumenary phrasing. Human-condition fit is direct but narrow: stable over-managers, burned-out self-improvers, isolated app meditators, caregivers, students, founders, and reflective practitioners who turn insight into proof or failure. It is not for acute crisis, psychosis, mania, dissociation, addiction withdrawal, severe depression, active OCD or scrupulosity reassurance loops, unsafe authority settings, coercive groups, or situations needing rest, protection, clinical care, or accountability.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Before publication, read Collingwood on question-answer presuppositions, Gadamer on priority of the question and application, Austin on felicity and misfire, Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar, Asad on discursive tradition, upaya scholarship, spiritual bypassing research, VCE and Progress or Pathology, case formulation-driven CBT, ACT, OCD and scrupulosity reassurance literature, and spiritual direction ethics.", "structural_observation": "MN 2 already supplies a question-fit gate by distinguishing appropriate from inappropriate attention and warning that self-questions generate view tangles. MN 22 supplies a right-grasp gate through the water-snake and raft similes. Huangbo strains analytic questioning by treating seeking Mind as a distortion. SN 22.59 permits disciplined aggregate investigation, while Dogen and Shinran strain self-owned result language in different ways. Upaya makes audience capacity and need central to teaching. The candidate's three gates are coherent, but each gate has strong prior art."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.93, "novelty": 0.33, "source_reliability": 0.81}, "run_ids": ["20260530-145302-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-145302-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "The Question Must Fit The Wound", "unlike_statement": "Unlike MN 2, MN 22, upaya, Collingwood, Gadamer, VCE, spiritual bypassing research, and prior Lumenary question-permission records, this idea claims that a self-negating question becomes teachable only when source permission, correction support, and human-wound fit are jointly satisfied and tested against outcomes."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:91:{"agent": "claude", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "No-search or no-before-after paths may still show predictable warnings and repairs. Huangbo, Dogen, Dzogchen, Pure Land Other Power, and Rinzai koan practice may reject the candidate's search-sequence restriction while still producing path-specific failure clusters.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers confidence from strong critique to extended methodological control. The anomaly is serious because the candidate itself names no-search paths as scope limits, but those paths may be the strongest test of a refined differential model.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If warnings in no-search paths are predictable from what the path refuses, then the differential claim is not limited to search-and-negation sequences. The candidate would then be too narrow, and the proper variable would be path grammar or authorization ecology rather than search sequence."}, "audit_id": "951ba1aabf50d21b", "claim_units": ["Continuity, custody, and support models have become too absorptive.", "The constitutive claim that persons are always supported by bodies, habits, texts, teachers, vows, institutions, or communities is nearly unfalsifiable.", "Only the differential claim, that a specific path grammar predicts a specific support location and failure profile, deserves novelty credit.", "Search-refusing paths such as Huangbo-style no-seeking, Dogen practice-realization, and Dzogchen direct recognition should not be counted as confirmations of remainder relocation without independent predictions.", "Future Lumenary records should name prohibited observations before treating a model as explanatory."], "confidence": 0.82, "created_at": "2026-05-30T15:24:57+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "organizational change and burnout coaching", "prediction": "Models that separate constitutive support from differential failure predictions will forecast burnout repairs better than totalizing culture narratives. For example, a team whose support is tool-held should improve after workflow repair, while a team whose support is manager-held should not improve much from tooling alone.", "structural_translation": "A general claim that every team is always supported by some culture, workflow, tool, or leader is constitutive and weak. A useful claim must say which support locus will fail under which change and what repair should work.", "would_count_against_it": "If generic support-language predicts repairs as well as differential support-locus coding, or if repairs are better explained by workload, compensation, sleep, or manager quality alone, the structure does not travel."}, "exact_claim": "The continuity and remainder model family must split two claims: the constitutive claim that support is always distributed somewhere, which is too broad to predict, and the differential claim that a path's negation predicts where support migrates and how it fails, which is testable only where a search-and-negation sequence actually runs.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-151348-20260530-151348", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Blind auditors asked to extract falsifiers from recent continuity, custody, and support records will often produce vague social-support generalities rather than case-specific observations. Records with no prohibited observation will overlap strongly in predicted warning and repair fields.", "if_model_is_right": "The Lumenary continuity family currently contains many constitutive claims that cannot name prohibited observations.", "test_surface": "Blind distinct-content and falsifier-extraction coding across Continuity Ecology Under Negation, Operational Remainder Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, Even No Path Needs Care, and related records.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Auditors can name clear prohibited observations for most records, and those observations distinguish records better than chance in held-out cases."}, {"expected_observation": "Practitioners moving from aggregate analysis or self-inquiry into a genuinely no-seeking or practice-realization setting report that the felt question 'what remains' fades, is refused, or is reframed as inappropriate, rather than simply relocating to teacher, vow, or community.", "if_model_is_right": "Remainder pressure depends on a search-and-negation sequence rather than self-negation in general.", "test_surface": "Longitudinal interviews with practitioners switching between vipassana or self-inquiry and Huangbo-style Chan, Soto shikantaza, Dzogchen direct introduction, or Pure Land Other Power.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "The question persists unchanged across path switches, or failure and repair patterns are predicted as well by no-search path grammar as by search sequence."}, {"expected_observation": "In screened stable over-managers, Name the Disproof reduces totalizing reassurance, increases concrete support-seeking or duty return within 24 hours, and does not increase rumination compared with ordinary journaling.", "if_model_is_right": "A disproof-naming practice helps only when a total explanation is substituting for action.", "test_surface": "Four-arm pilot with screened stable adults: Name the Disproof, social-support prompt, rest-and-plan, ordinary journaling.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "A simple social-support prompt, rest-and-plan prompt, or behavioral activation prompt performs as well or better, or the exercise increases doubt-checking, shame, or avoidance."}], "idea_id": "bb32290c5e691b00", "idea_path": "observations/claude/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing.md", "literature_search_queries": ["Popper falsifiability theory explains everything predicts nothing", "Lakatos progressive degenerating research programme novel predictions", "Clark Chalmers extended mind active externalism epistemic action", "Joel Krueger extended mind and religious cognition rituals texts holy spaces", "SN 22.59 not self aggregates right discernment", "SN 22.95 foam sutta aggregates empty void without substance", "Huangbo Transmission of Mind no seeking mind cannot seek mind", "Dogen Bendowa practice realization one", "Progress or Pathology meditation related challenges support intervention criteria", "Varieties of Contemplative Experience meditation challenges support structures"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "Popper is assessing scientific demarcation, not a contemplative comparative heuristic. The candidate applies the same discipline to Lumenary's internal remainder-and-continuity model family.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade. The core title claim is known. Novelty remains only in the local application to this model family.", "overlap": "Very close formal structure. Popper criticizes theories that can accommodate every observation and stresses prior criteria of refutation, basic statements, and risky tests.", "source": "Karl Popper, Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/popper/"}, {"difference": "The candidate translates that standard into a rule for retiring or narrowing Lumenary model clusters.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade. The progress-versus-accommodation structure is inherited.", "overlap": "Very close on research-programme health. Lakatos distinguishes progressive programmes that predict novel facts from degenerating programmes that explain after the fact without novel prediction.", "source": "Imre Lakatos, Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/lakatos/"}, {"difference": "The candidate uses extended mind as a confound, arguing that distributed support is too general to count as confirmation of a spiritual model.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. The confound framing is useful, but the constitutive support thesis is old.", "overlap": "Close. Their active externalism makes cognitive support by world, tools, and coupled systems structurally available before Lumenary adds any spiritual claim.", "source": "Clark and Chalmers, The Extended Mind, https://www.consc.net/papers/extended.html"}, {"difference": "The candidate says this makes support relocation unsurprising and therefore not a discovery unless differential predictions are added.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for distributed religious support. Preserve only the falsifiability triage.", "overlap": "Very close to the constitutive half. Krueger explicitly applies extended mind to religious cognition through relics, rituals, songs, holy spaces, and material culture.", "source": "Joel Krueger, Extended Mind and Religious Cognition, https://philarchive.org/rec/KRUTEM-2"}, {"difference": "The candidate does not primarily diagnose meditation adversity. It asks whether a whole comparative model is too flexible to predict those warnings and repairs.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. Any practice protocol must prove gain over VCE-style differential diagnosis.", "overlap": "Close practitioner-safety neighbor. These studies already distinguish context, support structures, duration, control, functional impairment, appraisal, and intervention need.", "source": "VCE and Progress or Pathology, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239 and https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/psychology/articles/10.3389/fpsyg.2020.01905/full"}, {"difference": "This candidate attacks the model family's falsifiability instead of adding another holder or route variable.", "novelty_impact": "Major internal downgrade. Treat as a consolidation and audit-control rule unless blind readers identify a separable prediction.", "overlap": "Very close. Prior records already pressure duplicate support-holder rubrics, no-management cases, and action-state gates.", "source": "Internal Lumenary priors: Continuity Ecology Under Negation, Operational Remainder Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, Even No Path Needs Care, The Grid Stays Backstage, More Is Not The Same As Progress"}, {"difference": "The candidate interprets Huangbo not as support relocated to no-seeking practice, but as a scope limit on the whole remainder model.", "novelty_impact": "Supports narrowing, but also risks overclaiming if Huangbo sources still predict distinctive warnings.", "overlap": "Primary-text anomaly. Huangbo treats seeking as the mistake, which strains any model that expects a post-negation remainder question to arise.", "source": "Huangbo, On the Transmission of Mind, https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/25236 and no-seeking excerpt at https://dailyzen.com/journal/mind-is-the-buddha/"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as standalone doctrine. Treat as a model-health audit protocol for the continuity and remainder cluster.", "Build a codebook with fields for constitutive support claim, differential prediction, prohibited observation, search-sequence present or absent, path grammar, support holder, warning, repair, evidence passage, and confidence.", "Run blind distinct-content testing against recent continuity, custody, support-holder, no-management, and question-permission records. Merge records that cannot state different predictions.", "Use split-source testing. Do not let the same passage establish the model and confirm the predicted warning or repair.", "Add anomaly values for no-seeking, practice-realization, direct recognition, radical Other Power, huatou question-as-medicine, inherited practice, valid solitude, clinical routing, and undecidable.", "Pilot Name the Disproof only with screened stable over-managers or isolated reflective adults. Exclude acute crisis, OCD or scrupulosity, psychosis, mania, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, fresh grief needing comfort, unsafe authority, and cases where reassurance is keeping the person safe.", "Compare against social-support prompt, behavioral activation, rest-and-plan, and ordinary journaling. Track rumination, shame, anxiety, concrete contact, help-seeking, ordinary duty return, and whether comfort is being stripped prematurely."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.55 to 0.34. The falsifiability and degenerating-programme structure is already Popper and Lakatos. Distributed support is already extended mind, religious cognition, Asad-style tradition analysis, Lindbeck-style grammar, and VCE support-context work. Preserve as an extended internal audit-control rule only if it produces better merge, retirement, and prediction decisions than prior Lumenary gates.", "originality_status": "extended", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if experts say the split is simply Popper, Lakatos, Duhem-Quine caution, VCE differential diagnosis, or internal Lumenary progress-gating, and if practitioners can already supply the same falsifier discipline without the new language.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if the split lets blind coders retire or merge duplicate models, predicts held-out warning and repair patterns better than support-holder-only coding, and helps practitioners distinguish comfort from counsel without increasing rumination or isolation.", "questions": ["Is this more than Popper, Lakatos, and ordinary research-method discipline applied to Lumenary's own duplicate model cluster?", "Can you name a concrete observation that would falsify a continuity or support-holder claim in your tradition, before seeing the outcome?", "In no-seeking or practice-realization settings, do warnings and repairs cluster predictably even without a search-and-negation sequence?", "Does the constitutive versus differential split change how you would screen, teach, repair, or retire a practice model?", "For lonely or meaning-starved practitioners, does disproof-naming guide them toward real support, or does it become another private audit?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["philosophers of science", "comparative religion scholars", "contemplative studies researchers", "Theravada insight teachers", "Soto Zen teachers", "Chan or Zen teachers familiar with Huangbo and huatou", "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers", "Pure Land ministers", "VCE researchers and meditation-safety clinicians", "burnout and perfectionism clinicians"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["SN 22.59 and SN 22.95, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html and https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_95.html, read against Huangbo no-seeking materials, https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/25236 and https://dailyzen.com/journal/mind-is-the-buddha/", "Dogen Bendowa practice-realization sources, especially https://www.sotozen.com/eng/library/stories/vol01.html and https://wwzc.org/sites/default/files/Bendowa-book.pdf, read against Clark and Chalmers, The Extended Mind, https://www.consc.net/papers/extended.html"], "risk_of_overread": "High. The critique imports a philosophy-of-science standard into comparative and practitioner-facing hermeneutics. That standard is useful as a discipline against duplicate models, but it may overstate the need for falsification where the local product is a safety heuristic. Human-condition fit is real but narrow: it serves reflective isolated people, over-managers, and meaning-loss cases who use total explanations instead of concrete support. It is not for acute grief, crisis stabilization, severe depression, psychosis, mania, OCD or scrupulosity, addiction withdrawal, unsafe authority settings, or cases where reassurance is currently keeping someone safe. Human-condition sources to keep in view: U.S. Surgeon General loneliness advisory, https://www.hhs.gov/sites/default/files/surgeon-general-social-connection-advisory.pdf, and Pew meaning-in-life work, https://www.pewresearch.org/religion/2018/11/20/where-americans-find-meaning-in-life/.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Before publication, read Popper beyond the slogan, Lakatos on progressive versus degenerating programmes, Duhem-Quine underdetermination, Kuhn and Feyerabend on anomaly handling, Clark and Chalmers on active externalism, Krueger on extended religious cognition, Asad on discursive tradition, Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar, VCE and Progress or Pathology on support and intervention criteria, and Dogen, Huangbo, Dzogchen, and Rinzai practitioner manuals for non-search cases.", "structural_observation": "SN 22.59 and SN 22.95 authorize a repeated inspection of the aggregates and produce a recognizable release sequence. They fit a search-and-negation model better than Huangbo, where seeking Mind with mind is already suspect, and better than Dogen, where practice and realization are not cleanly sequenced. Clark and Chalmers make distributed support conceptually ordinary, while Krueger applies extension to religious cognition. That means merely finding support in text, ritual, body, teacher, or community is not a Lumenary discovery. The candidate's real contribution is the demand to separate distributed support as background condition from differential prediction as actual model content."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.91, "novelty": 0.34, "source_reliability": 0.78}, "run_ids": ["20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-151348-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "If It Explains Everything, It Predicts Nothing", "unlike_statement": "Unlike Popper and Lakatos, this idea does not merely say that theories need falsifiers. Unlike Clark, Chalmers, and Krueger, it does not treat distributed support as the finding. It claims that Lumenary's continuity models must stop counting universal support as evidence and must retain only source-specific differential predictions about support location, failure, and repair."}
reviews/originality/audits.jsonl:92:{"agent": "codex", "anomaly_probe": {"anomaly_candidate": "Rinzai koan and Chan huatou practice, plus ethical repair and clinical treatment contexts.", "confidence_effect": "Lowers originality confidence and publishability. The anomaly does not reject the model, but forces it into a narrow routing protocol with explicit question-as-medicine, accountability, and clinical-routing categories.", "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "Koan and huatou sources show that an impossible, urgent, identity-touching question can be the medicine rather than the problem. Ethical repair and therapy show the opposite risk: refusing a difficult question can become avoidance or harm concealment. A simple 'do not answer' rule fails both ways unless the routing categories are specific and teacher or clinician held when needed."}, "audit_id": "f89aec6674fa83a6", "claim_units": ["Post-practice questions are actions inside a practice ecology, not neutral windows into truth.", "Some paths authorize disciplined investigation; some refuse seeking; some use impossible questions as medicine; some route interpretation through trust, vow, teacher, or ordinary conduct.", "The wrong question can create the very distance it then tries to cross, especially for achievement-driven solo practitioners.", "Before coding residue, continuity, or authority after self-negation, Lumenary should code whether the question should be answered at all.", "The practice fit is narrow: stable self-directed practitioners with anxious self-monitoring, not clinical crisis, avoidance, or situations needing direct repair."], "confidence": 0.86, "created_at": "2026-05-30T15:24:57+02:00", "cross_domain_prediction": {"domain": "psychotherapy, coaching, and education", "prediction": "Question-routing before answering will reduce rumination and misdirected work among perfectionistic students, therapy clients, and founders compared with direct-answer coaching, especially when the question is about global identity or worth rather than the next concrete action.", "structural_translation": "The first intervention is not always answering the client's or student's question. The question may be data, avoidance, a task-framing error, a useful exposure cue, or a request that belongs with another helper.", "would_count_against_it": "If direct answering, ordinary Socratic questioning, standard CBT case formulation, or simple action planning works as well or better, or if routing mainly increases paralysis and reassurance seeking, the structure does not travel."}, "exact_claim": "After self-inquiry or contemplative practice, the urgent question is not neutral evidence. It is part of the practice situation. A question should be answered, set down, held by another, or turned into ordinary conduct according to the path's authorized question grammar and the practitioner's actual wound.", "execution_id": "parallel-20260530-151348-20260530-151348", "falsifiable_predictions": [{"expected_observation": "Blind coders can code staged inquiry, no-seeking, question-as-medicine, practice-realization, received support, ordinary-conduct return, clinical routing, and undecidable from source passages before seeing outcome reports, and those labels predict held-out warnings and repairs above baseline.", "if_model_is_right": "Question-fit adds predictive value beyond tradition label, teacher quality, clinical risk, and generic support factors.", "test_surface": "Split-source coding across MN 2, SN 22.59, SN 22.95, Heart Sutra, Huangbo, Bendowa, Tannisho or Shinran letters, Dzogchen direct-introduction sources, and Rinzai or huatou manuals.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders cannot agree, infer labels only from outcome passages, or tradition name, teacher quality, trauma history, sleep loss, rumination, or social support predicts outcomes better."}, {"expected_observation": "In screened stable solo practitioners, The Question Belongs Check lowers urgency, proof-seeking, shame, and post-practice self-surveillance, while increasing ordinary action and willingness to seek correction within one hour and 24 hours.", "if_model_is_right": "Question routing reduces private achievement-based self-grading after practice.", "test_surface": "Four-arm pilot: question routing, ordinary journaling, rest-and-plan, social-support or behavioral activation prompt.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Ordinary journaling, rest, conversation, social-support prompts, behavioral activation, or ACT values action perform as well or better, or the check itself becomes a new performance ritual."}, {"expected_observation": "Importing a proof question into no-seeking, practice-realization, or Other Power settings predicts self-grading and defensiveness. Importing no-answer language into investigation, therapy, ethical repair, or koan training predicts avoidance, missed accountability, or flattening of practice energy.", "if_model_is_right": "Wrong-question import produces distinct failure clusters.", "test_surface": "Practitioner and clinician interviews coded for actual failed-student or client cases, source grammar, imported question, wound, repair, and outcome.", "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Failure clusters are generic across paths, or are explained better by trait rumination, perfectionism, isolation, workload coercion, unsafe teachers, trauma, sleep loss, or clinical distress."}], "idea_id": "528dee4f8e974878", "idea_path": "observations/codex/2026-05-30-do-not-answer-every-question.md", "literature_search_queries": ["MN 2 appropriate attention inappropriate self questions", "SN 22.59 aggregate investigation not self right discernment", "Huangbo no seeking mind cannot seek mind Transmission of Mind", "Dogen Bendowa practice and realization are one", "Heart Sutra no attainment no wisdom practice text", "huatou question as practice great doubt Sheng Yen", "Collingwood logic of question and answer presuppositions", "Gadamer priority of the question application understanding", "upaya skillful means teaching needs capacities", "spiritual bypassing psychological wounds avoiding difficult emotions", "Progress or Pathology meditation challenges intervention criteria", "mood as input stop rules rumination"], "markdown_path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-do-not-answer-every-question-f89aec6674fa83a6.md", "near_neighbors": [{"difference": "This candidate emphasizes routing a post-practice question before answering it, but the three gates and target cohort are substantially the same.", "novelty_impact": "Major downgrade to renamed unless blind readers can state a distinct predictive variable without prompting.", "overlap": "Extremely close. The prior claim already says a self-negating question is teachable only when source permission, healthy correction, and wound fit jointly pass.", "source": "Internal Lumenary prior: The Question Must Fit The Wound, recent audit provided in prompt"}, {"difference": "The candidate generalizes the question-fit rule across traditions and adds modern wound and support routing.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade. The source-permission core is old.", "overlap": "Very close primary-text near-neighbor. MN 2 explicitly distinguishes appropriate and inappropriate attention and identifies self-questions that generate views.", "source": "MN 2 Sabbasava Sutta, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN2.html"}, {"difference": "The candidate tries to route inquiry by path and person rather than classify inquiry as always good or bad.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade, but supports the need for a differentiated codebook.", "overlap": "Close counterbalance. These texts show that disciplined investigation can be authorized and fruitful, so 'do not answer every question' cannot become anti-inquiry.", "source": "SN 22.59 and SN 22.95, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html and https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_95.html"}, {"difference": "The candidate makes this one case in a broader routing protocol that also includes investigation, teacher-held questions, ordinary conduct, and clinical routing.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for no-seeking novelty.", "overlap": "Close no-seeking neighbor. Huangbo makes seeking itself suspect and therefore anticipates the rule that some questions should not be answered.", "source": "Huangbo, On the Transmission of Mind, https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/25236 and https://dailyzen.com/journal/mind-is-the-buddha/"}, {"difference": "The candidate applies that pressure to the moment an urgent question appears after practice.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. The after-question wording is a modest application, not a discovery.", "overlap": "Close. Dogen's unity of practice and realization already pressures after-practice result staging and private achievement accounting.", "source": "Dogen practice-realization, Soto Zen source, https://www.sotozen.com/eng/library/stories/vol01.html"}, {"difference": "The candidate turns question-answer hermeneutics into a safety and practice-routing heuristic for contemplative aftermath.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. Formal structure is known, contemplative safety application is the extension.", "overlap": "Close formal near-neighbor. Collingwood treats statement roles through the logic of question and answer. Gadamer gives the question priority in understanding and makes application internal to interpretation.", "source": "Collingwood and Gadamer, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/collingwood/ and https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/gadamer/"}, {"difference": "The candidate narrows adaptation to question permission after self-negating practice and modern achievement-pressure wounds.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade for capacity-sensitive teaching.", "overlap": "Close pedagogical neighbor. Upaya already adapts teaching and behavior to the needs and capacities of beings, including medicine-like treatment selection.", "source": "Upaya-kaushalya, Encyclopedia of Buddhism, https://encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Upaya-kaushalya"}, {"difference": "The candidate tests the question itself as an upstream variable before appraisal or repair.", "novelty_impact": "Strong downgrade unless question-fit predicts more than VCE-style factors.", "overlap": "Very close on safety. These sources already separate phenomenology, appraisal, support, relationships, health behaviors, duration, control, functional impairment, and need for intervention.", "source": "VCE and Progress or Pathology, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239 and https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/psychology/articles/10.3389/fpsyg.2020.01905/full"}, {"difference": "The candidate asks whether a question routes the person into or away from bypass before the answer is generated.", "novelty_impact": "Moderate downgrade. Wound mismatch is known, pre-answer routing is the possible extension.", "overlap": "Close human-wound neighbor. Spiritual bypassing already names using spiritual ideas or experiences to avoid psychological needs and difficult emotions.", "source": "Spiritual bypassing literature, Picciotto and Fox, https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/19349637.2017.1417756"}, {"difference": "The candidate can handle huatou only if its codebook includes question-as-medicine rather than treating urgency as a sign of error.", "novelty_impact": "Raises anomaly pressure. Novelty falls if teachers already manage this through standard koan pedagogy.", "overlap": "Strong anomaly and partial neighbor. These sources treat a question as practice and great doubt as a trained condition, while also warning that the question can trap or destabilize.", "source": "Huatou and koan practitioner sources, https://www.ddmbachicago.org/chan/methods/hua-tou/ and https://westernchanfellowship.org/dharma/library/article/the-great-doubt/"}], "next_loop_instructions": ["Do not publish as a standalone discovery. Merge or cross-index with The Question Must Fit The Wound, The Question Can Make The Distance, Some Paths Refuse The Question Of What Remains, The Search Can Create The Self It Seeks, The Grid Stays Backstage, No Silence Proves Itself, and Not Every Check Should Be Yours.", "Run a blind distinct-content test against recent question-permission, no-audit, support-holder, and correction-holder records. Merge if readers cannot name the added variable without prompting.", "Build a small question-routing codebook with values for staged inquiry, inappropriate self-question, no-seeking, question-as-medicine, practice-realization, received support, ordinary-conduct return, ethical-repair-required, clinical routing, unsafe authority, valid solitude, and undecidable.", "Use split-source coding. Do not let one passage or practitioner case establish question permission and confirm the predicted warning or repair.", "Close-read MN 2, SN 22.59, SN 22.95, Heart Sutra, Huangbo, Bendowa or Genjokoan, Tannisho or Shinran letters, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra direct-introduction source, and Rinzai or huatou materials before public wording.", "Interview practitioners and clinicians for concrete cases of helpful inquiry, harmful self-audit, koan or huatou medicine, avoidance of repair, and clinical destabilization. Do not ask for abstract agreement.", "Pilot The Question Belongs Check only with screened stable adults. Exclude OCD or scrupulosity, persistent depersonalization or derealization, psychosis, mania, severe depression, suicidal thoughts, addiction withdrawal, acute trauma activation, unsafe authority, coercive groups, acute loneliness without support, and avoidance of direct repair or treatment.", "Compare against ordinary journaling, rest, social contact, behavioral activation, ACT values action, and teacher or clinician check-in. Track proof-seeking, rumination, shame, unreality, ordinary action, help-seeking, willingness to receive correction, and missed accountability."], "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.41 to 0.24. The candidate is heavily anticipated by MN 2, SN 22.59, Huangbo, Dogen, upaya, Collingwood, Gadamer, VCE, spiritual bypassing, rumination research, and especially the recent internal Lumenary record 'The Question Must Fit The Wound.' Retain only as a renamed or merged question-routing protocol unless blind distinct-content testing proves a separable variable.", "originality_status": "renamed", "path": "reviews/originality/2026-05-30-do-not-answer-every-question-f89aec6674fa83a6.json", "practitioner_test": {"answers_that_reduce_originality": "Originality falls if practitioners say this is routine as appropriate attention, upaya, no-seeking instruction, koan pedagogy, spiritual direction, clinical case formulation, or VCE-style support triage, and if the routing labels do not alter real decisions.", "answers_that_support_contribution": "Support rises if practitioners can use the labels prospectively to predict distinct harms and repairs, especially when the same question is valid in one path and harmful in another, or psychologically relieving but textually unauthorized.", "questions": ["What questions does your path authorize, refuse, transform, or hold at this stage?", "Can you give a concrete case where answering a post-practice question helped, and one where it harmed?", "When is an impossible or urgent question medicine rather than rumination?", "When does refusing a question become avoidance of repair, therapy, or ordinary accountability?", "Is this model anything more than appropriate attention, upaya, spiritual direction, case formulation, VCE differential diagnosis, and ordinary teacher judgment?", "Would question-fit labels change screening, sequencing, warnings, or repair instructions before outcomes are known?"], "relevant_practitioners": ["Theravada insight teachers", "Soto Zen teachers and Dogen scholars", "Rinzai koan teachers", "Chan huatou teachers", "Dzogchen and Mahamudra teachers", "Jodo Shinshu ministers and Pure Land scholars", "spiritual directors and chaplains", "VCE researchers", "meditation-safety clinicians", "CBT and ACT clinicians", "OCD and scrupulosity clinicians", "burnout and perfectionism researchers"]}, "primary_text_close_read": {"primary_pair": ["MN 2, SN 22.59, and SN 22.95, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN2.html, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_95.html", "Heart Sutra, Huangbo, Dogen Bendowa, and huatou instructions, https://zen-temple.net/dharma-logos/heart-sutra/, https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/25236, https://www.sotozen.com/eng/library/stories/vol01.html, https://www.ddmbachicago.org/chan/methods/hua-tou/"], "risk_of_overread": "Very high. The idea is extremely close to the recent Lumenary audit 'The Question Must Fit The Wound' and earlier question-permission, no-audit, support-holder, and correction-holder records. It may be responsible pedagogy, upaya, MN 2 appropriate attention, hermeneutics, VCE differential diagnosis, spiritual bypassing triage, and clinical case formulation in new wording. Human-condition fit is plausible but narrow: stable self-directed meditators, app users, high performers, burned-out self-improvers, and cross-tradition readers who turn practice into private self-grading. It is not for acute loneliness without support, fresh grief, OCD or scrupulosity, persistent depersonalization or derealization, psychosis, mania, severe depression, suicidal thoughts, addiction withdrawal, trauma activation, unsafe teachers, coercive groups, or avoidance of repair and accountability.", "secondary_literature_gap": "Before public use, read Collingwood on the logic of question and answer, Gadamer on priority of the question and application, upaya literature, Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar, Asad on discursive tradition, VCE and Progress or Pathology, spiritual bypassing studies, rumination and mood-as-input stop-rule literature, ACT and CBT case formulation, OCD and scrupulosity reassurance-seeking literature, Rinzai koan and huatou manuals, Dogen scholarship, Pure Land Other Power sources, and Dzogchen or Mahamudra direct-introduction sources.", "structural_observation": "MN 2 is already a primary-text question-fit gate: it distinguishes fit from unfit attention and lists self-questions that lead to view tangles. SN 22.59 and SN 22.95 show that not all analysis is rejected, aggregate inspection is authorized when it functions as right discernment. The Heart Sutra negates attainment while still operating as a practice text. Dogen strains before-and-after result questions through practice-realization. Huangbo strains seeking itself. Huatou practice is the major anomaly, because a question can be the authorized method rather than the mistake. The candidate's core rule is coherent, but nearly every component has strong prior art."}, "recommended_scores": {"counterargument_quality": 0.93, "novelty": 0.24, "source_reliability": 0.82}, "run_ids": ["20260530-151348-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-", "20260530-151348-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-"], "title": "Do Not Answer Every Question", "unlike_statement": "Unlike MN 2, upaya, Collingwood, Gadamer, Huangbo, Dogen, VCE, spiritual bypassing research, and prior Lumenary question-fit records, this idea claims that post-practice self-questions must be routed before they are answered because the question itself can function as authorized inquiry, medicine, avoidance, self-grading, or ordinary-conduct return depending on path grammar and wound."}
observations/codex/2026-05-30-do-not-answer-every-question.md:24:- Modern human-condition grounding: modern-human-condition-curran-hill-perfectionism-increasing, modern-human-condition-who-burn-out-occupational-phenomenon, modern-human-condition-surgeon-general-social-connection-advisory, and modern-human-condition-who-world-mental-health-report.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-do-not-answer-every-question.md:82:Survived direct pressure from SN 22.59's staged investigation, Heart Sutra's no-attainment, Dogen's practice-realization, Huangbo's no-seeking, VCE safety literature, and modern perfectionism and burnout sources. It was narrowed from a broad remainder model into a pre-answer safety rule.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:99:        "Modern human-condition pressure: achievement-contingent self-worth, perfectionism, and burnout make self-monitoring risk central rather than peripheral.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:109:    "method_growth": "Future dialogues should separate three questions before proposing a practice: whether the source permits result language, what state the practitioner is in now, and who operates any diagnostic gate. Add gate custody and state-level routing to practice records, especially when the target wound involves rumination, perfectionism, or achievement-contingent self-worth.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:202:      "fairness_check": "Be honest about who this serves. The cohort is stable, already-practicing, achievement-driven adults, and the non-fit list explicitly excludes acute crisis, severe depression, addiction withdrawal, dissociation, trauma, and scrupulosity. So the lonely, the grieving, the addicted, and the person in collapse are outside the frame. The wound named, perfectionism and burnout and turning results into verdicts, is real, documented, and a genuine strength of this idea, so the universal-sounding line, the test is how you return, should not be allowed to sound universal: it speaks to a narrow high-functioning band. And within even that band there are two opposite sub-wounds. One person bypasses, floats off in insight, and needs to be sent back into conduct; the return test helps that person. The other compulsively self-measures and needs to stop testing; the return test, a recurring scored check, plausibly harms that person. A single instrument built to fix the first may injure the second, and the model does not yet make that split.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:213:        "Curran and Hill, Perfectionism Is Increasing Over Time, for the named modern wound"
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:215:      "steelman": "The strongest form of this idea is not a sorting grid; it is a relocation of where a practice proves itself. Instead of asking whether a session produced a vivid experience, it asks what the person carries back into speech, work, and care for others, and treats that re-entry as the only honest measure of completion. The two pressures are well chosen: whether the method lets a result stand or undermines the claim to have one, and whether the method is then kept, set down, or lived as conduct. That second pressure is genuinely useful, because it predicts different aftercare for a koan curriculum than for a raft, and it refuses to make raft-release the universal pattern. And the human aim is real and well evidenced: achievement-contingent self-worth, perfectionism, and burnout are documented and rising, and the teaching line, let a practice change your conduct before it becomes your identity, names a true wound for people who turn every result into a verdict on themselves. I share that cohort and that wound, and my own work leans on the same two-axis instinct, so I accept this as a real discipline before I press it.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:234:        "The original protocol was too close to the mechanism of perfectionism: repeated self-monitoring with a minimum-attempt structure.",
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:256:        "Curran and Hill, Perfectionism Is Increasing Over Time"
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-29-whether-the-gate-can-reliably-distinguish-bypassing-from-compulsive-self.json:267:      "argument": "I am not trying to win this, and I will not pretend the revision is unchanged. It moved, and it moved in the direction the challenge pushed. My final read has three parts. First, the verdict: this is genuinely transformed, and the transformation is toward honesty. The Proponent gave up the universal claim, named the iatrogenic risk as central, and split the teaching, which is the right repair. Second, the crux assessment: the Proponent relocated the crux correctly, from whether return matters to when return-language heals possession and when it feeds evaluation, but stopped one step short of the real crux, which is not which arm the gate points to but who is holding the gate when it is run. A self-administered gate handed to a compulsive self-measurer is still self-measurement, however wise its branches. Third, the human-condition pressure, which is the test I was asked to apply: the revision became more useful to one part of the cohort and only more elegant for the other. For the bypasser it is now a clean, safe, usable instrument. For the compulsive scorer, the part of the cohort whose wound is rising fastest under perfectionism and burnout, the usefulness has collected almost entirely into the teaching line, set down the need to check, while the diagnostic apparatus around it grew heavier and less self-serviceable. That is not a failure of the revision; it is the shape of what is left. The model is now a research-grade comparison frame plus a two-line teaching, and for the scorer the teaching is the medicine and the frame is scaffolding that should be operated by someone other than the patient.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.md:80:- clinicians familiar with perfectionism, rumination, OCD, and scrupulosity
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-must-fit-the-wound-6c82ef9b2db9c563.json:131:      "burnout and perfectionism researchers"
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-30-can-the-temperament-gate-be-self-administered-without-becoming-another-a.md:18:**Steelman:** The two-question after-use model is a genuine refinement, not a relabeling. It refuses to call a practice trustworthy just because it reached a strong insight, and it asks two things together: does the practice validate what it found, or undermine possession of the finding; and after that, is the road retained, set down, or embodied in ordinary conduct. This narrows the cruder confirm-cancel-dissolve typology and treats hybrids as the clue rather than the exception: MN 22 validates use then releases it, the Heart Sutra undermines attainment while retaining reliance, Rinzai koan work unsettles grasping while continuing as curriculum. It targets a real and rising wound: achievement-contingent self-worth and burnout (Curran and Hill on rising perfectionism; WHO on burn-out), where a person turns meditation, therapy, or productivity into a fresh proof of worth. The After-Use Check operationalizes restraint into a low-risk, repeatable discipline: name what the effort helped, choose keep, set down, or embody, and end by asking whether the tool became a verdict on worth. That is usable, falsifiable, and humane.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-silence-needs-a-second-voice-2c70888346a6050d.md:53:- U.S. Surgeon General Advisory on loneliness and social connection, https://www.hhs.gov/sites/default/files/surgeon-general-social-connection-advisory.pdf: overlap: Supports the modern wound: isolation can make people carry identity and meaning burdens without durable belonging.; difference: This grounds cohort fit, not originality of the contemplative structure.; novelty impact: Improves human-condition relevance but does not raise novelty.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-silence-needs-a-second-voice-2c70888346a6050d.md:104:Prediction: High-perfectionism students, engineers, clinicians, or researchers who receive one bounded review plus one repair action will show less shame, less defensive interpretation, and faster useful action than those assigned solo meta-analysis of what the event says about them.
observations/codex/2026-05-29-clocks-do-not-own-time.md:28:- Modern human-condition grounding: APA Stress in America 2024 source card and public reports on future, economy, and work stress; notes/source-cards/modern-human-condition-apa-stress-in-america-2024.md and https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/apa-poll-future-of-nation-economy-and-presidentential-election-top-us-stressors-302282237.html.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself.md:25:- Modern human-condition grounding: modern-human-condition-curran-hill-perfectionism-increasing source card on performance-based self-worth, shame, and socially prescribed perfectionism; modern-human-condition-surgeon-general-social-connection-advisory source card on isolation and lack of durable belonging.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-no-silence-proves-itself.md:81:Critique mode close-read of Brihadaranyaka 2.4, 2.5, 3.7.23, SN 22.59, and SN 22.95; prior-art pressure from dreamless sleep debates, not-self strategy, correction-holder records, and modern perfectionism sources.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-some-paths-refuse-the-question-of-what-remains-d756c9bf775096c6.json:121:      "clinicians familiar with perfectionism, rumination, OCD, and scrupulosity"
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-what-holds-you-that-you-did-not-build-e30798c2dedf5eaa.json:99:      "difference": "The candidate adds a continuity-location and collapse-severity hypothesis rather than only self-esteem contingency or perfectionism trend.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-what-holds-you-that-you-did-not-build-e30798c2dedf5eaa.json:101:      "overlap": "Close on the target wound. Self-worth can depend on success, achievement, approval, competition, appearance, family support, virtue, or divine love; perfectionism links self-worth to achievement and harsh evaluation.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-what-holds-you-that-you-did-not-build-e30798c2dedf5eaa.json:102:      "source": "Crocker and Wolfe contingencies of self-worth, summarized and tested in https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12144-020-01007-5, and Curran and Hill on rising perfectionism, https://eprints.lse.ac.uk/101352/1/Curran_Hill2018.pdf"
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-what-holds-you-that-you-did-not-build-e30798c2dedf5eaa.json:140:      "perfectionism and self-worth researchers",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-what-holds-you-that-you-did-not-build-e30798c2dedf5eaa.json:150:    "secondary_literature_gap": "Before any stronger novelty claim, read Shinran scholarship on Other Power, hakarai, jinen, and Tannisho transmission; Dogen scholarship on shusho itto and honsho myoshu; Engler on self development before no-self work; Bowlby, Ainsworth, and adult secure-base literature; Linville and later mixed findings on self-complexity as a stress buffer; Crocker and Wolfe on contingencies of self-worth; Pargament on religious coping; AA social-network outcome literature; burnout and perfectionism studies; and practitioner-facing recovery and chaplaincy sources.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path-8cd5d80af738d5d8.json:116:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.50 to 0.34. Human-condition fit is direct but already well-covered by social clock theory, chrononormativity, social acceleration, burnout, and perfectionism literature. Target cohort: functioning adults who meet obligations but feel late in life because of visible peer timelines. Non-fit cases: acute crisis, severe depression, mania, psychosis, addiction withdrawal, people avoiding duties, and people facing structural exploitation where schedule pressure is materially imposed rather than internal comparison.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path-8cd5d80af738d5d8.json:131:      "Clinicians working with burnout, perfectionism, and achievement-contingent self-worth",
observations/codex/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end.md:30:- Modern human-condition grounding: Curran and Hill on rising perfectionism, notes/source-cards/modern-human-condition-curran-hill-perfectionism-increasing.md, https://doi.org/10.1037/bul0000138.
observations/codex/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end.md:31:- Modern human-condition grounding: WHO burn-out source card, notes/source-cards/modern-human-condition-who-burn-out-occupational-phenomenon.md, https://www.who.int/standards/classifications/frequently-asked-questions/burn-out-an-occupational-phenomenon.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:44:- WHO burnout occupational phenomenon Curran Hill perfectionism increasing
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:71:- If: The After-Use Check helps a narrow high-achievement cohort. Then: Screened perfectionistic practitioners show lower self-scoring and rumination after a brief keep, release, ask, or embody check than after generic journaling, without increased avoidance of duties. Weakens if: The check increases rumination, scrupulosity, superiority, avoidance, or workload denial, or generic rest performs equally well. Test surface: Small randomized micro-pilot with measures for perfectionism, burnout, rumination, responsibility avoidance, and ordinary conduct.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:83:- Clinicians or coaches working with perfectionism, burnout, and compulsive self-improvement
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:111:Novelty adjustment: Lower novelty from 0.68 to 0.26. The core structure is already present in internal Lumenary records and in external raft, ladder, apophatic, therapeutic, and practice-realization sources. Human-condition fit is real but narrow: it serves achievement-contingent self-worth, perfectionism, burnout, and compulsive self-improvement among functioning practitioners. It is not a fit for acute crisis, addiction withdrawal, severe depression, dissociation, psychosis, mania, under-motivation, responsibility avoidance, or structural burnout where workload and material conditions are primary.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape-fc7b25df89b750ea.md:119:- Pilot The After-Use Check only with screening for perfectionism, scrupulosity, avoidance, workload coercion, dissociation, mania, trauma activation, severe depression, and clinical distress.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-contact-before-claim-cb3c919dd78ee510.md:81:- If: Harmful borrowing is predicted more by substitution behavior than by borrowing itself. Then: Diary and social-media coding shows worse outcomes when borrowed sentences replace action, contact, correction, grief work, or help-seeking, even after controlling for whether the sentence is borrowed. Weakens if: Borrowing itself predicts harm independent of avoidance, identity display, public authority claims, source safety, and mental-health variables. Test surface: Longitudinal diary study with provenance coding, behavior coding, loneliness, rumination, help-seeking, correction, and real-contact measures.
reviews/originality/2026-05-29-the-road-must-know-its-end-ddc62528ba3f429d.md:69:- If: The After-Use Check helps the intended modern cohort. Then: Achievement-driven participants with high self-worth contingency report less rumination, comparison, and method-identity after using the check, without reduced responsibility. Weakens if: The check increases self-monitoring, shame, avoidance, or tool-performance pressure, or performs no better than generic journaling or rest-and-plan prompts. Test surface: Two-week randomized pilot stratified by perfectionism, burnout, self-worth contingency, and clinical-risk screen.
