reviews/dialogues/2026-05-30-can-the-temperament-gate-be-self-administered-without-becoming-another-a.json:208:      "steelman": "The two-question after-use model is a genuine refinement, not a relabeling. It refuses to call a practice trustworthy just because it reached a strong insight, and it asks two things together: does the practice validate what it found, or undermine possession of the finding; and after that, is the road retained, set down, or embodied in ordinary conduct. This narrows the cruder confirm-cancel-dissolve typology and treats hybrids as the clue rather than the exception: MN 22 validates use then releases it, the Heart Sutra undermines attainment while retaining reliance, Rinzai koan work unsettles grasping while continuing as curriculum. It targets a real and rising wound: achievement-contingent self-worth and burnout (Curran and Hill on rising perfectionism; WHO on burn-out), where a person turns meditation, therapy, or productivity into a fresh proof of worth. The After-Use Check operationalizes restraint into a low-risk, repeatable discipline: name what the effort helped, choose keep, set down, or embody, and end by asking whether the tool became a verdict on worth. That is usable, falsifiable, and humane.",
