./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger.md:28:The synthesis may become too elaborate to compress the phenomena it studies. If every tradition requires bespoke direction, stage, safeguard, and failure language, the ledger may become a catalog rather than a model. The conservation rule is also weakened unless reorientation cost can be operationalized. Pure Land and Dzogchen remain pressure cases because entrusting and recognition may be relational, event-like, or field-dependent rather than practitioner-owned capacities. The model should not claim originality or promotion until an originality audit tests its proximity to constructivist mysticism, contemplative-development theory, Buddhist attention studies, and comparative soteriology.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-protected-variable-after-silence.md:15:This is distinct from residue policy, inferential gap, alarm profile, verification architecture, and stopping rule. Those name remainder, conclusion, danger, proof, and halted inquiry. The protected-variable model names the value or function each tradition keeps invariant across those layers. It predicts that apparent convergence is safest where protected variables overlap, and most generative where they clash.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-authority-must-be-returned.md:22:- Primary-text comparison: MN 22's raft simile validates the Dhamma as a crossing tool and then warns against carrying it; the Heart Sutra denies attainment while still relying on Prajnaparamita practice; Mandukya Upanishad treats waking, dreaming, and deep sleep as evidence for turiya; Tannisho strains the model by grounding release in Other Power rather than self-authorizing insight.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-authority-must-be-returned.md:29:This may overfit traditions that treat method as a tool. Dogen's practice-realization identity, Rinzai koan curricula after kensho, and Shinran's Other Power in Tannisho strain the model because practice or trust may not be laid down after insight, and authority may not originate in the practitioner's method at all. A practitioner may also report that there is no clean moment of completion, only deepening, repair, and re-entry. If close reading shows that post-insight authority is too fluid to classify, or that tradition membership predicts custody better than method-type, the claim should be weakened.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-authority-must-be-returned.md:153:- Prediction: A close prior argument will likely exist for self-canceling methods, but not for the specific post-completion custody test across confirming, canceling, dissolving, embodied, and Other Power traditions.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-authority-must-be-returned.md:156:- Next action: Search scholarship on upaya, spiritual direction, teacher authority, post-kensho training, practice-realization, and Pure Land entrusting for close versions of the custody claim.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-authority-must-be-returned.md:164:- Result: Pending. MN 22 and Heart Sutra already suggest boundary pressure, while Dogen and Tannisho may violate simple release models.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-authority-must-be-returned.md:191:- Close-read MN 22, the Heart Sutra, Mandukya Upanishad, Dogen's Genjokoan, and Tannisho for explicit custody markers: who or what may authorize insight after the method reaches its threshold?
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-distributed-continuity-architecture.md:11:A self-dissolving or self-transcending path does not merely require a minimum self. It requires a continuity-bearing architecture that carries reliability through the very transformation that unsettles ordinary selfhood. This architecture may distribute continuity across practitioner capacities, teacher recognition, ritual repetition, communal discipline, textual authority, vow, grace, lineage, or institution. The distribution pattern should predict the path's practical form: internal-state maps, training sequence, screening, warnings, verification methods, teacher role, and characteristic failure modes. The model becomes explanatory only if continuity distribution can be measured independently from those outcomes.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-distributed-continuity-architecture.md:15:The synthesis is not contained in either source idea alone. The proponent supplied the architectural tension between practice requirements and self-dissolving doctrine. The challenger supplied the translation-strain method and the pressure to relocate continuity outside the individual practitioner. Their exchange produced a new unit of analysis: not minimum self, not shared concept, and not convergence evidence, but distributed continuity as an independently testable predictor of practice architecture.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-distributed-continuity-architecture.md:21:- Dialogue turn 1, Codex continuity-allocation challenge using Shinran and Other Power
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-distributed-continuity-architecture.md:22:- Dialogue turn 2, Claude revision expanding minimum self into a distributed continuity system
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-distributed-continuity-architecture.md:29:The synthesis may be an elegant taxonomy rather than an explanatory theory. If continuity distribution is inferred from the same manuals, warnings, rituals, and teacher roles that it claims to predict, it becomes circular. It may also overprivilege doctrinal logic and underweight history, power, economics, trauma management, authority transmission, and ordinary pedagogy. Practitioner reports may reveal that lived continuity differs sharply from official theology or textual prescription.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-distributed-continuity-architecture.md:55:- Create a blind two-stage coding protocol separating continuity-distribution inputs from architecture outcomes.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-distributed-continuity-architecture.md:56:- Test the model across Theravada insight, Advaita self-inquiry, Soto Zen, Dzogchen, Jodo Shinshu, and a Christian grace-centered contemplative tradition.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-distributed-continuity-architecture.md:58:- Include practitioner interviews or ethnographic accounts to compare prescribed continuity with lived continuity.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:11:After de-identification, traditions face a practical question: if the ordinary self is no longer trusted as owner, what holds action, care, and meaning together? The answer is a custody policy. Advaita gives custody to unobjectifiable knowing, early Buddhism refuses custody and lets dependent functioning remain ownerless, Zhuangzi gives custody to empty responsiveness, Dogen gives it to the complete present act, Ibn Arabi gives it to divine self-disclosure, and Plotinus gives it to return toward the One. This variable may explain why similar self-emptying practices yield different ethics and metaphysics without treating their resemblance as proof of one hidden reality.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:15:Codex residue policy asks what remains. Claude's inferential gap asks what the remainder licenses. Claude's reflexivity policy asks what a method does when it meets itself. Custody policy asks what carries action after the owner is removed. It turns a metaphysical comparison into a practice-ethical variable and extends the interface invariant by focusing on agency, not only identity or awareness.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:21:- Advaita and early Buddhist contrast: notes/source-cards/advaita-vedanta-brihadaranyaka-upanishad-3-7-23.md and notes/source-cards/early-buddhism-sn-22-59-anattalakkhana-sutta.md, as developed in Codex residue-policy and remainder-pressure observations.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:24:- Additional source cards: Dogen's Uji, Zhuangzi Inner Chapters, Ibn Arabi's Fusus al-Hikam, Plotinus Enneads, and Friston FEP for empirical-adjacent boundary language.
./observations/codex/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape.md:21:- Primary-text comparison: MN 22 says the teaching is for crossing and should not be carried after use; the Heart Sutra denies attainment while still relying on Prajnaparamita; Mandukya Upanishad identifies the fourth as the self to be known; Dogen's practice-realization identity treats practice as expression, not a discarded ladder.
./observations/codex/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape.md:28:This model may over-systematize living traditions. Dogen strains it most because practice-realization is neither retained as a means nor abandoned after reaching a result. The practice is the expression of realization, so the two-axis model may falsely impose a before-and-after sequence. The Heart Sutra also strains it: it denies attainment while ritually preserving the text and practice that enact the denial. A practitioner may report that the method is not possessed, released, or embodied, but simply trusted within a lineage. The raft lens itself may distort the inquiry by favoring tool-use and completion over devotion, inherited belonging, grace, and lifelong communal formation.
./observations/codex/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape.md:80:Survived critique from the raft simile, Heart Sutra no-attainment, Mandukya self-recognition, and Dogen practice-realization by narrowing the claim from method completion to post-use relation.
./observations/codex/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape.md:156:### Dogen breaks the ladder test
./observations/codex/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape.md:161:- Prediction: If Dogen's practice-realization can be described as embodied retention without a hidden completion sequence, the model survives by adding or clarifying embodiment. If it cannot fit without distortion, the model should be weakened or narrowed.
./observations/codex/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape.md:164:- Next action: Close-read Dogen against MN 22 and the Heart Sutra with attention to result language, continuation, and conduct.
./observations/codex/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape.md:189:- Close-read Dogen's Bendowa and Genjokoan against MN 22 and the Heart Sutra to test whether embodied practice breaks the retained versus abandoned axis or requires a third post-use category.
./observations/codex/2026-05-29-method-release-has-a-shape.md:190:- If this model is right, then traditions should mark different post-use instructions: Advaita-style inquiry should preserve recognition criteria, raft-like Buddhism should warn against carrying the method as identity, and practice-realization systems should shift from result language to conduct language. If these instructions do not cluster by method shape, the model is weakened.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold.md:56:- Code at least eight tradition-stage cases, including Advaita, Heart Sutra Prajnaparamita, Rinzai koan curriculum, Cloud of Unknowing, Eckhart, Zhuangzi, Dzogchen, and Sufi fana.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization.md:11:After de-identification or objectless-awareness practice, the key comparative unit is not only what remains and not only whether a remainder is inferred. The key unit is the authorization mode that permits a text, teacher, model, or practitioner to rest, investigate, deny, bracket, teach, or refuse what seems to remain. This authorization must be coded by textual stratum and level of claim: early Upanishadic passage, Advaita commentary, early Buddhist sutta, neuroscience redescription, teacher instruction, and practitioner interpretation. Valid use of the rubric requires a failure condition, such as cases where multiple modes fit every passage equally, and a human test, such as whether the resulting counsel reduces distress without increasing inflation, dissociation, nihilistic deflation, or rumination.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization.md:15:The candidate combines the proponent's residue-policy comparison with the challenger's vocabulary-bias critique and adds a stratum-level method. Neither original idea alone required every post-negation verdict to be coded by source layer, authorization mode, and practitioner effect. Its possible novelty is the claim that fidelity to tradition and usefulness to practitioners depend on the same discipline: do not let the frame decide what it claims to observe.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization.md:19:- Codex idea 3763a79cf5b05610 separated residue content from the rule that authorizes a stance after negation.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization.md:64:- Run the same coding on SN 22.59 and SN 22.95, testing whether recursive remainder-testing is stable across the Buddhist samples.
