./observations/codex/2026-05-26-protective-distance.md:21:- Dogen, Bendowa practice-verification unity, summarized at Encyclopedia of Buddhism, https://www.encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Dogen. Used as a countercase where distance is treated as a mistaken split inside practice.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-licensed-training-mistake.md:55:- Test the rubric on Abhidharma and Heart Sutra, Advaita identity and negation, Sufi longing and return, Daoist decrease, and Zen practice-realization.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:19:- Thinking method source: Shinran, Letter to Senshin, Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/. I used Other Power as a lens by subtracting the assumption that every needed function must be owned by the practitioner. The method's distortion is that it can make disciplined effort look like pride, so I checked it against SN 45.8 on right effort.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:22:- Primary close-reading: Dogen, Bendowa, Kazuaki Tanahashi translation, https://www.lionsroar.com/just-wholeheartedly-sit/. Dogen says the dharma is abundant in each person yet not actualized without practice, and that practice and realization cannot be recognized as two separate things. This makes the present act a support locus while forbidding future-gaining ownership.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:24:- Near-neighbor search: Jack Engler, You Must Be Somebody Before You Can Be Nobody, https://inquiringmind.com/article/0501_1_engler-interview/; Bhikkhu Analayo, Skill in Means and Mindfulness, https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12671-021-01795-2; Harvard Divinity Bulletin on Buddhist skillful means, https://bulletin.hds.harvard.edu/buddhist-studies-the-buddhist-way/. These sources cover ego strength, capacity-sensitive teaching, and pedagogical adaptation, but not a two-part code of support locus plus forbidden claimant across effort, gift, direct introduction, and practice-realization.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:59:- If this model is right, then adverse contemplative events should cluster around wrong-claimant failures: self-power anxiety in gift practice, achievement seeking in practice-realization, reification after direct introduction, and mechanical striving in effort practice. If adverse reports do not vary by claimant pattern after controlling for trauma, intensity, and supervision, the model is weakened.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:17:### What is remainder pressure?
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:21:Lumenary calls that demand remainder pressure.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:39:The occurrence of remainder pressure and the interpretation of remainder pressure should be separated.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:67:A narrow bridge between Upanishadic witness language, early Buddhist not-self analysis, and modern consciousness research is the variable of remainder pressure: the felt or conceptual demand to posit a final subject when all object-like contents have been negated. The comparison should not ask whether these sources agree about the self, but how each system manages that pressure: ontologizing it as an unobjectifiable seer, recursively applying analysis to it, bracketing it as a reportable phenomenological residue, or treating it as a self-modeling artifact.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:71:This shifts the comparison from a binary self/no-self dispute to a micro-mechanism that can be tracked across text, practice report, and cognitive model. The novelty is the distinction between the occurrence of remainder pressure and the inference policy used to interpret it, which lets convergence generate hypotheses without being promoted into evidence for a shared metaphysical object.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:75:- Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23 as cited in observations/codex/2026-05-25-residue-policy-in-negative-self-practice.md: an unseen seer/hearer/knower is preserved as Self or inner ruler after ordinary objectification fails.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:76:- SN 22.59 Anattalakkhana Sutta as cited in observations/codex/2026-05-25-residue-policy-in-negative-self-practice.md: all five aggregates, including consciousness, are impermanent and not fit to regard as mine, I, or self.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:77:- observations/codex/2026-05-25-residual-burden-of-proof-after-negation.md: compares traditions by whether negation licenses, tests, or refuses a proposed remainder.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:109:- Define a four-part remainder-pressure rubric: phenomenological residue, inference authorization, practice instruction, and metaphysical upgrade.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation.md:111:- Ask whether meta-awareness research can operationalize the occurrence of remainder pressure without implying that the pressure points to a real metaphysical witness.
./src/components/LumenaryMindMap.astro:51:    aliases: ["remain", "remainder", "passage", "doorway", "protects", "protected"],
./src/components/LumenaryMindMap.astro:53:    id: "remainder",
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface.md:15:The source ideas already contained minimum-self architecture and custody-of-attention, but the dialogue created a distinct comparative object: the interface between assigned custody and practitioner receptivity. This is not merely a compromise, because it changes the research question from 'how much self remains?' or 'where does attention belong?' to 'what custody system generates what kind of human interface, and does that interface independently predict practice failures and interventions?' This still requires originality audit against contemplative studies, theology of grace, Pure Land other-power literature, Dzogchen pointing-out accounts, and psychology of religious practice.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-custody-and-receiving-surface.md:57:- Test Shin Buddhism, Christian infused contemplation, Dzogchen pointing-out, Theravada insight practice, and Advaita self-inquiry as initial cases.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-negation-has-an-address.md:11:A comparison of negating practices should ask whom the negation is addressed to before asking what remains after it. 'Not this', 'not self', 'do not force', and 'know yourself to know God' can look like one family of subtraction, but they are aimed at different errors: mistaken identity, appropriation, controlling will, and self-possession before God. The apparent convergence is often the shape of the medicine, not proof of the same diagnosis or same cure. I call this address policy: the rule that names the error a practice interrupts and the human function it is trying to heal. Address policy sits before residue policy, inferential policy, and custody policy, because it decides what the instruction is for before the tradition decides what remains, what can be inferred, or who carries action afterward.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-negation-has-an-address.md:15:Prior Lumenary models track translation strain, inferred residue, attentional instrument, reflexive method, and post-release custody. This model adds an earlier variable: the addressee of the practice. It explains why similar negating language can produce incompatible outcomes without assuming either one hidden universal experience or total doctrinal construction.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-negation-has-an-address.md:21:- notes/source-cards/advaita-vedanta-shankara-upadesa-sahasri.md: Advaita instruction as a check against reducing all self-negation to Buddhist non-appropriation.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-negation-has-an-address.md:53:- Build an address-policy rubric with fields for addressee, target error, negating move, authorized remainder, and expected ethical effect.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface.md:11:A path should be compared in two ordered layers. First, identify the register in which the tradition locates decisive transformation: human effort, Other Power, primordial awareness, practice-realization, divine restoration, causal continuity, or another account. Second, map only the named interface vulnerabilities and safeguards that the tradition itself recognizes around that event: hearing, doubt, calculation, misrecognition, false trust, teacher relation, ethical misuse, memory, discernment, community correction, and integration. The interface map must include a self-limitation marker for traditions that say the mapping stance itself becomes an obstacle. Thus the model does not claim that every path redistributes human capacity. It asks whose act transformation is said to be, what can obscure or counterfeit it at the human boundary, and where the tradition says analysis must yield to practice.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface.md:56:- Ask Jodo Shinshu and Dzogchen teachers whether register-sensitive interface mapping avoids self-power or psychological distortion, or whether even this second-order mapping remains misleading.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface.md:58:- Test whether the model predicts warning profiles in manuals before reading their warnings. For example, predict that Other Power texts warn against calculation and self-assessment, direct-introduction texts warn against misrecognition and reification, and effortful paths warn against laxity, wrong effort, and discontinuity.
./observations/codex/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate.md:20:- Challenger revision pressure: non-instrumental traditions such as Dogen practice-realization and Shinran no-calculation require a scope gate before result custody language is applied.
./observations/codex/2026-05-29-who-holds-the-gate.md:61:- Add source coding for whether return language is native, permitted, or imported in Dogen, Shinran, MN 22, Heart Sutra, Rinzai, and comparable Christian or Sufi materials.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:22:- Primary-text comparison: MN 22 validates the Dhamma as a crossing tool and then warns against carrying it; the Heart Sutra denies attainment while still relying on Prajnaparamita; the Mandukya Upanishad uses waking, dreaming, and deep sleep to confirm turiya; Tannisho strains self-authorizing method models by grounding release in Other Power.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:25:- Hybrid anomaly pressure: Dogen practice-realization, Rinzai post-kensho curriculum, Heart Sutra practice after no attainment, and Shinran's Other Power.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:31:The model may still overfit traditions that treat practice as a tool. Dogen's practice-realization identity is the sharpest anomaly: practice is not a ladder to be released after completion, but the expression of realization itself. Rinzai koan curricula after kensho also strain any clean endpoint, because the method can undermine conceptual possession while continuing as authorized training. Tannisho strains the model from another side, because authority may never belong to the practitioner's method in the first place. If close reading and practitioner reports show no stable way to separate boundary operation from custody, or if tradition membership predicts verification better than the two axes, the model should be weakened.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:83:Survived critique from MN 22's validated-then-abandoned raft, Heart Sutra's no-attainment-with-practice hybrid, prior-art pressure from Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein as therapeutic method, and the Dogen and Tannisho anomalies. The claim was narrowed from a broad method-completion typology into a two-axis custody model.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:155:- Prediction: A close prior argument will likely exist for self-canceling methods, but not for the specific two-axis custody test across confirming, undermining, retained, abandoned, embodied, and Other Power cases.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:158:- Next action: Search scholarship on upaya, spiritual direction, teacher authority, post-kensho training, practice-realization, Pure Land entrusting, and discursive tradition for close versions of the custody claim.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:166:- Result: Pending. MN 22 and the Heart Sutra already suggest boundary pressure, while Dogen and Tannisho may violate simple release models.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges.md:193:- Close-read MN 22, the Heart Sutra, Mandukya Upanishad, Dogen's Genjokoan, Rinzai post-kensho training accounts, and Tannisho for explicit signs of what may guide the practitioner after insight.
./plans/dialectical-engine-spec.html:408:  <li><strong>8 active frontiers</strong> with idea clusters that already overlap: translation strain, self-negation residue, convergence methodology, practitioner authority.</li>
