./notes/source-cards/neoplatonism-plotinus-enneads.md:32:**Emanation vs. Creation:** Emanation preserves ontological continuity between source and product; creation ex nihilo posits a fundamental gap. This structural difference has profound implications for consciousness's relationship to matter.
