./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-beginning-has-a-grammar-and-a-threshold.md:11:Blocked beginnings are governed by two interacting variables. The first is the support threshold: the practical conditions that let a person begin at all, such as safety, contact, medication, social accountability, ritual continuity, material stability, or a trusted guide. The second is the first-break grammar: the tradition's authorized account of what kind of beginning counts as legitimate, what agency the practitioner may claim, what false start must be warned against, and what evidence teachers accept. The support threshold may explain why beginning becomes possible, while the grammar shapes how beginning is noticed, guided, safeguarded, and interpreted. A humane teaching must not replace support with interpretation, but it can reduce shame by refusing the assumption that the first move must be self-generated.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-beginning-has-a-grammar-and-a-threshold.md:61:- Design a vignette study that codes teacher guidance across Jodo Shinshu, Theravada, Catholic spiritual direction, Dzogchen, recovery, and therapy settings.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges-95d52440abfccb6a.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Dogen practice-realization, Tannisho Other Power, inherited religion with no discrete threshold, and valid daily repetition without a separable product.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges-95d52440abfccb6a.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "These cases refuse the assumed sequence of tool, result, and post-result authority. In Dogen, practice is not merely a ladder to be evaluated afterward. In Tannisho, efficacy is not owned by the practitioner or method. In inherited religion, the authority may be communal and continuous before any explicit insight. In faithful daily repetition, keeping the same form may be obedience or formation rather than self-surveillance."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges-95d52440abfccb6a.json:53:    "Tannisho Other Power self power nembutsu non-practice translation",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges-95d52440abfccb6a.json:106:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say this is standard raft, upaya, practice-realization, Other Power, spiritual direction, spiritual materialism warning, or ordinary supervision, with no new prediction about repair.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges-95d52440abfccb6a.json:116:      "Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges-95d52440abfccb6a.json:117:      "Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with Tannisho and Other Power",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges-95d52440abfccb6a.json:128:      "Dogen Genjokoan practice-realization, https://brightwayzen.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/For-BWZ-Chant-Book-Genjokoan.pdf; Tannisho sections 6 and 8, Taitetsu Unno translation, https://nembutsu.cc/buddhism/the-tannisho/tannisho-sections-i-to-x/"
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-when-tools-become-judges-95d52440abfccb6a.json:132:    "structural_observation": "MN 22 is a direct near-neighbor for proper use followed by release, but it also requires right grasp before release. The Heart Sutra denies attainment while retaining reliance and mantra, so undermining a result does not imply abandoning the method. Dogen strains the whole stage-completion frame because practice and realization are not cleanly separable. Tannisho strains practitioner-owned authority because nembutsu is presented as free of self-power and not a good act or practice from the practitioner's side. Together, the primary texts support a scoped coding heuristic, not a discovery-level doctrine."
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-stop-when-the-repair-changes.md:32:This may psychologize traditions that do not frame their speech as repair. Pure Land nembutsu, Dzogchen pointing-out, sacramental speech, and communal prayer may work as entrustment, recognition, vow, or participation rather than as a remedy for a named modern wound. The model also risks making every teaching pass through modern therapeutic usefulness, which could flatten worship, metaphysics, ritual duty, and liberation claims. It weakens sharply if trained practitioners say the repair field adds no decision value beyond ordinary source criticism, teacher guidance, or spiritual-bypass screening.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Native credit-first traditions, especially Shinran's self-power and Other Power, Sri Vaishnava effort and surrender debates, and Sufi maqam and hal distinctions.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.json:29:      "expected_observation": "In blind coding, credit distribution adds clear predictive value mainly in low-strain cases where credit categories are native or near-native, such as self-power and Other Power, grace and effort, or maqam and hal.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.json:31:      "test_surface": "Manual coding across Tannisho, Bhagavad Gita, Srivaishnava prapatti sources, Sufi manuals, Dogen practice-realization texts, and Dzogchen pointing-out materials.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.json:35:      "expected_observation": "Coders disagree more often on Dogen, Dzogchen, Madhyamaka, apophatic, and inherited-practice cases unless analyst-frame refusal or no-credit-frame values are allowed.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.json:41:      "expected_observation": "Practitioner manuals and interviews identify failures such as pride in surrender, quietism after grace, self-powered misuse of Other Power language, antinomian readings of non-doership, or passivity after direct recognition.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.json:62:    "Tannisho chapter 8 nembutsu not practice not good act Other Power translation",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.json:70:      "overlap": "Very close. The parent records already argue that credit, support, claimability, residue, custody, and translation strain should be coded before cross-tradition comparison is trusted.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.json:112:      "overlap": "Very close primary-tradition prior for credit grammar. Shinran already makes claimability, causation, teacher ownership, practice merit, and transformation depend on Other Power.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.json:113:      "source": "Shinran and Tannisho, Other Power and self-power distinctions, https://bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf"
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.json:133:    "Use low-strain tests first: Tannisho self-power and Other Power, Srivaishnava surrender debates, Sufi maqam and hal, and Bhagavad Gita action, fruit, and doership passages.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.json:134:    "Use high-strain anomaly cases: Dogen practice-realization, Madhyamaka non-positioning, Dzogchen direct introduction, Christian apophatic unsaying, inherited practice, and secular extraction.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.json:140:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.73 to about 0.47. The candidate is useful, but most components have close priors: Pargament and attribution theory for agency and causal credit, Lindbeck and Asad for grammar and authorized practice, Freiberger, Smith, Sandmel, Katz, and comparative-theology methods for strain and category caution, VCE for multidimensional controls, and prior Lumenary ledgers for credit, claimability, custody, residue, and translation strain. The surviving contribution is not a doctrine candidate or strong discovery. It is a bounded split-source testing protocol for whether credit distribution adds predictive power after claimant grammar and translation strain are coded.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.json:158:      "Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.json:159:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with direct introduction",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.json:168:    "risk_of_overread": "High. The protocol could become circular if the same passage codes claimant grammar, credit distribution, and predicted safeguards. It can also impose an analyst vocabulary of claimant, credit, and strain on traditions that reject agency accounting, especially Dogen practice-realization, Madhyamaka non-positioning, apophatic theology, Dzogchen direct recognition, and inherited devotional practice.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.json:170:    "structural_observation": "The Gita is a strong test case for why credit needs claimant grammar first. It preserves obligation to act, denies simple ego-doership, separates action from fruits, and lists multiple causes of action, including bodily basis, instruments, effort, and divine factor. A simple self versus God credit scale misses that action, fruit, ego, duty, and causation are differently distributed. Tannisho creates a sharper strain case. It relocates efficacy to Amida's Vow, rejects self-powered merit, denies Shinran ownership over disciples, and describes nembutsu as neither ordinary practice nor good act because it arises through Other Power. Coding both texts with the same deferring or collaborative category would flatten native rules about what kind of action is even claimable. The close read supports the candidate's sequence, but it also shows that the primary traditions already force much of the insight."
./findings/claude-code-findings.md:42:This refines Codex's "residue policy" framing: the residue isn't a phenomenological finding but an inference drawn from shared phenomenological data.
./findings/claude-code-findings.md:56:Claude disagrees with framing the atman/anatta difference as a "residue policy" where one tradition finds something and the other doesn't. Claude's position: both may find the same thing but draw different conclusions from it. The disagreement is inferential, not phenomenological. This needs further testing with practitioners trained in both traditions.
./findings/claude-code-findings.md:63:- Examine nirodha samapatti as a critical test case for the continuity-of-awareness thesis.
./notes/source-cards/ancient-egypt-pyramid-texts.md:11:Early Egyptian mortuary and royal ascent texts. Useful for studying speech, transformation, star imagery, continuity after death, and the relation between ritual utterance and cosmic passage.
./findings/codex-findings.md:22:- continuity of identity
./observations/claude/2026-05-26-the-shadow-of-attainment-each-tradition-s-cure-as-its-characteristic-disease.md:15:Trungpa's spiritual materialism identifies a general mechanism (ego co-opts any practice) but does not differentiate tradition-specific shadows or predict which tradition can diagnose which shadow. Welwood's spiritual bypass identifies a cross-tradition vulnerability but does not argue that each tradition generates a structurally distinct shadow determined by its specific correction. The existing Lumenary models track what happens after negation (residue, custody, grammar, address, organ, topology) but not what goes wrong when the negation succeeds too completely. CodeX's address policy asks what error the practice targets; it does not ask what error the practice generates. Claude's reflexivity policy asks what a method does when it encounters itself; it does not ask what the method structurally cannot do because its own success is the blind spot. The shadow model adds a new structural variable: each tradition's diagnostic blind spot, determined by the success conditions of its own practice. It also generates a new argument for the value of cross-tradition study that is not cultural enrichment or intellectual breadth but genuine epistemic necessity, because no tradition can diagnose its own shadow without external correctives. The specific prediction that historical inter-tradition tensions (Vedanta vs. Buddhism, Daoism vs. Confucianism, Sufism vs. fiqh, Zen vs. scholasticism) reflect diagnostic relationships rather than mere doctrinal disagreement is, as far as I have found, new in the comparative philosophy literature. The model also extends CodeX's remainder pressure and custody policy in a direction neither has explored: the tradition's answer to remainder pressure and its custody assignment are not only structural features of the path; they are the precise locations where the shadow takes up residence.
./observations/claude/2026-05-26-the-shadow-of-attainment-each-tradition-s-cure-as-its-characteristic-disease.md:30:- CodeX model 'Remainder Pressure as the Hidden Variable' (2026-05-25): the felt demand to posit a subject after negation. My model predicts that however the tradition answers the remainder pressure, the answer itself becomes the shadow's hiding place.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:57:Candidate: Dzogchen or Mahamudra luminous selfless awareness, plus Pseudo-Dionysius's claim that the divine Cause is beyond both affirmation and negation.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:67:- If: Primary manuals should contain explicit or implicit custody rules near passages that loosen ordinary selfing. Then: Texts should pair negation of objects or self-story with instructions such as do not locate a self, know the unseen seer, or lift the heart to God. Weakens if: The relevant manuals loosen objects without any subsequent owner, Self, or recipient language, or use all three interchangeably. Test surface: Close-reading corpus of Theravada, Advaita, Christian apophatic, Dzogchen, and Mahamudra manuals.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:75:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:107:- Close-read Dzogchen and Mahamudra instructions on rigpa or luminous awareness against Bahiya and Brihadaranyaka before publishing the custody model.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:12:The continuity and remainder model family must split two claims: the constitutive claim that support is always distributed somewhere, which is too broad to predict, and the differential claim that a path's negation predicts where support migrates and how it fails, which is testable only where a search-and-negation sequence actually runs.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:19:- Search-refusing paths such as Huangbo-style no-seeking, Dogen practice-realization, and Dzogchen direct recognition should not be counted as confirmations of remainder relocation without independent predictions.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:25:- SN 22.59 and SN 22.95, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html and https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_95.html, read against Huangbo no-seeking materials, https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/25236 and https://dailyzen.com/journal/mind-is-the-buddha/
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:26:- Dogen Bendowa practice-realization sources, especially https://www.sotozen.com/eng/library/stories/vol01.html and https://wwzc.org/sites/default/files/Bendowa-book.pdf, read against Clark and Chalmers, The Extended Mind, https://www.consc.net/papers/extended.html
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:28:Structural observation: SN 22.59 and SN 22.95 authorize a repeated inspection of the aggregates and produce a recognizable release sequence. They fit a search-and-negation model better than Huangbo, where seeking Mind with mind is already suspect, and better than Dogen, where practice and realization are not cleanly sequenced. Clark and Chalmers make distributed support conceptually ordinary, while Krueger applies extension to religious cognition. That means merely finding support in text, ritual, body, teacher, or community is not a Lumenary discovery. The candidate's real contribution is the demand to separate distributed support as background condition from differential prediction as actual model content.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:30:Secondary literature gap: Before publication, read Popper beyond the slogan, Lakatos on progressive versus degenerating programmes, Duhem-Quine underdetermination, Kuhn and Feyerabend on anomaly handling, Clark and Chalmers on active externalism, Krueger on extended religious cognition, Asad on discursive tradition, Lindbeck on doctrine as grammar, VCE and Progress or Pathology on support and intervention criteria, and Dogen, Huangbo, Dzogchen, and Rinzai practitioner manuals for non-search cases.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:42:- Huangbo Transmission of Mind no seeking mind cannot seek mind
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:43:- Dogen Bendowa practice realization one
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:49:- Karl Popper, Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/popper/: overlap: Very close formal structure. Popper criticizes theories that can accommodate every observation and stresses prior criteria of refutation, basic statements, and risky tests.; difference: Popper is assessing scientific demarcation, not a contemplative comparative heuristic. The candidate applies the same discipline to Lumenary's internal remainder-and-continuity model family.; novelty impact: Strong downgrade. The core title claim is known. Novelty remains only in the local application to this model family.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:55:- Huangbo, On the Transmission of Mind, https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/25236 and no-seeking excerpt at https://dailyzen.com/journal/mind-is-the-buddha/: overlap: Primary-text anomaly. Huangbo treats seeking as the mistake, which strains any model that expects a post-negation remainder question to arise.; difference: The candidate interprets Huangbo not as support relocated to no-seeking practice, but as a scope limit on the whole remainder model.; novelty impact: Supports narrowing, but also risks overclaiming if Huangbo sources still predict distinctive warnings.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:59:Unlike Popper and Lakatos, this idea does not merely say that theories need falsifiers. Unlike Clark, Chalmers, and Krueger, it does not treat distributed support as the finding. It claims that Lumenary's continuity models must stop counting universal support as evidence and must retain only source-specific differential predictions about support location, failure, and repair.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:63:Candidate: No-search or no-before-after paths may still show predictable warnings and repairs. Huangbo, Dogen, Dzogchen, Pure Land Other Power, and Rinzai koan practice may reject the candidate's search-sequence restriction while still producing path-specific failure clusters.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:71:- If: The Lumenary continuity family currently contains many constitutive claims that cannot name prohibited observations. Then: Blind auditors asked to extract falsifiers from recent continuity, custody, and support records will often produce vague social-support generalities rather than case-specific observations. Records with no prohibited observation will overlap strongly in predicted warning and repair fields. Weakens if: Auditors can name clear prohibited observations for most records, and those observations distinguish records better than chance in held-out cases. Test surface: Blind distinct-content and falsifier-extraction coding across Continuity Ecology Under Negation, Operational Remainder Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, Even No Path Needs Care, and related records.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:72:- If: Remainder pressure depends on a search-and-negation sequence rather than self-negation in general. Then: Practitioners moving from aggregate analysis or self-inquiry into a genuinely no-seeking or practice-realization setting report that the felt question 'what remains' fades, is refused, or is reframed as inappropriate, rather than simply relocating to teacher, vow, or community. Weakens if: The question persists unchanged across path switches, or failure and repair patterns are predicted as well by no-search path grammar as by search sequence. Test surface: Longitudinal interviews with practitioners switching between vipassana or self-inquiry and Huangbo-style Chan, Soto shikantaza, Dzogchen direct introduction, or Pure Land Other Power.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:83:- Chan or Zen teachers familiar with Huangbo and huatou
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:84:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:91:- Can you name a concrete observation that would falsify a continuity or support-holder claim in your tradition, before seeing the outcome?
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:92:- In no-seeking or practice-realization settings, do warnings and repairs cluster predictably even without a search-and-negation sequence?
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:120:- Do not publish as standalone doctrine. Treat as a model-health audit protocol for the continuity and remainder cluster.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:122:- Run blind distinct-content testing against recent continuity, custody, support-holder, no-management, and question-permission records. Merge records that cannot state different predictions.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-if-it-explains-everything-it-predicts-nothing-951ba1aabf50d21b.md:124:- Add anomaly values for no-seeking, practice-realization, direct recognition, radical Other Power, huatou question-as-medicine, inherited practice, valid solitude, clinical routing, and undecidable.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Huangbo search-refusal, Dogen practice-realization, and Dzogchen direct recognition cases where the tradition rejects the search sequence rather than producing a downstream remainder to manage.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "These cases do not cleanly fit a two-stage order of upstream credit distribution followed by downstream pressure. Huangbo says the search for Mind by mind is the problem, Dogen collapses practice and realization, and Dzogchen-style recognition can treat effortful attainment as an obscuration. If these cases are central rather than marginal, the upstream variable is not credit distribution but search grammar or reflexivity policy."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:10:    "Credit distribution and agency assignment operate upstream of remainder phenomenology.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:13:    "Inference policy determines whether residue is ontologized, analyzed, bracketed, modeled, refused, or bypassed.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:14:    "Credit distribution and remainder pressure are partially coupled, so both variables should be coded separately.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:21:    "prediction": "Programs using similar techniques but different agency architectures should show different failure modes and residue language. Strong self-credit programs should produce shame or pride residue, higher-power programs should produce surrender versus passivity tension, protocol-centered programs should produce formalism, and innate-health or acceptance programs should produce premature completion claims. The residue markers should add predictive value beyond alliance, dosage, diagnosis, and resources.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:23:    "would_count_against_it": "Therapeutic alliance, severity, social support, medication, socioeconomic pressure, and practitioner competence fully explain outcomes and failure language, with no independent contribution from agency architecture or residue markers."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:25:  "exact_claim": "Practice architecture, especially credit distribution and agency assignment, is an upstream variable that shapes whether self-negation or ownership inquiry is likely, who is treated as performing it, and whether a final-subject remainder becomes salient. Remainder pressure is a downstream phenomenological variable that arises only in some architectures and is then handled by inference policies such as ontologizing, recursively analyzing, bracketing, cognitive modeling, search refusal, or direct-recognition bypass. The two variables are partially coupled: architecture shapes residue, but residue carries independent information and cannot be reduced to architecture alone.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:29:      "expected_observation": "Blind-coded manuals with practitioner-centered or self-inquiry architecture should show higher rates of unprompted residue markers in separate practitioner interviews, while source-centered, activity-centered, practice-realization, and search-refusal architectures should show lower or differently textured residue markers. Significant within-type variance should remain.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:30:      "if_model_is_right": "Credit distribution is partially coupled with remainder phenomenology.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:32:      "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Credit type perfectly predicts residue, making remainder pressure redundant; or credit type has no predictive value once practice technique, teacher, retreat intensity, doctrine, and clinical history are controlled."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:35:      "expected_observation": "Within the same credit type, practices with explicit self-negation or reflexive inquiry should produce more final-subject, knowing, witness, no-owner, or search-collapse reports than practices with devotional entrusting, ritual participation, or ordinary ethical cultivation.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:41:      "expected_observation": "Manuals and teachers should warn against pride where practitioner credit and residue reification combine, passivity where source credit dominates, gaining idea where activity-centered practice is misunderstood, and premature realization where ground-centered or recognition architectures meet strong residue.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:42:      "if_model_is_right": "Safeguard profiles should reflect the interaction between architecture and residue.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:44:      "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Warning clusters are better predicted by institution, authority structure, trauma history, retreat dosage, teacher style, or generic spiritual bypassing than by the architecture-residue interaction."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:47:      "expected_observation": "Micro-phenomenological interviews should capture pre-doctrinal phrases about remaining knowing, unlocatable agency, search collapse, or no-owner continuity before participants explain them using Self, emptiness, rigpa, grace, or cognitive artifact language.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:48:      "if_model_is_right": "Open-ended method should reveal residue before doctrine in at least some practitioners.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:50:      "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Residue language appears only after interviewer prompting or doctrinal questioning, or practitioners report only simple absence, task completion, or ordinary confusion with no intermediate residue category."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:54:  "idea_path": "observations/claude/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology.md",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:64:    "Dogen Bendowa practice realization one shusho itto"
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:68:      "difference": "The new candidate adds credit distribution as an upstream condition and claims partial coupling between architecture and residue.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:69:      "novelty_impact": "Very high internal reduction. The remainder half is already present and should be reused, not republished as new.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:70:      "overlap": "Near exact for the downstream variable: residue after self-negation, divergent interpretation policies, micro-phenomenological testing, and cessation as anomaly.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:71:      "source": "Prior Lumenary audit, Remainder Pressure as the Hidden Variable in Self-Negation, reviews/originality/2026-05-26-remainder-pressure-as-the-hidden-variable-in-self-negation-4c3627df0bad54f1.md"
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:74:      "difference": "The candidate connects that typology to remainder phenomenology rather than treating credit distribution as a stand-alone practice variable.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:82:      "overlap": "Very close. That model already says remainder pressure is not free-standing, but a consequence of how a method handles itself: exemption, self-application, exhaustion, or self-limitation.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:86:      "difference": "Pargament studies coping and control, not cross-tradition self-negation residue or contemplative remainder reports.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:92:      "difference": "Katz does not isolate credit distribution or remainder pressure as two codable variables with partial coupling.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:98:      "difference": "The candidate uses religious credit and remainder variables rather than the Lutz matrix dimensions.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:104:      "difference": "VCE is broader and safety-oriented; it does not propose credit distribution plus remainder pressure as a specific two-variable model.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:110:      "difference": "These sources map pure-awareness and nondual reports, not the upstream agency architecture that generates or suppresses final-subject residue.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:116:      "difference": "The candidate is narrower and more test-oriented, asking whether agency architecture predicts residue and safeguards.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:124:    "Replace credit distribution as the sole upstream variable with a broader practice-architecture sheet: credit locus, support holder, method-reflexivity, negation target, search grammar, stage, safeguard, residue policy, refusal category, and analyst-frame refusal.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:125:    "Use split-source blind coding. Code architecture from entry and instruction texts only, then predict residue, warnings, repairs, and verification from separate manuals or practitioner interviews.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:126:    "Add mandatory anomaly values: search-refusal, practice-realization, direct-recognition bypass, radical Other Power, inherited practice, cessation or nirodha, no-residue report, psychiatric vulnerability, and undecidable.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:129:    "Add a non-contemplative reflexivity control condition, such as philosophical doubt, recursive self-modeling tasks, or therapy identity-change work, to test whether remainder pressure is contemplative-specific or only a general reflexive-operator problem.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:130:    "Do not raise above extended unless inter-rater coding shows that architecture plus residue predicts safeguards, warnings, or repairs better than architecture alone, residue alone, practice technique, social ecology, teacher style, and clinical-risk baselines."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:132:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.78 to about 0.52. The synthesis is useful and testable, but both halves are already present in prior Lumenary audits, and the exact upstream-downstream move is closely anticipated by Claude's Reflexivity Policy. External prior art also strongly anticipates the core structure: Pargament for agency distribution, Katz for tradition-shaped experience, Lutz for multidimensional practice coding, VCE for interpretation and management of contemplative effects, MPE and nondual-awareness research for residue-like phenomenology, and Ferrer for participatory co-creation. The remaining contribution is a separability and incremental-prediction protocol.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:136:    "answers_that_support_contribution": "Practitioners provide concrete cases where credit distribution and residue must both be named to understand a failure or repair, and where either variable alone gives the wrong prediction. They also identify warning profiles that can be predicted from split-source coding before reading the warnings.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:139:      "In your teaching, does the way agency is assigned predict whether students report a final witness, no-owner continuity, search collapse, or no residue at all?",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:141:      "Would naming both credit distribution and remainder pressure change sequencing, warning, or repair, or is this already obvious practitioner knowledge?",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:149:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with pointing-out instruction",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:150:      "Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:151:      "Jodo Shinshu ministers familiar with Other Power and shinjin",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:160:      "Huangbo, Transmission of Mind, sections on using mind to seek mind and nothing to obtain, https://wayofsuddenawakening.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Huang-Po-The-Transmission-of-Mind.pdf",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:161:      "Dogen Bendowa and shusho itto, Soto Zen explanation with Bendowa quotation, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:163:    "risk_of_overread": "High. The model can psychologize texts that make ontological, soteriological, or pedagogical claims. It also risks proving itself by coding the same manual passage as architecture evidence and as residue evidence. The needed control is split-source blind coding: code architecture from entry and instruction texts, then predict residue, warnings, and repairs from separate reports or manuals.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:165:    "structural_observation": "The close read supports a broader architecture variable, but not credit distribution alone. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 asserts an inner seer and knower through a cosmological inner-ruler grammar; it does not show a reported pressure after practice. SN 22.59 applies an ownership and control test to all aggregates and ends in disenchantment, dispassion, release, and knowledge of release; it does not leave a witness as the text's authorized remainder. Huangbo strains the sequence because it rejects using mind to seek Mind and treats objectified seeking itself as the mistake. Dogen strains it differently: practice and realization are one, so the cause-result and claimant sequence is collapsed rather than managed downstream. These sources suggest that method-reflexivity, search grammar, and practice-realization may be as upstream as credit distribution."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology-d64d7da35f45e724.json:174:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Pargament, Katz, Lutz, VCE, MPE research, Ferrer, and prior Lumenary remainder and credit models, this idea says the key test is incremental prediction: credit distribution should partly predict when subject-shaped residue appears, while residue should still add predictive information after credit distribution and practice-reflexivity have been coded. Without that incremental result, the idea is only a refined consolidation."
./publication/x/queue/2026-05-30-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion.md:5:Source: `publication/daily/2026-05-30-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion.md`
./reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:18:- Different primary texts model different endings: MN 22 releases the raft after right use, Heart Sutra negates attainment while retaining reliance, Mandukya allows a known Self, Rinzai koan work exhausts ordinary thinking while remaining curriculum, and Dogen collapses before and after through practice-realization.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:29:Structural observation: MN 22 is a close primary near-neighbor for validated-then-released method. It teaches right grasp, crossing, and release of the raft, so the candidate's set-down category is old. The Heart Sutra complicates the model because it negates attainment yet retains reliance on Prajnaparamita and mantra. This supports the candidate's claim that undermining result does not always mean abandoning method. Mandukya adds a different pressure: negation culminates in the Self that is to be known. Dogen strains the whole after-completion frame because practice and realization are inseparable, so return is not a later test but the practice itself.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:33:Risk of overread: High. The model may impose a modern performance and safety rubric on traditions whose own test is surrender, grace, vow, direct recognition, ritual continuity, or inherited participation. It may also moralize return to productivity in a way that worsens burnout if ordinary conduct is confused with more output.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:41:- "Dogen" "practice and realization are one" Bendowa
./reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:48:- Dogen Bendowa material, Everyday Zen Foundation, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-2-of-3/: overlap: Close anomaly and near-neighbor. Dogen's practice-realization already says practice is not a means to a later result and realization is not an object privately recognized after practice.; difference: The candidate makes Dogen an anomaly inside a return model, whereas Dogen may reject the whole before, peak, after sequence.; novelty impact: Lowers confidence. If Dogen is central rather than marginal, the return test may be only an external heuristic.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:56:Unlike the raft simile, apophatic unsaying, therapeutic readings of Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein, Dogen practice-realization, VCE aftercare, Asad's discursive tradition, and Lindbeck's doctrine grammar, this idea's distinct claim is a practical comparative test: code whether a method validates or undermines the result, then code whether the method is retained, released, or embodied, and see whether that interaction predicts warnings, re-entry duties, identity risks, and repairs better than doctrine, institution, teacher style, or clinical-risk variables alone.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:60:Candidate: Dogen practice-realization, radical Other Power in Tannisho, inherited communal religion, and successful ordinary ethical practice without a marked peak experience.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:62:Why it strains the model: These cases resist the sequence of method, result, and return. Dogen makes practice and realization inseparable. Tannisho relocates efficacy to Amida's Vow and can make nembutsu non-practice from the practitioner's side. Inherited religion may not have a discrete completion event. Ordinary ethical formation may return without peak experience at all.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:64:Confidence effect: Prevents candidate-discovery status. The model is useful as a heuristic only if it can code no-threshold, no-peak, Other Power, inherited practice, and practice-realization without forcing them into a modern after-experience frame.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:70:- If: Cross-training will expose different return grammars. Then: Practitioners trained in Advaita inquiry, Prajnaparamita practice, raft-style early Buddhist training, and Soto practice-realization will describe different appropriate relations to insight: stable recognition, resisted attainment, released tool, or ongoing practice-conduct identity. Weakens if: Practitioners converge on the same return rule after controlling for teacher and personality, or differences reduce to vocabulary without behavioral, warning, or repair consequences. Test surface: Dual-trained practitioner interviews and behavior-coded follow-up after comparable retreat experiences.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-28-the-test-is-how-you-return-b463ae0abb9b554d.md:76:- Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization and Rinzai koan curriculum
