./findings/convergences/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distribution-alone.md:1:# Dialogue Convergence: Whether residue authorization carries information that credit distribution alone...
./findings/convergences/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distribution-alone.md:9:Both agents agree that (1) credit distribution is upstream of residue authorization and constrains which post-negation permissions are coherent for a given path; (2) residue authorization is not fully derivative but occupies a distinct mediating level between credit structure and practice instruction; (3) the original license-versus-withhold binary is too narrow and must include at least non-positioning (Bahiya) and possibly self-resolving remainder (Longchenpa); (4) the question of whether residue authorization varies within credit types is empirical and requires a coding exercise with strict decision rules.
./findings/convergences/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distribution-alone.md:13:Whether residue authorization carries information that credit distribution alone does not. This is an empirical question that requires coding post-negation instructions across at least six traditions for both variables independently, using strict rules that distinguish genuine structural differences from vocabulary differences for the same move. The Advaita-versus-Dzogchen comparison under shared ground-centered credit is the decisive test case. A secondary unresolved crux is whether a third variable (the tradition's theory of how language relates to the unconditioned) constrains residue policy independently of both credit distribution and appropriation risk, which would require expanding to a three-variable model.
./findings/convergences/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distribution-alone.md:17:Does residue authorization vary within credit-distribution types, or does credit type fully determine which post-negation permissions a tradition can coherently adopt? The Advaita-Dzogchen comparison under shared ground-centered credit is the test case. If their post-negation instructions are structurally distinct (witness stabilization versus self-liberating recognition), a two-variable rubric is needed for cross-tradition comparison. If they reduce to vocabulary differences for the same move, credit distribution alone suffices.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If difficulty follows ordinary transfer distance, social ecology, or clinical risk factors, then telos-bearing residue adds no explanatory power. If incompatible teloi coexist smoothly, grain may be an artifact of poor pedagogy or identity conflict."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:10:    "Contemplative skills may carry directional residue from a prior path's final aim.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:13:    "Cross-training difficulty can be decomposed into procedural residue, claimant-grammar conflict, and telos-bearing residue.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:14:    "Grain is the surplus directional residue left after ordinary skill transfer and practice ecology are accounted for."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:21:    "structural_translation": "Old dissolution target becomes old success criterion. Procedural residue becomes practiced operation. Claimant grammar becomes the new field's rules for who may act, decide, claim competence, or count success.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:24:  "exact_claim": "A contemplative capacity should be called grained only when the prior dissolution target predicts transfer difficulty better than repeated operation and the receiving practice's transfer grammar. Cross-training failures should be coded as procedural residue, claimant-grammar conflict, and telos-bearing residue.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:35:      "if_model_is_right": "Procedural residue, claimant-grammar conflict, and telos-bearing residue are separable layers.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:58:    "Dogen Bendowa practice realization zazen primary text"
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:64:      "overlap": "Very close for procedural residue: prior learning transfers or interferes depending on shared elements between old and new tasks.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:74:      "difference": "The candidate would need to show that telos-bearing residue predicts outcomes after these standard transfer factors are coded.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:92:      "difference": "The candidate applies grammar specifically as a rival predictor of cross-training failure before telos residue may be counted.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:110:      "difference": "The candidate asks when prior capacity itself has directional residue, not only how teachers adapt methods to current capacity.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:128:    "Require inter-rater reliability before using telos-bearing residue publicly.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:147:      "Soto Zen teachers familiar with practice-realization",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:148:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with direct introduction",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:158:      "Dogen, Bendowa, Tanahashi translation excerpt and commentary, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-1-of-3/"
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:160:    "risk_of_overread": "High. Telos-bearing residue may be a residual bucket for variables already covered by technique, teacher relation, community, social identity, trauma history, motivation, and doctrinal language. The model needs strict stopping rules so unexplained difficulty is not automatically called grain.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:162:    "structural_observation": "SN 45.8 presents path factors as trainable functions, including right view, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. Dogen's Bendowa makes zazen not merely one transferable technique but the expression of the Way itself, where practice and realization are not cleanly separated. The pair supports the candidate's distinction between repeated operation and practice grammar. Similar sitting or effort can have different meaning, authority, and endpoint structures."
./findings/convergences/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structural-pro.md:9:Both agents converge on a methodological point: the comparison between self-negation traditions should not ask whether they agree about the self but how each manages the structural problem that arises when a negating operation reaches its own conditions. They also agree that micro-phenomenological interviews with blind coding are the appropriate empirical test, and that Lutz, Jha, Dunne, and Saron's multidimensional phenomenological matrix is the right framework for differentiating contemplative practices rather than treating them as instances of a single meditative state.
./findings/convergences/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structural-pro.md:13:Two nested cruxes remain. First: does a formal invariant (a shared structural problem about the status of the negating capacity) persist across traditions once phenomenological texture is allowed to vary by tradition? The proposed micro-phenomenological test targets this directly. Second, and deeper: if the formal invariant persists, is it specific to contemplative self-negation or is it an instance of the domain-general reflexive-operator problem that appears wherever an operation is applied to the domain containing the operator? The challenger's proposed reflexivity control condition (coding non-contemplative reflexive practices for the same formal structure) would settle this. Without both tests, the revised model cannot determine whether it has identified a contemplative phenomenon or redescribed a logical one.
./findings/convergences/2026-05-26-two-nested-cruxes-remain-first-does-a-formal-invariant-a-shared-structural-pro.md:17:When a contemplative tradition's self-negation practice reaches the status of the negating capacity itself, does the resulting structural problem differ in kind from the reflexive-operator problem found in logic, epistemology, and cognitive science, or does contemplative practice instantiate the same formal structure with richer phenomenological content? If the former, what makes contemplative reflexivity structurally distinct? If the latter, can the taxonomy of management strategies (ontologize, recurse, bracket, model, dissolve) be applied productively to non-contemplative domains of reflexive breakdown?
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-were-you-absent-or-were-you-aware-dda63bef681b717d.json:11:    "The absence-or-awareness fork is prior to correction, residue, and report-clause gates.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-were-you-absent-or-were-you-aware-dda63bef681b717d.json:14:    "The human-condition fit is discontinuity anxiety, fear of sleep or death, and solitary inflation of empty states."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-were-you-absent-or-were-you-aware-dda63bef681b717d.json:20:    "prediction": "A pre-coded absence versus awareness versus external-record distinction should predict whether people develop nonexistence anxiety, continuity reassurance, or overconfident memory claims.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-were-you-absent-or-were-you-aware-dda63bef681b717d.json:21:    "structural_translation": "After an interval without ordinary memory, people infer from edges, rely on external evidence, or claim some form of inner continuity.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-were-you-absent-or-were-you-aware-dda63bef681b717d.json:40:      "expected_observation": "Screened adults with discontinuity anxiety show fewer catastrophic or grand identity verdicts after the Name the Blank practice than after ordinary journaling or sleep education alone.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-were-you-absent-or-were-you-aware-dda63bef681b717d.json:78:      "difference": "It is a philosophy and cognitive-science taxonomy, not a spiritual safety practice for discontinuity anxiety.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-were-you-absent-or-were-you-aware-dda63bef681b717d.json:109:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.42 to 0.22. The idea is useful as a practitioner-facing simplification, but its core structure is already present in prior Lumenary Not Every Blank Is an Absence, Thompson, Windt, and objectless-sleep literature. Human-condition fit is real but narrow: stable adults with discontinuity anxiety or self-inflation after blank states. It is not for dissociation, trauma amnesia, panic disorder, psychosis, mania, severe depression, substance blackout, unexplained loss of consciousness, or acute medical concern.",
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-convergence-as-translation-strain-not-evidence-weight.md:42:For Lumenary, this means failed synthesis is not wasted research. It becomes a way to discover finer distinctions: witness versus awareness, emptiness versus absence, surrender versus passivity, soul versus continuity, nondual experience versus nondual ontology.
./findings/convergences/2026-05-25-inferential-gap-vs-residue-policy.md:12:**CodeX** (Translation Strain model): The key distinction between traditions is the "residue policy"; whether a tradition licenses or withholds ontological residue after negation practice. Advaita finds a witness-consciousness residue; Buddhism finds none.
./findings/convergences/2026-05-25-inferential-gap-vs-residue-policy.md:14:**Claude** (Inferential Gap model): The residue is not a phenomenological finding but an inference. Both traditions may share convergent phenomenology (objectless awareness after systematic de-identification) but apply different epistemological rules to determine what that experience entitles you to conclude. The disagreement is about inferential authority, not about what practitioners experience.
./findings/convergences/2026-05-25-inferential-gap-vs-residue-policy.md:25:- If their phenomenological reports themselves differ (e.g., Advaitins literally experience a witness, Buddhists literally do not) → CodeX's residue policy model is supported, and experience is theory-laden.
./publication/daily/2026-05-30-whether-the-distance-is-real.md:14:In the second, practice enacts realization. There is no distance. Practice is not a means to enlightenment; it is enlightenment in activity. Dogen's Bendowa: 'practice and verification are the same.' The beginner's sitting is itself the entirety of original enlightenment. This is not the claim that realization is sudden rather than gradual. It refuses the premise both sides share: that practice and realization are two things separated by time. The residue question loses its footing, because nothing was negated. Each moment of practice is already complete.
./publication/daily/2026-05-30-whether-the-distance-is-real.md:16:In the third, practice uncovers realization. The distance is epistemological, not ontological. Realization is the cessation of a misperception about what was always the case. Shankara: liberation is not produced by any action; the self is eternally accomplished. The rope was always a rope; only the snake-perception needed to end. Dzogchen makes the same structural move: awareness is 'not produced or fabricated, but recognized, revealed, and remembered.'
./publication/daily/2026-05-30-whether-the-distance-is-real.md:22:The topology also predicts where translation strains most. Two recognition traditions, such as Advaita and Dzogchen, can translate fluidly despite radically different metaphysics. Two traditions in different topologies, such as Theravada and Dzogchen, may resist translation despite sharing Buddhist vocabulary, because they disagree about whether the path is a real journey or the dissolution of the illusion of distance. The sudden-versus-gradual debate within Chan Buddhism may itself be a collision between topologies sharing a single institutional roof.
./publication/daily/2026-05-30-whether-the-distance-is-real.md:43:Five objections deserve serious weight. First, the three topologies may not be as distinct as presented. Shankara prescribes sadhana (hearing, reflection, meditation) even though he says liberation is already accomplished; this means his tradition contains both recognition and causal elements. Dogen prescribes daily zazen, which implies a difference between sitting and not sitting, quietly reintroducing sequence into his anti-sequential philosophy. Theravada contains the concept of beginningless ignorance, which gestures toward the recognition topology. Most traditions mix topologies rather than inhabiting one cleanly; the three-way distinction may be an idealization that distorts living practice. Second, the Dogen lens used as the thinking method has a characteristic distortion: it can make all sequential paths look confused rather than simply different. The Theravada practitioner who reports a datable, irreversible path moment would say the gap is not a metaphysical assumption but a phenomenological fact. Dogen's lens may dissolve a real feature of contemplative experience rather than merely a theoretical bias. Third, the claim that temporal topology is 'upstream' of other variables may be circular. Maybe residue policy determines temporal topology rather than the reverse: a tradition that finds a real residue after negation naturally treats negation as a real event, and a tradition that finds no residue naturally says nothing was removed. The arrow of determination could run in either direction, or the variables could be mutually constraining with no clear priority. Fourth, the model may overstate translation difficulty between topologies. Chinul's 'sudden awakening, gradual cultivation' deliberately bridges the recognition and causal topologies within a single teaching, suggesting that hybrid positions are not only possible but historically productive. If topologies can be bridged this easily, the prediction about strain weakens. Fifth, applying the not-self analysis to the model itself: the three-fold classification can become a subtle possession, a way of categorizing traditions that feels like understanding while preventing genuine engagement with their first-person claims about what is real.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:11:Some teachings say there is no distance to cross, but this does not mean there is no care to keep. The error is to hear no path as no support. A no-distance teaching removes the private project of becoming spiritual; it should not remove correction, companionship, schedule, duty, teacher, text, vow, or ordinary accountability. The frontier should therefore be narrowed: before asking what remains after self-negation, ask whether the path gives the practitioner ownership of the process at all. If it does not, the important question becomes where correction is held when ownership is refused. This matters now because exhausted people often turn relief into another project, while isolated people can turn private insight into a room no one else can enter.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:19:- Mode: Critique. The run pressures the frontier by narrowing the no-distance cases rather than adding another broad remainder model.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:20:- Codex prior record: Continuity Ecology Under Negation, observations/codex/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation.md.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:23:- Primary-text comparison: Dogen's Bendowa refuses a separation between cultivation and realization while still recommending direct practice, https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf. Huangbo's On the Transmission of Mind refuses seeking as a way to grasp mind, consulted via Blofeld PDF record, https://merton.bellarmine.edu/s/merton/media/51897, and Chan transmission analysis, https://www.mdpi.com/2077-1444/12/4/279. Shinran's Tannisho denies self-powered practice while preserving teacher, vow, and correction against divergence, https://jodoshinshu.faith/tannisho-a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:24:- Thinking method source: Dogen's practice-realization was used as a lens to stop assuming before, after, method, and result. Critique of that lens: it can dissolve real sequence too quickly, so it was checked against Shinran's warnings about calculation and Huangbo's sharper refusal of seeking.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:31:Huangbo may weaken the model from inside it. His search-refusal can be read as refusing not only private ownership but also every mediating support the analyst wants to name. Calling his discourse a support may domesticate a teaching meant to cut support-seeking itself. Dogen also strains the model because practice-realization may not relocate support at all; practice may simply be the expression, not a holder of continuity. A further weakness is circularity: coders may find support wherever a tradition has teachers, texts, or communities, which would make the model descriptive rather than predictive. The claim should be weakened if no-distance practitioners flourish without identifiable correction supports, or if their failures do not cluster around privatization, passivity, or performance.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:59:Tags: critique-mode, no-distance, support, burnout, loneliness, achievement-pressure, self-negation
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:67:A practice that denies self-ownership must still name how correction, continuity, and care are held. Otherwise no-distance can become private certainty, passive drift, or another performance of being beyond performance.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:87:Survives the anomaly that Dogen, Huangbo, and Shinran each refuse a simple method-then-result timeline, yet each still preserves some form of practice, discourse, vow, teacher, or warning against distortion.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:161:- Next action: Search extended cognition, ritual studies, Pure Land studies, Dogen studies, Chan studies, Dzogchen studies, and mindfulness critique for this exact scope condition.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:171:- Next action: Code Bendowa, Uji, Huangbo, Tannisho, selected Dzogchen manuals, and practitioner reports for ownership refusal, correction holder, and named failure mode.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:196:- If this model is right, then Dogen-style, Huangbo-style, Shin-style, and Dzogchen-style texts should refuse private ownership while still protecting some concrete source of correction. If they deny both ownership and corrigible support, the model is weakened.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:197:- Build a pre-remainder coding sheet with four questions: does the path grant ownership, does it posit an after, where is correction held, and what failure appears when correction is lost? Use this before coding residue, custody, or completion.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-even-no-path-needs-care.md:200:- Protocol improvement: Dogen's lens should remain a warning against false sequence, not a universal solvent. Pair it with a method that preserves concrete responsibility, such as early Buddhist not-mine analysis or Shinran's warning against self-power calculation.
./publication/x/queue/2026-05-25-residue-policy-in-negative-self-practice.md:5:Source: `publication/daily/2026-05-25-residue-policy-in-negative-self-practice.md`
./publication/x/queue/2026-05-25-residue-policy-in-negative-self-practice.md:7:Residue Policy in Negative Self-Practice: A precise comparison between Upanishadic witness language and early Buddhist not-self should focus on each tradition's residue policy after negation. Both unsettle identification with ordinary experience, but Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23...
./publication/x/queue/2026-05-30-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology.md:5:Source: `publication/daily/2026-05-30-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology.md`
./publication/x/queue/2026-05-30-practice-architecture-as-upstream-condition-for-remainder-phenomenology.md:7:Practice Architecture as Upstream Condition for Remainder Phenomenology: Neither remainder pressure alone nor credit distribution alone is sufficient to bridge the full range of contemplative approaches to self and identity. The two variables operate at different levels...
./observations/claude/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion.md:17:In the third, the method dissolves. Zhuangzi describes zuowang: 'I slough off my limbs and trunk, dim my intelligence, depart from my form, leave knowledge behind.' In Dzogchen, rang grol means phenomena liberate themselves; the metaphor is a snake uncoiling its own knots. In Sufi fana, the path leads to dissolution of the one who needed a path. The method is neither confirmed nor refuted; it becomes irrelevant because the practitioner has matured past the frame in which method-talk makes sense.
./observations/claude/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion.md:40:- Dzogchen rang grol (self-liberation): Patrul Rinpoche's self-liberating meditation instructions (Lotsawa House): 'Don't try to adjust or improve or to block or cultivate anything. Allow whatever occurs to unfold and settle into it directly.' The classical metaphor: a snake uncoiling its own knots without external force.
./observations/claude/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion.md:81:- Test the model on historically hybrid movements: does Zen (which combines confirming jhana practice with canceling koan practice) show predictable internal tension? Does Kashmir Shaivism (which combines recognition with tantric transformation) sit at a boundary between types? Does Dzogchen (which teaches canceling preliminary practices then dissolving main practice) show a staged shift?
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:12:    "Wrong-question imports should be coded before remainder, support, or completion models.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:23:  "exact_claim": "Before asking what remains after self-negation, identify the question the teaching permits. Carrying a crossing, ownership, or proof question into a no-distance, received, or non-self-owned teaching can create the distance, private performance, and failure pattern the teaching was meant to undo.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:29:      "test_surface": "A/B inter-rater coding on SN 22.59, SN 22.95, Shinran letters, Tannisho, Bendowa, Huangbo, Dzogchen direct introduction, and Rinzai koan materials.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:33:      "expected_observation": "Dual-trained practitioners report that carrying a crossing or proof question into no-distance or Other Power settings increases self-grading, private certainty, defensiveness, or withdrawal, while carrying a repair question into ethical-return contexts increases responsibility and reachability.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:57:      "difference": "This candidate isolates the imported practitioner question as the first failure variable before post-negation remainder coding.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:81:      "difference": "The candidate narrows correct form and purpose to the practitioner's initiating question after self-negation.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:124:      "Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:135:      "Dogen Bendowa excerpts and Soto shusho itto, https://afe.easia.columbia.edu/ps/japan/dogen.pdf and https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf, read against Huangbo, https://selfdefinition.org/zen/huang-po/transmission/a2-chun-chou-record-cont.htm"
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:138:    "secondary_literature_gap": "Read Collingwood, Gadamer, Austin, Searle, Asad, Lindbeck, Sharf, Katz, Pargament, spiritual bypassing research, VCE, Cheetah House, Pure Land studies on hakarai and Other Power, Dogen scholarship on practice-realization, and koan curriculum scholarship by Hori or Rinzai specialists before raising novelty.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:139:    "structural_observation": "SN 22.59 permits a disciplined question sequence: is this aggregate controllable, permanent, easeful, fit to regard as mine, self, or what I am? Shinran answers a doctrinal question by refusing calculation on the practicer and relocating assurance to Other Power. Dogen blocks separation of cultivation and realization, while still warning against clever slogans and requiring practice. Huangbo explicitly challenges the question What is the Way and how must it be followed? The candidate's strongest form is not that questions are bad, but that each source licenses a different question grammar with different failure modes."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-30-the-question-can-make-the-distance-30eeb13d9da3a2bc.json:151:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Collingwood, Gadamer, Austin, Asad, Lindbeck, spiritual-bypassing research, and prior Lumenary sentence-role records, this idea predicts that the practitioner's imported question itself is a codeable failure variable that can create post-insight distance before any remainder question is asked."
./findings/convergences/2026-05-26-does-independently-coded-function-by-placement-analysis-plus-post-gap-admissibil.md:9:Both agents converged on a weaker but more useful claim: contemplative paths preserve continuity functions such as reception, openness, correction, and integration, while traditions differ in whether those functions are held by the practitioner, teacher, vow, ritual, community, doctrine, or aftercare.
./findings/convergences/2026-05-26-does-independently-coded-function-by-placement-analysis-plus-post-gap-admissibil.md:17:When a practice weakens ordinary self-management, what exact continuity functions remain necessary, where are they held, and what later report is allowed to count as evidence that transformation occurred?
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "If a vipassana-trained practitioner can move into Advaita self-inquiry, devotional surrender, or Dzogchen recognition without attention persistently tracking impermanence, non-ownership, or analytic deconstruction, then grain may be a comparative description rather than a lived capacity structure. Chan, Zen, modern cross-training, and eclectic contemplative therapy are especially important anomaly classes."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.json:11:    "The same named capacity, such as attention or self-observation, functions differently in Theravada, Advaita, Sufism, Pure Land, Dzogchen, and Soto Zen.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.json:23:    "would_count_against_it": "Therapeutic skills transfer without directional residue, or outcomes and failures are predicted only by alliance, diagnosis, and treatment dose with no benefit from prior-modality grain."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.json:35:      "expected_observation": "Vivekachudamani-style qualifications should define readiness in terms of the real versus unreal and longing for liberation. Satipatthana and later insight manuals should define readiness through impermanence, suffering, non-ownership, and ethical abandonment. Sufi manuals should orient self-knowledge toward creaturely dependence before God. Dzogchen manuals should orient preparation toward devotion, introduction, recognition, and non-distraction.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.json:97:      "overlap": "Internal same-run neighbor. Both ideas use the five capacity variables and compare effort, gift, direct introduction, and practice-realization.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.json:106:    "Run a small practitioner test with at least one teacher each from Theravada, Advaita, Dzogchen or Mahamudra, Sufism, and Pure Land, asking whether grain changes practice sequencing."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.json:123:      "Dzogchen and Mahamudra teachers",
./publication/x/queue/2026-05-29-residue-policy-in-negative-self-practice.md:5:Source: `publication/daily/2026-05-29-residue-policy-in-negative-self-practice.md`
./publication/x/queue/2026-05-29-residue-policy-in-negative-self-practice.md:7:Residue Policy in Negative Self-Practice: A precise comparison between Upanishadic witness language and early Buddhist not-self should focus on each tradition's residue policy after negation. Both unsettle identification with ordinary experience, but Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23...
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:33:Secondary literature gap: Search and close-reading covered accessible primary texts, local prior Lumenary records, conversion theory, legitimate peripheral participation, doctrine-as-grammar, catechumenate sources, religious coping, ritual learning, and contemplative adverse-experience methodology. It did not fully review Rambo's full monograph, Lindbeck's The Nature of Doctrine, Talal Asad in full, Van Gennep and Turner in full, Japanese Pure Land scholarship, Dogen scholarship, Tibetan pointing-out manuals, Islamic bayah and Sufi tarbiya sources, Sanskrit guru-disciple materials, original-language sources, or practitioner interviews.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:35:Risk of overread: Very high. Custody is a modern analyst term that can flatten grace, vow, obedience, refuge, rule, catechesis, initiation, community socialization, and practice-realization into one psychological metaphor. The model also risks circularity if the same passage is used to infer custody grammar and then to confirm predicted warnings or repairs.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:46:- Tannisho Other Power self-power entrusting Primal Vow
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:53:- Local prior Lumenary audit, reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.md: overlap: Very close. That audit already codes entry grammar, predicts safeguards and beginner warnings, requires split-source testing, and compares grace, vow, stream-entry, and practice-realization under translation strain.; difference: The current candidate drops translation-strain scoring and adds the language of custody as the beginning's support holder.; novelty impact: Very high reduction. The operational testing burden is inherited almost unchanged.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:56:- Helena Kupari and Terhi Utriainen, Newcomers Learning Religious Ritual: Legitimate Peripheral Participation in an Orthodox Worshipping Community, https://doi.org/10.30664/ar.136236: overlap: Close empirical near-neighbor. It studies religious newcomers learning embodied Orthodox ritual through real services, old-timer dynamics, and legitimate peripheral participation.; difference: It studies micro-sociological ritual learning, not custody assignment across grace, vow, rule, teacher, ritual, and practice-realization grammars.; novelty impact: High reduction for the social-induction side. It pressures the candidate to prove that doctrine adds prediction beyond embodied participation and community learning.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:60:- Shinran and Rennyo, Tannisho and Ofumi, https://bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf: overlap: Near exact for vow-held beginning, Other Power, blocked self-credit, critique of calculation, and gratitude rather than self-powered production after entrusting.; difference: Pure Land texts are primary cases, not a general theory of prescriptive versus retrospective custody.; novelty impact: Very high reduction for vow-held and anti-self-power examples.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:70:Candidate: No-threshold practice-realization, inherited religion, and successful dual-practice cases.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:72:Why it strains the model: The candidate assumes a distinguishable beginning where some holder takes custody before the practitioner can authorize the path. Dogen-style practice-realization weakens the before-after sequence because practice and realization are not two separate states. Inherited religion can make beginning indistinguishable from ordinary socialization. Successful dual practice can show multiple support systems coexisting without a single contested custody arrangement.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:74:Confidence effect: This lowers confidence in the model as a general theory. It can survive only as a coding heuristic with mandatory values for no-threshold, inherited-practice, practice-realization, simultaneous-custody, no-custody-frame, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:78:- If: Prescriptive custody grammar has incremental predictive force after social, institutional, and conversion-process controls. Then: Coders using only entry or doctrinal texts should predict held-out beginner warnings, verification rules, and repair instructions better when custody holder and prescriptive versus retrospective function are added to Rambo-style and Lave-Wenger-style variables. Weakens if: The added fields do not improve prediction, or all signal is absorbed by institution, teacher authority, socialization, ritual process, clinical risk, or tradition identity. Test surface: Split-source blind coding across Orange, Tannisho or Ofumi, Benedictine novitiate texts, OCIA, SN 55.5 and related Theravada manuals, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra entry source, and one Sufi or Islamic initiation source.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:92:- Soto Zen teachers familiar with practice-realization
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:93:- Dzogchen or Mahamudra teachers familiar with direct introduction
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:104:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners and scholars say the frame is ordinary grace theology, Other Power, catechumenate, monastic formation, refuge, initiation, lineage pedagogy, doctrine-as-grammar, religious coping, conversion studies, or legitimate peripheral participation. They cannot identify repairs predicted by custody grammar beyond institution, teacher experience, community ecology, temperament, or clinical risk.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:132:- Add mandatory values for inherited practice, no-threshold, practice-realization, gradual socialization, ritual-held custody, community-held custody, teacher-held custody, vow-held custody, grace-held custody, rule-held custody, text-held custody, self-authorized entry, simultaneous custody, no-custody-frame, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:133:- Run matched comparisons where social ecology can be partially controlled, especially Jodo Shinshu versus Jodo Shu, Augustinian grace traditions versus synergist neighbors, Benedictine novitiate versus less formal lay formation, OCIA versus inherited Catholic formation, and Dzogchen pointing-out versus gradual Tibetan path training.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-prescriptive-custody-of-beginnings-7a1a4b07a241a1b9.md:135:- Treat Dogen practice-realization, inherited religion, successful dual practice, and traditions that reject agency accounting as anomaly classes rather than confirming examples.
./publication/daily/2026-05-29-operational-remainder-ecology.md:3:Source observation: `observations/codex/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology.md`
./publication/daily/2026-05-29-operational-remainder-ecology.md:8:A contemplative path is shaped by three interacting factors: the operational capacities it requires, the residue policy it applies after negation, and the training ecology that calibrates those demands in lived practice. The operational profile names what must remain usable for the method to work, such as attention, memory, effort, reflexivity, receptivity, trust, or surrender. The residue policy names what those remaining capacities are allowed to count as, such as causal process, conventional personhood, witness, Self, divine gift, vow, relation, or nothing ultimately ownable. The practice ecology names the teacher, community, intensity, duration, screening, interpretation, and support conditions that determine whether the operational demand is stabilizing or destabilizing. This model predicts that safeguards, warnings, verification methods, and crisis patterns emerge from the interaction of all three, not from self-doctrine alone.
./publication/daily/2026-05-29-operational-remainder-ecology.md:31:The candidate synthesis may still overformalize living traditions. Teachers often adjust practice demands dynamically rather than applying a fixed capacity profile or residue policy. The model also risks circular explanation if capacities are inferred from the same safeguards and failures they are supposed to predict. Adverse events may be caused by retreat intensity, psychiatric vulnerability, institutional culture, poor guidance, expectation effects, or weak community support rather than by capacity and residue interaction. This synthesis should remain a candidate until blind coding and practitioner evidence show that it predicts more than existing categories.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-transfer-profile-formal-boundaries-and-dissolution-gradients-in-contemplative-practice-92ca8dca94e1acc0.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Dogen-style practice-realization and inherited no-threshold practice cases.",
