./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2130:    "structural_observation": "The contrast is textually real but needs narrowing. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 is not merely a meditation report after negation. It is part of the antaryamin sequence, where the inner ruler is within cosmic elements, beings, organs, mind, and knowledge. SN 22.59 is not a general ontology of every possible remainder; it is an analysis of the aggregates as unfit for appropriation. The proposed residue policy works if it is limited to the comparison between authorized Self-language and non-appropriation of aggregate consciousness."
