./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2424:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.58 to 0.39. The exact structural split is already present in classical Indian debate, contemporary dreamless-sleep taxonomy, objectless-sleep micro-phenomenology, and prior Lumenary gap-report audits. Human-condition fit is real but narrow: discontinuity anxiety and death anxiety after ordinary blank gaps. It is not for trauma amnesia, dissociation, panic disorder, substance blackout, frequent unexplained loss of consciousness, or people who will use the gap to intensify metaphysical rumination.",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2450:    "risk_of_overread": "High. Claimed transparency is not proven transparency. Micro-phenomenological work can reveal residual ownership, location, agency, modality-like sensations, and interview effects. A practice for discontinuity anxiety can also feed derealization, sleep fear, or obsessive checking if it is used by people with trauma, dissociation, panic, or unexplained loss of consciousness.",
