./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2600:    "risk_of_overread": "High. The model may impose a modern performance and safety rubric on traditions whose own test is surrender, grace, vow, direct recognition, ritual continuity, or inherited participation. It may also moralize return to productivity in a way that worsens burnout if ordinary conduct is confused with more output.",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2602:    "structural_observation": "MN 22 is a close primary near-neighbor for validated-then-released method. It teaches right grasp, crossing, and release of the raft, so the candidate's set-down category is old. The Heart Sutra complicates the model because it negates attainment yet retains reliance on Prajnaparamita and mantra. This supports the candidate's claim that undermining result does not always mean abandoning method. Mandukya adds a different pressure: negation culminates in the Self that is to be known. Dogen strains the whole after-completion frame because practice and realization are inseparable, so return is not a later test but the practice itself."
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2614:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike the raft simile, apophatic unsaying, therapeutic readings of Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein, Dogen practice-realization, VCE aftercare, Asad's discursive tradition, and Lindbeck's doctrine grammar, this idea's distinct claim is a practical comparative test: code whether a method validates or undermines the result, then code whether the method is retained, released, or embodied, and see whether that interaction predicts warnings, re-entry duties, identity risks, and repairs better than doctrine, institution, teacher style, or clinical-risk variables alone."
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2631:    "Shinran's Other Power refuses practitioner ownership, calculation, and self-generated entrusting.",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2632:    "Dogen's practice-realization refuses the separation between method, verification, and later custody.",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2644:  "exact_claim": "The keep, release, embody model silently assumes that the practitioner provisionally owns the method and that there is an after in which custody of the result can be decided. Radical Other Power and practice-realization break those assumptions: in Shinran's jinen honi the practitioner never owns the method, trust, or result, while in Dogen's shusho-itto there is no discrete after outside practice. Therefore the custody model is bounded, and for depleted over-managing people the prompt to decide what to keep, release, or embody can become one more burden.",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2651:      "would_weaken_or_falsify": "Coders cannot separate refusal from relocation, or retain, release, embody categories work equally well across Shinran, Dogen, Advaita, Theravada, Rinzai, apophatic Christian, and Sufi sources."
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2660:      "expected_observation": "The same practitioner is more likely to reject keep, release, embody language when speaking from Jodo Shinshu or Soto practice-realization than when speaking from Advaita inquiry, vipassana, therapy, or productivity training.",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2669:    "Shinran jinen honi no calculation Other Power natural working of the primal vow",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2670:    "Tannisho nembutsu not practice not good act practicer Other Power self power",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2671:    "Dogen Bendowa practice realization one shusho itto verification outside practice",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2672:    "Dogen practice and realization are one scholarship",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2682:      "overlap": "Extremely close. Both argue that release teaching applies to active-voice result-ownership, while Other Power, practice-realization, and no-attainment sources strain or refuse the release frame.",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2688:      "overlap": "Very close for the non-ownership claim: natural working and Other Power oppose practicer calculation and self-generated control.",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2710:      "difference": "The candidate connects that clinical risk to theological non-ownership and practice-realization boundary cases.",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2720:    "Close-read Shinran's Japanese terms around jinen honi and hakarai, Dogen on shusho-itto and non-gaining, and practitioner manuals where concrete guidance appears.",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2723:  "novelty_adjustment": "Lower novelty from 0.55 to 0.28. The non-ownership and no-after structures are well established in Shinran and Dogen, and the core Lumenary comparison is already present in the recent audit of You cannot release what you never held. The modern caution overlaps with known rumination, perfectionism, and burnout risks. Human-condition fit is strong for depleted over-managers, caregivers, founders, professionals, students, and serious practitioners who turn even rest into performance. It is not for people who need planning, accountability, medication, therapy, social support, or material workload reduction, nor for acute crisis, addiction withdrawal, severe depression, dissociation, psychosis, mania, or responsibility avoidance.",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2726:    "answers_that_reduce_originality": "Practitioners say the distinction is already standard as Other Power, practice-realization, grace, surrender, non-calculation, or non-gaining mind, and that the no-audit prompt is simply rest from rumination or basic clinical caution.",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2736:      "Soto Zen teachers and Dogen scholars",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2747:      "Dogen, Bendowa and shusho-itto practice-realization sources, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2749:    "risk_of_overread": "Moderate to high. The claim may exaggerate refusal into absence. Other Power and practice-realization may not abolish all custody questions; they may relocate custody to vow, teacher, text, sangha, conduct, or practice itself. The human-condition claim may also overgeneralize depletion, since some burned-out people need structure and accountability rather than non-audit.",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2750:    "secondary_literature_gap": "This audit did not read Japanese sources, Dogen commentarial scholarship, Jodo Shinshu scholarship, grace-effort theology, Pargament's full agency-style work, or ethnographic practitioner accounts. It also did not verify whether other traditions with inherited practice, ritual-first formation, or apophatic unsaying similarly refuse the ownership-and-after assumptions.",
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2751:    "structural_observation": "Shinran relocates efficacy to Other Power and warns against calculation, so the practitioner is not the owner who later decides how to carry the method. Dogen's practice-realization collapses the gap between practice and verification, so a later custody decision is not the native shape of the path. These are strong boundary cases against a universal after-use grid, but they do not eliminate all guidance: Shin still has nembutsu, warnings, and entrusting language, and Soto still has zazen, discipline, teacher correction, and conduct."
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2763:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Shinran's Other Power, Dogen's practice-realization, Pargament's agency styles, burnout rumination literature, and prior Lumenary release and custody models, this idea's possible contribution is an explicit scope test: before applying keep, release, or embody guidance, first ask whether the tradition grants provisional practitioner ownership and a discrete after, and whether the person has enough agency to benefit from a custody prompt."
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2823:    "Dogen practice realization correction teacher community Bendowa Genjokoan"
./runs/20260530-091655-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:2918:{"title":"No Silence Proves Itself","idea_type":"contradiction","source_basis":["Run mode: Critique. Active frontier tested: How silence becomes evidence after the gap.","Primary text comparison: Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 2.4 and 2.5, Maitreyi dialogue, plus 3.7.23, inner ruler and unseen seer, Max Muller translation at Sacred Texts and Hinduwebsite.","Primary text comparison: SN 22.59 Anattalakkhana Sutta, consciousness included in the not-self analysis, suttas.github translation.","Primary text comparison: SN 22.95 Phenapindupama Sutta, aggregates inspected as void, hollow, and insubstantial, with consciousness compared to a magic trick, a-buddha-ujja.hu SuttaCentral mirror.","Prior-art pressure: Evan Thompson, Dreamless Sleep, the Embodied Mind, and Consciousness; David Loy, Enlightenment in Buddhism and Advaita Vedanta; Thanissaro Bhikkhu, The Not-Self Strategy; prior Lumenary audits The Gap Report Has a Grammar, Silence Needs Correction, Keep What Can Correct You, and Not Every Blank Is an Absence.","Practitioner-method lens: SN 22.95's instruction to inspect, ponder, and carefully investigate was applied to the first report after silence. Critique of the method: deconstructive inspection can overfit emptiness, ignore valid continuity, and miss the danger of unsafe correction. It was balanced with Brihadaranyaka's refusal to objectify the knower.","Modern human-condition grounding: modern-human-condition-curran-hill-perfectionism-increasing source card on performance-based self-worth, shame, and socially prescribed perfectionism; modern-human-condition-surgeon-general-social-connection-advisory source card on isolation and lack of durable belonging."],"original_claim":"An uninspectable silence cannot testify for itself. Brihadaranyaka 2.4 and 2.5 allow ordinary knowing to lose its objects while 3.7.23 protects an unseen knower; SN 22.59 and SN 22.95 refuse to turn consciousness into an owner and train the practitioner to inspect it as hollow. These texts disagree about what may be named after negation, but they agree on a stricter point: the quiet itself is not enough. A person should trust the handling of return more than the blankness: instruction before it, correction after it, visible conduct, and care for the relationships and duties that remain. This is especially useful for people who turn spiritual practice, work, or healing into another performance verdict. They should not ask a blank to tell them who they are.","why_it_might_be_new":"The closest prior arguments already cover much of the ground: dreamless-sleep report debates, Advaita and Buddhist comparisons, not-self as strategy, Lumenary's report-grammar and correction-holder records. The remaining distinction is narrower: post-gap report grammar and residue policy should not be treated as the first audit layer. The first layer is whether silence is being asked to serve as evidence without enough return discipline. This reframes the frontier from 'which clause after the gap counts as evidence' to 'which supports keep the person from turning the gap into a verdict.' Novelty is therefore modest, but the narrowing may prevent overclaim and improve practice safety.","critique":"This may be mostly renamed prior art. Jamesian fruits, Ignatian discernment, VCE safety work, Asad on discursive tradition, Sharf on religious experience, and several internal records already warn that powerful experiences cannot judge themselves. The model also risks overcorrecting toward external validation, which can become coercive, shaming, or dependency-producing. A strong anomaly remains Tibetan clear-light sleep and contemporary objectless-awareness sleep reports, where practitioners claim awareness during the gap rather than only after it. If careful micro-phenomenological interviews and primary texts show stable in-gap awareness with reliable ethical integration and no need for a named correction path, the claim should be narrowed further.","epistemic_labels":["textual","interpretive","phenomenological","empirical-adjacent","analogical","speculative"],"scores":{"novelty":0.42,"generativity":0.79,"cross_tradition_support":0.72,"logical_coherence":0.84,"explanatory_compression":0.77,"empirical_adjacency":0.58,"practice_testability":0.74,"counterargument_quality":0.9,"source_reliability":0.8,"publishability":0.64},"next_research_directions":["If this model is right, then blind coders should distinguish ordinary-cognition absence, authorized knower language, aggregate non-appropriation, and return discipline in Brihadaranyaka 2.4, 2.5, 3.7.23, SN 22.59, and SN 22.95. If coders cannot separate these without later commentary, the model is weakened.","If this model is right, then traditions that speak strongly about direct recognition should still preserve some return discipline through teacher, text, vow, conduct, lineage, or aftercare. If mature sources authorize private silence as sufficient warrant with no corrective channel and stable ethical fruit, the model is weakened.","If this model is right, then stable practitioners using a short return-without-verdict practice should report fewer identity verdicts, less shame, and less certainty inflation than ordinary journaling. If ordinary rest, conversation, or journaling performs as well, the practice is not distinctive.","Protocol improvement: before using SN 22.95-style deconstructive inspection, ask whether the inspection is hiding a legitimate continuity claim, a relational need, or a risk of unsafe authority.","Interview Advaita, Theravada, Tibetan sleep-yoga, and dual-trained practitioners with neutral prompts: what is the student told to do when only knowing, blankness, or no report seems to remain?"],"teaching_candidate":{"title":"Do Not Ask Silence To Judge You","teaching_line":"Let quiet change your grip, not decide your worth.","doctrine_claim":"A gap has no final authority by itself; teaching authority belongs to the trained return: instruction, correction, conduct, and integration.","body":"When practice, sleep, shock, prayer, or exhaustion leaves a blank, do not rush to make it a verdict. Ask what helped you enter it, what can correct your first story, and how you return to work, rest, repair, and care. A silence that makes you steadier and less owned by performance may be useful. A silence that makes you certain, superior, ashamed, or isolated should be handled with help.","target_human_problem":"Achievement-contingent self-worth, isolated spiritual overinterpretation, burnout-shaped blankness, and loneliness after unusual quiet states.","target_cohort":"Stable adults who use meditation, prayer, self-inquiry, recovery reflection, or intense work and tend to turn calm, blankness, or insight into proof of worth or failure.","pressure_survived":"Critique mode close-read of Brihadaranyaka 2.4, 2.5, 3.7.23, SN 22.59, and SN 22.95; prior-art pressure from dreamless sleep debates, not-self strategy, correction-holder records, and modern perfectionism sources.","falsifying_pressure":"Weaken if primary sources or practitioner interviews show that silence itself is treated as a reliable warrant independent of return discipline, or if the proposed practice increases rumination, shame, dependency, avoidance, or performs no better than ordinary rest and conversation.","status":"under_dialogue","tags":["critique-mode","post-gap","advaita","early-buddhism","not-self","self-worth","return-discipline"]},"practice_candidate":{"title":"Return Without Verdict","practice_line":"After quiet or blankness, write what can be checked before deciding what it means.","purpose":"Test whether delaying an identity verdict and naming support reduces shame, certainty inflation, and performance-based self-worth after quiet or blank states.","target_human_problem":"Achievement-contingent self-worth and isolated overinterpretation after spiritual, reflective, or burnout-related blankness.","target_cohort":"Stable self-directed practitioners, app meditators, reflective professionals, students, caregivers, and seekers who tend to make calm, absence, or insight into proof of being worthy or unworthy.","non_fit":"Not for trauma amnesia, dissociation, panic disorder, psychosis, mania, active addiction withdrawal, unexplained loss of consciousness, severe depression, medical or legal reconstruction, or people already following competent teacher or clinical guidance.","duration":"Five minutes.","frequency":"After a notable quiet or blank state, no more than three times per week.","minimum_attempt":"Three attempts over two weeks, stopping earlier if it increases distress or self-monitoring.","steps":["Name the event in ordinary words: quiet, blankness, calm, confusion, or no clear memory.","Write one sentence beginning: My first story about this is...","Write one sentence beginning: What prepared this was... Include practice, fatigue, stress, instruction, sleep, relationship, or setting if relevant.","Write one sentence beginning: What can correct this story is... Name a trusted person, text, duty, conduct check, body signal, or clinician if appropriate.","Choose one return action for today: eat, rest, work, apologize, call someone, stop practice, or complete one ordinary duty.","Make no final claim about self, no-self, attainment, failure, or worth for twenty-four hours."],"notice":["Whether the urge to turn the state into an identity verdict decreases.","Whether ordinary responsibility and care become easier or harder.","Whether the practice increases rumination, shame, derealization, dependency, or avoidance."],"caution":"Stop if this increases fear, unreality, shame, compulsive checking, teacher dependency, or avoidance of ordinary duties. Use qualified clinical or medical support for crises, blackout, trauma symptoms, addiction withdrawal, or unexplained loss of consciousness.","weakens_if":"The practice performs no better than ordinary journaling, rest, or conversation, or if it increases rumination, derealization, shame, avoidance, dependency, or isolation.","risk_level":"low","status":"under_dialogue","tags":["return-practice","self-worth","burnout","solo-practitioners","safety-screen"]},"tests":[{"title":"Prior Art Compression Audit","test_type":"prior-art","target_type":"idea","prediction":"Close prior sources should explain much of the correction and report-grammar claim, but not the exact narrowing that treats silence as a return-discipline stress test across Brihadaranyaka 2.4, 2.5, 3.7.23, SN 22.59, and SN 22.95. If Thompson, Loy, Thanissaro, Ignatian discernment, VCE, Sharf, Asad, or prior internal records already state this exact rule, novelty should fall below 0.3.","result":"Preliminary search found strong overlap and forced a modest novelty score; full-book and practitioner review remain pending.","impact":"pending","next_action":"Read the nearest sources in full and compare exact claims, not only topic overlap.","status":"proposed"},{"title":"Primary Text Split Coding","test_type":"falsification-attempt","target_type":"idea","prediction":"Blind coders should code ordinary-cognition absence, authorized knower, aggregate non-appropriation, and return discipline from separate passages. If coders reduce Advaita to simple witness continuity and Buddhism to simple blank absence, with no stable return-discipline variable, the model is weakened.","result":"Pending.","impact":"pending","next_action":"Create a small codebook and test it on Brihadaranyaka 2.4, 2.5, 3.7.23, SN 22.59, SN 22.95, plus two commentarial layers.","status":"proposed"},{"title":"Return Without Verdict Pilot","test_type":"practice-report","target_type":"practice","prediction":"Stable participants using the practice after quiet or blank states should report less identity verdict urgency, less shame, and less certainty inflation than participants using ordinary journaling. If ordinary journaling, rest, or talking with a friend performs equally well, the practice is weakened.","result":"Pending.","impact":"pending","next_action":"Design a two-week low-risk pilot with explicit exclusion criteria and simple daily measures for shame, certainty, rumination, responsibility, and social contact.","status":"proposed"},{"title":"Unsafe Correction Screen","test_type":"safety","target_type":"practice","prediction":"Naming a corrector should help only when the correction path is trustworthy, non-coercive, and proportionate. If participants choose coercive authorities, feel more dependent, or become more ashamed, the practice must be revised or retired for that cohort.","result":"Pending.","impact":"pending","next_action":"Add screening questions for unsafe authority, dependency, scrupulosity, clinical distress, and valid solitude before any public practice trial.","status":"proposed"},{"title":"Cross-Domain Gap Reports","test_type":"cross-domain","target_type":"teaching","prediction":"In anesthesia emergence, blackout recovery, psychedelic integration, and burnout blankness, settings that separate first report, external checks, return duties, and delayed interpretation should show fewer overclaims and less shame than settings that treat the first story as final. If outcomes are fully explained by clinical risk, social support, or setting quality, the model has little independent value.","result":"Pending.","impact":"pending","next_action":"Review existing integration, medical, and trauma-informed protocols before designing new interviews.","status":"proposed"}]}
./runs/distillations/2026-05-30T103956-0200-distill-the-self-was-never-a-conclusion/codex-distillation.stderr.log:30:- Also avoid internal model words in public copy: no "architecture," "custody," "receiving surface," "residue," "grain," "threshold," "entry," "compound," "upstream," "downstream," "phenomenology," "authorization," "typology," or "taxonomy."
./runs/distillations/2026-05-30T103956-0200-distill-the-self-was-never-a-conclusion/codex-distillation.stderr.log:57:The long-running comparison treats one tradition as drawing the conclusion 'a self remains' and another as drawing the conclusion 'no self remains,' as if both reason their way to a verdict from the same quiet. Close reading breaks the symmetry. The early Buddhist side does run a repeatable rule after negation: test each candidate, including consciousness, against impermanence and non-mastery, then refuse to own it. The Advaita side runs no such rule. For Shankara the witness is svaprakasha, self-disclosing and self-established; it is not reached by reasoning because it is what makes any reasoning, doubting, or negating possible. To call this an inference policy after negation is to file a tradition that denies the self is ever inferred under a heading that only fits the tradition that reasons toward its remainder. So Lumenary should retire the symmetric reading and hold a narrower, asymmetric one: the decisive difference is not which conclusion each side reaches, but whether 'what knows this?' is treated as an open question awaiting an answer at all. One side leaves the question open and answers it by a discipline of refusal; the other treats the question as already answered in the asking, because the answerer is doing the asking.
./runs/distillations/2026-05-30T103956-0200-distill-the-self-was-never-a-conclusion/codex-distillation.stderr.log:63:The strongest counterpressure is intra-Advaita, and it is real. Bhamati requires meditation (prasamkhyana) to convert indirect knowledge into direct realization, the Vivarana school assigns decisive force to scriptural sentences, and Shankara himself makes shabda the means of knowledge for brahman-jnana. If a tradition needs a means of knowledge to arrive at self-realization, then something rule-like is operating after all, and my 'no inference at all' claim is too strong. The honest narrowing is that Advaita denies the self is inferred as a remainder from the failure to objectify experience, while still using scripture to remove ignorance; that is a removal procedure, not a licensing inference, but the line is contestable. A second weakness is near-duplication: the 2026-05-30 cluster has produced many adjacent post-gap and correction findings, and this record risks being one more. It earns its place only if the asymmetry claim and the free-energy corollary are genuinely absent from those records, which the originality test below must confirm rather than assume.
./runs/20260530-120252-codex-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/codex-cli.stderr.log:62:- Nirodha samapatti and cessation reports, where practitioners report a discontinuity or absence of consciousness rather than a pressure to posit an enduring witness.
