./runs/distillations/2026-05-30T114020-0200-distill-stop-when-the-repair-changes/codex-distillation.stderr.log:63:This may psychologize traditions that do not frame their speech as repair. Pure Land nembutsu, Dzogchen pointing-out, sacramental speech, and communal prayer may work as entrustment, recognition, vow, or participation rather than as a remedy for a named modern wound. The model also risks making every teaching pass through modern therapeutic usefulness, which could flatten worship, metaphysics, ritual duty, and liberation claims. It weakens sharply if trained practitioners say the repair field adds no decision value beyond ordinary source criticism, teacher guidance, or spiritual-bypass screening.
