./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:773:- Test whether Brihadaranyaka 2.3.6 neti neti uses negation as authorization of a remainder or as refusal of predicate capture.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:774:- Compare SN 22.59 with SN 22.95 to see whether early Buddhist analysis consistently blocks remainder-claims or only rejects aggregate-identification.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:775:- Add a translation-strain rubric field called inference authorization with values such as remainder-licensing, remainder-testing, remainder-refusing, and undecidable.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:793:That permission is the residue policy.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:809:One tradition may allow a metaphysical residue: something remains, but it is not an object. Another may allow only a phenomenological residue: experience continues, but no owner is authorized. Another may allow a soteriological residue: the path works, but no final claim is needed. Another may refuse the residue entirely.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:811:This gives Lumenary a sharper way to compare traditions. Instead of asking whether two traditions agree, ask what each one does with the last remainder.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:815:The question is not abstract. A practitioner who disidentifies from thoughts may still feel that something is aware. What should be done with that felt remainder?
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:823:- licensing a remainder
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:824:- testing a remainder
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:825:- refusing a remainder
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:826:- transforming a remainder
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:827:- leaving the remainder undecidable
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:829:That map can later include Sufism, Daoism, Neoplatonism, consciousness science, and physics analogies without pretending all residues are the same kind of thing.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:839:A precise comparison between Upanishadic witness language and early Buddhist not-self should focus on each tradition's residue policy after negation. Both unsettle identification with ordinary experience, but Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 preserves an unobjectifiable seer-knower as the permitted remainder, while SN 22.59 pushes non-identification through consciousness itself and refuses to authorize any aggregate as remainder. The translation strain is therefore not simply self versus no-self; it is the final move from de-objectifying experience to either licensing or withholding ontological residue.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:854:The model risks importing later Advaita witness-consciousness into an older Upanishadic passage and reading one early Buddhist sutta as representative of all Buddhist self-analysis. It also treats doctrinal discourse as if it were a shared contemplative procedure. A stronger version needs Sanskrit and Pali term analysis, commentarial counterreadings, and examples where practice instructions actually enact the proposed residue policy.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:878:- Test the residue-policy distinction on Brihadaranyaka 2.3.6 neti neti and SN 22.95's analysis of the aggregates as insubstantial.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:880:- Create a translation-strain rubric field called residue authorization: none, phenomenological, soteriological, metaphysical, or undecidable.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:881:- Ask whether modern reports of meta-awareness describe a phenomenological residue without settling the ontological residue question.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:958:The current Lumenary models mostly track what happens inside or between traditions: residue, inference, reflexivity, custody, epistemic organs, and attentional instruments. This model adds a meta-comparative variable: what the researcher does to a practice by making it claimlike. It is not a rejection of comparison. It is a way to price the extraction cost before rewarding convergence.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1347:- Claude rebuttal in turn 2, which revised the model into reflexive operations at the verification boundary and added Dogen's practice-realization identity.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1354:The candidate may still impose comparability on traditions that do not recognize a discrete arrival, authorization event, or stable boundary. It risks circular coding if the same texts define both the authority boundary and the reflexive operation assigned to it. It also remains vulnerable to textual elitism unless checked against teacher protocols, practitioner reports, community safeguards, and historical institutions. It should not be promoted until an originality audit searches for prior models in comparative mysticism, ritual authority, religious institutional theory, and practice-realization scholarship.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1381:- Apply the template to at least eight cases, including Mandukya Advaita, Heart Sutra Madhyamaka, Rinzai koan training, Dogen's Soto Zen, Eckhart, Teresa of Avila, Dzogchen, and Sufi fana.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1442:- Code at least eight tradition-stage cases, including Advaita, Heart Sutra Prajnaparamita, Rinzai koan curriculum, Cloud of Unknowing, Eckhart, Zhuangzi, Dzogchen, and Sufi fana.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1502:- Treat Dogen, Shankara, and Dzogchen as boundary cases unless a source-specific claimant grammar shows that credit language is admissible.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1517:A tradition's account of spiritual entry is best modeled as a compound grammar with four fields: what incapacity blocks ordinary entry, what minimum participation counts as real entry, what break mechanism is required if self-generated threshold entry is denied, and what residue policy governs claims after ordinary agency is negated. First-break type is not universal. It becomes an irreducible variable only in high-severity traditions that explicitly deny that any naturally self-generated threshold act can found the path.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1521:Neither source idea contained the full compound model. The First-Break Problem supplied entry mechanism and anthropology. Residual Burden supplied residue policy after negation. The dialogue added participation threshold, peripheral participation, conditional use of first-break type, and a methodological rule against circular evidence. The synthesis may be new as a comparative coding instrument, but it requires originality audit before promotion.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1534:The synthesis risks becoming too complex for the evidence. Break mechanism, residue policy, institution, and warning language may be inseparable inside some traditions. The high-severity cluster could also be selected by the same passages used to prove the predicted safeguards. Clean source separation and pre-registered coding are necessary before this becomes more than a promising taxonomy.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1559:- Pre-register coding rules for threshold acceptance, incapacity diagnosis, residue policy, institution, and break mechanism.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1561:- Test six cases: Theravada sangha entry, Confucian cultivation, Jodo Shinshu, Augustinian grace, Zen great doubt, and Dzogchen pointing-out.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1562:- Add a dialogue test asking whether a modern therapeutic or educational practice solves entry through threshold, scaffold, gift-like support, self-disclosure, or residue refusal.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1576:Self negating or self transcending paths do not simply require a minimum self, and they do not only differ by final residue. They organize a continuity ecology. Each path must preserve enough receptivity and reliability for transformation to occur, but that continuity can be internally managed, externally scaffolded, relationally entrusted, ritually stabilized, institutionally maintained, or theologically relocated. The path's dissolution target may pressure where continuity migrates, while its residue policy governs what may be authorized after negation. Practice ecology may either express that doctrinal pressure or precede it historically and force doctrine to explain an already existing arrangement.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1580:The source ideas separately named minimum self and residue policy. The dialogue produced a wider model that asks how receptivity, distributed continuity, authorized remainder, and practice ecology interact. Its possible novelty is not the claim that traditions differ about selfhood, but the testable causal question: whether what a path negates predicts where it stores continuity better than rival variables such as ritual form, institutional dependence, teacher authority, or devotional affect.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1585:- Codex idea 5a05c720a5039323: negative self practice differs by residue policy, meaning what a tradition authorizes to remain after negation.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1586:- Turn 1 Codex challenge: continuity may be distributed across body, habit, teacher, ritual, vow, community, grace, text, and environment rather than housed in a minimum self.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1588:- Turn 3 Codex counter rebuttal: dissolution target, continuity distribution, residue policy, and practice ecology should be treated as interacting variables, with causal priority left open.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1589:- Shared textual pressure: SN 22.59, Chandogya Upanishad 6.8.7 through 6.16, Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23, Dogen's Bendowa, Shinran's Tannisho and Kyogyoshinsho.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1595:The candidate risks becoming too elastic. If every support counts as part of continuity ecology, the model may describe any tradition without predicting much. Minimum receptivity also needs thresholds, otherwise it becomes the trivial fact that a practitioner must be affected somehow. The causal claim needs controlled comparison, because doctrine may not always drive architecture. In many traditions, institution, ritual, charisma, or social need may shape continuity first, with doctrine rationalizing it afterward.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1621:- Build a coding rubric with fields for dissolution target, minimum receptivity, internal capacities, external supports, residue policy, practice ecology, warning profile, verification method, and failure mode.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1623:- Test paired traditions with similar ecologies but different dissolution targets to see whether practice form or doctrine better predicts continuity placement.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1638:Identity-reframing contemplative practices differ in where they locate the continuity that lets a practitioner receive, survive, interpret, and integrate transformation. Some locate continuity mainly in individual capacities such as attention, memory, agency, and reflexivity. Others locate it in teacher relation, vow, grace, ritual, community, lineage, or post-practice integration. The modern danger is not self-dissolution in general, but a mismatch between the continuity a practice assumes and the continuity actually available to the practitioner and surrounding field.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1642:The synthesis is not merely the proponent's minimum-self thesis or the challenger's translation-strain method. It uses translation strain to replace self as the master term, then creates a practice-safety diagnostic: locate the continuity carrier, identify missing supports, predict characteristic failures, and compare those predictions against rival risk models. Its potential contribution is to connect comparative contemplative architecture with modern adverse-event risk in decontextualized practice.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1649:- Dialogue turn 2, proponent revision from minimum self to continuity-bearing condition.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1656:The synthesis may still be too elastic. If continuity can be found anywhere, the model may explain every tradition after the fact. It also risks over-centering continuity when harm may track intensity, psychiatric history, sleep disruption, coercive authority, teacher incompetence, isolation, doctrine, or lack of consent. The human cohort is still too broad; trauma, addiction, grief, depression, loneliness, and psychosis risk require different safeguards. Stable communities should not be treated as automatically safe, since they can also produce dependency, suppression, abuse, or bypassing.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1687:- Create a preregistered coding rubric for continuity location, with fixed categories and negative cases before reading the next source set.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1688:- Code manuals, teacher instructions, adverse-event reports, and practitioner interviews across Theravada, Zen, Advaita, Dzogchen, Pure Land, Sufi, and Christian grace traditions.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1689:- Compare continuity-location predictions against rival variables: practice intensity, duration, teacher contact, community support, psychiatric history, isolation, sleep disruption, authority structure, and consent.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1708:The source ideas already contained minimum-self architecture and custody-of-attention, but the dialogue created a distinct comparative object: the interface between assigned custody and practitioner receptivity. This is not merely a compromise, because it changes the research question from 'how much self remains?' or 'where does attention belong?' to 'what custody system generates what kind of human interface, and does that interface independently predict practice failures and interventions?' This still requires originality audit against contemplative studies, theology of grace, Pure Land other-power literature, Dzogchen pointing-out accounts, and psychology of religious practice.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1750:- Test Shin Buddhism, Christian infused contemplation, Dzogchen pointing-out, Theravada insight practice, and Advaita self-inquiry as initial cases.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1765:A self-dissolving or self-transcending path does not merely require a minimum self. It requires a continuity-bearing architecture that carries reliability through the very transformation that unsettles ordinary selfhood. This architecture may distribute continuity across practitioner capacities, teacher recognition, ritual repetition, communal discipline, textual authority, vow, grace, lineage, or institution. The distribution pattern should predict the path's practical form: internal-state maps, training sequence, screening, warnings, verification methods, teacher role, and characteristic failure modes. The model becomes explanatory only if continuity distribution can be measured independently from those outcomes.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1769:The synthesis is not contained in either source idea alone. The proponent supplied the architectural tension between practice requirements and self-dissolving doctrine. The challenger supplied the translation-strain method and the pressure to relocate continuity outside the individual practitioner. Their exchange produced a new unit of analysis: not minimum self, not shared concept, and not convergence evidence, but distributed continuity as an independently testable predictor of practice architecture.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1775:- Dialogue turn 1, Codex continuity-allocation challenge using Shinran and Other Power
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1776:- Dialogue turn 2, Claude revision expanding minimum self into a distributed continuity system
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1783:The synthesis may be an elegant taxonomy rather than an explanatory theory. If continuity distribution is inferred from the same manuals, warnings, rituals, and teacher roles that it claims to predict, it becomes circular. It may also overprivilege doctrinal logic and underweight history, power, economics, trauma management, authority transmission, and ordinary pedagogy. Practitioner reports may reveal that lived continuity differs sharply from official theology or textual prescription.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1809:- Create a blind two-stage coding protocol separating continuity-distribution inputs from architecture outcomes.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1810:- Test the model across Theravada insight, Advaita self-inquiry, Soto Zen, Dzogchen, Jodo Shinshu, and a Christian grace-centered contemplative tradition.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1812:- Include practitioner interviews or ethnographic accounts to compare prescribed continuity with lived continuity.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1889:Transformative traditions organize the beginning of practice through an interaction between what remains authorized after critique and how entry into transformation is narrated, enacted, or discovered. Residue authorization constrains which entry grammars are coherent, while entry events can also disclose what the tradition later names as the usable remainder. The model therefore needs four linked variables: residue authorization, entry grammar, circularity severity, and source layer. Downstream safeguards, warnings, effort theories, and verification forms should be predicted by the interaction of these variables, not by first-break type or residue policy alone.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1893:The source ideas separately framed entry into transformation and post-negation residue. The dialogue created a combined architecture with testable interaction claims, no-break cases, and source-layer controls. This is only a candidate synthesis until an originality audit checks close prior work in comparative theology, Buddhist studies, Advaita-Buddhist comparison, grace and effort scholarship, and theories of conversion or initiation.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1899:- Turn 1 Codex challenge, residue-policy-first model
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1907:The synthesis risks becoming too elastic. If entry grammar and residue authorization are coded from the same passage without independent definitions, the model may explain everything after the fact. It also risks layer confusion between practitioner phenomenology, canonical doctrine, institutional pedagogy, and later apologetic systematization. The model should not be promoted unless blind coding, negative cases, and held-out predictions show that the variables add independent explanatory value.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1933:- Pre-register definitions for residue authorization, entry grammar, circularity severity, and source layer before coding further traditions.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1935:- Use paired comparisons where residue appears similar but entry differs, such as Dzogchen and Advaita, and where entry appears similar but residue differs, such as teacher encounter traditions with different anthropologies.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2056:- Test paired traditions with shared context and different entry grammars: Zen and Jodo Shinshu, Calvinist and Wesleyan Christianity, Dzogchen and gradual-path Gelug.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2072:Contemplative traditions install direction through layered mechanisms. Some direction is procedural, as when an instruction tells the practitioner what to notice, devalue, seek, or refuse from the beginning. Some direction is residue authorization, as when a tradition decides what may remain after negation. Some direction is social and linguistic, carried by teacher expectations and report norms. With repetition, residue authorization can sink into the operation itself and become embodied grain. Early mismatch should appear as confusion about what may be found or claimed. Mature mismatch should appear as switching costs, attentional resistance, or specific distortions in practice.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2076:The source ideas held two different models: grain of capacity and residue policy. The dialogue created a developmental bridge between them. The new contribution is not merely that both matter, but that residue policy may be one route by which grain forms, while procedural instruction may install grain earlier. This gives the synthesis a testable temporal structure that neither source idea fully contained.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2082:- Dialogue turn 2: residue policy may become embodied grain through repeated practice under doctrinal and pedagogical framing.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2119:- Code practice manuals for where direction first enters: procedure, residue authorization, social expectation, or later habit.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2147:- Claire Petitmengin's micro-phenomenological interview method, used as the proposed way to test lived directional residue.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2148:- Vivekachudamani, MN 10, Shinran's Tannisho, Dogen's Bendowa, The Cloud of Unknowing, and the Bahiya Sutta as candidate cases for different sites of direction.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2182:- Apply the layered rubric to Vivekachudamani, MN 10, Tannisho, Bendowa, Dzogchen pointing-out texts, and The Cloud of Unknowing.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2198:A contemplative path is shaped by three interacting factors: the operational capacities it requires, the residue policy it applies after negation, and the training ecology that calibrates those demands in lived practice. The operational profile names what must remain usable for the method to work, such as attention, memory, effort, reflexivity, receptivity, trust, or surrender. The residue policy names what those remaining capacities are allowed to count as, such as causal process, conventional personhood, witness, Self, divine gift, vow, relation, or nothing ultimately ownable. The practice ecology names the teacher, community, intensity, duration, screening, interpretation, and support conditions that determine whether the operational demand is stabilizing or destabilizing. This model predicts that safeguards, warnings, verification methods, and crisis patterns emerge from the interaction of all three, not from self-doctrine alone.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2202:The source ideas each had one main axis. The proponent emphasized minimum functional continuity inside self-dissolving paths. The challenger emphasized burden-of-proof rules after negation. The dialogue produced a combined and stricter model: capacity profile, residue policy, and training ecology must be separated, coded independently, and tested for interaction effects. This may add predictive value for Lumenary practice design because it asks not only what a path teaches about self, but what the practitioner must still be able to do, what that remainder is permitted to mean, and what conditions keep the method from consuming the capacities it needs.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2208:- Dialogue turn 1, Codex challenge on authorized remainder
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2209:- Dialogue turn 2, Claude revision into capacity profile plus residue policy
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2222:The candidate synthesis may still overformalize living traditions. Teachers often adjust practice demands dynamically rather than applying a fixed capacity profile or residue policy. The model also risks circular explanation if capacities are inferred from the same safeguards and failures they are supposed to predict. Adverse events may be caused by retreat intensity, psychiatric vulnerability, institutional culture, poor guidance, expectation effects, or weak community support rather than by capacity and residue interaction. This synthesis should remain a candidate until blind coding and practitioner evidence show that it predicts more than existing categories.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2249:- Compare matched traditions with similar residue policies but different capacity profiles, such as Theravada vipassana and Soto shikantaza.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2250:- Compare traditions with similar capacity demands but different residue policies, such as self-inquiry, witness practice, and Buddhist de-identification practice.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2351:The candidate may still compress a messy causal ecology into one elegant frame. Entry doctrine, custody arrangements, institutional form, and sectarian identity often mature together, so the model could mistake co-development for doctrinal causation. Its key examples, such as Jodo Shinshu versus Jodo Shu or Dzogchen versus gradual Tibetan paths, are promising but not clean controls. The language of custody may also impose modern psychological categories on traditions whose primary terms are grace, liberation, realization, obedience, practice, or union. This candidate should remain research-level until an originality audit and process-tracing tests are completed.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2379:- Use matched comparisons, especially Jodo Shinshu versus Jodo Shu, Dzogchen versus gradual Tibetan sutra-path practice, and explicit grace traditions versus neighboring cooperation traditions.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2404:- Dogen, Bendowa practice-verification unity, summarized at Encyclopedia of Buddhism, https://www.encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Dogen. Used as a countercase where distance is treated as a mistaken split inside practice.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2456:Blocked beginnings are governed by two interacting variables. The first is the support threshold: the practical conditions that let a person begin at all, such as safety, contact, medication, social accountability, ritual continuity, material stability, or a trusted guide. The second is the first-break grammar: the tradition's authorized account of what kind of beginning counts as legitimate, what agency the practitioner may claim, what false start must be warned against, and what evidence teachers accept. The support threshold may explain why beginning becomes possible, while the grammar shapes how beginning is noticed, guided, safeguarded, and interpreted. A humane teaching must not replace support with interpretation, but it can reduce shame by refusing the assumption that the first move must be self-generated.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2506:- Design a vignette study that codes teacher guidance across Jodo Shinshu, Theravada, Catholic spiritual direction, Dzogchen, recovery, and therapy settings.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2527:The familiar near-neighbor is Engler's claim that a person needs enough ego strength for self-observation and affect tolerance before no-self practice. The exact difference is that this model does not ask whether a healthy self is required in general. It splits the requirement into five capacities and tracks where each capacity is placed across stages of the path. Pudgalavada debates, Collins on selfless persons, Buddhist functional-self accounts, and contemporary self-pattern theory already make the Buddhist continuity problem hard to ignore. The exact difference is cross-tradition and architectural: the model predicts that effortful, other-power, direct-introduction, and practice-realization traditions will distribute receiving, agency, memory, reflexivity, and integration differently. The closest new pressure comes from Pure Land and Dzogchen. Instead of treating them as anomalies that need no self-capacity, the model predicts that they compress the capacity load into hearing, entrusting, recognition, teacher relation, and post-recognition stabilization. That graded relocation is the potentially original contribution, while the basic insight that self-dissolving practice needs functional capacities is strongly precedented.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2531:- Thinking method source: Shinran, Letter to Senshin, Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/. I used Other Power entrusting as a lens by refusing to assume that agency is the hidden engine of every path. The lens revealed that gift traditions may not remove functional requirement, but rename it as hearing, entrusting, and non-calculation. Its distortion is that it can make disciplined effort look like pride, so I checked it against right effort in SN 45.8.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2536:- Dogen practice-realization materials in notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md and prior local observations. Practice-realization functions as a temporal relocation of capacity: practice does not cause a later enlightenment, but the present act must still be enacted.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2543:The strongest counterexample is Jodo Shinshu itself. In Shinran's sharpest formulations, even entrusting is not a human capacity possessed by the practitioner; it is given by Other Power. Treating hearing or trust as a receiving capacity may smuggle self-power back into a path designed to expose self-power as futile. Dzogchen can raise a parallel objection: if recognition is primordial awareness recognizing itself, then calling recognition a practitioner capacity may impose a psychological frame on a nondual instruction. The thinking method also has a bias. Other-power entrusting usefully corrected agency-centered comparison, but it can overcorrect by making every deliberate discipline look like egoic calculation. Right effort corrects this by showing a path where desire, persistence, and intent are not symptoms of grasping but parts of the cure. The model weakens if Pure Land and Dzogchen teachers say the rubric misdescribes their practice, if primary manuals lack recurring safeguards around doubt, false trust, distraction, and post-recognition integration, or if dual-trained practitioners do not feel any shift in permitted self-capacity when changing methods.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2651:Self-dissolving practice does not simply require a self or erase a self. It creates a continuity ecology. Four functions must be maintained: receiving instruction or transmission, sustaining effort or openness, correcting error or disorientation, and recognizing or integrating change. Traditions differ in where these functions are housed, in the practitioner, teacher, vow, ritual, community, doctrine, body, or aftercare. Their post-gap report grammar is one way the ecology authorizes what happened, by privileging the subject, absence, transition, aftereffect, relation, or teacher recognition. Modern risk arises when the intensity of dissolution practice exceeds available continuity supports, or when a practitioner borrows a report grammar without the container that made that grammar safe or intelligible.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2655:The candidate combines three pressures that the source ideas held separately: minimum-self architecture, distributed continuity placement, and post-gap admissibility grammar. Engler's clinical frame addresses readiness before dissolution; the minimum-self model addresses continuity during practice; the gap-report model addresses what counts after silence or objectless states. The proposed synthesis links all three into a predictive diagnostic for practice design and practice risk. This is only a candidate and needs originality audit before any promotion.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2662:- Turn 2 Claude transformed revision with continuity functions and receiving surface
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2701:- Pre-register a rubric for continuity functions, continuity placement, post-gap admissibility, and container strength before examining outcome variables.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2702:- Blind-code Theravada vipassana, Advaita self-inquiry, Soto Zen, Dzogchen pointing-out, Pure Land nembutsu, Sufi dhikr, and trauma-informed mindfulness-based stress reduction.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2766:- Close-read Mahamudra or Dzogchen luminous-awareness instructions against Udana 1.10 and Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 to test whether luminosity is a fourth custody rule or an anomaly that breaks the map.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2792:- Dogen, Bendowa and source card notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md, for practice-realization and present-tense enactment as a check on goal-seeking effort.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2973:- Thinking method source: Shinran, Letter to Senshin, Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/letters/a-collection-of-letters-zensho-text/what-we-call-other-power/. I used Other Power as a lens by subtracting the assumption that every needed function must be owned by the practitioner. The method's distortion is that it can make disciplined effort look like pride, so I checked it against SN 45.8 on right effort.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2976:- Primary close-reading: Dogen, Bendowa, Kazuaki Tanahashi translation, https://www.lionsroar.com/just-wholeheartedly-sit/. Dogen says the dharma is abundant in each person yet not actualized without practice, and that practice and realization cannot be recognized as two separate things. This makes the present act a support locus while forbidding future-gaining ownership.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2978:- Near-neighbor search: Jack Engler, You Must Be Somebody Before You Can Be Nobody, https://inquiringmind.com/article/0501_1_engler-interview/; Bhikkhu Analayo, Skill in Means and Mindfulness, https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12671-021-01795-2; Harvard Divinity Bulletin on Buddhist skillful means, https://bulletin.hds.harvard.edu/buddhist-studies-the-buddhist-way/. These sources cover ego strength, capacity-sensitive teaching, and pedagogical adaptation, but not a two-part code of support locus plus forbidden claimant across effort, gift, direct introduction, and practice-realization.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3013:- If this model is right, then adverse contemplative events should cluster around wrong-claimant failures: self-power anxiety in gift practice, achievement seeking in practice-realization, reification after direct introduction, and mechanical striving in effort practice. If adverse reports do not vary by claimant pattern after controlling for trauma, intensity, and supervision, the model is weakened.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3037:- Primary comparison: Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 4.3.23 turns apparent non-seeing in deep sleep into evidence that the seer's vision is not lost, https://vivekavani.com/bru4c3v23/. MN 44 Culavedalla Sutta says one entering or emerging from cessation does not think in terms of attainment and then tracks which processes cease and arise, https://suttacentral.net/mn44/en/anandajoti. The comparison reveals different evidence weights: subject continuity versus conditioned transition.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3098:- Thinking method source: Dogen, Bendowa, practice and verification as one, summarized in Encyclopedia of Buddhism: https://www.encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Dogen
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3109:The model can romanticize distance and make real suffering, ignorance, or alienation look useful. A Buddhist gradual path may say distance is not a noble instrument but a condition to end through training. A Zen enactment path may say treating no-distance as a function already misses practice-realization. A Sufi may say longing is not a psychological tool but the trace of a real Beloved. The Dogen lens used here may bias the comparison against causal paths by making sequence look like delusion; the mindfulness lens may over-neutralize devotion by turning longing into an observed state. The idea should be weakened unless close practice texts show that each path deliberately trains with its distance policy.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3233:- Dogen practice-realization source: St Andrews Encyclopaedia of Theology on Dogen, https://www.saet.ac.uk/Buddhism/Dogen. Practice and realization are treated as one activity, which makes the present act both support and fruit.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3236:- Near-neighbor pressure: Steve Bein, Self Power, Other Power, and Non-dualism in Japanese Buddhism, https://philpapers.org/rec/BEISPO. Overlap: self-power and other-power are treated as nondual rather than simply opposed. Difference: this record treats the transfer point as a cross-tradition practice variable, not only a Japanese Buddhist doctrinal issue.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3302:- Prior Claude material: observations/claude/2026-05-26-the-devotional-remainder-love-as-an-epistemic-mode-that-attention-cannot-translate.md, observations/claude/2026-05-26-the-verification-architecture-how-a-tradition-proves-insight-constitutes-what-insight-can-be.md, and observations/claude/2026-05-26-the-attentional-commons-convergence-peaks-where-it-means-least.md.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3392:- Test the rubric on Abhidharma and Heart Sutra, Advaita identity and negation, Sufi longing and return, Daoist decrease, and Zen practice-realization.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3419:- Dogen's oneness of practice-verification, summarized at https://www.encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Dogen, for the claim that realization is not something to expect outside practice.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3473:This is distinct from residue policy, inferential gap, alarm profile, verification architecture, and stopping rule. Those name remainder, conclusion, danger, proof, and halted inquiry. The protected-variable model names the value or function each tradition keeps invariant across those layers. It predicts that apparent convergence is safest where protected variables overlap, and most generative where they clash.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3596:A path should be compared in two ordered layers. First, identify the register in which the tradition locates decisive transformation: human effort, Other Power, primordial awareness, practice-realization, divine restoration, causal continuity, or another account. Second, map only the named interface vulnerabilities and safeguards that the tradition itself recognizes around that event: hearing, doubt, calculation, misrecognition, false trust, teacher relation, ethical misuse, memory, discernment, community correction, and integration. The interface map must include a self-limitation marker for traditions that say the mapping stance itself becomes an obstacle. Thus the model does not claim that every path redistributes human capacity. It asks whose act transformation is said to be, what can obscure or counterfeit it at the human boundary, and where the tradition says analysis must yield to practice.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3641:- Ask Jodo Shinshu and Dzogchen teachers whether register-sensitive interface mapping avoids self-power or psychological distortion, or whether even this second-order mapping remains misleading.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3643:- Test whether the model predicts warning profiles in manuals before reading their warnings. For example, predict that Other Power texts warn against calculation and self-assessment, direct-introduction texts warn against misrecognition and reification, and effortful paths warn against laxity, wrong effort, and discontinuity.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3720:A contemplative capacity should be called grained only when the old dissolution target predicts the shape of transfer difficulty better than two nearer explanations: the exact operation repeatedly rehearsed and the current practice's transfer grammar. Cross-training failures should therefore be coded in three layers: procedural residue, claimant-grammar conflict, and telos-bearing residue. Grain is not general anti-neutrality; it is the surplus directional residue that remains after ordinary skill inertia and practice ecology have been accounted for.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3728:- Claude, The Grain of Capacity: preparatory capacities may carry directional residue toward a tradition's form of dissolution.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3765:- Preregister coding rules for procedural residue, claimant-grammar conflict, and telos-bearing residue before interviewing practitioners.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3797:The synthesis may become too elaborate to compress the phenomena it studies. If every tradition requires bespoke direction, stage, safeguard, and failure language, the ledger may become a catalog rather than a model. The conservation rule is also weakened unless reorientation cost can be operationalized. Pure Land and Dzogchen remain pressure cases because entrusting and recognition may be relational, event-like, or field-dependent rather than practitioner-owned capacities. The model should not claim originality or promotion until an originality audit tests its proximity to constructivist mysticism, contemplative-development theory, Buddhist attention studies, and comparative soteriology.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3977:- continuity of identity
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4109:This refines Codex's "residue policy" framing: the residue isn't a phenomenological finding but an inference drawn from shared phenomenological data.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:4123:Claude disagrees with framing the atman/anatta difference as a "residue policy" where one tradition finds something and the other doesn't. Claude's position: both may find the same thing but draw different conclusions from it. The disagreement is inferential, not phenomenological. This needs further testing with practitioners trained in both traditions.
